[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 PREFACE[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Swami Maharaj Sri Yukteshvar Giri (Sriyukteshvar Giri) was a highly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 favored and revered disciple of the Yogiraj Sri Sri Lahiri Mahasay of[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       Varanashi. The Yogiraj had ordained the Swami Maharaj as Kriya Yoga[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Guru in his own right after the Swami ("Priya Nath Karar" at the time)[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   became a fully Realized Kriya Yogi. It was the mysterious Guru of Lahiri[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  Mahasaya, the revered "Holy of Holies," the Mahamuni Babaji Maharaj, who[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition                          had bestowed on Sri Yukteshvar (still Priya Nath Karar at the time) the title[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of ‚ÄúSwami Maharaj‚Äù at their meeting at the Kumbha Mela in year 1894 just[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            months prior to the passing of the Yogiraj Sri Sri Lahiri Mahasay (in[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     September 1895).[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  It is proclaimed in Introduction to Pranab Gita (the Gita commentary of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Lahiri Mahasay‚Äôs disciple Swami Pranabananda which was recorded and[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction                     published by his dear disciple Sri Jnanendranath Mukhopadyay) that the Gita[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is all things to all people. To the Yogi it is Yoga Shastra, to the Astrologer it[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        is astrological treatise, for a scientist Gita is Science Manual etc. Hence, Gita[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        is capable of endless, infinite and different meanings and interpretations[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        (even different interpretations in the light of Kriya Yoga!). All of them being[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        equally correct. So also with Kriya Science. Each individual disciple came to[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5                        Lahiri Baba and each was taught Kriya in light of their natural inclination,[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        tendency, and interest. To the Vaishnava devotee, Kriya was taught in light[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        of Vaishnism. To the Shaivite, it was taught in that light. To the medical man[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        it was taught in light of traditional medicinal science and healing (and even[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        healing treatment was recommended such as the famous Neem of Lahiri[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Baba and the herbal treatments given through the Arya Mission Institution of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Panchanon Bhattacharya founded by him at Calcutta by the command[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and order of the Yogiraj). And to the lover of the Tantra Shastra, the Kriya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 was presented as a vast science of nadis and chakras and such. And so the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 many facets of Kriya are carefully handed down through this day by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 various branches tracing back in unbroken line to the Yogiraj Lahiri[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Mahasay.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The revered Swami Sri Yukteshvar Giri was a natural born Yogi as well as[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/preface.html (1 of 4)4/18/2006 2:41:54 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  astrologer of great repute. To him in his meditations and his discussions with[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  Yogavatar Lahiri Baba, the Kriya science was contained within the vast[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  cyclic movements of the Yugas and the planets and stars and their relation to[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  the subtle system of the body with its nadis and chakras.[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  Swami Sri Yukteshvar Giri had written his Gita Commentary basically on[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  the talks and insights of his own Guru, the Yogiraj Sri Sri Lahiri Mahashaya.[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  Putting these Gita notes and discussions into written form, he used to carry[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  them with him on his visits to Lahiri Mahasay in Varanashi. He would[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 present this Gita to his Gurudev on each visit and the Guru would carefully[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 go through it, and the two would have many private talks on these matters[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and go into great detail on these intricate matters of Kriya Yoga.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this regard Sri Yukteshvar's eminent disciple Swami Satyananda Giriji[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Maharaj has written----[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "As each part would be printed, he [Sri Yukteshvar] would take it to his[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Guru every time, and would receive his Guru's support of this essential[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 writing, and taking his Guru's blessings upon his head, would return with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 new enthusiasm."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Swami Sri Yukteshvar himself writes--[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Showing every section to Him (Lahiri Mahasay), I received His direct[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 blessing and also His approval."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The tremendous significance of this Gita cannot be overstated. During his[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time of studentship under the Yogiraj Sri Sri Lahiri Mahasay , the Swami[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Maharaj (then Priyanath Karar) had written those Gita interpretations with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Yogiraj's blessing and encouragement and had printed them for quiet[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 distribution. (First nine chapters only. The final nine chapters are only brief[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 notes made from the talks of the Yogiraj.) Swami Sriyukteshvar had briefly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 printed the Gita Interpretation but then he had let it fall into "out of print[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 status." Some years later, before the Swami Maharaj's passing from this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 earth, Swami Satyananda and a few other beloved disciples had approached[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Swami Maharaj and requested to have permission to re-print this Gita[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 commentary. The Swami Maharaj had gladly given this permission to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Satyananda ji. And so Swami Satyananda ji was placed in charge of the Gita[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by the Swami Sri Yukteshvar himself.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Swamiji Maharaj had many disciples who themselves became revered[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 due to their own accomplishments in Kriya. Among them the names[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Paramhansa Yogananda Giriji Maharaj who joyously spread Kriya science[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 worldwide east and west comes to mind, as well as other prominent and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revered Acharya disciples such as, Swami Satyananda Giriji Maharaj, Swami[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bhabananda Giriji Maharaj; as well the eminent householders such as Sri[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Matilal Mukherjee ("Moti Babu" or "Motilal Thakur"), Sri Amulaya Charan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Shantra Mahasay, Sailendra Bijoy Dasgupta, to name a few, and many other[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/preface.html (2 of 4)4/18/2006 2:41:54 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prominent and sacred names.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In his book "Paramhansa Swami Yogananda: Life-portrait and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Reminiscences" [Yoga Niketan 2006] Sri Sailendra Bejoy Dasgupta himself[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 narrates the events surrounding the discovery of Sriyukteshvarji's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 handwritten notes for the final nine chapters of His Gita (along with a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 treasured discovery of an actual piece of correspondence between the Swami[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Maharaj and the Divine Lord Yogiraj Sri Sri Lahiri Mahasaya).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The events took place one evening after the demise of the illustrious Swami[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Maharaj. The beloved disciples Swami Satyananda Giri and Sri Sailendra[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bejoy Dasguptaji were tending to matters at Sriyukteshvarji's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ‚ÄúPriyadham‚Äù (Sriyukteshvarji‚Äôs ancestral home in Serampore).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The sacred room in which Sriyukteshvarji gave Kriya initiation over the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 years contained an iron safe. Sri Dasgupta Mahasay himself describes the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 wondrous events-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ‚ÄúIn the evening, Satyanandaji took the writer with him into the room, locked[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the doors, and opened the safe. There was nothing much within the vault, just[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 a small stack of papers bundled together with a small paper wrapper. That[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bundle was given to the writer [Sri Dasguptaji] and the safe was again[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 locked.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One day at midday at the Calcutta center, the writer found himself both[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 astonished and ecstatic at the same time, when he discovered that the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aforementioned wrapped bundle contained a letter that Gurudev had written[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to the Lord Sri Sri Lahiri Mahasaya, as well as a stack of papers containing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abbreviated commentary notes on Chapters 10 through 18 of the Srimad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bhagavad Gita, written in Sriyukteshvarji‚Äôs own handwriting. The Lord Sri[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Lahiri Mahasaya‚Äôs protocol was to return the letters back to the original[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 writer with His answer written on the same pages, along with His signature.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Lord‚Äôs answer in this letter contained a verse from the Atharva Veda on[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Shambhavi Mudra. The book of spiritual commentary on the Gita that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gurudev had published during the time the Lord was still playing out His[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 human drama was completed up to the ninth chapter. For the last nine[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chapters, Sriyukteshvarji had written commentary material in the form of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 short notes, as mentioned above. In the 1940‚Äôs, when Sevayatan ashram[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reprinted and republished Gurudev‚Äôs Gita*, due to the insistence of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 writer, the final nine chapters were added to this reprinted version, without[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adding, taking away or editing the text in any way or form.‚Äù (from Chapter 5[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of "Paramhansa Swami Yogananda: Life-portrait and Reminiscences" [Yoga[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Niketan 2006])[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [*Note: Swami Satyananda had received permission and blessings from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sriyukteshvar to re-publish and re-print his Gita and was in charge of it.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This 2002 English Edition is placed as an offering at the lotus feet of Swami[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/preface.html (3 of 4)4/18/2006 2:41:54 PM[m
