[32m+[m[32m                                                      OM[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 PREFACE TO THE NEW EDITION[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mukam karoti vachalam pangum lamghayete girim[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatkripa tamaham vande paramanandamadhavam[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             By the Grace of Supremely Compassionate Lord of Lords, and after having[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 traversed many obstacles and conflicts, the Srimad Bhagavad Gita, with[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       commentary by His Holiness Swami Sriyukteshvar Giri Maharaj, is thus[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being presented. Almost 65 years ago, having received Grace and initiation[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   from Guru Yogiraj Sri Sri Shyamacharan Lahiri Mahasaya, the sadhaka Sri[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  Priyanath (as Swamiji Maharaj was known at that pre-monastic time)[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition                          established the "Gita Sabha" [congregation for discussions on the Srimad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bhagavad Gita] in Srirampur of the Hoogly district with certain sadhakas,[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            where he, by Guru's grace and spiritual Light, and with his own experiences[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     from sadhana and analysis, held discussions on the Gita; it is that which he[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   confined to paper, and with Sriguru's [Yogiraj Sri Sri Shyamacharan Lahiri[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  Mahasaya's] blessings - on section after section - he was able to present up to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the ninth chapter in book form. Swamiji Maharaj [Swami Sriyukteshvar Giri[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction                     Maharaj] used to say, "Sitting ! at His feet in Kashi [Benares], I used to listen[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to His beautiful experiential discussions on the Gita. Sometimes His[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        condensed expository language seemed complex to understand. Through[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        applicable questions when I presented myself in person to Him, and from[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        time to time via the use of letters, I resolved many issues. What I have been[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        able to realize by my own understanding about the scientific and[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5                        philosophical perceptions pertinent to the age is what I have written; and,[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        having shown every section to Him, I received His direct blessing and also[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        His approval. But whether I have been successful in this work at adopting[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        Gurudeva's [Yogiraj Sri Sri Shyamacharan Lahiri Mahasaya's] total essence -[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        that kind of surety I cannot claim. What I have understood myself by having[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 had His Presence is what I have written. If there are imperfections or if there[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is incompleteness, then I am the one who is responsible for that."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 A few years ago, when we proposed to Swamiji Maharaj to republish his[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/satyananda_preface.html (1 of 3)4/18/2006 2:41:55 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  commentaries on the Gita, he elatedly gave us his permission. As the subject[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  would arise, he would say that before publishing this book again, the[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  language and style of exposition of the previously written commentaries[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  needed to be presented in an even more simple and explanatory way, because[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  some complexities due to the language of that time still remained. Later,[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  whatever attempts had been started on this aspect of the work can be said to[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  have been insignificant.[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  He left his body almost twelve years ago; thus, in his absence, the previously[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 published version authored by him up to the ninth chapter is being presented[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 again in exactly the same form as before, and what was discovered later - a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 very abbreviated version of the tenth through the eighteenth chapter written[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in his own handwriting on a few pieces of paper - is being presented[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unaltered from the original and thus completing the book.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Scripture is boundless and eternal; its understanding is also ever-new. From[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the realizations of innumerable sadhakas and great beings of wisdom, we[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 have received great joy from the radiance of the many perspectives of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gita-scripture. That this beautiful spiritual writing with analysis from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 philosophical treatises lit by the Consciousness-Flame of the supremely great[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 guru Swamiji Maharaj will give guidance on the path to help the progress of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Kriyavan sadhakas and provide joy and enthusiasm, there is no doubt.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 After having to go past many obstacles such as retrieving the text from the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 out-of-print book whose pages were being eaten away by insects and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 recompiling the manuscript, problems with the printing press, the expense of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 paper etc., this longed-for book for many years is being published. That a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 precious photograph of Swamiji Maharaj from that time has been presented[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with this edition is also a matter of joyful and sacred remembrance. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 devotion, work and perseverance of the servants of Sevayatan headed by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 very dearest Swami Premananda, and the enthusiasm of certain Kriyavan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhakas have made the realization of this project possible. It is their very[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 self-giving that will bring them the blessings of Sriguru for their beneficence.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                            salutations,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                     Swami Satyananda Giri[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kojagari Purnima, 1355 [Bengali calendar], 248 Dvapara[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                    Sevayatan -- Yogamandir[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                      Jhargram (Medinipur)[m
