[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 INTRODUCTION[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Purnamadah purnamidat purnat purnamudachyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                  Purnasya purnamadaya purnamevavashishyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                 Shantih shantih shantih[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Sri Guruveh namah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             (Translator's Note----all parentheses and the text within them in the book are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from the original and not the translator's, unless specifically noted.)[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Satchitananda-filled Brahman-Consciousness is All and Everywhere. This[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   phenomenal world is all His, filled with innumerable names, forms, world-[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  activities all in Him. This Consciousness and the phenomena-filled[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition                          Brahmanda [Universe in different levels] has arisen from the Absolute[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman. Therefore, discarding the denotation of "manifested" from this[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            Consciousness-pervading phenomena-filled Brahmanda, that Eternal[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     Knowledge-Essence-Feeling-Being Itself, the Par-Brahman remains. Having[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   surrendered and received Peace from that Absolute Brahman - Sri Sri[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  Gurudev's Lotus Feet, in Peace and for the sake of spreading Peace, I invoke[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the sacred singing of this book in this introduction.[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With mantra, brahmins and upanishads, Maharshi Krishnadvaipayan[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        Vedavyas compiled the four divisions of the Vedas - Rg, Sama, Yajur and[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        Atharva; and seeing that Sudras did not have any right to these, he composed[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        the fifth Veda, the Mahabharata, on their behalf. Therefore, this is esteemed[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        among the Vedanta scriptures, as in:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        vedanto nam upanishad pramanam tadupkarini[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        sharirak sutradinicha -- (from Vedantasar - 2nd sutra)[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        The Upanishads, named 'the Essence of the Vedas', are the foundation;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and the 'Aphorisms on the Self' (the Brahma-Sutras) are their accessory.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The goal of the treatises of Vedanta philosophy is the allaying of ignorance[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/intro.html (1 of 10)4/18/2006 2:41:56 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  or illusion and the revelation of knowledge. But scientific thinking is of[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  absolute necessity for the study of the shastras. The knowledgeable ones[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  compare the study of the shastras as akin to butter churning. Just like the[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  food that may actually be appropriate for the sustenance of life, when[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  curdling, brings on rheumatism, lameness, colds, coughs and finally the[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  oncoming of death from the exhaustion of life -- but if, by using a churning[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  stick, one can discard the worthless part and separate the cream as a new[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  substance from the churning, then one has contentment, strength and long[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  life -- it is in this way, that although it is necessary to obtain knowledge of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the shastras, studying the scriptures with blind belief causes the growth of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 restlessness, pride, vanity, unnecessary arguments and anger, which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eventually leads to the loss of knowledge and the stupor of ignorance. But[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 churning those shastras with the stick of scientific thinking, if one can leave[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the useless part and take up the part of wisdom, then contentment and peace[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 arise and the radiance of knowledge is manifested, destroying ignorance.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, it is not appropriate to study the shastras by only trusting the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reputation of their creators and without using logic, because sages can make[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mistakes as well. Addressing this, philosophical authorities have said that if[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the words of even a child is logically sound, then it is our duty to receive it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and deem it worthy; but if talk of Brahman Itself is unscientific, then it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 should be considered worthless chaff and abandoned. One should not make[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 discernments about anything without using scientific thinking and just[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 relying on the scriptures; this is unrighteous, as in:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yuktiyuktamupadeyam vachanam balakadapi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 annyam trinamiva tyajyampyuktam padajanmana[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 A statement endowed with reason (logic) is acceptable even by a child.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One that is not is abandoned as worthless, even if spoken by a noble person.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kevalam shastramasritya na kartabyo binirnayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yuktiheena vicharetu dharmahanih prajayate[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One shouldn't make decisions only on the authority of the scriptures;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 for ideas that are devoid of reason (logic) cause the destruction of Dharma.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 To study the shastras one must be aware of four things: what is the subject[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 written about, what is our relationship to that, what is our need for that and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who has the right to this shastra. These four are considered inseparable, as in:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatranubandho nam adhikari vishaya sambandha prayojanani[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- (from Vedantasar - 4th sutra)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the aforementioned aggregate of four - subject, relationship, and need -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these three are described in the Vedanta scriptures as:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vishayah jiiva-brahmaikyam shuddha-caitanyam prameyam tatraiva[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/intro.html (2 of 10)4/18/2006 2:41:56 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vedaantam taatparyaat.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sambandhastu tadaikya-prameyasya tat-pratibodhakopanishat-pramaanasya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ca bodhya-bodhaka bhaava-lakshanah.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prayojanastu tadaikya-prameya-gata-jnaana-nivrittih tat-svaruupaananda-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vyaaptish ca[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatari shokam aatmavid ityaadi-shruteh brahmavid brahmaiva bhavati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ityaadi-shrutesh ca[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The subject is the Oneness of the soul and the Absolute, pure Consciousness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the essence of the Vedanta, which is to be established. [In other words: the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 subject which the text under scrutiny tries to establish, which is the essence[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the Vedanta is: the Oneness of the soul and the Absolute][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The connection [of the subject with the text] is thus: a relationship of ‚Äòwhat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is to be known‚Äô and ‚Äòwhat makes it known‚Äô exists between the Oneness to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 established and the Upanishads which elucidate it. [In other words: the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Oneness of the soul and the Absolute is explained by the Upanishads, hence[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 a connection exists between the Upanishads and the subject, the Absolute.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And the purpose is the attainment of the knowledge of that Oneness to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 established, which is pervaded by the Bliss of the true Self. This is expressed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the scriptural passages: "the knower of the Self passes beyond all sorrow"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and "the knower of the Self verily becomes the Self." [In other words: the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purpose of presenting the text is to obtain the knowledge of Oneness][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- (from Vedantasar - 10th sutra)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Realization of the jiva to be the one and the same as Brahman, the pure[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Supreme Consciousness, is the aim and the same Supreme Consciousness is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 also the subject matter of Vedanta. The jiva is also the inseparable expresser[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Brahman, the Perfect Consciousness perceivable by us, meaning, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowable substance and the proof of Upanishad is indicative of that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman-Consciousness. That which is knowable from this and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 awareness of the feeling of Its significance is called relationship. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realization by said jiva of the knowledge of the oneness of the Pure[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness of Brahman, thereby destroying ignorance, and the attainment[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the manifested bliss of the aforementioned knowable substance is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 need. It is said in aural wisdom that those cultivators of Soul-substance who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 know Brahman go beyond suffering and become Brahman Itself, etc.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Finally, the inextricable point of having the right, meaning, who has the right[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to this Srimad Bhagavad Gita and facing the profound necessity of that will[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 be revealed in its due place. For the time being, I will explain why Sudras[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 have no right to the Vedas.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 A Sudra does not the have the ability to utter the Pranava [Divine Sound],[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and if the Divine Sound is not uttered, it is forbidden to recite the Vedas.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Hearing this statement, ordinary people decide upon the apparent[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/intro.html (3 of 10)4/18/2006 2:41:56 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 crookedness of the creators of the Shastras, thereafter ridiculing and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 condemning them. However, the brahmins of Vedic times were very simple;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they did not even know what crookedness was. They were steadfast in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 spreading knowledge for the eradication of ignorance. Later, being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 misunderstood, that very ignorance became the norm. And so, this highest[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge of Brahman was not revealed to the Pranava-less.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 A possible interpretation of Pranava is that it is just a word. It can be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pronounced by any human being by just wishing it. But this is not so. This[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cannot be pronounced by the mouth. In reply to this, the Lord Sri Krishna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 said in the Gita that no part of the Pranava can be expressed by the mouth. It[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is indivisible like the flow of oil, and the sound is eternally sustaining like[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the long resonance of a bell. Upon experiencing this, the knowledge of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vedas become manifest. As in:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 taila-dhaaraam ivaacchinnam deergha-ghantaa-ninadavat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avaachya-pranavabyangam yastam veda sa vedavit[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He who knows That, the unblemished, indescribable Pranava (Om), like an[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unbroken flow of oil, like the long sound of a bell, he indeeds knows the [true[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning of the] Vedas.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The type of sound that is heard by the ears after the second quarter of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 night, when all is silent - ch(n)oooooooo,* through the special practice of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kriya by the Grace of Sadguru, when, being filled with inner experience,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness is stilled, that kind of an unearthly sound - O(N)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 OOOOOOOOONG** - is heard. This is the evidence of the stilling of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness. When this is sounded within, certain mudras, meaning,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indications appear outside. Seeing these, sages recognize each other. These[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 signs are extremely secret. One can become aware of them through Guru.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without such stilling of consciousness, manifesting Supreme Awareness and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the consequent growth of the power of internal knowing, the meaning of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vedas are not internalized in the heart.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *The (n) symbolizes a nasal sound and is not actually pronounced as an "n".[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 **Same as the previous asterisked note.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge is of two types: indirect and direct. The type of incomplete[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge that is born of description - that is called indirect knowledge.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And that which is born of one's own experience - that is called direct[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge. Like the "Darimba" [ordinary pomegranate] - whose character is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that the taste is at first sour and then it changes to honey-sweet and finally it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is astringent. At the mature stage this fruit is called "Bedana" [the best[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 variety of pomegranate]. It is true that this kind of description can bring[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 about a certain type of knowledge but it is very incomplete, because if one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 says that the Darimba is deliciously sweet, it can easily be mistaken for a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bedana. This is called indirect knowledge. But when one actually sees and[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/intro.html (4 of 10)4/18/2006 2:41:56 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tastes a Bedana, there is no possibility of delusion in the knowledge born of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that. This is called direct knowledge or experience. It is true that indirect[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge helps somewhat in the understanding of external things, but it has[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 no place in the internal field. For example: winter, summer, happiness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sorrow, bitter, sweet, etc. - without a direct experience of these things,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nothing is understood by indirect knowledge, meaning description. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 recitation of books and listening to lectures, which are the means of gaining[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge these days - they are prone to this kind of error. Because of this,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in Vedic times such things were not even accepted as knowledge. There is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 very little of indirectly received knowledge in the Vedas; one can even say[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that it is not really there at all. These are completely filled with internal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowing. Nothing can be internalized in the heart without the experience of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 direct knowledge. Let us not even talk about the Vedas; everyone is quite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aware of the fact that if the mind is not steadied, then it is not possible to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 even understand anything of some inconsequential subject from a simple[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 book, regardless of reading it over and over.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is not only so that the Vedas cannot be internalized in the heart if the mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is restless, but the consequential arising of aberrant thinking can cause great[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 danger when baseless meanings according to one's own liking are given to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these Vedas containing the highest inspiration of the Knowledge of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman. I will give a small example of this below in relation to the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vaishnava's book, Manabhanjan.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is written in the Manabhanjan that Radhika became extremely desperate at[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 her separation from Sri Krishna, and was feeling so hurt that no matter how[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 much Sri Krishna fell at her feet and tried to comfort her, she kept her face[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 turned away and did not want to look at Him, no matter what. But once the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eyes meet, nothing of the suffering remains and all is flooded with the ocean[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Bliss. This is its significance: being a Vaishnava is to be know that Sri[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Krishna is the Brahman-Consciousness manifesting in the human body, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Radhika is the three-guna-filled Nature manifesting in the human body. It[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 can be understood that when this feeling is not present, Nature without[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman-Consciousness is feeling rejected and has turned her face away,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning - the attention is turned outside, and is experiencing who knows[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 how much of the suffering of the world; and that All-pervading Eternal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness is the way of liberation from this suffering, present within[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 everyone. But Nature's feeling of rejection has become so maddeningly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intense that She will not turn around and look even once. Once the attention[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is turned inwards, that Eternal Consciousness is experienced and this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 impermanent worldly suffering is dispelled, after which the mind becomes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 completely filled with Bliss.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But what bizarre and distorted thinking! Seeing this as a love-affair between[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 a woman and a man, with the true perspective having become subject to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 worldly dogma, the Love of the Full-Brahman Sri Krishna towards the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Trigunamayi Radhika, has been replaced with the disgusting lust between a[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/intro.html (5 of 10)4/18/2006 2:41:56 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 harlot and her paramour. And even more incredible is that certain ignorant[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vaishnavas from certain sects try to attain that Full-Brahman Sri Krishna by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this method. Their way of worship is also very strange. The men - forcibly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 wearing tight underpants, putting on women's clothes and jewelry, making[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all kinds of gestures of love - try to live with the Lord. I have heard that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sometimes they even menstruate. What a terribly sad thing! These infinitely[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 powerful souls who are part of that Infinite Consciousness, who, if they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 wanted, could possess an infinite number of universes in the palms of their[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hands -- what stupor of ignorance has taken them, and what suffering they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are experiencing from the fault of distorted thinking! When one sees the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 workings of this kind of dogmatic, aberrant thinking, one can clearly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 understand how benevolent it was to prohibit the restless-minded, Pranava-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 less Sudras from touching the Vedas.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, in order to determine who has the right to the Srimad Bhagavad Gita, it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is necessary to know something about Krishnadvaipayan Vedavyas. There[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 was a king named "Das". One of the things he did was catch fish. One day,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 he caught a fish, from whose womb emerged two children. One of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 children was Birat; he was the king of the world of fishes. The other child[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 was a supremely beautiful girl. Because she had inextricable fish-scent on[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 her body, she was named Matsyagandha. The king Das took his daughter by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 boat to the banks to do good for the passers-by, with the intention and hope[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of finding a great soul who might be able to free his daughter from this fish-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scent. After staying at the riverbank for a while in this way, there was a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meeting with Parashar, the son of Shakti. He graced them, and created a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mist in the river in order to keep them protected from the sight of others, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to steady the boat he created a dark island [krishnadvipa], in which, after[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bestowing lotus-scent on Matsyagandha, he presented his own seed in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fully youthful yoni of her tiny body. It is from this that Vedavyas was born[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 on that ‚Äúkrishnadvipa,‚Äù and because of that, became known as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Krishnadvaipayan. At that time, Maharshi Parashar instructed the girl in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mantra and methods of worship and said that worshipping in this manner,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 she will eventually become married to the main king of the earth.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There is a fable like this in the Mahabharata. All have a right to this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Mahabharata - Sudras, Brahmins, Vaishnavas. No one is prohibited to recite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it as well. It is created in such a way that everyone can gain some wisdom[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from it. In all of the stories of the Puranas, there are three types of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 commentaries - adhibhautic [physical], adhidaivic [subtle] and adhyatmic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [spiritual]. I will explain below the three types of commentaries in relation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to the aforementioned story.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For the physically enmeshed, steeped in ignorance Sudras the commentary is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 given that, in order to free her of the fish-scent, the king Das took[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Matsyagandha, the child he reared, and went to the riverbank to serve[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 travelers and in doing so, by the grace of Maharshi Parashar, she was[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bestowed the smell of lotus-scent and then became the queen of the main[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/intro.html (6 of 10)4/18/2006 2:41:56 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 king. Therefore, it is one's duty to humbly serve everyone. In this way, it is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 possible to please some great saint. This is the adhibhautic explanation.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For the steady minded Brahmins, whose awareness of the subtle body has[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealed the eye of knowledge - for them, this type of commentary is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prevalent: docking at the shore is pilgrimage. This is not a riverbank but the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pilgrimage site established at the shore of worldly life. In this place, all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledgeable and ignorant people are milling about. The ignorant ones[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 come here to attain knowledge, and the knowledgeable ones come here from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time to time to bestow wisdom. The king Das asked the child he reared to go[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 on a pilgrimage. Thereafter, upon meeting the Shakti-endowed Maharshi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Parashar and receiving his grace, she became lotus-scented, learned the ways[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of worshipping the gods and became the queen of the main king. Therefore,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it is important to go on pilgrimages. Many saints gather about in these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 places. Receiving the grace of someone in an unseen way, this type of great[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beneficence is possible. This is the adhidaivic explanation.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But the God-united Vaishnavas, who have become aware of the Supreme[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Substance of Vishnu, say that this type of external explanation of the story[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 never occurs to knowledgeable Soul-culturists and those established in Soul-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness. It is impossible that there is anything in this but the subject[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the elevation of Soul-Consciousness. If one reads with a little earnestness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of mind, the hidden significance is understood. The servant - "Das" -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 carrying out the work of the individual soul, represents the senses. During his[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rulership, meaning in a capable state the catching of fish - Matsya (Mad sya)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [fn 1] - meaning, one of the things that happen from desire is obsessive[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 addiction. In this way, the manifestation of desires one after another[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eventually leads to a mad addiction from which the great - "Birat" - kingdom[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the world is born, meaning, the attention goes to this world in the midst of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 infinite universes. And along with that, the desire of this kingdom arises and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the inner senses are driven by the mind. Even though this desire is beautiful,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it has a fish-scent, meaning the sense of obsessiveness. To destroy this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sense, it imperative to go on a pilgrimage. The subject of pilgrimage has[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 already been mentioned. [Translator's note: see the previous paragraph.][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Great saints walk about in this place all the time. When the unseen is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pleased, the son of Shakti - Parashar's - meaning, the kundalini shakti, which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is a part of the Primordial Shakti, unites with Consciousness - doing which,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 there is someone who has the seed of Purusha - it is possible at this time to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meet this type of great saint. Then the teaching and technique of those types[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of great saints is told: a fog in order to shut out the sight of the outside world[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is created along with a dark island, where the Pure Yoni (because this body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is created from that)[fn 2] is revealed and it is there that the fire of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Supremely Awakened Kundalini Shakti is offered. This technique is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Yonimudra" in the shastras (meaning the symbol of the Mother of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe)[fn 3]. Being a sadhaka is being aware of this. From the fire of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sadguru, this is what is experienced first. Then the addictive madness is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 removed and gradually one by one the lotus-experience appears. From this,[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/intro.html (7 of 10)4/18/2006 2:41:56 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vedavyas (Vid -knowledge of substance; vyas - to know the substance[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 specifically and in detail)[fn 4], meaning, the knowledge insight arises. This[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is also written about in Tulsidas's couplets, as in:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sadguru pave, ved batave[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Jnan kare upadesh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tab koyelake mayla cchute[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Jab aag kar prabesh[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [English translation of the Hindi: One finds a Sadguru. He is given insight,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 instruction and knowledge. Then the darkness of the coal disappears when[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fire enters it.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Revealing Yonimudra in this way, Maharshi Parashar gave instruction on[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mantra (that which rescues the mind)[fn 5], meaning connecting the breath[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with Consciousness, and said that remaining fixed in the practice of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kriya one will become united with the Main King of the Universe, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Satchitananda-filled Par-Brahman. This is the adhyatmic explanation. This[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is the yoga-technique of the yogis and the Consciousness-revealing kriya.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There is this type of example in Tantra, as in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmaadi-krimi-paryantam praaninaam praana-vartanaa[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nishvaasah sva-saruupena mantro'yam vartate priye[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From Brahma down to the smallest creature, all beings live by Prana.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The breath, which has the form of a Mantra, is always present, O beloved.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Mahadeva said to Parvati: The breath, which holds the prana of living[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   things, even down to the worm, is called mantra.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   mantraartham mantra-caitanyam yoni-mudraam na vetti yah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   shata-koti-japen nityam tasya siddhir na vidyate[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Unto him who knows neither the meaning of the Mantra, nor the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   consciousness of the Mantra, nor Yoni-Mudra, Siddhi (perfection) shall not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   come even by constantly repeating it a hundred million times.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The appropriate meaning of mantra is breath, and the method to unite it with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Consciousness is pranayam (kevalikumbhak)[fn 6], and without knowing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Yonimudra, millions of japas do not bring success.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   [fn 1- 6: All of these parentheses and the text within them are in the original.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Being aware of this type of spiritual significance in relation to Vedavyas and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   saying that this Vedavyas' composed the Mahabharata with the Srimad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Bhagavad Gita, one can clearly understand that without having received the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Sadguru-graced initiation into the Knowledge of Insight and its[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/intro.html (8 of 10)4/18/2006 2:41:56 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 establishment, one cannot properly understand the true meaning and spiritual[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 significance of these books. Therefore, the Sadguru-initiated sadhakas are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the rightful ones for these scriptures, but there is no salvation even in that.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Through that Knowledge of Insight, Dhritarashtra (dhritam rashtram yena),*[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning mind, and Pandu (without description and pure), meaning the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intelligence, are perceived. Later, Kunti (that which calls the substance)** -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the field of that intelligence, meaning the three above the navel able to call[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Divine Fire in the spine, and Madri (Madayate ity),*** meaning the two[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 below the navel - with the presence of these five elements, the nature of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind via different faculties becomes fraught with great danger. Because of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that, some elements become distorted and consequently, physical and mental[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 illnesses arise. With the help of the physician's medicine and Guru-given[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 techniques respectively, it is possible to be rescued from that. But when[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 those five elements become engrossed in the fire of delusion and become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ready to surrender the very Soul, then there is no possibility. Even the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 strictest meditators and great yogis fall from their ever-practiced yogic state.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [*, **, *** - These parentheses and the text within are in the original.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 To provide salvation from this horrific condition, the Srimad Bhagavad Gita,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 containing all of the Shastras in the form of an Upanishad, was created in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 midst of the fifth Veda, the Mahabharata. The liberation from this terrible[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 predicament is why this scripture is of the utmost necessity. One who is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perfectly aware of the true meaning and significance of this shastra - there is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 no shastra unknown to that person. Addressing this, great saints have said[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that it is one's duty to keep lovingly in mind the Gita that emerged from the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Fire of Brahmin connecting with the lotus of the navel. After this, there is no[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 need for any other shastra.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 giitaa sugiitaa kartavyaa kim anyaih shaastra-samgrahaih[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yaa svayam padma-naabhasya mukha-padmaad vinihsritaa[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 What with all the other Scriptures? The Gita, the lovely[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gita, should one recite, which flowed directly from the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 lotus-mouth of the Lord Padmanaabha (Sri Krishna).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The true meaning and significance of the Gita has always been passed on[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 orally through the lineage of guru and disciple. This cannot be understood[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 except by the Sadguru-initiated sadhakas - not just scholars. Now, with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 permission of Sri Sri Bhagavan His Holiness, and according to His[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 instructions, I present this treasure of the supremely holy hearts of yogis, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Srimad Bhagavad Gita, with simplified Sanskrit explanation and, in order to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 make memorization easier, the poems of Vaishnavas, and the explanation of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Gita‚Äôs secret spiritual significance, paralleling it with treatises of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 country and the West. If by this even one devotee is able to become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ecstatically immersed in the awareness of the Full-Brahman Sri Krishna,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 then I will know that this effort was successful.[m
[32m+[m
