[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 CHAPTER ONE[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 SEEING AND NAMING THE SOLDIERS[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Dhritarashtra said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       dharmakshetre kurukshetre samaveta yuyutsavah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mamakah pandavashchaiva kimakurvata sanjaya - 1 -[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dhritarashtra said, "Listen, O Sanjaya!"[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            The hundred with Duryodhana of mine[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     With Yudhisthira the five sons of Pandu[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   To fight they've come together[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  What do they do in Dharmakshetra and Kurukshetra[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Tell me in detail all that is happening[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        It is written in the Mahabharata that Dhritarashtra, Pandu etc. were all from[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        the lineage of the Maharaja Santanu. He had two wives - Ganga and[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        Satyavati. Eight sons were born in the womb of Ganga. From which Ganga[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5                        destroyed seven of them in the flow of her own waters immediately after[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        birth, and the eighth was left and Ganga united with her own flow and[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        disappeared. The name of this eighth son was Devabrata. He was supremely[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        powerful and mighty. It is through the fire of this Devabrata, or Bhisma, that[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        this kingdom of Bhaarat was to be saved. It is true that he settled to fight on[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 behalf of the sons of Dhritarashtra, but he never lost himself in the work or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyment of the kingdom. And Satyavati, who was formerly known as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Matsyagandha, in whose womb the Maharshi Vedavyas fathered by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Maharshi Parashar was born - having become lotus-scented, she was[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 immersed in the mantra-practice which she received from Maharshi Parashar[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to become the queen of the main king. Maharaja Santanu, seeing the lotuses[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 resulting from her worship floating in blue waters, became enraptured by her[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (1 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  beauty and proposed to marry her, and then withdrew his proposal after[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  seeing that Devabrata was the rightful king. When he saw the despondent[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  Santanu, Devabrata renounced his ownership of any kingdom, and in case a[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  son would be born of him and cause problems in this, he vowed to remain[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  unmarried in his natural life, and thereafter, to the great joy of Maharaja[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  Santanu, he brought forth Satyavati and united Maharaja Santanu and her in[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  marriage. Two sons were born to Maharaja Santanu from Satyavati:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  Chitrangada - the oldest, and Vichitravirya, the youngest. The oldest became[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  corrupted in demonic warfare, and Vichitravirya remained as himself on his[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 own. For the marriage of Vichitravirya, Devabrata-Bhisma brought forth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Amba, Ambika and Ambalika, three daughters of the king Kashi. In this,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because Amba desired to marry Madraraj, Devabrata let her go and married[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vichitravirya to the two others.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vichitravirya, enjoying his wives, became ill and died. Later, fathered by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vedavyas - the son of Parashar who was born in the womb of Satyavati -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pandu was born of Ambalika and Dhritarashtra was born of Ambika.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because Ambika closed her eyes upon seeing Vyasdeva, her conceived son[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 was born blind, and because Ambalika was indifferent, her conceived son[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 was born as Pandu [pale]. When Pandu found out that he was cursed and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that he would die if he had intercourse with his wives, he renounced all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desire of enjoyment and went to live in the woods. He had two wives: Kunti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and Madri. Kuntidevi knew a mantra that could attract gods. To test this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mantra, when she was unmarried, she called forth the sun god, Surya. Karna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 was born, fathered by Suryadeva. With the permission of her husband,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kuntidevi used the attraction-mantra on the lord of righteousness, Yama,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from whom the righteous son Yudhisthira was born. Thereafter, calling forth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the supremely mighty and powerful wind-god, Pavandeva brought about the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 birth of the frighteningly powerful Bhima, and attracting the supremely fiery[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Indra who contained all qualities, brought forth Arjuna, who was excellent in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all things. Later, at the request of her husband, Kuntidevi taught that mantra[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to Madri, after which, Madri called to her the god of twins, Ashwinikumar.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From that the twin sons Nakula and Sahadeva were born. Pleased at all of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this, one day in springtime, Maharaj Pandu went for a private walk with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Madri and having become stricken with the arrow of love, embraced Madri.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This resulted in his death. Madri also killed herself feeling that she was the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cause of her husband's death. Thereafter, Kuntidevi returned to her[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 husband's kingdom with the previously mentioned five children. Later, those[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 five Pandavas, along with their older cousin Duryodhana and his one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hundred brothers, were educated by Kripacharya and Dronacharya. At that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time, Arjuna went and learned from many places and became extremely[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 powerful. Then, when the five Pandavas were expressing their power, Karna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 arrived and prostrated to them. But Duryodhana and the one hundred[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brothers tricked the five Pandavas about the problems of their kingdom and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 took Karna to their side, and having his strength which made them very[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 powerful, tried many ways to ruin the five Pandavas. Falling prey to many[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of these trickeries, the Pandavas were forced to live in exile for twelve years[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (2 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the woods, and one year in total anonymity in the kingdom of Birat.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Later, they were found out and tried to regain their kingdom with the help of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Krishna. Now, let us see how we can understand this subject through[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 spiritual scriptures.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If we research into the subject of creation in the philosophical treatises, we[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 find that this immense Universe is created out of two fundamental[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 substances. One is consciousness-substance and the other is matter-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 substance. ParaBrahman is beyond this creation, tranquil and One.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Transcending all of the conditions of creation and becoming only Soul, in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 state of kaivalya one experiences this Brahman-Consciousness. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 previously mentioned consciousness and matter are not separate from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ParaBrahman, but are two types of nature being created from ParaBrahman.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In philosophy, this ParaBrahman beyond creation is called Parampurush, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness substance in creation is called Purush and the matter substance[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is called Prakriti. This is explained in detail in the seventh chapter of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 book.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The above mentioned Prakriti is unconscious, but because of the presence of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Parampurush, as a magnet can magnetize a piece of metal, some[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness becomes present in Prakriti, causing a transmutation. This[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 transmutation is called Mahattatva [great substance].[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 satsannidhanakadhistatritvam manivat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- Kapila sutra 1/99[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The presence of this consciousness in Prakriti, bringing about Mahattatva,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 causes the arising of self-rulership in oneself. This feeling of self-rulership[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is called Ahamkara. Because of this, one thinks that one is his own lord.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But it is that Mahattatva that is the unseen ruler. Due to this demonic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 thinking, the quality of Mahattatva eventually disappears and Ahamkara is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 established. In Ahamkara, there is no sense of the present. This is a god-like[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ahamkara. This world is created through many permutations of its power.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of the presence of Purush in this created substance, the infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe, united with consciousness, is appearing.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The cultivators of scripture saw this Universe to have manifested in three[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 levels: physical, subtle and causal. This visible world that is evident through[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the senses of cognition - that is called the physical universe. The inner subtle[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 elements (electricity)* that are present in every molecule and atom, and are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 carrying out the work of creation, preservation and transformation - this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 represents the subtle body of the Universe. The cause of these elements,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Nature with Her tamas, rajas and sattva gunas, is the causal body of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe. This subject is focused upon in the 4th chapter of this book.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *The parentheses and the text in English are in the original.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (3 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the scriptural treatises, there is the use of the words "samasti" and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "vyasti". "Samasti" means totality and "vyasti" refers to the individual things[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 within the totality, as in - the whole forest relates to samasti and every tree[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 spread out within that forest relates to the concept of vyasti. Samasti is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness prevailing in the maya of the causal body of the Universe,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 called "Ishvar," and the vyasti condition is the consciousness presiding[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unawares in the causal body of every created thing, called "praajna."[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Samasti is the consciousness present in the maya of the subtle body of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe, called "hiranyagarbha," and vyasti is the consciousness present[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unawares in the subtle body of every created thing, called "taijas." In the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samasti condition, consciousness prevailing in the physical body of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe is called "birat," and in the vyasti state, consciousness present in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the physical body of every created thing is called "vishva." The presiding[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness is the same in samasti and vyasti. Manifesting as samasti in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 maya it is Ishvar, hiranyagarbha and birat, and residing unawares as vyasti, it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is praajna, taijas and vishva.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This Consciousness-filled world is manifesting in these six ways. To reveal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this, Consciousness is present in another two ways. In that, one is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Abhaschaitanya" or "Chidabhas" and the other is "Kutasthachaitanya" or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Sakshichaitanya." I am bringing forth an example from the eighth chapter[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Panchadashi in order to explain this matter. Just as in a dance-theater the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 light at once illuminates the proprietor, the audience and the dancer/actors in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the same way but is not involved in anything that they are doing, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 remains the light whether they are there or not, so is Kutasthachaitanya, Who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 remains apart from the sensory work of seeing, hearing, etc. and all of their[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 objects and is uninvolved in ego, intellect etc. He simply reveals the truth of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 them with His own Light, and remains the same Self-Effulgent One whether[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they are there or not. Whatever is thought of by the human mental-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intelligence, this Kutasthachaitanya is the witness to that, therefore Its name[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is "Sakshichaitanya." And It Itself is uninvolved with any work, thing or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 authority, not part of any of these states, and is completely incorruptible and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 totally in the present. Because of this, Its name is "Kutasthachaitanya."[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutabinnikarane sthiti ity kutastha, meaning, the word "kuta" is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 goldsmith's anvil. Regardless of all the gold and other materials that are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 transformed from their convoluted states into beautiful things, He remains[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unchanged and in the present, like the goldsmith's anvil. This Light of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness lives with all souls and reveals all about their minds, but mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is not able to know Him. The smallest thing is appearing because of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutashthachaitnya, but the individual soul is not able to know that. And the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva also has a natural internal light. When, because of the jiva's mind, that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 light falls upon some thing, then that thing is revealed double its existence,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and the knowledge of its function in the jiva happens. This internal light of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the jiva is also seen under the Light of Kutasthachaitanya. This internal light[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the jiva is only a reflection of that Light of Kutasthachaitanya. Its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 existence is in the Existence of Kutasthachaitanya. Does that mean that there[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is no light of the jiva itself? Of course there is. But that light has only the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (4 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 quality of reflection. Without the Light of Kutasthachaitanya, it is darkness.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Just as without external light no knowledge of anything is possible with one's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 own light, in the same way, unless all things are revealed unknowingly by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Light of Kutasthachaitanya, no thing could be revealed by the mind of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the jiva. That internal light is called "Abhaschaitanya" or "Chidabhas." In[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the maya and unawareness of creation, Consciousness is present in this way,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 represented by these eight names. In that, seven of those, being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indistinguishable in the Infinite-Consciousness-Nature, is not experienced in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 separate forms. Only the Abhaschaitanya or Chidabhas is experienced[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because it happens to work with the constructs of the mind. This[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Abhaschaitanya is not enmeshed in the workings of worldly life nor its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyment.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It can clearly be understood now that Santanu (samam vikarashunyam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tanuryarsya)[fn 1] is the Unchanging, beyond creation, Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness. He has two (wives)[fn 2] Prakriti. Ganga is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-Prakriti (gang brahmandam gacchati ity)[fn 3] and Satyavati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is the Matter-Prakriti (satyam chaitanyam vidyate adhitisthati yasyam)[fn 4].[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the above-mentioned Consciousness-Prakriti, the eight children are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 born: Ishvar, Vaishvanar, Birat, Praajna, Taijas, Vishva, Kutasthachaitanya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and Abhaschaitanya - these eight rays of Consciousness appear. In these,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 seven are not perceived (they are immersed in the waters of Ganga)[fn 5] -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 immersed in the flow of Consciousness. When the eighth (Devabrata)[fn 6],[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Abhaschaitanya, appears, then (Ganga)[fn 7] the Consciousness-Prakriti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Herself disappears, uniting with her own flow. That Abhaschaitanya is now[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 present as the supremely mighty one in this body (kingdom)[fn 8]. Even[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 though he works with the constructs of the mind, he does not rule over nor is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 he enmeshed in any of the enjoyment. The entire world (kingdom)[fn 9] is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manifested because of the light of this Abhaschaitanya (the power of Bhisma)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [fn 10].[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [fn 1 - 10: All of the parentheses and the text within are in the original.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The aforementioned three-guna-filled Matter-Nature (Satyavati)[fn 1], the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one who was spoken about in the introduction of this book, the one who by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Grace of Sadguru received his fire and perceived in Yonimudra the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Penetrating Knowledge which was established there, renounces the mad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 addiction and in order to unite with the Main King of the Universe, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beyond-creation, Satchitananda-filled, Brahman-Consciousness, she[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 becomes immersed in the practice of the Guru-instructed Kriya. By that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kriya, she experiences through the flow of Consciousness in the spine the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revelation of the six lotus-chakras located there (she meets Santanu)[fn 2].[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But because of the Abhaschaitanya (Devabrata Bhisma)[fn 3] still turning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 toward worldly enjoyment, she is unable to meet Him. Then, upon seeing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the disappointment of the Brahman-Consciousness (Santanu's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 disappointment)[fn 4], the Abhaschaitanya (Devabrata Bhisma)[fn 5][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renounces all worldly enjoyments and to prevent the disruption of this[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (5 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renunciation, decides to remain unattached (unmarried)[fn 6] from all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 physical shakti. In this way, the Abhaschaitanya (Devabrata Bhisma)[fn 7][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 turns Nature (Satyavati)[fn 8] inward and unites her with Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness (Santanu)[fn 9] and expresses his joy in that. When one turns[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the mind in this way by the Sadguru-instructed Kriya and, being established[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in renunciation, one directly experiences the eternal joyfulness of Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness. When human nature is united with Consciousness, then the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 part of foundation of the appearing body of creation called Mahattatva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (Chitrangada)[fn 10] is known, and along with that a sense of self-rulership[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 arises, which is called Aishwarik Ahamkara (Vichitravirya)[fn 11]. Then[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one sees oneself as the lord of creation, preservation and transformation of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this Universe. When this realization was complete in Rajarshi Janaka, he[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 said, "Oh, how incredible I am!! I bow to myself. There is no one equal to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 me. Without touching it with by body, I am containing this world." As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aho aham namasyahaham daksho nastiha matsamah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asamsprishya sharirena maya vishvam chiram dhritam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- [Ashtavakrasamhita - 2nd part - 13][fn 12][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [fn 1 - 11: All of the parentheses and the text within are in the original.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fn 12: The brackets and the reference within are in the original.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From this inner realization, the sense of Mahattatva eventually disappears[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and the feeling of that god-like Ahamkara remains. This sense is not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealed in the jiva. To experience the individual part of that Aishwarik[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ahamkara (bringing forth a son)[fn 1], the daughters of the knowledge-race[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the king Kashi (ranjan kashate ity Kashiraj, meaning, knowledge,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealing everything, by which he rules): amba - sense of experience,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ambika - sense of questioning or doubt, and ambalika - sense of certainty --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these three things come to being through the Chidabhas (Devabrata Bhisma)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [fn 2]. In that, amba - the sense of experience, ddesiring to unite with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fire in the area below the navel (Madraraj - mad ra: madra)[fn 3], leaves[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these other two to unite with that Aishwarik Ahamkara. The union with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 senses of doubt and certainty causes the Aishwarik Ahamkara to be lost.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Then by the Guru-given Knowledge of Insight (by Vedavyas)[fn 4], the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dhritarashtra-mind (dhritam rashtram yena)[fn 5] is experienced from the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sense of doubt. But inner doubt puts itself in sight of the eyes all the time -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this is why the mind also becomes restless and therefore cannot observe[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anything with steadiness. Seeing the mind being in a blind condition, by that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge of Insight, the Pandu-perception (non-descriptive, transparent)[fn[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 6] is born out of the sense of certainty. This perception can steadily observe[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all things; no thing can color it. It is always clean (Pandu)[fn 7], description-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 less.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [fn 1 - 7: All of these parentheses and the text within are in the original.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of the difference in qualities, sadhakas have divided this body into[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (6 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these four parts: upper, lower, front and back. The upper part is the northern[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 division, full of divine power and revealer of divine manifestations; the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 lower part is the southern division and the cause of delusionary madness.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The front part is the eastern division causing the pravritti-oriented[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 involvement and enjoyment of worldly things, and the back is the western[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 division, the nivritti-oriented renouncer of wordly enjoyment and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bestower of liberation. Even being blind, the mind still moves towards[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pravritti-driven pleasures of worldly life and is in the front (kingdom)[fn 1][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the body. And intellect, fearful of its own destruction if it mingles with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 any physical forces remains detached and in the back of the body (away from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the kingdom)[fn 2]. This intellect's field (wives)[fn 3] is the sushumna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 power located in the spine which is divided in two parts. The section above[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the navel has the ability to call forth divine forces - her name is Kunti (kun[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhatu ahvane)[fn 4] - and the segment below the navel has the power to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cause delusionary intoxication - her name is Madri (mad dhatu matta kara)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [fn 5]. Before Kunti is united with intellect (married to Pandu)[fn 6], she[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 calls forth the sun-god Surya by her ability, from which the very powerful[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Karna is born, settling between the eyebrows representing the door of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sushumna and ruling over the pravritti-causing front part of the body. Then,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 having united with intellect and now on the path revealed through intellect[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (her husband's permission)[fn 7], because of having no relations, she calls[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 forth the king of righteousness Yama and gives birth to the steady and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 righteous ether-element (Yudhisthira)[fn 8] in the area of the throat in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vishuddhakhya lotus; then she calls to her the force of the incredibly mighty[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 wind-god Pavana, which gives birth to the frighteningly powerful air-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 element (Bhima)[fn 9] in the Anahata lotus in the heart; and then by the seed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the supremely fiery, containing all qualities Indra, the fire-element[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (Arjuna)[fn 10] is born, the one excellent in all talents, in the lotus named[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Manipura, located in the area of the navel. Later, when by intelligence that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shakti goes below the navel area (teaching the mantra to Madri at her[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 husband's request)[fn 11], with the seed of the extremely beautiful[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ashwinikumar, at once the water-element (Nakula)[fn 12] is born in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Swadhisthana chakra in the area of the sex organ, and the earth element[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (Sahadeva)[fn 13] takes birth in the Muladhara chakra located in the area of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the anus. Enjoying the beauty of these five elements in his field (his wives)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [fn 14], because of the power of delusionary intoxication under the navel (in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Madri)[fn 15], the intellect embraces her and according to natural ways[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (because of the previous curse)[fn 16], intellect is destroyed, and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 delusionary power (Madri seeing herself as the cause of the her husband's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 death)[fn 17], dies herself with intellect (sahamrita)[fn 18]. In this way, after[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the destruction of the delusionary power through her union with intellect, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 five elements establish themselves as rulers of their individual chakras, from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Muladhar to the Vishuddha with their specific divine powers.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Then, the five elements (returning to the kingdom)[fn 1] becoming present in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body, with the characteristics of mind including vanity etc.(the sons of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dhritarashtra as in Duryodhana - durdu-stam yudham yasya - the ability to[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (7 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fight in an evil way)[fn 2], and accompanied by grace (krip)[fn 3] and its kin[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shakti (kripipati)[fn 4], come to know the particulars - samskaras - of bodily[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 life. These particulars are extremely powerful and very important in worldly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 life. Under these particulars, people do every kind of work. No one can do[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 any work beyond these. But when the element of highest importance, fire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (Arjuna)[fn 5] is revealed, through his fire and by the many Guru-given[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 methods one can become more powerful than these samskaras. When this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fire element (Arjuna)[fn 6] is about to realize its fire, the duties of worldly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 life (Kuntidevi's illegitimate son Karna)[fn 7] appear at his side (the pravritti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 part of the nivritti side)[fn 8]. The mental ways with vanity etc.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (Duryodhana and his group)[fn 9] then take the power of Karna and in order[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to cause trouble in one's duty (the obtaining of the kingdom)[fn 10], apply[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 many kinds of trickeries.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [fn 1 - 10: All of these parentheses and the text within them are in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 original.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, the five elements, having lost to the pravritti side - meaning the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 power of Karna, their own brother at the front-facing twin-petaled lotus,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 whose power is being used by the constructs of the mind - spend twelve very[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 difficult years in brahmacharya, studying etc. Then for one more year, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 spend time immersed in the godly Consciousness present in maya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (anonymously in the kingdom of Birat)[fn 1], meaning remain in the sadhana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 for liberation from Birat. Then after coming out, they try to reclaim their[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 own kingdom with the help of Sri Krishna. Now, the Supreme Person in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scripture is Sri Krishna Chaitanya. Meditating on Him, it is known that He[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 resides in the bosom of Radha. Sa, ra and ee - the word "sri" is sounded by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these three letters. And "Krishna" is a separate word. Sa - beneficent, ra -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 seed of fire, ee - shakti and Krishna is dark. When these are put together it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 can be understood that the fire element, meaning the dark form that is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealed by the beneficent power of fire in the bosom of the lightning/[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 electric form of Radhika - that is Sri Krishna. In other words, when one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 takes the fire filled with the sattvic guna up to a place between the eyebrows[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (it an be known from the mouth of Guru)[fn 2], the physical lightning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (animal electricity)[fn 3] collects in stillness and becomes like a flame and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 instantly a dark circle appears in the middle of that lightning. That is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Krishna or the third eye. The Consciousness that is present there is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by saints as Kutasthachaitanya or Sri Krishna Chaitanya. The entire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe is in this Kutasthachaitanya. When this is established, this infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe is experienced as if in the palm of one's own hand and nothing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 remains unknown.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [fn 1 - 2: The parentheses and the text within are in the original.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fn 3: The parentheses and the text within in English are in the original.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, this first sloka is like this: as in - After having established the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge of Insight from Sadguru and having taken the help of[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (8 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya (Sri Krishna)*, what are the mental constructs and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 five elements from the field of intellect who have come together in this field[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the body doing? To observe this, the king of the imagination of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world, mind, is using his own divine sight.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *The parentheses and the text within are in the original.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sanjay said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dristvatu pandavanikam byudham duryodhanastada[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 acharyamupasangamya raja vachanamabrabit - 2 -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pashyaitam panduputranamacharyamahatim chamum[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 byudham drupadapudtrena taba shishyeana dhimata - 3 -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 These words did Sanjay hear from the king[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With respectfulness to Dhritarashtra said he[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the line of battle do I see the Pandavas and Duryodhana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 To the acharya then they went and spoke[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The pandava soldiers are a great many[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Look at the battlefield acharya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Your servant the magnanimous Dhrishtadyumna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now will take care of the story of the battlefield[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The events surrounding Dhrishtadyumna's birth in the Mahabharata is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 written in this way: Because of Drona humiliating the king Drupada through[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Drona's disciples, the king Drupada invited several sages and performed a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fire ritual to kill Drona. From that, one son and one daughter came about.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The daughter's name was Draupadi, and the son's name was[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dhrishtadyumna. The spiritual significance of this is (krip's sister's husband[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is Drona; the substance of krip is imagination; with kin shakti the result is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fire) that when one is enslaved by samskaras, and by the quickening force of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Consciousness-revealing Kriya (drupada) disrespect to the king is born in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the jiva, then it is necessary to take the company of saints; because, by that,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the speedy force again takes place and establishes Kriya in order to destroy[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samskaras. By that, restlessness is subdued and a Consciousness-Light is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealed, and right alongside that the kundalini shakti is experienced. This[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kundalini shakti is Draupadi and this Consciousness-Light is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dhrishtadyumna (dharshanena dyuh jyotih vidyate yasya). Now, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning of the sloka is like this, as in:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, through divine sight, mind observes that: the primary element of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the pravritti side, vanity/egoism, upon seeing the happenings on the back part[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the body, meaning, the happenings on the nivritti side by the power of[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (9 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kriya with the six chakras, five elements and the rest of the company of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nivritti, feels that without samskaras no one can ever do any work. Methods[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or techniques are all learned via the particulars of living in the world. This[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world-guru is samskara-educated (disciple of Drona). After the subjugation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of restlessness via the fast, quickening force of the Consciousness-revealing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kriya, by the Tranquil Light (the son of Drupada, Dhrishtadyumna) the six[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chakras are revealed, and the five elements with their company are in their[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 places. - 2 and 3 -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atrashuramaheshvasa bhimarjunasama yudhi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yuyudhano biratashcha drupadashcha maharathah - 4 -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhrishtaketushchekitanah kashirajashcha viryaban[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purujit kuntibhojashcha shayvyashcha narapungavah -5 -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yudhamanyushcha vikranta uktamoujashcha viryavan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 soubhadro draupadeyashcha sarva eva maharathah - 6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [no poetical version in the original][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is written in the Patanjal shastra that those who, through the power of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 discrimination, see the world as an illusion and keep themselves in only Soul-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness, and those who, experiencing the Universe as the Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Itself, experience themselves as pervading the Universe - the sages in these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 states attain Kaivalya by themselves, without the aid of anyone or anything.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But for the ordinary rest, in order to attain that state it is necessary to have[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the help of reverence, vigor, memory, absorption, inner knowledge and such[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 methods, and by using speedy force to manifest these, the work is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 accomplished rapidly. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the Patanjal Yogasutra Samadhipada:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhavapratyayo videhaprakritilayanam - no. 19[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sraddhaviryasmritisamadhiprajnapurvakamitaresham - no. 20[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tivrasambeganamasannah - no. 21[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Along with these: yama, niyama, asana, pranayam, pratyahara, dharana,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhyana, samadhi - when the impurity-dispelling knowledge is illuminated[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 through the technique of this eight-limbed yoga, discrimination is established[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and the cause of all harm - ignorance - is destroyed, and by this Kaivalya is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attained. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In Patanjal Yogasutra Sadhanapada:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasya heturvidya - no. 24[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tadbhavat samyogobhavo hanantaddrishyeh kaivalyam - no. 25[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vivekakhyatirviplava hanopaya - no. 26[m
