[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yoganganushthanajashuddhikshaye jnanadiptiravivaka khyateh - no. 28[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yamaniyamasana-pranayama-pratyahara-dharana-dhyana-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samadhayorshtavangani -no.29[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, if we leave the outer form, the methods mentioned by Patanjal is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealed in these three slokas. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yuyudhan (in the battle, meaning the desire to do the Consciousness-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealing Kriya) reverence.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 uttamouja (excellent vigor, meaning fire-endowed) vigor.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chekitan (consciousness, the substance of which is knowing) memory.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 birat (to prevail in the Soul, meaning becoming immersed) absorption.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kashiraj (the one who is revealed after having revealed the world) inner[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 drupada (endowed with fast motion) speedy force.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhrishtaketu (technique to destroy harm) yama.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahimsasatyasteya brahmacharyaparigrahah yamah. -- Patanjal Sadhanapada -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 no. 5[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When ahimsa [physical and mental non-meanness or non-violence (mental[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and physical)] is manifested, meaning when no meanness ever arises in ones[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind, then these types of people have no enmity with anyone. Violent and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aggressive animals such as tigers and bears remain docile towards these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beings. When meanness and aggression are forgotten for life, a beautiful[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 radiance arises whose qualities of trustworthiness and deep contentment are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 seen in the eyes of and experienced by even violent and aggressive animals.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, not even a hint of aggression arises in their minds. This is written in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Mahabharata. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abhayam sarvabhutebhyo datva yashchayate munih[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na tasya sarvabhutetya bhayamutpadyate kvachit[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shaiva (the beneficent) niyama.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shouchasantoshatapah svadhyayeshvana pranidhanani niyamah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kuntibhoja (the state in which one can attract divine powers) asana.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yudhamanyu (battle, meaning the one whose Kriya is the revelation of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness) pranayam.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purujit (meaning the one who is victorious over the god of the senses)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pratyahara.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 soubhadra abhimanyu (the revealer of all divine manifestations) the union of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dharana, dhyana and samadhi, meaning samyama.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 trayamekatra samyama -- Patanjal Bibhutipada - no. 4[m
