[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And the kulakundalini shakti, united with the five elements manifests the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 five points, by which the mind becomes absorbed. These extremely[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 powerful faculties, as in the air element, fire element and such, in steadfast[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 faith are presiding with great might. - 4, 5, and 6 -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asmakantu vishishta ye tannibodha dvijottam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nayaka mama sainyasya samjnanartham tan brabimi te - 7 -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhavan bhismashcha karnashcha kripashcha samitinjayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ashvatthama vikarnashcha soumadattirjayadratha* - 8 -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [*Translator's note: In some versions of the Gita, the last line of sloka eight[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reads: "ashvathvama vikarnashcha soumadattis tathaiva cha." The version[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being translated here mentions "Jayadratha." The footnoted version just[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mentioned does not.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The greatest of our soldiers[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Listen guru to their names[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The primary charioteers of our soldiers[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I present them for you to hear -7-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 You and Bhisma, Karna, Krip - great warriors[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The son of Drona, Vikarna, Jayadratha and Bhurishrava -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The five kleshas [troubles], karma and its detrimental consequence -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samskara, and ambition, meaning desires -- these ones are the great obstacles[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 on the path of liberation. Regarding this, it is written in the Patanjal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 philosophical treatises that the one who cannot be touched by the five[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kleshas -- namely avidya [ignorance/illusion], asmita [egoism], raag[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [passion], dvesh [hatred] and abhinibesh [attachment], as well as karma with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 its detrimental consequences -- is God. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avidyasmitaragadveshacinibeshah panchakleshah -- Sadhanapada - no. 3[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kleshakarmavipakashaiyeraparamristah purushavishesha ishvarah --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Samadhipada - no. 24[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, if we leave the outer form, these eight great obstacles on the path of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 liberation mentioned by Patanjal will be revealed in these two slokas. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Krip (krip whose essence is to imagine) - This imagination is the foe of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge and is the source of all of the kleshas. By this, the one is deluded[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 into perceiving the finite as infinite, the impure as pure, misery as happiness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the non-soul as soul. This is the primary klesha of the five kleshas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mentioned by Patanjal. Its name is "avidya." As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (12 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anityashuchiduhkhanatmasu nityashuchisukhatmakhyatirvidya --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sadhanapada - no.5[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It has been clearly shown in the commentary to the first sloka that Bhisma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (Chidabhas) is a type of consciousness, the observer of this world and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 inner light of a jiva, without which nothing can be seen by the jiva.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore he is the power of perception. In this consciousness both of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 qualities of observation and perception are existent. Because of this, the jiva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is entrapped in the worldly matters. This is the second klesha mentioned by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Patanjal. Its name is "asmita." As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 drikadarshanashaktorekatmataivasmita -- Sadhanapada - no.6[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Karna (kri-na): dutiful work. One can have sublime happiness in worldly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 life if one can do this dutiful work. Because of this, the mind has great[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 affection for it. This is the third klesha mentioned by Patanjal. It's name is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "raag." As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 duhkhanushayi raagah -- Sadhanapada - no. 7[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vikarna (vi-kri-na): work that is not one's duty. Because of this, one has to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 suffer much in worldly life. Therefore, the mind quite detests it. This is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fourth klesha mentioned by Patanjal. It's name is "dvesh." As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 duhkhanushayi dveshah -- Sadhanapada - no. 8[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Jayadratha (residing in affection with doership) - he is "Sindhuraj," the king[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the ocean of the world, meaning the primary reason for being enchained to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 worldly life. Great knowledgeable beings do not want to leave the body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because of this inclination; they want to remain bound to the body. This is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the fifth klesha mentioned by Pantanjal. It's name is "abhinibesh." As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 svarasabahividushopi tamvanubandhohbhinibeshah -- Sadhanapada - no. 9[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The son of Somadatta, Bhurishrava (who is continuously deteriorating):[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karma. About this subject, here is what is written in the book, "Atmajnana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Nirnaya": Whether it is good or bad, if at one point karma is not finally[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 worn away and finished, the jiva will not be liberated, not in innumerable[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ages. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yavanna kshiyate karmashubhanchashubhameva ba[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tavanna jayate mokshah nrisham kalpashatairapi[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The union of Drona (the liquid form of karma, meaning samskara) and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 power of imagination (Kripi) give rise to desire. It is this bondage to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samskara (the detrimental consequence of karma) that causes the jiva to[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (13 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 travel from womb to womb and acquire lifespan and pleasure accordingly.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In Patanjal, this is what is written about the subject: as in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 satimule tadvipako jatyaurbhogah -- Sadhanapada - no. 13[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ashvatthama (that which is stored and is not destroyed with the body):[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desire. It is because of this desire that the body of a jiva is created again.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Even at the end of ages there is no destruction of it. The world is appears[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because of the presence of desire in the three-guna-filled Prakriti. It is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 referred to as "anadi" in Patanjal. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasamanaditvanchashishe nityatvat -- Kaivalyapada - no. 10[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 These faculties, as significant characters on the side of the worldly life of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pravritti, are standing as adversaries to nivritti, meaning the forms of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 obstacles to liberation. - 7 and 8 -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anye cha bahavah shura madarthe tyaktajivitah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nanashastrapraharanah sarve yuddhavisharadah - 9 -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Many others of eminence and valor[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Doing everything possible because of me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Numerous weapons and mastery of them[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All great mighty ones supremely skilled at war -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There are many who are ready to surrender their lives in order to rescue ego/[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vanity on the side of pravritti. They are skilled at destroying the side of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 five elements via many different methods. - 9 -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aparyaptam tadasmakam balam bhismabhirakshitam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 paryaptam tvidametesham balam bhimabhirakshitam - 10 -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bhisma's is the power for my soldiers[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But these soldiers seem weak[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Pandavas‚Äô strength lies in Bhima[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 They seem ready to triumph -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (14 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
