[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Krishna sounded His conch shell, "Panchajanya"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Falguni [Arjuna] sounded his conch shell, "Devadatta"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The conch named "Poundra" which was great in size[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Was sounded by Bhimsen [Bhima] on whom is this great task -15-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Yudhisthira Maharaj, the son of Kunti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Trumpeted fully the conch shell "Anantavijaya"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Nakula blew the one called "Sughosh"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sahadeva sounded the "Manipushpa" conch shell -16-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The mighty Kashiraj, the strong Shikhandi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dhrishtadyumna, Birat and Satyaki - extraordinarily powerful -17-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Drupada, and the sons of Draupadi, the valorous son of Subhadra[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All blew their respective conches, O king -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the earth element presiding in the Muladhar, the Pranava is[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (16 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experienced as the sound of mad bumblebees. When this is heard, sadhakas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 know that attunement has happened in that area. In this state, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 questioning faculty of mind is dominant, and therefore, the question "Is this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pranava or not?" is present. It is because of this that this state is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Savitarka [in argument] Samprajnata Samadhi."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 After the attainment of the aforementioned sound of bumblebees, from the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 water element presiding in the Svadhisthana a sound like that of a flute is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experienced. This is the sign of the state known as "Savichar [observation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with enquiry] Samprajnata Samadhi." When the absorbed state of sadhakas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 elevates a little and the doubting faculty has been destroyed, from the faculty[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of certainty arises the enquiry, "What type of a thing is this Pranava?"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the fire element presiding in the Manipura, the Pranava is experienced[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 like that of the delightful sound of a vina (Indian stringed lute). This is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sign of "Sananda [joyful] Samprajnata Samadhi." When the absorption of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhakas has elevated to this state, the faculties of doubting and certainty are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dissolved, and by experiential consciousness one experiences the meaning of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pranava and an unspeakable bliss arises.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Through focused Kriya, from the air element presiding in the Anahata lotus,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 a profound sound like that of a long-sustaining bell is experienced. In this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pranava all of these internal faculties are dissolved and, because of the still[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 remaining Ahamakara, by Asmita is this God-spoken Pranava-resonance[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experienced. Hearing this, sadhakas know that they have ascended to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Sasmita [blossoming] Samprajnata Samadhi."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the ether element in the all-important sushumna, victorious over all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 faculties, the Pranava expresses Itself like that of the sound of thunder. In[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this sound, even Asmita is annihilated and the entire Universe is experienced[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 as filled with Brahman and the perception of separateness in Nature is at[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 once dissolved. When this arises, sadhakas know that they have arrived at[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samadhi's highest, seedless state, or Asamprajnata Samadhi. When one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ascends to this state, no form of samskara can emerge.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Then, the mad bumblebees, flute, vina, long-sustaining bell and thunder -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these five types of sound become one, and from that all-revealing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya an unspeakable resonance of Pranava rises and from the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness presiding in the different main nadis, many different types of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sound spring forth.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The above-mentioned states of Asamprajnata and the four types of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Samprajnata samadhis, the sushumna nadi etc., the six chakras and their[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 respective elements, and the many different types of Pranava-sound -- these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are all matters of direct experience; they cannot be acquired by indirect[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge. It is useless to try to make onne understand this through writing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or any other method. Without experiencing this oneself, there is no way of[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (17 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 understanding it. However, some help in awareness may be possible by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shastras, as I will explain below.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 On the subject of the six chakras, studying the science of physiology from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this country and the West one comes to know that the brain, meaning the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sahasradal lotus, is the place of Total Consciousness. Under the brain and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 above the spinal column, there is a nadi (medulla) located between the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eyebrows formed like the shape of the back of a tortoise. When one has total[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 absorption - samyama - in that tortoise-nadi, then immediately restlessness is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eradicated and a tranquil Light prevails. About this subject, here is what is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 written in the Patanjal philosophical treatises: as in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kurmanadyam sthairyam -- Bibhutipada - no. 32[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is signified by being two-petaled (pons varoli). This the Ajna Chakra.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Through this, the mind enters the sushumna. This is the door of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sushumna. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhyanatma sadhakendra bhavatiparpure ityadi -- Shatachakra - no. 35[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Like a string, that tortoise-nadi extends through the center of the spinal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 column to the area of the anus. That is called "sushumna" (spinal cord). To[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the left of it, one named "ida," and to the right of it, one named[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "pingala" (gangliatid cords of sympathetic nerves) -- two very powerful[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nadis on either side of the spinal column extend from the area of the anus up[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to the back of the area of the eyes. The consciousnesses present in these two[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nadis (the presiding gods Moon and Sun, respectively) are responsible for the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 functioning of blood circulation, digestion, the intake of physical substances,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 urination and excretion, breathing etc. These consciousnesses are only a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reflection of the Moon and Sun forms in the sushumna. Because of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Primordial Shakti Kulakundalini being asleep at the bottom of the sushumna,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the aforementioned blood circulation, digestion, breathing etc. are works that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are not under the control of the jiva. The jiva is not able to willfully stop or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 start those functions. Mind is unable to enter the sushumna via the two-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 petaled lotus and therefore faces front. Because of this neither the sushumna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nor any of the sixty-thousand nadis extending from it are under the control of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the jiva. They are operated by their own gods that preside within them, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the jiva controls by his own will the nadis in the front. This is why in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scriptures, the saints call the back part "purusha" and the front part[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "prakriti." That prakriti, being dominant, tries always to cover up the jiva's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness. When this prakriti finds the jiva's consciousness to be weak[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 for any reason and veil it, through the united power of the all samskaras[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (resultant force), the jiva again takes birth according to where that samskara-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 power is attracted. In this way, the jiva, who is a part of that Infinite All-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Powerful Satchitananda-filled Brahman-Consciousness, goes through endless[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 suffering through birth, death etc. This behavior of prakriti is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "stree" [wife or woman]. Now, with the spiritual sense destroyed, the sense[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (18 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that -- when a daughter is born from the marriage and physical union of man[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and woman, and the daughter is preferred over the husband - "the daughter is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 more important" -- this sensibility is shown. But if even through the veil of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this body the purusha catches the beneficent glance of prakriti, then the eyes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meet and become mesmerized. Filled with this feeling, the visionary[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vaishnavas sing:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Oh behold, eyes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The delight of the lovers - Radha and her Beloved[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Oh behold, eyes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Dark One - the new rain-cloud, and Radha, His lightning[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, when this type of beneficent glance occurs, prakriti gives up her need[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and reason to be dominant and, renouncing her behavior, becomes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enraptured in ecstasy. It is in this that union of prakriti and purusha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happens. This is what is called "yoga." With the Sadguru-graced Kriya, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind, in a subtle form, passes through that door-like Ajna chakra and enters[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the sushumna by which the Kulakundalini Shakti is awakened. That[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sushumna functions in five divisions. Through the Kriya of the Sadguru-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 initiated sadhakas, the five distinctions in the sushumna are eventually and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gradually experienced as five lotuses in the forms of chakras. At the area of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the anus at the bottom of the spinal column - the four-petaled lotus[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Muladhar, at the root of the sex organ - the six-petaled lotus Svadhisthana, at[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 area of the navel - the ten-petaled lotus Manipura, in the heart - the twelve-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 petaled lotus Anahata and the sixteen-petaled lotus in the area of the throat --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these chakras along with their respective elements: earth, water, fire, air and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ether -- the awakened Kulakundalini expeeriences them when they are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealed. When that Primordial Shakti is awakened in the Muladhar, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mad buzzing of bumblebees is heard and the state of absorption comes into[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being, and when that chakra is pierced, the sound is heard like that of a flute[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 upon arriving at the Svadhisthana. In this way, as the sadhaka's states of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samadhi evolve from one to another, piercing through the chakras one by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one, through the different sounds of the Pranava the mind, intellect, small[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness and ego are eventually dissolved. These states have been[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 expounded upon previously. Thus, the jiva-consciousness becomes free of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body of five elements and becomes completely purified. This process is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 called "Bhuta-shuddhi." Later, when by the practices under Guru's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 instructions those sixty-thousand nadis' gods come under control, one can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 leave the workings of the body to them, meaning that one can become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 detached and separate oneself while keeping the body awake and alive and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reside in God. Then, after leaving the sushumna and arriving at the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sahasradal lotus - the place of Total Consciousness - one becomes united[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with the Satchitananda-filled Brahman-Consciousness and the Self-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge "This Infinite Universe is Me" is revealed. Therefore, there[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being nothing that exists separately to experience, Pranava, life, nothing is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experienced. -15, 16, 17 and 18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (19 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sa ghosho dhartarashtranam hridayani vyadarayat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nabhashcha prithivinchaiva tumulohabhyanunadayan -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Immense - that sound filling earth and sky[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Tearing hearts of Duryodhana‚Äôs side -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the earth element in the Muladhar to the space element presiding in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 throat, all of these sounds come together and tear apart the congregation of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mental constructs. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atha vyavasthitan dristva dhartarashtran kapidhvajah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pravritte shastrasampate dhanurudyamya pandavah -20-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hrishikesham tada vakyamidamaha mahipate[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 senayorubhayormadhye ratham sthapaya mehachyuta -21-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yavadetan nirikshehaham yoddhukamanvasthitan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kairmaya saha yoddhavyamasmin ranasamudyame -22-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yotsyamananavekshyehaham ya etehatre samagatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhartarashtrasya durbuddheryuddhe priyachikiryavah -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna, seeing the Kauravas on the battlefield[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With their weapons -- picked up his own bow and arrow -20-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Said he this, O king, to Krishna,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Lord, please stop this chariot between the two armies -21-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All these noblemen ready for war[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Let me observe who they all are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With whom will I be engaged in this confrontation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Let me see all of them at the onset of this battle -22-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 These valorous ones who are here to fight[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Are here because of Duryodhana's malintention[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 They have come here to this battle site[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Let me observe all of these mighty ones -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, sensing the positions of the mental faculties, by the power of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fire element at the two-petaled lotus in the middle of the eyebrows which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reveals the bow/lingam of Mahadeva, transcending the spinal column[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (20 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (gandiva - ganda iva - like a knot) by Kriya, this type of desire occurs - that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "let me once see with full consciousness the evil-minded side of ego/vanity[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (otherwise, the need for Kriya is not there for the Eternally Awakened[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Jiva)." Who have come here against the five elements, during the practice of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 his [the sadhaka‚Äôs] beloved work? -20, 21, 22 and 23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evamukto hrishikesho gudakeshen bharata[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 senayorubhayormadhye sthapayita rathottamam -24-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhismadrona pramukhatah sarvoshancha mahikshitam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 uvaca partha pashyeitan samavetan kuruniti -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sanjay said, now listen, O king[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 These words of Arjuna did the Lord hear[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The best and most excellently made,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the midst of the two armies, this chariot He placed -24-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bhisma, Drona, so many more noblemen[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The chariot was positioned in front of them[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Look, Dhananjaya!" said the Lord[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "At the Kaurava military assembled" -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When, with this type of desire, the force of that delusion-vanquishing fire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 element situates itself within these parties, Chidabhas and samskara - the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world's guru - are experienced as the primarily presiding ones along with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 others of the opposition in the Presence of Kutasthachaitanya. -24 and 25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatrapashyatasthitan partha pitrinath pitamahan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 acharyanmatulan bhratrin putran pautran sakhimstatha*[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shashuran suhridaschaiva senayorubhayorapi -26-**[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tan samikshya sa kaunteyah sarvan bandhunabsthitan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kripaya parayavishto vishidannidamabrabit -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 drishtveman svajanan krishna yuyutsun samavasthitan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sidanti mama gatrani mukhancha parishushyati -28-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vepathushcha sharire me romaharshashcha jayate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gandivam sramsate hastat tvak chaiva paridhyate -29-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na cha shaknomyavasthatum bhramativa cha me manah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nimittani cha pashyami viparitani keshava -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [*Important note: The numbering of the slokas in this chapter from this[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (21 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 point on can differ in various renditions of the Gita. In some popular[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 versions, the asterisked point marks the completion of the 26th sloka. In this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 version of the Gita, the sloka is not completed until the next line. Therefore,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in some Gitas, the total number of slokas in the first chapter is 47, whereas in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this version of the Gita, the total number of slokas is 46. However, the total[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 text in either type of the Gita is the same. There are no omissions. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 apparent unevenness of this sloka 26 is balanced out in sloka number 36,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being another three-line sloka. It is necessary to point this out since readers[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 might be following this translation with either the Sanskrit or transliterations[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of other versions of the scripture and the numbers may not coincide.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 **In some Gitas, this line is the first line of sloka 27, as previously[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mentioned.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Among those soldiers were many of the paternal side[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Grandfathers, teachers and maternal uncles[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Nephews, grandsons, companions, in-laws and others of one's own[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In that place did Arjuna see -26-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna, observing his friends present there[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Said with much compassion and pathos -27-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I see all have come desiring war[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Paralyzed is my body and dry is my mouth -28[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 My body trembles with hair standing on end[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The bow slips from my hand and my skin is burning -29-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am unsteady, my mind feels this is a mistake[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Krishna, the reason for this I see as gravely contradictory -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The cause of the endless appearances of births is represented by the father[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 figure Bhurishrava/karma, along with the Abhaschaitanya as the grandfather,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samskaras as guru, the maternal uncles being the faculties of attachment and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 obsession from Madraraj, vanity/ego being like brothers, race/class-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness as sons, grandsons being offsprings of that race/class-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness, the elders/Ashvatthama representing desires, Drupada, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 father of the Kundalini Shakti Draupadi, as the father-in-law, meaning the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 speedy force, and many other benevolent faculties are present among this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 opposing side. When this is experienced in the energy of the fire element,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one succumbs to maya, becomes depressed and dry-mouthed while the body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is rendered not wanting to do anything. The body shakes and chills run[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 through it leading to the feeling that the body is on fire. The spinal column[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is not accessible. Even the patience to sit still is shattered and the stability of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind is ruined. These types of troublesome signs point to a lower state of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being. -26, 27, 28, 29 and 30-[m
[32m+[m
