[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Killing kin will bring the death of all virtue[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Killing virtue leads all lineages to immoral ways -39-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The sin of family will corrupt the women of the line[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   When the women are evil then half-breeds will be born, O Lord -40-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The family and those who slay kin[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   For this, all, with their half-breeds, go to hell[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   No more the offerings of food to them[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Their forefathers fall from grace -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The slaying of kin brings about the destruction of the forever practiced[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   universal codes of familial behavior, meaning the end of the enjoyment of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   physical things experienced by sight, touch, etc. The presiding family will[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   be overcome with that which is outside the codes and the physical experience[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   will be nothing. When the physical experience becomes nothing, those[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   powers of sight and touch will become corrupt and many kinds of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   delusionary experiences will arise. Because of these delusionary[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   occurrences, the five elements who are responsible for the destruction of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   sensory experience face grave danger from mind, intellect, karma etc. having[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   lost the things that kept them alive. -39, 40 and 41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   dosheiretaih kulaghnanam varnasankarakaih[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   utsadyante jatidharmah kuladharmashcha shashvatah -42-[m
