[32m+[m[32m                                 has turned away and is Kriya-less, it would be a good thing inndeed.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thinking in this way, the fire element renounced his power and sat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 downheartedly and impotently in the body. -45 and 46-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ity srimadbhagavadgitayam padabodhineevrittou prathamohadhyah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [End of first chapter][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   SUMMARIZED DESCRIPTION:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The usual practice is that things that are necessary to know in the beginning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   without which a book may be difficult to understand are often stated in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   "introduction" section in the book. But this practice is not common in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Sanskrit scriptures. The Sanskrit scholars presented those matters in the first[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   chapter. Following this custom, the first chapter of the Srimad Bhagavad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Gita is an introduction only. The kind of state in which it becomes necessary[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   to read this Gita is what is written in this first chapter.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   When Kutasthachaitanya is established through the practice of Sadguru-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   instructed Kriya, one no longer wishes to partake in societal functions which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   are full of disease, uncertainty, confusion, indolence, illusion, the ceaseless[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   nature of it all, and throwing away all of these, he has no more desire to take[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   part in winter, summer, sorrow etc. and the innumerable conflicts and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   endless suffering because of them. Wanting to leave these things behind,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   one desires to immerse oneself to attain the Endless Universe of that Infinite,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   All-Powerful, Infinite Knowledge and Eternally Blissful Brahman.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   For this reason, to become aware of the faculties of pravritti and nivritti in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   the body, the sadhakas use mental divine sight, meaning the eye of wisdom[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   and see that the five elements on the nivritti side, having been educated by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   the world-guru samskara, are revealed by the disturbance-vanquishing[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (27 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Tranquil Light to be presiding in the six chakras, and are beckoning with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 their mighty and powerful comrades: reverence, creative energy, memory,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 absorption, wisdom, quickening, yama, niyama, asana, pranayam,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pratyahara, dharana, samadhi, samyama and the Kundalini Shakti awakened[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by the power of the five elements giving rise to the five points etc. On the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pravritti side, the clans of mind and ego along with their faculties -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ignorance, conceit, passion, hatred, attachment, karma, samskara, desires and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 other such primary ones are positioned to stand in the way of liberation,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ready to use many kinds of methods and tricks. Even so, the pravritti side is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 well aware of their inferiority in power in comparison to the abilities of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nivritti side, and thereby carefully placing themselves in their own stations of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 strength in the senses, along with self-consciousness and ego are making the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body ring with their own sounds. At this, on the nivritti side, from the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Muladhar the earth element's mad buzzing of bees, from the Svadhisthana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the water element's flute, from the Manipura the fire element's vina, from the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Anahata the air element's long-sustaining bell, from the Vishuddha the ether[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 element's thunder, and from the Kutasthachaitanya the five Pranava sounds --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all unite and an unspeakably beautiful sound arises, along with different[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sounds from different nadis, and by this, mind, iintellect, small[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness, ego and their cohort faculties are being decimated. When this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experience happens, for the vanquishing of the pravritti side, by the power of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the fire element Mahadeva appears in the middle of the eyebrows and upon[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ascending the spinal column and ready to apply Kriya, a desire comes up to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 observe the ones on the opposing side. Thus, revealed by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya, one sees that the opposing side is Chidabhas, samskara,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karma, desire, vanity etc. who have been lifelong companions; seeing which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the fire element becomes heart-broken, the mouth becomes dry, chills run[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 through the body, and sweating and trembling, the spinal column wilts and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the mind becomes restless and impatient. Even if one dies by the hands of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these lifelong companions who have given one sensory pleasures, one cannot[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 destroy or abandon them. They are the foes of this Kriya. What of rulership[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of this small body, even for rulership of this Universe in the midst of Infinity[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 we do not think it right to destroy or renounce this worldly happiness. If[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they are destroyed, what is the need of our rulership at all, and what is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 need of life even? We cannot possibly become happy in any way by this and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 there is significant danger in that as well. Destroying the always prevalent[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sensory experience or renouncing it can bring about delusions by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 corrupted imagination of the powers of sight, touch and other sensual[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 faculties and that will result in deprivation of food for the five elements,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind, intellect etc., which will bring about their ruin. Although these virtues[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of race and religion are not a concern of the murderous side of the ego,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 having experienced all this via the five elements, how can we proceed with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this kind of work? Alas, alas! What a terribly unholy work we were[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prepared to do! "Let these five elements be destroyed." Thinking thus, in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this despondent state of the fire element, the sadhakas settle themselves,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renouncing Kriya.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter1.html (28 of 29)4/18/2006 2:41:58 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the first chapter of the yogashastra upanishad Srimad Bhagavad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gita with analysis via various scriptures of this country and the West, along[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with spiritual commentary.[m
