[32m+[m[32m                                 CHAPTER TWO[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 SAMKHYAYOGA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Sanjay said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       tam tatha kripyavishtamasrupurnakulekshanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vishadantamidam vakyamuvacha madhusudanan -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kutastva kashmalamidam vishame samupasthitam[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            anaryajushtamasvargyamakirtikaramarjuna -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sanjay said, listen O king[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction                     Immersed in compassion was Dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Broken-hearted and overcome, eyes filled with tears[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        To him this said the Lord -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        Why has this delusion befallen you in the midst of war[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        That which is done be the lowly and ignorant[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        Illusion of this kind destroys virtue[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5                        And brings disgrace, listen O son of Kunti -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        In this state, through the eye of wisdom, one becomes aware that as the fire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 element of the sadhakas, despondent over the destruction of the familial[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mental faculties, is filled with compassion for them, at that time, this type of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 understanding emerges from the Kutasthachaitanya - that it is undutiful to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 turn away from the Consciousness-revealing Kriya because of the terrible[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enemies residing in the body; these who are ignorant and unrighteous wrong-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 doers. -1 and 2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (1 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  klaivam masma gamah partha naitat tvayuppadyate[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  khudram hridayadourbalam taktvottishtha paramtapa -3-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  Do not become weak O son of Kunti[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  Never is this befitting you[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  Trivial it is, this weakness of mind[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  Abandon it Partha, and get up and fight -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is not befitting for this highest-of-all human life to succumb to slavery[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 under the senses and become like an animal by destroying one's soul-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness. One's duty is to abandon this trivial weakness of the heart[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and perform the Consciousness-revealing Kriya. -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 katham bhishmaham samkhye dronancha madhusudan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ishubhih pratiyotsyami pujarharvarisudan -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said, Sri Madhusudan listen[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The venerable Bhisma, Drona and others are here[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 How can I fire my arrows in this battle Lord[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Great is the sin even with these clever words -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When this type of awareness occurs, it is again experienced by the fire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 element that: under the power of Chidabhas we are existing in this form of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva, and by the power of the samskara we have become as mighty as we are;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 now, how can we go on to destroy by Kriya the highly revered Chidabhas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and samskara? -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gurunahatva hi mahanubhavan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sreyo bhoktum bhaikshyamapihaloke[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hatvarthakamamstu gurunihaiva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhunjia bhogan rudhirapradigdhan -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (2 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 These gurus of nobility I will not kill[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Better to eat by begging I feel[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By killing gurus, wealth and pleasure[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Will be enjoyed and eaten with blood -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Instead of destroying this immensely powerful Abhaschaitanya and other[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 venerable ones like samskara and living in this world in disgrace, it is more[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 proper to live with whatever they decide to give as alms, life after life. -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na chaitadvidmah katarannogariyo[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yadva jayema yadi va na jayeyuh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yaneva hatva na jijirvashamas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tehavasthitah pramukhe dhartarashtrah -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I do not see benevolence in what will happen to us[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Whether victorious over Kuru or Kuru is victorious[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those without whom I do not want my own life[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All these wise Kurus in front of us -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 We do not see anything all that great either in becoming a siddha by this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kriya or not becoming one. Because the method by which perfection will[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 be attained will destroy the clans of mind and ego and their faculties at the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 very beginning, without whom this life itself is pointless. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karpanyadoshopahatasvabhavah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pricchami tvam dharmasammudhachetah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yacchreyah syannishchitam bruhi tanme[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shishyastehaham shadhi mam tvam prapannam -7-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na hi prapashyami mamanupadyat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yacchokamucchoshanamindriyanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avapya bhumavasapatnamriddham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajyam suramapi chadhipatyam -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am overcome by the power of pity and guilt[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Confused about dharma I ask You[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 What is truly best please tell me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Teach me, your disciple who has taken refuge in You -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (3 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I cannot see any way, thus I turn away[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this grief by which my senses run dry[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It matters not if I receive the whole world over[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Uncontested kingdom and rulership over gods -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In sorrow, the power to do work has lost its energy. Uncontested/[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unhampered, meaning without obstacles and able to anything, meaning the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 strength of the elemental physical body or even lordship over the entire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 subtle body will not relieve me of this grief it seems. Therefore, O[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya! My character has been tainted by the flaw of pity,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning that I am unable to do any harm even though I might gain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 immensely by doing so, and my consciousness is devoid of Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness. I take refuge in You with all that I can do. Please teach me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 what is truly for my good. -7 and 8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sanjay said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evamukta hrishikesham gudakeshah paramtapah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na yotsye ity govindamuktva tushnim babhuva ha -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sanjay said, hear, hear O king[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 These words he said to Govinda[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I will not fight, listen Madhava[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And saying so became silent, the valorous Pandava -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is experienced through the eye of wisdom that it is necessary for that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 delusion-vanquishing, enemy-burning energy of the fire element, meaning all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 work done with rajoguna, to renounce all of that and in stillness rely upon[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya (Sri Krishna). -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tamuvacha hrishikeshah prahasanniva bharata[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 senayorubhayormadhye vishidantamidam vachah -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pleased, so said Krishna, O king[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 To Partha encircled by the two armies -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (4 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is written in the Patanjal philosophical treatise that when stillness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manifests out of the openness of sadhakas, the Soul-Consciousness Itself[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 becomes satisfied. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nirvicharavaisharadyehadhyatmaprasadah -- Samadhipada - no. 4[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When Soul-Consciousness becomes thus contented, then imaginary[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 falsehoods disappear and the Truth, unmanufactured by imagination, is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealed to the faculty of inner sight. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ritambhara tatra prajna -- Samadhipada - no. 48[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By this, it can be known that when the fire element in the midst of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 families of pravritti and nivritti becomes sullen, meaning when the rajoguna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 becomes low and is incapable of doing what needs to be done, then the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhakas, having arrived at the navel-lotus, awaken the Kundalini Shakti by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Guru-instructed Kriya and become still and open. In that,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya (Sri Krishna) becomes pleased and through the inner[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 wisdom-sight, Truth, unmanufactured by imagination, is experienced in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these ways. -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ashochyananvashochastvam prajnavadamshcha bhashase[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gatasunagatasumshcha nanushochanti panditah -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Lord said to Arjuna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For the unworthy do you grieve[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As a wise man speak Partha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Like the unwise are you becoming deluded[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Whether friends are dead or alive[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For them grieve not the wise -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Divinity, creative energy, glory, beauty, knowledge and non-attachment -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 together these six are called "bhaga." As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aishvarya samagrasya viryasya yashasah shriyah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanavairagyayoshchaiva yannam bhaga ity smritam[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the Divine Kutasthachaitanya endowed with these six qualities, this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 type of experience happens: that being a wise and discriminating person, it[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (5 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is not proper to grieve over unworthy things, because scientifically[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledgeable beings are not remorseful over the presence or absence of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anything in this ever-changing world.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na tvevaham jatu nasam na tvam neme janadhipah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na chaiva na bhavishyamah sarve vayamatahparam -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Supreme Lord, Myself, these persons of royalty[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And you, it was never that we did not exist[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That we will not be in the future[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For that to happen is impossible[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Blissful Consciousness Paramatman is eternal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Neither is He born and nor does He ever die[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Only because of this strife this appearance and disappearance[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is not possible to grieve over this -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Before commenting on this sloka, it is necessary to clarify what the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 substance of these matters are.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Tattva, meaning karan (cause) -- sattva (neutral), raja (positive) and tama[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (negative) -- these three gunas working together are called Trigunamayi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Prakrriti. The gunas themselves are the cause of creation. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sattvarajastamasam samyavastha prakritih prakritermahan mahato ityadi --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 K. Su. - 1:61[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is written in the Patanjal philosophical treatises that the three gunas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mentioned above, the five elements and the eleven sensory faculties form the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scenery of purush or jivachaitanya. The jiva enjoys objects through these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and when awareness manifests about their behavior, it is also by these that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 liberation is attained. Among the above-mentioned three gunas, the sattva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 guna is tranquil and still in an awakened state, while the tama guna is inert[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with stupor. Only the rajoguna is ever-moving, meaning operative. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prakashkriyasthitishilam bhutendriatmakam bhogapavargartham drishyam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- Sadhanapada - no. 18[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The above-mentioned raja guna being the one with the capacity for action, is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mixed with the sattva guna and tama guna giving rise to two different forms -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajasik sattva and rajasik tama. By the Guru-instructed Kriya, in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya the sadhakas experience the gunas of Nature as these five[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 types. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (6 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 darpane samalokya tatra shvasam vinikshipet -- Svarodaya[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Darpan" (drp-un)[mirror]: that by which the forms of all things are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 illuminated, meaning that by which things are reflected. With the exception[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of physical objects, what is ordinarily called "darpan" does not reflect mind,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intellect or any such internal things. For this reason, that darpan is only a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 model and does not convey the complete function of darpan. It has been[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 touched upon previously and it is also written in every other scripture that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this body is the place of all pilgrimages, the place of all gods, and all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge is present in it. One becomes aware of this through the teachings[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Guru. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dehasthah sarvavidyashcha dehasthah sarvadevatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dehasthani cha tirthani guruvakyena labhyate[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, in this body itself there is a place where by the experience of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya the physical, subtle and the subtlest of subtle qualities of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Nature are experienced. The scriptural scholars have stated this as the true[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 darpan. Because Kutasthachaitanya is experienced here, this is also called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Kutastha."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kutasthe kalpita buddhistatrachitprativimbakam -- Panchadashi[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The saints knowledgeable in yogic scriptures have referred to the above-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mentioned five types of states which represent the cause of Nature as the five[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 elements. In the clear mind of the field of Pandu - the sushumna - these five[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 elements are experienced in their pure states. This is why the Mahabharata[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 has called these the five Pandavas, the doubt-ridden and blind mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dhritarashtra, and the different types of quintelemental and sensory internal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 faculties and elements as the sons of Dhritarashtra. The five elements:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 earth, water, fire, air and either are referred to as places of emergence (cause)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and these five are mentioned as "earth-element," "water-element," "fire-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 element," "air-element" and "space-element." All of these elements are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 always dutifully abiding in the whole of human nature and exists in it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 inextricably. Sadhakas can become aware of this through the practice of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Guru-instructed Kriya. If one is able to be aware of this, then no other[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 instruments or mechanisms are necessary to help one know things. Without[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being aware of this, astrological work cannot be carried out correctly. There[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is a saying by Mahadeva about this subject: astrology without awareness of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 svara - meaning the five elements along with the substance of breath - is like[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 a house without a lord, a speaker without wisdom and a body without nerves,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and it fails. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 svarahinohadha daivajno nathadinam yatha griham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shastrahino yatha vakta shirohinancha yadvapuh[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (7 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Through the experience of these elements, past, future, present - all can be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 known exactly. With this no other astrological treatises are necessary. This[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is why the great sages of Vedic times ascertained that it was impossible to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attain wisdom through books. Cultivating the Practice of Brahman by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhana of Sadguru-given Kriya, they attained the all-containing Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Brahman and acquiring omniscience, they had this Infinite Universe as if[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the palms of their hands. Therefore nothing remained unknown to them.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of the emergence and the disappearance of the above-mentioned[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 five elements, the arising of the many different substances with different[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 qualities establishing themselves in the subtle body (electric body) and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 working in the physical body (material body) as the perceptional and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experiential powers of mind along with physical matter, many types of things[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happen in relation to us in greater or lesser ways. I will give a description[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 below about how the above-mentioned elements are experienced.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 During the emergence of the earth element, without touching either side of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the nose, breath flows exactly through the middle in 12 finger-lengths. A[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 honey-liquid is experienced in the throat, giving birth to an addiction to the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 honey-liquid. The feeling of yellow forms rises in the mind and a desire to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 see yellow forms is born. A four-sided yellow form appears in the Kutastha.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In a pure state, human nature remains in this condition for 50 pala, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 20 minutes.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 During the emergence of the water element, breath flows through the lower[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 part of the nose in 16 finger-lengths. An astringent-liquid is experienced in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the throat giving birth to an addiction to the astringent-liquid. The feeling of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 white forms arises in the mind and a desire to see white forms is born. A[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 white half-moon form appears in the Kutastha. In a pure state, human nature[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stays in this condition for 40 pala, meaning 16 minutes.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 During the emergence of the fire element, breath flows through the upper[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 part of the nose in 4 finger-lengths. A bitter-liquid is experienced in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 throat, giving birth to an addiction to the bitter-liquid. The feeling of red[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 forms arises in the mind and a desire to see red forms is born. A red triangle[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 appears in the Kutastha. In a pure state, human nature remains in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 condition for 30 pala, meaning 12 minutes.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 At the time of the air element, breath flows through the side of the nose in 8[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 finger-lengths. A tart-liquid is experienced in the throat giving birth to an[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 addiction to the tart-liquid. The feeling of blue forms arises in the mind and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 a desire to see blue forms is born. A blue circular form appears in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutastha. In a pure state, human nature remains in this condition for 20 pala,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning for 8 minutes.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 At the time of the space element, breath flows through the nose without any[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 force/pressure. A pungent-liquid is experienced in the throat giving birth to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 an addiction to the pungent-liquid. The feeling of dark purple forms arises in[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (8 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the mind and a desire to see dark purple forms is born. In the dark purple of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Kutastha, many kinds of forms appear like points. In a pure state, human[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nature remains in this condition for 10 pala, or 4 minutes.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One equally sees the above-mentioned elements, the divine consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 presiding in the main nadis, and the Kutasthachaitanya all as eternal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 substances, meaning not created by the world and not destroyed even at the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time of total dissolution. -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dehinohasmin yatha dehe kaumaram yauvanam jara[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatha dehantarapraptidhirastatra na muhyati -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As the body in childhood, youth and old age[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without attention goes, not making a sound[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The same, after death another body acquired[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By that the wise are not deluded -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Just as the embodied souls naturally and gradually change physical states of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 childhood, youth, old age etc. yet the consciousness remains the same, in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 same way, also naturally, one body is discarded after death and another body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is taken. The Soul is not destroyed by that. The wise ones are not deluded in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 any way by all of these changes. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 matrasparshastu kaunteya shitoshnasukhaduhkhadah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 agamapayinohanityastam stitikshasva bharata -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Through sensory faculties in the physical realm[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Comes the experience of cold, heat, pleasure and sorrow at different times[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Over and over they come and go never are they still[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Know this Dhananjaya and endure them -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of the senses, everyone experiences cold, heat, pleasure, sorrow etc.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All of these remain only for a while. Therefore one should endure them. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yam hi na vyathayantyete purusham purusharshabha[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (9 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samaduhkhasukham dhiram sohamritatvaya kalpate -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one to whom these do not bring distress[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pleasure and sorrow are the same in that freedom -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who are not distressed by all of these sensory experiences, those that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perceive happiness and unhappiness as the same, those intelligent ones are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 qualified for the path of liberation. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nasato vidyate bhavo nabhavo vidyate satah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ubhayorapi drishtohantastrinayostatvadarshibhih -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Cold, heat and such are ever of the world[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Which has no Soul-dharma or Truth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Truth Itself means the presence of Soul[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The wise know the discernment of these two -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There is no permanence in these fleeting things and the Permanently Eternal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness has no death. The seers, being aware of the irrefutable fact of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these two, learn to endure. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avinashi tu tadviddhi yena sarvamidam tatam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vinashamavyasyasya na kashchit kartumarhati -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The One who pervades all Universes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Know Him as deathless, O Falguni[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This indestructible Soul, Dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 No one is capable of killing It -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This world-pervading Consciousness is indestructible; nothing at all can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 destroy it. -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (10 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 antavanta ime deha nityasyoktah sharirinah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anashinohaprameyasya tasmad yudhyasva bharata -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman cannot be divided or destroyed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But this body in which It resides, is not true[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This the wise ascertain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore fight, O son of Kunti -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 These fleeting things are only the elemental and physical statement of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indestructible and boundless Eternal Consciousness. Therefore, if these are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 destroyed, the destruction of that Consciousness is not possible. Instead, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 existence of these things happens because of Its Presence. Therefore, one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 should practice Kriya without fear. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ya enam vetti hantaram yashchainam manyate hatam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ubhou tou na vijanitou nayam hanti na hanyate -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who believes that Atman is being killed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Or the one who thinks that Atman is killing him[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Neither of these know the truth of Soul[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman is neither the slayer nor the slain -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who discern that the Eternal Consciousness in this body is the slayer[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or the slain, they are injudicious and devoid of Soul-Knowledge because He[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is immutable, and therefore cannot be slain by any means; and He is non-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 doing, therefore He slays no one. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na jayate mriyate va kadachit[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nayam bhutva bhavita va na bhuyah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ajo nityah shvashvatohayam purano[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na hanyate hanyamane sharire -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 No birth, no death, nor will It cease after birth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Devoid of erosion, extension and without corruption[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman is untouched by these six faults[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Never is It destroyed when the body is slain -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (11 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This Eternal Consciousness never has birth or death. He neither manifests[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nor presides, nor is He non-existent and non-manifesting. He is Eternal,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 without birth, immutable, from time immemorial He is ever-new, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 forever existing as He is. Even the destruction of this body cannot bring[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 about His death. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vedavinashinam nityam ya enamajamavyayam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 katham sa purushah partha kam ghatayati hanti kam -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman has no erosion, birth, extension or death[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who believes this Partha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 How can he kill anyone here[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Or how can he cause anyone to be killed -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who knows the Atman to be birthless and deathless, ever-existing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and indestructible, how can he be deluded into thinking "I am killing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 someone," or "I am causing someone to be killed?" -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vasamsi jirnani yatha vihaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 navani grihnati narohaparani[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatha sharirani vihaya jarna-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nyanyani samghati navani dehi -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Discarding old clothes and putting on the new[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The way that everyone does[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman discards the worn-out body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And naturally takes a new body -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Just as human beings discard worn-out clothes and put on new ones, in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 same way this embodied Consciousness discards the body when it is worn[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 out and again embodies Itself in a new one. -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nainam chidanti shastrani nainam dahati pavakah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (12 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na chainam kledayantyapo na shoshayati marutah -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Weapons cannot cut this Atman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 No one has the power to burn it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman cannot be sodden by water[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Cannot be dried up by the strongest wind -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because this Consciousness has no form, no weapon can pierce it, fire cannot[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 burn it, water cannot make it sodden and air cannot dry it up. -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 acchedyohayamadahyohayamakledyohashoshya eva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nityah sarvagatah sthanurachalohayam sanatah -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman cannot be pierced or burned[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Unable to be wetted and cannot be dried[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because this Atman is Eternal and All-pervading[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universal, immovable and unchanging -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This Consciousness is impenetrable, inflammable, cannot be made wet,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cannot be dried up, cannot be eroded, always present and is inextricably[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 existing within everything in the world. -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avyaktohayamachintohayamavikaryohayamuchyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasmadevam viditvainam nanushochitumaharsi -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Not seen by the eyes, beyond the mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Not held by hand this is the truth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore know Atman in this way[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is not proper for you to grieve -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This Consciousness cannot be experienced by the senses of perception, nor[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 can one become aware of It through the mind. He is not corrupted by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 organs of action. When one becomes aware of Consciousness in this way,[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (13 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 then nothing is left about which to grieve. -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atha chainam nityajatam nityam va manyate mritam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tathapi tvam mahavaho naivam shochitumaharsi -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If you say that Atman is takes birth and dies again and again[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Then Arjuna, why lament -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When you ascertain that Consciousness takes birth and dies with these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 faculties over and over endlessly, then renouncing these faculties should not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 be a cause for any kind of grief. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jatasya hi dhruvomrityu dhruvam janma mritasya cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasmadapariharyeharthe na tvam shochitumaharsi -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who is born must die and after dying must be born[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore do not mourn unjustifiably -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If there is birth, then there is for certain death, and if there is death, then[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 there is birth for certain. This has been profoundly established with proof by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all types of scriptures. Therefore, it is not appropriate to become saddened at[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abandoning these faculties which follow this inevitable process. -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avyaktadini bhutani vyaktamadhyani bharata[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avyakta nidhananyeva tatra ka paridevana -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the beginning It was in unmanifest form[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who is Supreme in the scriptures[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Then having become manifest will be unmanifest again[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Why be distressed over the destruction of this body -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This entire elemental world is born of the Nature of that unknowable,[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (14 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 subtlest of subtle substance, and again it merges back into That. In between,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it only appears for a little while. Therefore, what is the reason to bewail this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dream-like Prakriti's illusory workings? -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ashcharyavat pashyati kashchidenam[m
