[32m+[m[32m                                 work other than the acquisition of pleasure - as taught by flowery words,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 through which they aim to fulfill all kinds of desires and wish to acquire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 heavenly enjoyments as mentioned in the Vedas; those who have succumbed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to desire and perceive as the highest thing the attainment of heaven through[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the good karmas of birth and work, as well as perform all kinds of actions in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 order to get many kinds of pleasures and wealth -- the minds of those[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 addicted to enjoyments and riches are always pulled by such things; because[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of which, their minds cannott become resolutely steady in the absorption of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Soul-Consciousness, and they are not able to attain samadhi. -42, 43 and 44-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   traigunyavishaya veda nistraigunyo bhavarjuna[m
