[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   For those seeking good works is the cause of pravritti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Karmakanda is described in the Vedas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   O Partha, be free of desire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In stillness endure pleasure, pain, heat, cold[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Acquiring what one does not have, protecting what one already has[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   With careful mind be without such wants -45-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   For persons willing to fulfill desires, many kinds of rituals based on the three[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   gunas - sattva, raja and tama - are described in the Vedas. But one should go[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   beyond these three gunas and endure pleasure, pain and conflicts, meaning -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   have profound patience, and renounce the desire to acquire what one does[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   not have and the concern to protect what one does have, and be calm,[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (20 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning - be at peace. -45-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   yavanartha udapane sarvatah samplutodake[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   tavan sarveshu vedeshu brahmanasya vijanatah -46-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The usefulness of a little water in a well[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   And that which is for all from a great lake[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In that way whatever is in the whole of the Vedas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The Brahman-absorbed wise ones have all of that -46-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The way that all the services of a well or a small reservoir are more than[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   provided for by a great lake, in the same way all of the temporary[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   fulfillments of desires described in the Vedas are always there for those[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   resolutely and completely residing in the Bliss of Brahman. -46-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   karmanyavadhikaraste ma phaleshu kadachana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   ma karmaphalaheturbhumate sangohastvakarmani -47-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Only to karma is there the right[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Not to its results for you[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In desireless karma never is there fruit[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   No need to do forbidden work -47-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Everyone has the rightful authority to karma [action] only, but on the fruits[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   of action no one has authority of control. Therefore, it is inappropriate to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   engaged in karma desiring its fruits, and should not abandon karma upon[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   perceiving a delay in the manifestation of its fruits. -47-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   yogastha kuru karmani sangam tyaktva dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   siddhasiddhou samou bhutva samatvam yoga ucchyate -48-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Being in the Lord, O Dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Renouncing attachment do karma properly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Whether the results of action are successful or not[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (21 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Seeing them as the same is called yoga -48-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, one should perform Kriya with all attention, renouncing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attachment and perceiving success or failure as the same. The wise ones call[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this type of knowledge yoga. -48-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 durena hyvaram karma buddhiyogaddhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 buddhou sharanamanviccha kripanah phalahetavah -49-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The practice of Truth is devoid of desire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The wretched is accompanied by want[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In knowledge doing karma, steadying the mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This wisdom is lost to the minds of those craving results -49-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Performing all actions - other than Kriya - with nischayatmika [sense of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 certainty] is very inferior. Therefore, one should perform Kriya having taken[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 refuge in indubitable wisdom, because all action enmeshed with the desire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 for results are lowly. -49-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 buddhiyukto jahatiha ubhe sukritaduskrite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasmad yogaya yujyasva yogah karmasu kaushalam -50-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmajam buddhiyukta hi phalam tyaktva manishinah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 janmabandhavinirmuktah padam gacchantyanamayam -51-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who do karma with God intention[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In scriptures it is called "buddhiyoga"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who do karma with God in mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Destroy all their good and sin in this life[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore take care and do yoga with intensity[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With the technique of yoga wisdom is born in action -50-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Having knowledge, do karma without results[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Attain liberation, cutting the shackles of life -51-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When the mind is stilled by Kriya, all work of heavenly pleasures and all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 work of hellish suffering are destroyed. In this way, having eradicated all[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (22 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fruits of karma and being devoid of all sense enjoyments, Kriyavan sages are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 liberated from the chains of life and attain supreme peace. Therefore, one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 should perform this Kriyayoga, the highest of all actions. -50 and 51-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yadi te mohakalilam buddhirvatitarishyati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tada gantasi nirvedam shrotavyasya shrutasya cha -52-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the body the Atman-buddhi is in the forest of delusion[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But when such buddhi goes beyond that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 At that time whatever you have heard or will hear[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the two there will be great detachment born -52-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When the buddhi transcends delusion and its danger, a non-attachment[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manifests about what is heard and what will be heard. -52-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shrutivipratipanna te yada sthasyati nishchala[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samadhavachala buddhistada yogamavapsyasi -53-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Secular and religious talk is of many kinds[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Which your confused mind hears[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When that buddhi is stilled in God[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge of All you will receive -53-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The mind is confused by all kinds of secular and religious matters. When the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind detaches itself from those things and becomes absorbed and tranquil, it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 becomes united with Consciousness. -53-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sthitaprajnasya ka bhasha samadhisthasya keshava[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sthitadhih kim prabhasheta kimasita brajet kim -54-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said Lord, please tell me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Whom shall I call steadfast in mind, absorbed in Brahman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 How do they speak these wise ones[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (23 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 How do they sit and how do they walk -54-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Experiencing all of these things, questions arise in the energy of the fire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 element: who are the sthitaprajna*; how do they hold themselves and even,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 how do they move? -54-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [*Translator's note: "Prajna" is the conglomeration of mind, consciousness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intellect, discrimination and wisdom. "Sthitaprajna" is the merged and still[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "prajna." Because there is no adequate parallel in English, this definition is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 necessary.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   prajahati yada kaman sarvan partha manogatan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   atmanyevatmana tushtah sthitaprajnastadochyate -55-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   duhkheshvanudvignamanah sukhesu vigatasprihah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   vitaragabhayakrodhah sthitadhirmuniruchyate -56-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   yah sarvatranabhisnahastattat prapya shubhashubham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   nabhinandati na dveshti tasya prajna pratishthita -57-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   yada samharate chayam kurmohanganiva sarvashah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   indriyanindriyarthebhyastasya prajna pratishthita -58-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The Lord to Arjuna said[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   When in the Bliss of Atman one is absorbed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   All desires of mind will be discarded by him[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Then he will be called "sthitaprajna" -55-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The ones without anxiety and sorrow in mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Being in this bliss do not care about such[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In whose consciousness there is no infatuation, anger or fear[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   All scriptures call that sage "sthitaprajna" -56-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   He who has affection to nothing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Does not coddle himself in excessive pleasure[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Receiving great suffering does not hate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   His mind is established [in Brahman] the scriptures say -57-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The way a tortoise with all its limbs[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The same way the senses from its objects[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Those who effortlessly draw them within[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Know that his mind is established [in Brahman] -58-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   When the mind becomes concentrated in the Kutasthachaitanya, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   experience happens that those who renounce all mental cravings and remain[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (24 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 content in themselves; those who are devoid of enmity in suffering, devoid[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of envy in pleasure and free from all obsession, fear and anger; those who do[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not have particular affection for anything; those who do not experience[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 satisfaction from propitious matters, and do not experience dissatisfaction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from unpleasant matters; and those who, like the tortoise that withdraws its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 limbs, effortlessly withdraw their senses from their objects of sight, sound,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 touch etc. and reside in Atman -- their prajna is established and they are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 called sthitaprajna. -55, 56, 57 and 58-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vishaya vinivartante niraharasya dehinah[m
