[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who fast for them the bodily experience[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Is eliminated but greed remains in the mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The sage, attaining the Bliss of Para Brahman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All cravings of the heart are extinguished, Falguni -59-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is true that for the ignorant and body-obsessed persons the senses become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 weakened through fasting and for a while they are able to turn away from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 external things; but because the mind itself does not turn away from worldly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desires, once the senses regain their strength, they again become engaged in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 their objects. The sthitaprajna ones, being in the experience of the Supreme[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Substance, remain apart from these meaningless desires. -59-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatatohyapi kaunteya purushasya vipashchitah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indriyani pramathini haranti prasabham manah -60-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The senses perceive the objects[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For even the carefully discriminating[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The senses cause all unhappiness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With their power they draw the mind -60-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The agitating senses can capture the mind of even the most carefully[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 discriminating persons. -60-[m
[32m+[m
