[32m+[m[32m                                 With that comes much obsession[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When indulgence ends anger arises -62-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In anger and frustration is delusion born, and delusion kills memory[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If memory goes, so does reason, when reason goes all is lost -63-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Continuously thinking about things of sense perception, one becomes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 obsessed with that, and from that a craving, meaning excessive obsession, for[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 those objects manifests. When such enjoyment is disrupted, anger emerges.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Anger gives rise to delusion. Delusion destroys reason, and destruction of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reason causes total stupor in ignorance and one becomes as if dead. -62 and -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 63-[m
[32m+[m
