[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 becomes illuminated by the impurity-eroding performance of yoga is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "viveka." As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yoganganushthanadashuddhikshaye jnanadiptiravivekakhyateh --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sadhanapada - no. 28[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, without the erosion of impurity by performing Kriya, viveka does[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not become manifest. When viveka is not present in this way, there is no[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stillness in meditation. And when there is no stillness in meditation, one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cannot attain tranquility. And without attaining tranquility by turning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness away from sensory objects, happiness can never be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experienced. Because, if the senses are restless, the mind follows them and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 like an incompetent sailor whose boat is at the mercy of the wind on the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ocean, it engages the intellect in the sense objects. -66 and 67-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasmad yasya mahabaho nigrihitani sarvashah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indriyanindriyarthebhyastasya prajna pratishthita -68-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore those whose senses[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Desist from sense enjoyments through great strength[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Under the control of Atman do the senses stay[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Their minds are ever still -68-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, those whose senses have subjugated all sense pleasures and are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 under the control of Atman are sthitaprajna. -68-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ya nisha sarvabhutanam tasyam jagarti samyami[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yasyam jagrati bhutani sa nisha pashyato muneh -69-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is night for all elements when in Atman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In that awakens the sagacious and knowledgeable being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When people are awake in physical affairs[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That is night for the sage, nothing is seen -69-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When the sense-oriented elemental world is extinguished, the focused Soul[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 then attains awakenedness. And when the sense-oriented world is awake[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 then the Knowledge of Atman dissolves. -69-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (28 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   apuryamanamachalapratishtham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   samudramapah pravishanti yadvat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   tadvat kama yam pravishanti sarve[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   sa shantimapnoti na kamakami -70-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In the calm and immensely complete ocean[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   All waters enter there in undisturbed ways[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Those whose sense matters are as this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   These unattached ones attain liberation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   But one whose mind is anxious in enjoyment of the world[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Does not receive the Supreme Kaivalya, know that -70-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Just as the sea, already full of water, remains calm regardless of rivers and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   streams entering it, in the same way, those who, even being filled with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Bliss of Brahman, can partake in sense matters in an unperturbed and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   desireless manner, meaning as if done by an unseen doer -- they are the ones[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   who live liberated from the imprisonment of this material world.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In previous slokas, it was stated that because of the emergence of anger from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   desire, the jiva becomes as if dead, enveloped in the stupor of ignorance.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Therefore, one should cut the root of this desire. Then it was stated in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   sloka [70] that partaking without desire will liberate one from this material[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   enchainment. There is a possibility of misunderstanding these statements.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Therefore, it is appropriate to explain what type of thing this desire is.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The matters of the three gunas of Prakriti - the cause of creation - were[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   spoken about in the twelfth sloka of this chapter. The sadhakas using the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   operative power of rajoguna, experience these in five forms, and scriptural[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   scholars have called each of the residing places of the five subtle elements,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   meaning substance (cause) - earth-element, water-element, fire-element, air-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   element and ether-element, and they have also said that all three gunas -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   sattva (neuter), raja (positive) and tama (negative) - are magnetized to those[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   subtle elements present in Nature.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   It is written in the Vedanta shastras that all organs of perception (sensory[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   organs) in the Universe were created from the experiential part (sentient part)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   of those great elements' aspect of sattva guna, and the five types of sattva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   guna respective to the elements from those organs of perception brought[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   about the all-experiencing, meaning all-knowing (omniscient), mind. And[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   the operative aspect - the rajoguna aspect - of all of those great elements[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   created the organs of action (motor organs), and the conglomeration of the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (29 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajoguna aspects of those five elements from all of the organs of action[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brought about the creation of the all-powerful (almighty) prana (magnetism[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or vital fluid). And the inert tamoguna aspect of those great elements,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mixing with together created the scenery of this Universe in its physical form.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If Prakriti were not filled with these three gunas, then none of these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 substances would manifest. Because Prakriti is the root cause of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 creation, It is called the causal body of Brahmanda [Universe in all levels].[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the great elements, sattva and raja guna-manifested prana and other[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 subtle substances comprise what is called the subtle body; and the tamoguna-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manifested visible, material and form-oriented scenery of planets and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 satellites and the entire physical world comprise what is called the material[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body. It is the subtle body that is operating the entirety of atoms and sub-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atoms etc. necessary for the creation, preservation and destruction of all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 planets, satellites and solar worlds.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All of manifested creation is a part of this immense Brahmanda. Therefore,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all three bodies, material, subtle and causal, are present in everything, some[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 parts evident and some parts hidden. With the erosion of impurities, all of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these bodies, and eventually five levels, are revealed. Because of this the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vedanta scholars have called this Universe "panchakoshamaya" [with five[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 covers]. Fearing excessiveness, I am unable to elucidate about these in detail[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 here. But it is important to say this much: that the human body is also a part[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of this Immense Brahmanda and all - mind, prana, senses and everything else[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 - are present here in their highest forms.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because this all-pervading mind was born of the all-revealing and all-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experiencing aggregate of the sattvic elements, it is omniscient. When there[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is a lack perceived in the organs of perception, this completely immersed in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sattva guna (neutralized) mind becomes desirous and slightly diverted which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gives rise to sattva and rajoguna (polarized). The way that, if in the midst of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 innumerable magnetic compasses, one magnet of sattva guna (neutralized[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 magnet) becomes somehow influenced by raja or tamoguna (polarized), all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of those innumerable magnetic compasses will in the sympathizing process[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become attracted to that and cause a corrupted condition, in the same way,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 when the sattva guna-filled mind becomes desirous, sensing lack in some[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sense, and gets slightly corrupted, it becomes attached to raja and tamoguna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (polarized). And by this, as the pranas become gradually attracted, this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 entire world and universe is under the force of prana. This prana, being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 created from the operative quality of the collective rajoguna, is all-powerful.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, all things present in the Brahmanda are under its control.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Endowed with the above-mentioned force, this all-powerful prana, by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 organs of action (motor fluid or organs of motion) makes possible the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyment of those corrupted things desired by the mind through the organs[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of perception (sensory fluid or organs of sense) and by thus satisfying the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind, returns it to its natural state.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (30 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The organs of perception in this Immense Brahmanda (motor electricity) is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experiencing everything by themselves and because no substance exists[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 without them, they have no need for the enjoyment of anything. Thus, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 senses being satisfied in every way (in full satisfaction), the mind, which is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 born of them, resides in a still, undisturbed and unaffected state. In this way,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with the mind ever-remaining in its natural condition, prana does not get[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 agitated and therefore, the organs of action dependent upon it remain ever-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dormant. Thus unhindered in any way, the prana of this Immense[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda (universal magnetism vitality), in its all-powerful form (with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 almighty power), operates, like Its blood and guts, this Infinite Universe with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 its planets and satellites according to the course of natural law. The Overlord[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness of this Immense Brahmanda is called by the scriptural[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scholars as Paramatman or Parampurush. Being in the state of non-doing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and tranquility, He is ruling over the world and Brahmanda by prana in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 awakened condition. The individualized parts of Him are called Jivatman or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Purush.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the course of natural law, the jiva matures from knowing only its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 annamaya kosha [food covering] to the realization of the pranamaya kosha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [prana covering], and, further within that, when it is able to realize the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manomaya kosha [mind covering], impurity is gradually diminished and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva acquires many types of sub-human bodies, going progressively higher[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 until the jnanamaya kosha [knowledge covering] is prevalent, which is when[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the jiva takes a human form. When the jiva completes the fulfillment of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body and mind with its senses through the miraculous power of yoga, having[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experienced all mind, prana, senses etc. of this Immense Brahmanda as its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 own body, the jiva realizes the anandamaya kosha [bliss covering]. In this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 way, one attains Parampurush or Paramatman.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Having attained this wholeness, if at some moment it cannot experience the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe, desires for enjoyment arise in the jiva's mind, one after another.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Once the jiva's mind moves from its natural state even a little, prana becomes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attracted to that and calls forth the force of the all-powerful prana-airs -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prana vayu - of this Brahmanda. Thus, that corrupted substance which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 should be avoided appears in order to satisfy the craving of the jiva. By[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 partaking in those objects of desire, the jiva pacifies the mind or returns it to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 its natural state. The mind being natural and peaceful, the jiva's prana-vayu[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (vitality or animal magnetism) becomes completely without force, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 having its full strength, meaning being its awakened state, continues to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 operate all things in their normal ways. When one can keep his own prana in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 its awakened state, at the emergence of any desire in the mind, the object of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that desire immediately appears in order to appease the jiva. This[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 omniscient, omnipotent, omnipresent mind is so great that no thing and no[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 power in this Universe can tolerate its unhappiness. This Infinite Universe is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 waiting with extreme eagerness to satisfy the mind. No matter what is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 necessary to fulfill the mind's desires, even if the thing does not exist in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda - it is immediately created to quell the mind's craving. In this[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (31 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 way, this solar system/universe in the Infinite Universe is a servant of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva's will power, and is existing to fulfill its desires and bring it peace.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But, being small-minded and restless, one desire is immediately followed by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 another in the jiva's mind and it is always perturbed and distorted. Because[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of this, the prana-vayu's force is working with many different objects and,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not being able to apply its power into anything in a focused way, a very[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fragmented and scattered state manifests. The prana-vayu cannot properly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 work with the prana of the Brahmanda in this corrupted condition, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because the force is being used for all kinds of conflicting thoughts, nothing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is able to manifest. And by this the body begins to not function properly and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eventually becomes useless. When the present body is destroyed, because[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the force of those numerous types of desires were not renounced, the jiva has[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to take another body appropriate to the aggregate power of those forces[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (resultant force). Therefore, because of all of the accumulated desires, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva has to again take birth and be bound to this worldly life. Thus, without[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 their fulfillment, the jiva has no way out. About this subject, it is written in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Tantra that the good and bad karma of human beings, meaning the matters of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desire, must be fulfilled. There is no diminishing of this without fulfillment.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Until all of the these good and bad karmas are completely eliminated, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva has no possibility of peace or liberation.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ma bhukta kshiyate karma kalpakoti shatairapi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avashyameva bhoktavyam kritam karma shubhashubam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yavanna kshiyate karma shubhanchashubhameva va[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tayanna jayate moksham nrinam kalpashatairapi[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All of these accumulated desires are what the scriptural scholars call[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "adrishta" [unseen fate].[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For this reason, in order to renounce the desires of adrishta, it has been stated[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the previous slokas that one should be detached from its roots of affection[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and dislike. And in this sloka, because there is no other way than to fulfill[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the accumulated desires of adrishta, it has been taught that one should in an[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unaffected way, meaning without creating any new adrishta, return the mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to its natural state and make it tranquil by the fulfillment of the previously[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 accumulated adrishta.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When by yogakriya the foundation of desire - like and dislike - is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 extinguished, the revelation of Divinity fulfills all matters of desire, upon[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 which the mind returns to its natural state and becomes tranquil. And[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experiencing all mind, prana and senses of this Immense Brahmanda as one's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 own body and pervading throughout the Universe, the jiva becomes the Total[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness of the Universe - Parampurush or Paramatman. Thus, there[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being nothing else existing in the Universe other than the Self, the scriptural[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 saints have called this attainment "Kaivalyapada." -70-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter2.html (32 of 36)4/18/2006 2:42:00 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vihaya kaman yah sarvan pumamshcharati nisprihah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nirmamo nirahamkarah sa shantimadhigacchati -71-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who is unperturbed and without ego[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Whose heart is devoid of attachment[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Fulfills his resultant destiny from the past[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He extinguishes himself in the Supreme -71-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who fulfill in desireless, unaffected, egoless and unattached ways all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that is left to be fulfilled, they attain Tranquility. -71-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 esha brahmi sthitih partha nainam prapya vimuhyati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sthitvasyamantakalehapi brahmanirvanamricchati -72-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Listen about devotion to this Knowledge of Brahman, Dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Once this is attained, never is one captivated again[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If at the time of death this Knowledge of Brahman manifests[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who dies in Its refuge merges into the Infinite -72-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is this that is known as devotion to Brahman, meaning residing in Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness. When this is attained, the jiva is never captivated again. If[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one is in this state at the time of death, he merges into Brahman. -72-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 SUMMARIZED DESCRIPTION OF CHAPTER 2:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this chapter, it has been expressed that when conflict disappears, an[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 understanding happens in the Kutasthachaitanya that residing in this body of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 carnal passions and turning away from performing Kriya is not proper.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, doing Kriya intensely with the fire element is proper [1 - 3]. But in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajoguna, this type of discernment appears that - it is from the venerable and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 guru-like Chidabhas and samskara that we exist in this elevated state;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 therefore, to maintain this repulsive lordship, one should follow them birth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 after birth instead of destroying them. Without them, our lives are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaningless [4 - 6]. As such, I cannot see anything that great or that wrong[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in performing or not performing Kriya. I am unable to perceive; I am unable[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to do little harm for great gain; I have become powerless; I am unable to[m
[32m+[m
