[32m+[m[32m                                 CHAPTER THREE[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 KARMAYOGA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jayasi chet karmanaste mata buddhirjanardana[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       tat kim karmani ghore mam niyojayasi keshava -1-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition                          Hearing the wisdom of the second chapter[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Requested Partha to Govinda[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            If jnana is greater than karma, Lord[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     The why give me the order to be in this intense fight -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction                     After examining all of these things, a question arises in the rajoguna that - O[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness, if jnana [knowledge/wisdom] is the most superior thing, then[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        why should I become engaged in this intense Kriya? -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        vyamishreneva vakyana buddhim mohayasiva me[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        tadekam vada nishchitya yena shreyohhamapnuyam -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        One time you say that jnana is superior[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        Then again you praise karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It makes me confused, these two[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With whichever I will attain the highest, tell me the resolution -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge or action - whenever I look at one or other, that one seems the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (1 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  best. Thus, my intellect is stupefied. Explain to me now which is the best[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  for me. -2-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  lokehasmin dvividha nishtha pura prokta mayanagha[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  jnanayogena samkhyanam karmayogena yoginam -3-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Two forms of paths in this plane[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I have said to you before, Dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One whose consciousness has been purified[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Listening to Atman is the way for that mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One whose consciousness is not pure and wanting jnana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Desirelessly should do karma sadhana -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 After thinking like this, when the consciousness is completely focused in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutastha, His answer can be heard, meaning that an experience occurs which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 expresses: it has already been established that the discipline is of two types.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those with purified consciousness attain liberation through jnanayoga. But[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 those without purified consciousness, in order to acquire such Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [jnana], must engage themselves in the performance of Kriya yoga. -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na karmanamanarambhannaishkaryam purushohshnute[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na cha sannyasanadeva siddhim samadhigacchati -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na hi kashchat kshanamapi jatu tishthatyakarmakrit[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karyate hyavashah karma sarvah prakritijairgunai -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without karma [action] people cannot have knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without knowledge one cannot attain liberation in sannyas -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without action the jnani or the ignorant[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Cannot remain even for a moment, not even the wise[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of the natural impulse of affection and hatred[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Powerlessly are they doing karma -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without attaining Knowledge through the performance of Kriya yoga, just[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abandoning all types of karma [actions] and taking up sannyas will not bring[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that [Knowledge] without work, because the knowledgeable and ignorant[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 alike cannot exist even for a moment without karma. Thus, if one does not[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (2 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 do the karma of the Purusha-guna that reveals Consciousness, one falls under[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the stupor of the Prakriti-qualities of sattva, raja and tamoguna, and being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enslaved by affection, hatred, wants etc., one becomes involved in an[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unaware state with the workings of worldly life. -4 and 5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmendriyani samyamya ya aste manasa smaran[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indriyarthan vimudhamtma mithyacharah sa ucchyate -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Hands, feet - physical organs such as these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Controlling them and always thinking about things[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One shows people "I meditate on Brahman"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But that deceiver is a liar -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who want to be free of work in worldly life and live without doing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anything, for which purpose they forcefully subjugate all of the organs of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 action such as hands, feet, speech etc., and try to be mute and inanimate, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are very ignorant; because their minds, ever-bound to habit, is always[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 involved in thinking about sense matters. Therefore, due to their lack of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 inner stillness, all of their efforts are useless. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yastvindriyani manasa niyamyarabhateharjuna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmendriyah karmayogamashaktah sa vishishyate -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By karma the senses are controlled[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who use the body for action thus[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But without a taste for the results of action if they do[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 They become the greatest, listen Savyasachi -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who renounce all attraction towards sense-things by controlling the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind and all of the organs of action through the performance of yogakriya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and fulfill the karma [work] at hand in this way, they are the great ones. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 niyatam kuru karma tvam karma jyayo hyakarmanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sharirayatrapi cha te na prasiddhyedakarmanah -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (3 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, perform your eternal duty[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Action, instead of inaction, is proven by this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If you abandon all karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The body itself cannot be maintained -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, jivas should be ever-engaged in the performance of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-revealing Kriya, because without being involved in action,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one cannot even maintain one's body. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajnarthat karmanohnyatra lokohayam karmabandhanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tadartam karma kaunteya muktasangah samachara -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The karma that does not please the Lord[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That karma enchains people, Partha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, pray to please the Lord[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Do work renouncing desires of its fruits -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The action that is performed with the intention of the revelation of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness is called yajna. Besides that, performance of any karma of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 worldly desire causes one to remain bound to samsara for the fulfillment of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 its results. Therefore, one should do work that is devoid of the desire for the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyment of its fruit, meaning only the desireless practice of yogakriya. -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sahayajnah prajah srishtva purovacha prajapatih[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anena prasavishyadhvamesha vohstvishta kamadhuk -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Creator created Its subjects with yajna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the Lotus Seat did He say at the beginning of creation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By yajna you will acquire the Immense[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This yajna will be the fulfillment of your desires -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 At the very beginning, before giving initiation, the operator of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness, meaning the Full Consciousness-united Gurudev, teaches that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body of providence will be elevated by this Kriya and by the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (4 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manifestation of the miraculous Divine, all desired objects will be acquired.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 devan bhavayatanen te deva bhavayantu vah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 parsparam bhavayantah shreyah paramavapsyatha -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By homa [yajna] are the gods benefited[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Doing them you are benefited[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Like rain will the gods bless you[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By helping one another you will greatly prosper -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By the elevation of the body of providence itself does one have improvement[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in oneself. By helping each other in this way, one attains Kaivalyapada. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ishtan bhogan hi vo deva dasyante yajnabhavitah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tairdattanapradayaibho yo bhungkte stena eva sah -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Having been worshipped, like rain the gods will[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Give you the desired objects[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Offer that divine thing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without doing so and enjoying is the same as being a thief -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When the body of providence is felicitated by yajna, and by which, when all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desired objects are acquired by the manifestation of miraculous Divinity, if[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one does not use them for further advancement of the body of providence[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and thereby for the reduction of prarabdha [resultant manifestations due to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the past], and only use them for even more enjoyment of the senses, one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 actually destroys oneself. -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajnashishtashinah santo muchyante sarvakilvishaih[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhunjate te tvagham papa ye pachantyatmakaranat -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who eat of the divine yajna[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (5 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the sins of the five gunas are they freed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The sinners who for themselves eat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those persons eat only sin -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Attaining the nectarous Tranquility after Kriya, sadhakas are liberated from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all pains of worldly life. But those who do Kriya for the sake of sense[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyments - those soul-destroyers suffer greatly in the end. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 annadbhavanti bhutani parjanyadannasambhavah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajnadbhavati parjanyo yajnah karmasamudbhavah -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From food are all jivas born[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That food is born of the clouds, Dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The clouds are born of the presence of yajna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That yajna exists because of the Kriya by the performer of yajna -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Food, meaning the ever-sustaining nectarous thing that is the object of all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desires -- from that all of the elements in the body are nourished and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 content. This nectar emerges from the Sahasrara, the spirituall cloud. And[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that thousand-petaled lotus is revealed in full bloom by yajna. This yajna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happens by the Guru-given Kriya. -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karma brahmodbhavam viddhi brahmaksharasamudbhavam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasmat sarvagatam brahma nityam yajne pratishthitam -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This work is spoken of in the Vedas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The cause of the Vedas is the Eternal Incorruptible Brahman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, always is the Para Brahman everywhere[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By yajna this is attained, the Lord of the yajna -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This Guru-given yogakriya has come from the Kutasthachaitanya, and this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya is from that Infinite Consciousness Para Brahman. Thus,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by yajna, meaning yogakriya, sadhakas attain the Eternal Consciousness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Paramatman-ness. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (6 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evam pravartitam chakram nanuvartayatiha yah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aghayurindriyaramo mogham partha sa jivati -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This wheel of karma is of the law of God[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who abstains from its work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And enjoys for himself only[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He lives in vain in this sinful world -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those on this plane who do not follow this kind of yogakriya, living[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaninglessly addicted to the senses, they suffer throughout life. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yastvatmaratireva syadatmatriptashcha manavah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atmanyeva cha santushtastasya karyam na vidyate -17-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 naiva tasya kritenartho nakriteneha kashchan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na chasya sarvabhuteshu kashchidarthavyapashrayah -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one whose pleasure is only in Atman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the experience of Atman whose heart is in bliss[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 To the one in whose mind enjoyment of cravings never occurs[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Over that one karma has no right -17-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He is not sanctified by doing holy work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If he does not work, no sin he incurs[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the three worlds there is not for that Atman-residing one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Any dependence on anything -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who have renounced the thirst for all things and upon attaining the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bliss of Atman-experience have become satisfied; those whose passion and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pleasure is in Atman alone, and who are content in Atman Itself -- they do[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not need to perform any action. Because what can these Atman-realized[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beings who have the Bliss of Brahman gain byy performing any karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [action]? It means that there is nothing to gain. And it is written in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Patanjal philosophical treatises that "vyadhi," meaning physical incapability,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "styan," meaning mental incapability, "pramad," meaning intoxication,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "alasya," meaning laziness, "avirati," meaning lust, "bhrantidarshan,"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning delusionary knowledge, "alabdhabhumikatva," meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 incapability of getting results, and "anavasthitachittatva," meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 restlessness -- the Bliss of Brahman is prevented by these scattering the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (7 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind. But the revelation of the Knowledge of Atman annihilates all of these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 things mentioned above. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatah pratyakchetanadhigamohapantarayabhavashcha -- no. 29[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vyadhistyanasamshayapramadalasyaviratibhrantidarshanalabdha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhumikatvanavasthitatvani chittavikshepastehantarayam -- no. 30 -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Samadhipada[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, if the Atman-realized beings, because they always remain in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman-Consciousness, do not perform the all-obstacle-free Kriya, there is no[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 wrong. And because they always reside in the Bliss of Brahman, they do not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 have to even think about taking the slightest refuge in Brahman in order to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 protected from the enslaving desires of the sattva, raja and tamogunas of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Prakriti. -17 and 18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasmadasaktah satatam karyam karma samacharah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asakto hyacharan karma paramapnoti purushah -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore perform your eternal duty[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without searching for the fruits of karma in your mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Performing work with results renounced[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Doing so the purush finds the Supreme Absolute -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, one should renounce the anxiety for results and perform the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eternal yogakriya, because by discarding all obsession and continuously[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 doing Kriya, sadhakas become liberated from the bindings of karma and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attain Kaivalyapada. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmanaiva hi samsiddhimasthita janakadayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 lokasamgrahamevapi sampashyam kartumaharsi -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Janaka realized Oneness by action[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For the salvation of people perform action -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The sages such as Janaka attained perfection, meaning the attainment of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 liberation, by yogakriya, and yogakriya is also necessary to bring our[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 outgoing faculties [pravritti], which have gone astray, into the path of Truth.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (8 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, for no reason should one abandon Kriya. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yad yadacharati shreshthastattadevetarojanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sayat pramanam kurute lokastadanuvartate -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The manner in which the great ones behave[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That do the ordinary emulate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That which will be proved by the great ones[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That will be followed by ordinary people -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Except rajoguna, there is no guna in Prakriti in the area of Kriyashakti.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, this is the highest of all karmas. By this, whatever work is done, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ordinary faculties take on that good character, and whatever is decided upon[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by this, all of the faculties follow that path. -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na me parthasti kartavyam trishu lokeshu kinchana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nanavaptamavaptavyam varta eva cha karmani -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus the one who is on the path of Atman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Nothing he does not acquire in the three worlds[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For that to acquire will I endeavor[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 So in all work I reside -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There is nothing in these physical, subtle and causal bodies that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness does not possess nor is anything unattainable for It; therefore,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It does not even need to perform any type of action in order to acquire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anything. Thus, Consciousness-Shakti is present in all karma [work]. -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yadi hyaham na varteyam jatu karmanya tandritah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mama vartmanuvartante manushyah partha sarvashah -23-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 utsideyurime loka na kuryam karma chedaham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samkarasya cha karta syamupahanyamimah prajah -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because, and even though, I am beyond the senses[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (9 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I do not ever stop practicing karmayoga[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Everyone seeing me renounce work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Will renounce work as well, listen O Arjuna -23-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If I do not practice eternal karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 These subjects will be ruined, devoid of action[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Then I will be the cause of confusion[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All of these subjects I will dishearten -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If Consciousness would not remain even for a moment as Its beyond-the-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 senses awakened state, then this entire world and Brahmanda at once would[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become motionless and inert, and the pravritti ones would take the evil path[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and stupefy the prajna in ignorance, making it live in a disheartened state.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By this, many kinds of delusionary knowledge would arise. -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 saktah karmanyavidvamso yatha kurvanti bharat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karyadvidvamstathasaktashchikirshulokasamgraham -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The way with desire and results of karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus they perform acts, the ignorant ones[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For the welfare of those, will the knowledgeable ones[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Do all karma, son of Pandu -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this Brahmanda, there is no one who has the capability to prevent the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 force of the accumulated desires, meaning the prarabdha-bound fulfillment[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of karma. Without their completion, the mind can not be natural in any way.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The ignorant, liking some of those enjoyments at the time of the fulfillment[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of prarabdha, desire for more of the same in the future, and disliking some[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 things in which they must also partake, desire to be freed of that, which is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 another desire. In this way, again and again, by their own design, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 continue to create prarabdha like a silkworm and remain enmeshed in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samsara. But the wise ones renounce these types of likes and dislikes and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fulfill prarabdha karma desirelessly in order to bring the pravritti elements[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who have taken the wrong road on to the path of Atman, and thereby return[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the mind to its natural state. -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na buddhibhedam janayedajnanam karmasanginam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yojayet sarvakarmani vidvan yuktah samachan -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (10 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The ones who are attached to working in ignorance[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The wise do not force wisdom upon them[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Instead, they do their own work with care[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Inspire the others in the practice of karma as such -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, one should reside in Atman-Consciousness and take up the karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 at hand, and fulfill the partaking prescribed by prarabdha, without[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 endeavoring to judge in any way the ignorant who are addicted to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyments. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prakriteh kriyamanani gunaih karmani sarvashah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahamkaravimudhatma kartahamiti manyate -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The organs of action, the organs of perception - that are in the body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All of the numerous types of work are done by them[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One whose wisdom is tattered by ego[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In vanity, thinks of himself as the lord and doer -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The material jiva is inert. All work is executed by Prakriti's sattva-, raja-,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and tamoguna-based senses. Entangled in ignorance, the jiva discerns the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sense oriented ego-substance to be the Atman and being captivated by that,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ascertains "I am the one who is doing." -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatvavittu mahavaho gunakarmavibhagayoh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 guna gunashu vartanta iti matva na sajjate -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But the one who knows the True Form of Atman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He remains apart from the karma of the gunas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Partha, he does not think himself as the doer in vanity[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He knows that the enjoyment of the senses are such -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But the knowledgeable, wise ones who have realized themselves as being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beyond the twenty-four substances of the Prakriti-gunas, understand that the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 guna-born cause-oriented senses are the ones who are engaged in the guna-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (11 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 born action-oriented things, and thus they do not see themselves as the doers[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of any action. -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prakritergunasammudhah sajjante gunakarmasu[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tankritsnavido mandan kritsnavinna vichalayet -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The deluded person is bound by maya's illusion[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Believing Atman to be doing the sensory work of the senses[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That ignorant and wrong perception should never[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Be reason for the wise to display his wisdom -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With the Prakriti-guna-based senses being deluded in ego, ignorant persons[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 think themselves to be the doer of all work actually being done by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 senses. Self-realized beings should not be distressed by such short-sighted[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mentality. Otherwise, there will be disrespect for work, and lacking[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge, very destructive and corrupted possibilities will arise. -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mayi sarvani karmani samnyasyadhyatmachetasa[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nirashirnirmamo bhutva yudhyasva vigatajvarah -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Offering all work to me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing oneself, engaged in God[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Desirelessly, renounce all attachment[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Fight, Dhananjaya, abandoning grief -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All work is being done according to the law of the Consciousness-God[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 present in the Universe. We need not make any effort in this. With a mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 devoid of desire and attachment, meditating completely in God and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abandoning all lamentation, one should perform one's own Atman-Kriya. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ye me matamidam nityamanutishthanti manavah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sharaddhavantohanasuyanto muchyante tehpi karmabhih -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (12 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who listen to My words reverently[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In sorrow-filled karma remain without grudge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Take refuge always in this way[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 They are eventually liberated from karma -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Being devoid of thinking "this work is laborious" or "this is not right" etc.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and not taking part in any kind of blame, those who perform Atman-Kriya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with reverence are the ones who are liberated from the shackles of karma. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ye tvetadabhyasuyanto nanutishthanti me matam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvajnanavimudhamstan viddhi nashtana chetasah -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those do work begrudgingly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Do not take up My teaching[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Know him to be without discrimination, Partha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Deluded by ignorance, without any knowledge -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who endeavor to perform Kriya yet thinking that it is too laborious,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they lose all knowledge and eventually ruin their own consciousness. -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadrisham cheshtate svasyah prakriterjnanavanapi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prakritim yanti bhutani nigrahah kim karishyati -33-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indriyasyendriyasyarthe ragadveshou vyavasthitou[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tayornavashmagacchet tou hyasya paripanthinou -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The samskara that is born of ancient karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 According to nature it is say the shastras[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Following one's nature as it is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Helplessly even the wise do karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In meaningless karma all jiva's are bound by their nature[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 So what will you do by restraining the senses -33-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Getting that which the senses favor[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As satisfaction is born, turn away from it then[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the same way, when unfavorable things one gets[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Turn away from the hatred arising because of them[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Do not be enslaved by like and dislike, Dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (13 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Cultivating these cause vices to rise -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Not to even mention ordinary people, even knowledgeable persons habitually[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 engage themselves in sense-oriented karma according to their personal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nature, which is the result of previously created samskara from past actions.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, it is in the nature of the senses to have affection for favorable things[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and repulsion for unfavorable things, which are both from previous[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samskara. This like and dislike are the obstacles to liberation. One should[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not be subjugated by them. There is no need to restrain the senses; that is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unnatural; because this entire world and Brahmanda is under the rule of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samskaras; no one is beyond it. -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shreyan svadharmo vigunah paradharmat svanushthitat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 svadharme nidhanam shreyah paradharmo bhayavahah -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Baseless work of one's own nature is true[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is superior to high work of others' nature[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dying in one's own work is best[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Know that following others nature is a horror -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, although the Consciousness-revealing Atman-Kriya is formless, it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is supreme, as opposed to all work that has beautiful form and desired[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 results. Because action with desire is a tremendous horror; it is by this that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the jiva remains bound to this mundane world and experiences this immense[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 suffering. -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atha kena prayuktohayam papancharati purushah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anicchannapi varshneya baladiva niyojitah -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna asked the Lord[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Engaging in what does the wise incur sin[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Even though he has no desire for sin[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Is forced into committing sin -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (14 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Experiencing this, the question arises in the energy of the fire element that --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 even without desiring, it seems that the jiva is forced into committing sin.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 What is the cause of this? -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kama esha krodha esha rajogunasamudbhavah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mahashano mahapapna vidhyenamiha vairinam -37-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Hearing this, said Govinda to Arjuna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With unsatisfied desire immediately rises anger[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus anger is born of desire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Which is born from rajoguna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This terrible desire has no satisfaction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Know it to be the enemy on the path of liberation -37-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the Kutasthachaitanya, the experience arises that -- it is desire itself that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 changes into anger. It emerges from rajoguna, is very evil and nothing ever[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 satisfies it. Know this to be the enemy in this worldly life. -37[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhumenavriyate vahnirshathadarsho malena cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatholvenavrito garbhastatha tenedamavritam -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Just as smoke envelopes fire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The way a mirror is covered by dust[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As the embryo is covered by membrane in the womb[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In that way is Knowledge in us covered -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Just as fire by smoke, a mirror by dust, and the embryo-child by the amnion[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are all covered, in the same way, discrimination is covered in this worldly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 life by desire. -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avritam jnanametena jnanino nityavairina[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kamarupena kaunteya dushpurenanalena cha -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (15 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The eternal enemy of the sage is this desire unsatisfied[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Like fire it gives much sorrow and pain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This evil desire covers[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Reason in people, listen son of Kunti -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The eternal enemy of the wise, the insatiable desire, keeps Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 covered in the great heat of its fire. -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indriyani manobuddhirasyadhishthanamuchyuta[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etairvimohayatyesha jnanamavritya dehinam -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Eyes, ears and such senses of this form[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Are the cause of all desires[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In desire, the mind and intellect are under the senses[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Destroying knowledge and giving birth to delusion -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The desire within the body controls the areas in which it appears - the mind,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intellect and senses - and covering up Knowledge, it keeps the jiva in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 delusion. -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasmat tvamindrinyadou niyamya bharatarshabha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 papnanam prajahi hyenam jnanavijnananashanam -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, before becoming captivated[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Control the senses as instructed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who destroys Atman-Knowledge and knowledge of scriptures --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Destroy this sinner - desire -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, at the very beginning, by controlling the senses along with mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and intellect and by doing Kriya according to the rules, one should destroy[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this Atman-Knowledge and Guru-given-wisdom-destroying, tremendously[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evil, insatiable and sinful desire. -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indriyani paranyahurindriyebhyah param manah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (16 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manasastu parabuddhiryobuddheh paratastu sah -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the body the senses are superior[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the senses the mind is greater[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the mind the intellect is superior and should be cared for[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Beyond the intellect is the Atman as the witness -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This physical-world-revealing senses are superior to the body; the subtler-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 than-the senses and subtle-world-revealing mind is greater than that; greater[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 than the mind is the doubt-free, all-revealing intellect; and the One who is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 greater than this intellect -- That is Atman. -42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evam buddhehparam buddha samstabhyatmanamatmana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jahi shatrum mahavaho kamarupam durasadam -43-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing the Atman beyond the intellect[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By intellect keeping the mind disciplined[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The enemy, desire, whom you can know in sorrow[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For its destruction engage yourself, Dhananjaya -43-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, realizing the Atman beyond the intellect, keeping oneself[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 separate from all of the senses, mind, intellect etc. and abiding in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness only, one should destroy this evil enemy - desire, who is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 difficult to capture, right at the beginning. -43-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 SUMMARIZED DESCRIPTION OF CHAPTER 3:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Listening to the matters of karma [action] and jnana [knowledge] in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 previous chapter, this type of experience occurs in the rajoguna that - if[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge is greater than action, then what is the need for this intense work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (battle)? In this way, seeing its intellect as being deluded, it relies upon the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya [1 - 2]. There, the awareness emerges that discipline is of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 two types. The ones of jnana practice jnanayoga in a state of non-doing, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because of that Knowledge itself, sadhakas have to perform yogakriya.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without the performance of yogakriya, not even for a moment can one reside[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the state of non-doing; instead, one does karma in an unaware way, being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enslaved by the usual likes and dislikes, and by only forcing the organs of[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (17 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 action to be subjugated like the sannyasis do, one cannot achieve non-doing,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because the mind, in its perpetual habit, constantly remains engaged in sense[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 objects. Without work, even the body cannot be maintained; therefore it is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 superior to do work [Kriya] than not. It is true that by all kinds of karma one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is bound to this worldly life, but only by the performing the Consciousness-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealing Kriya [work] does the jiva attain liberation. Therefore, keeping the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 organs of perception controlled by the mind, one should use the organs of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 action with continuous desireless awareness and perform yogakriya [7 -9].[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Saints have perceived through prajna that by nourishing the body of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 providence through Kriya as the desires of mind come up and pacifying the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body of providence by fulfilling such through Kriya, the jiva tastes the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Immortal Nectar and attains liberation. But if the jiva does not do so and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 uses the manifestation of miraculous Divinity for further enjoyment of sense-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pleasures, then there is a possibility of great detriment [10 - 13]. By the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Eternally-present Form of Brahman-Consciousness - Kutasthachaitanya -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 performing yogakriya causes the manifestation of Ambrosia from the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sahasrar [14 -15]. Those who do not endeavor in this type of practice in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body - the lives of those sense-addicted persons are in vain, and their life-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 span passes in great sufferning [16]. Those who remain in the Self in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 satisfaction and contentment, they do not need to perform any karma,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because they have no diminution or expansion; they also do not have to take[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 refuge in anything for any reason. Therefore, in order to attain this Supreme[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Substance, one should always desirelessly perform Kriya [17 -19]. Sages[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 such as Janaka have attained Kaivalyapada by this yogakriya. Rajoguna is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 supreme in Kriya; whatever is established by this is followed by the other[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 faculties. Therefore, if only for the purpose of keeping the faculties of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pravritti - which have taken the evil road - on the path of Atman, one should[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perform Kriya [20 -21]. There is nothing that Consciousness does not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 possess in the Universe, and nothing is unattainable for It. If Consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 did not remain present and beyond the senses, meaning if It were even[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 slightly in stupor, then by the arising of many kinds of delusionary[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge, all jivas would become devoid of knowledge and become as if[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dead [22 - 24]. The ignorant act under the power of desire and its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyment. The wise do not behave like the ignorant, and to gather the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 faculties of pravritti which have taken the wrong road on to the path of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman, they perform yogakriya with a consciousness devoid of desire and its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 need for enjoyment [25 - 26]. The senses act on things. The ignorant,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 believing the Atman to be the sense-based ego substance, think themselves to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 be the doers of all those karmas. But the wise remain tranquil, knowing the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman to be uninvolved and beyond all twenty-four matters of the senses;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they do not engage themselves in any kind of judgment of the ignorant with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 little understanding [27 - 29]. The senses of even the knowledgeable can -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because of habit and the influence of their personal samskaras - express[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 affection towards favorable things, and hatred toward unfavorable things.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 They do not have a reason to become involved with that enemy of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge. Therefore, one should remain unaffected by like and dislike,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renounce all perception of blame, and surrendering all with desireless[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter3.html (18 of 19)4/18/2006 2:42:01 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness to Atman, become engaged in Atman-Kriya. One should not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 turn away from this because of many different kinds of doubts. If that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happens, one becomes enveloped in ignorance and has to live in samsara in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 an unaware state. Even though Atman-Kriya is without form, it is superior[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to actions of desire that have beautiful form, because the jiva becomes bound[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and has to go through this horrific suffering due to these actions of desire [30[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 - 35]. After this type of experience, a question arises in the fire element that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 - who forces the jiva into destroying itself, even though it does not want to?[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [36] Then, when consciousness is focused in the Kutasthachaitanya, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experience occurs that - just as fire by smoke, a mirror by dust and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 embryo-child by the amnion are covered, in the same way, the eternal enemy[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Knowledge - the insatiable fire of desire, and anger, which is born of it, by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 delusion envelope the knowledge present in the senses, mind and intellect[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and lead one to self-destruction [37 - 40]. Therefore, one should control the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 senses and destroy this knowledge- and wisdom-destroying evil desire right[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 at the beginning [41]. The senses are supreme in this body; greater than that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is the mind and even greater is the intellect. But one should reside in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 awakened awareness of Atman - Who is the Greatest of All, and eradicate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this very evasive enemy in the form of desire [42 - 43].[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the third chapter of the yogashastra upanishad Srimad Bhagavad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gita with analysis via various scriptures of this country and the West, along[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with spiritual commentary.[m
