[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 CHAPTER FOUR[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 JNANAYOGA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 imam vivasvate yogam proktavanahamavyayam[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       vivasvan manave praha manurikshvakavehabravit -1-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evam paramparapraptamimam rajarshayo viduh[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   sa kaleneha mahata yogo nashtah paramtapa -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition                          Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            The Lord again spoke to Arjuna[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     I taught this Eternal Knowledge to the Sun-god[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   The lord of the day taught it to the god of obsequies, Manu[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  Manu taught it to Ikshvaku -1-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Through lineage sages attained perfection through this yoga's method[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction                     That lineage-bestowed yoga disappeared -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        By scientific research in both this country and the West, it has been[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        thoroughly proven that the sun is an incredibly powerful sphere of electrical[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5                        conduction (powerful electric conductor). From its electricity, the creation,[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        sustenance and dissolution work of this world is being accomplished. The[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        light that is radiating all around it is only pure, condensed electricity. The[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        saintly scriptural scholars have analyzed the subtle body's source as[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        "suksham bhuta," "mahabhuta" or "tanmatra." And that, by focusing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 steadily, the blue sphere that can be seen in the middle of the sun is from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 where that "mahabhuta" (electricity) emerges and dissolves. This place is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hidden from all of the senses, and as such, it is empty and dark, which is why[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it appears as a blue form. All of the sukhsham bhutas [electricity] arise from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that and accomplish the works of creation, preservation and dissolution. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scriptural scholars have said that blue form in the sun is the cause of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world-Brahmanda and thus called it the three-guna-endowed Prakriti[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (1 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  [Trigunamayi Prakriti]. All of these sukhsham bhutas (electricity) emerge[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  from that and manifest themselves as many conditions of existence, the[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  mixing of which creates the appearance of this physical world, and flooding[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  the world internally, pervading everything, they are perpetually eroding and[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  doing the work of destruction. Because all of these mahabhutas (electricity)[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  are coagulated, meaning condensed, around the sun, they are visible to the[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  senses, but because they are in a rarefied state in other things of the world,[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  one cannot even perceive their existence. The saintly scriptural scholars[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  have called this aggregate of different kinds of suksham bhutas pervading the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 inner workings of everything and operating the creation, preservation and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dissolution of all as the "subtle body" of the world. The mixing of these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 suksham bhutas (by five elemental ways) give rise to this visible world of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 material substances which the scholars have called the "physical [or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 material] body." A sun and its planets and satellites can be called a "solar[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 system" or Brahmanda. All of the stars that we see in sky are other suns,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 most of which are many times larger than our sun. They also have planets[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and satellites orbiting them; each of them is also a solar system or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda. There are infinite numbers of Brahmandas in this Universe, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 throughout the every Brahmanda are the three bodies - physical, subtle and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 causal - present, which comprise the Universe. All matter in the world is a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 part of this Brahmanda; therefore, the three bodies - physical, subtle and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 causal - are present in everything, partly visible and partly invisible. With[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the diminution of impurity, these bodies gradually reveal themselves. This[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 subject has been explained extensively in sloka 70 of the second chapter.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 After traveling through eight million four hundred thousand yonis, the jiva is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purified and attains the highest physical form in this Brahmanda as a human[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being, in which all of these bodies are fully revealed. Because the above-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mentioned three bodies, sun, moon, stars etc. - everything in the Brahmanda[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 as mentioned are present in this body, the saintly scriptural scholars call this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the "miniature Brahmanda." By the Sadguru-graced Kriya, when the mind is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stilled, one experiences the above-mentioned sun, moon etc., all in full form[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the body. This cannot be acquired by indirect knowledge; it can only be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 known by one's direct experience. Without the sacrament of the Holy Feet[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Sadguru, this direct knowledge cannot be experienced.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From the sacrament of Sadguru, one can also become aware that among the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nadis present in this body, there are three which are primary - ida, pingala[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and sushumna. Ida is on the left side, pingala is on the right and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sushumna is in the middle of the body. Ida is like a door of meditation. By[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it, the mind can rid itself of unhappiness and become cheerful. For this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reason, the saintly scriptural scholars call the presiding god in it, "Chandra[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [moon]" (chad - the substance of delight). By the Guru-instructed Kriya,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhakas experience this moon as a comely, snowy sphere in front of them.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pingala is like a door of knowledge. When the mind is stilled by this,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge is revealed. For this reason, the scriptural saints call its presiding[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 god, "Surya [sun]" (sri - substance of motion and knowledge). The sadhakas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by Guru-instructed Kriya experience this in the as a fiery sun in the back. By[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (2 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 singing, "The right-side air; in the back country beneficence, etc.," in his[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world-renown song, the great sadhaka Ramprasad gave a hint of the method[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the practice to call forth the presiding god of the impurity eroding,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge-revealing pingala. Meditation, knowledge, renunciation and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tranquility are the first, second, third and fourth levels, respectively, of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gradual progress on the path of sadhana. When the mind eventually becomes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happy through meditation, knowledge becomes necessary for its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 steadfastness. In this way, as the mind attains happiness and steadiness by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meditation and knowledge, it is then understood that -- all of the things about[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 which I was so concerned saying, "Mine, mine" - none of it, not even the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body is owned by the jiva.. Thus, as a jiva I own nothing in this world-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda, or, All is Mine as this World-Pervading Consciousness. If I[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 were not here, then none of all this could be here. This world and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda are existing in Me. The king-sage Janaka expressed this, after[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 having received Knowledge-initiation from his gurudev, Maharshi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ashtavakra. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatha prakashayamyekam dehamenam tatha jagat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ato mama jagat sarvamathava cha na kinchana -- Ashtavakra Samhita 2:2.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When knowledge is established, all desires are renounced at once, and in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 way, when meditation, knowledge and renunciation are established, the mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 moves into the sushumna and procures tranquility. This sushumna is a place[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 filled with peace. When the mind is pacified by it, the Eternal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness Itself is revealed. For this reason, the saintly scriptural[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scholars call the Lord of All, world-ruling, Triguna-owning Consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 as the presiding God of the sushumna. It is from these three nadis that the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sixty thousand nadis have arisen and are actively present throughout the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body. Maharshi Vedavyas wrote about these three in the Mahabharata as the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 moon-family, the sun-family and the "vrishni"-family (vrish-ni: "vrish" -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being the lord; ruling) as primary families.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When one becomes aware of all this by acquiring Sadguru's teaching, one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 can explain these two slokas as such: when by the previously mentioned[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 way the evasive desire is eradicated and the Supreme Self-Substance is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realized, gradually the causal body in the form of the sun appears between[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the eyebrows in this miniature Brahmanda-body, the place of manifestation.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And by that, it can be clearly known that this causal body, or the sun, is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 united with Consciousness by the union with the Kutasthachaitanya. And[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from this sun, the electricity radiating from all around it having attained[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness is existing as Manu, the source of the human body. And it is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from this, having attained Consciousness, the ajna chakra is existing as the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 primary door to the wisdom of nivritti. And from this the chakras such as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Muladhar etc. are residing in the significant parts of the body, prevailing in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-union. Finally, this Consciousness is spread out all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 throughout the sixty thousand nadis in such a way that even Its existence[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cannot be readily known. -1 and 2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (3 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sa evayam maya tehdya yogah proktah puratanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhaktohsi me sakha cheti rahasyam hyetaduttamam -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Hidden was that ancient yoga for a time[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now I teach this to you again[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 You are my friend and disciple[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For this reason I tell you this most high affair -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, with the devoted mind being concentrated in the Kutastha and with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 condensing of that awakenedness usually spread throughout the sixty[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 thousand nadis, I have become awakened and I am comprehending this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 highest mystery. -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aparam bhavato janma param janma vivasvatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kathametadvijaniyat tvamadou proktavaniti -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said, Lord this is most extraordinary[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 You were born after the sun which was born before[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 So how is it possible, may I know[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That You revealed this Knowledge to the sun before -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When all this is revealed in the Kutasthachaitanya, the experience occurs in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the fire element that -- first, the sadhakas experience the sun through Kriya;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 then when there is stillness in the sun, the Kutasthachaitanya is revvealed.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, how is it that I am seeing the sun before the revelation of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya, and then the sun united with Consciousness in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya. -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bahuni me vyatitani janmani tava charjuna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tanyaham veda sarvani na tvam vettha paramtapa -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (4 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Govinda said, your births and mine[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 What can I say, there have been many[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of knowledge, I know all of them[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Helpless in ignorance you do not know, Falguni -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When the mind is concentrated in the Kutastha, the experience happens that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- this Kutasthachaitanya has revealed Itself with the five elements in a body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 many times; being under the power of ignorance,, the jiva cannot experience[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that. But when maya is vanquished by the concentration of mind in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutastha, all of these things are experienced. -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ajohapi sannavyayatma bhutanamishvarohpi san[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prakritim swamadhishthaya sambhavamyatmamaya -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because I am without birth or death[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All samsara is under My power[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Still I take on a form of Nature[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Within My own maya, I take a body -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Although Kutasthachaitanya is free of birth and death, and is the Lord of all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmandas, even up to the highest level, still, remaining the Lord of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Prakriti, He reveals Himself in this world-Brahmanda through the maya-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 caused body. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yada yada hi dharmasya glanirbhavati bharata[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abhyutthanamadharmasya tadatmanam srijamyaham -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When sin is rampant and virtue [dharma] is not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Then I manifest Myself, Dhananjaya -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is necessary to know what is "dharma" before commenting on this sloka. I[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 will try my best to explain this subject below.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Western scholars had deduced that heat and force constituted the life-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 energy in this world. The great scientist Tyndal concluded that heat is also a[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (5 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 type of force or shakti in motion. Now, in all scientific treatises of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 country and the West, it has been extensively proven that shakti (force) is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 life of the Universe, and that it is indestructible; it never ceases to exist.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When shakti engages any inert matter, it remains present there eternally.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This solar system is endlessly orbiting with its planets and satellites because[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of this law. From this a question can appear that if shakti uses a stone and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that stone travels endlessly in space without stopping, then what stops it, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 how, if shakti does not diminish, does it cease? It has been concluded in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 science that for the stone to travel on its own, shakti employs the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gravitational force of the earth and the air. When force is used in this way,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the stone becomes forceless and stops. That is not the diminution of shakti;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it is only a transfer of power from one object to another. Therefore, shakti is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 infinite and thus unborn. It is this shakti that rules in all matter as the forces[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of attraction and repulsion, by which It is making the existence of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 innumerable designs of matter and scenarios possible, through birth and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 death, again and again. These two types of shakti is in every atom of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world. The attraction aspect of the shakti in atoms and molecules is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "anavik asakti" (molecular attraction), and the repulsion aspect is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "abhyantarika taap" (latent heat). Because of the shakti of molecular[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attraction, the atoms and molecules are bound to each other and are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perpetually manifesting this world-Brahmanda. And because of that heat or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 repulsion shakti, the atoms and molecules have divided and created the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 different and separate forms of this world-Brahmanda. It is by the power of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this shakti of Prakriti that all molecules take on the five states - kshiti (solid),[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ap (liquid), teja (subgaseous), marut (gaseous) and vyoma (ethereal).* The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scholars of shastra have called these "suksham bhutas" or "mahabhutas." It[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is they who, by mixing with one another, are appearing as this physical[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world. Their abilities are amazing. They are breaking down this material[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world and again reconstructing everything appropriate for the existence of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the jiva. By these, all jivas are designed according to what is appropriate in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 terms of the materials necessary for existence, and after the leaving the body,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 again by them does the jiva take a new form as necessary and reenter[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samsara. In this way, it is by their power that all matter in this world is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 created, sustained and dissolved, and it is because of their presence that this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world-Brahmanda is existing.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [*Translator‚Äôs note: kshiti, ap, teja, marut and vyoma are also the Sanskrit[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 names of the five elements - earth, water, fire, air and ether, respectively.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The neutralized state of these forces of attraction and repulsion is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unmanifest potential condition of the world. Just as when a neutralized[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 magnet is altered for some reason it becomes imbued with the three gunas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sattva (neuter), raja (positive) and tama (negative) and manifests attractive[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and repulsive forces, in the same way, when the neutralized Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman-Consciousness' unmanifest potential condition, meaning the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 condition of Prakriti is altered in the slightest, the three gunas sattva (neuter),[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 raja (positive) and tama (negative) appear, spawning attractive and repulsive[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (6 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 forces which create the world in its many forms. The neutralized state of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sattva, raja and tamogunas born of the world-creating Shakti is called the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unmanifest potential state, the revealed condition or Prakriti of that Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman-Consciousness. As in-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sattvarajastamasam samyavastha prakritirityadi -- ka. su. 1:61[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When this gunas of Prakriti rest even for a moment, this vast solar system[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dissolves with its planets and satellites, and this Universe at once disappears.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Creation is existing by holding the revealed condition or Prakriti of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Infinite Consciousness. That which can be held on to is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "dharma" (dhri - holding). Therefore, the only "dharma" in this vast solar[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 system and this Universe is the realization of this Eternal Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, this sloka can be explained as such: when the revealed condition of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this Eternal Brahman-Consciousness, meaning Prakriti's quality-less or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 neutralized or inner-directed state-dharma, is altered, then the outer-directed,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-hidden "adharma" [non-dharma] state manifests, giving rise[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to the three gunas with the forces of attraction and repulsion, by which that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Eternal Consciousness plays out Its own "sport" [lila] in innumerable ways,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning that via the vehicles of different bodies, It appears as this visible[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 paritranaya sadhunam vinashaya cha dushkritam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dharmasamsthapanarthaya sambhavami yuge yuge -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I save the persons of dharma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Evil people are the cause of everyone's demise[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And to establish universal [sanatan] dharma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I take birth age [yuga] after age -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 To comprehend this sloka, it is important to first understand the meaning of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the word "yuga" and find out the reason for its repeated use. Thus, I will[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 explain the matter below.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One meaning of yuga is time divided in four parts, as in - Satya Yuga, Treta[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Yuga, Dvapara Yuga and Kali Yuga. These divisions of yugas have been so[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 named because of the condition of dharma at the time; meaning that when all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 four parts of dharma - complete - manifiest, the age is named Satya; when[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 only three parts manifest, it is Treta; when two, it is Dvapara and when only[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one part of dharma manifests, the yuga is called Kali. In the previous sloka[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it has been extensively addressed that only the Eternal Brahman-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (7 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness is sustaining this vast solar system and this Universe, and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realization of this Satchitananda-filled Brahman-Consciousness is the only[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dharma. That Eternal Consciousness can be perceived in this creation in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 three forms: one form being the tama-ruled physical cosmos; another form is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the raja-ruled subtle state of molecules as the holder of the physical world,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and the third form is the atomic level as the creator of the world and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cause of emergence and dissolution.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Conditions always change in creation; no condition is permanent. When[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 creation transforms from Eternal Consciousness into physical matter, in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 order to again return progressively on the path of Consciousness, it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 continuously transmutes all forms of life, mind etc. from their present states.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For this reason, the saintly scriptural scholars have said that the tama-ruled[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 physical part is the destroyer/transformer; the raja-ruled subtle part is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cause of the accomplishment of the creation of the physical part, and thus has[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 been called the creator, and the sattva-ruled causal part has been called the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 holder/sustainer. These forms of the lords of creation, sustenance and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 destruction have been named in Tantra as Brahma, Vishnu and Maheshvara[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [respectively]. Consciousness is the only One who is present in all three as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 named in creation; therefore, these three are just that One Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Perceiving these three parts in the Consciousness-prevailing creation, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 saintly philosophical scholars have said that the fourth part, being beyond[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 name, form, the hierarchal structure of the three conditions [previously[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mentioned in this and the previous paragraph] and creation itself, is still[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 presiding inseparably and behind everything in the manifested world. They[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 have called that "Turiya Brahman-Consciousness."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 At the time when the jiva in any planet or satellite perceives only the first[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 part of consciousness - the physical world, that time for that planet or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 satellite is called "Kali Yuga." When, by the evolution of the jiva's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experiential powers, the jiva can perceive the second part of Consciousness -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the subtle world, which is the creator of the physical world, that time is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 called "Dvapara Yuga." At the time when the jiva's purification allows the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perception of the third part of Consciousness - the causal form, which is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sustaining and holding creation, that time is called "Treta Yuga." And the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time when the jiva is completely purified and awakened in Truth, and thus[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perceives the Satchitananda-filled Turiya Brahman-Consciousness, that time[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is called "Satya Yuga." The saintly scriptural scholars have also called the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 same progressive states in this miniature Universe of the human body as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 such, meaning: experiencing one part of Eternal Consciousness is the state[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of being called Kali Yuga [kali yugavastha], experiencing two parts[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 constitute the state of being called Dvapara Yuga [dvapara yugavastha],[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experiencing three parts comprise the state of being called Treta Yuga [treta[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yugavastha], and the realization of the complete four parts of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Satchitananda-filled Turiya Brahman-Consciousness is the state of being[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (8 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 called Satya Yuga [satya yugavastha].[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of perpetually transforming into different forms, in accordance with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 physical law, the previous forms of all matter in this body gradually decay.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And by sweat, respiration, urination etc., the waste from such decay are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 expelled from the body. One has to eat every day in order to compensate for[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this erosion. Food is assimilated and spread throughout the body by blood,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 filling the place left by the cleaning out of waste products brought about by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 decay, and thus the body is sustained. In this way, old fluids and blood in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body are transformed into new fluids and blood. The daily gradual decay[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the old and replenishing with the new accumulates into changing all of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 muscle and fat of a person into all new muscle and fat in the span of a lunar[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 month. In this way, in one solar year, all of the veins, arteries and nerves,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and thereby even the ten senses and five pranas of the subtle body are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 completely transformed into new creation. For this reason, one year of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 physical world has been said to be one day in the plane of the gods or the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body of the subtle world. In three solar years (which is 39 lunar months,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 when calculated with the intercalary month, the beginning and end), sperm,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 marrow etc., and thereby even the mind and intellect and all subtle elements[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are completely transformed into new creation. These three years are referred[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to by some as one "khanda yuga." In four of these khanda yugas, meaning in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 twelve solar years - according to Western physiology, in seven solar years -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the entire natural body, including even consciousness and the causal body -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all three bodies, are completely changed and the human being takes a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 completely new natural form. In this way, in 12 years, all parts of a human[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being are transformed, and with new nature, intellect, mind, prana, senses[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etc., a new human body and being are created.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The jiva eats many kinds of food, but not all of them are appropriate for the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 maintenance of the body. Because of cultural habits and the norms of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 company one keeps, affinity for certain things and repulsion toward certain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 things arise in the subtle body. Thus, the subtle body maintains the body by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eating the foods with which it has affinity, and unknowingly leaves out food[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 which it dislikes. In this way, according to its habits and desires due to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samskaras, the body gradually changes into a completely new thing in 12[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 years. For this reason, although meat and milk are both excellently[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nourishing foods, neither the meat-eating person relying on milk, nor the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 milk-consuming person relying on meat can properly maintain the health of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 their respective bodies. According to the jiva's nature and samskara-based[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desires, it maintains its body with either with "high quality" foods, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that which aids in the revelation of Consciousness, or "low quality" foods,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning that which is bound to the material world and keeps one in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ignorance. This means that when sense-desires are predominant, one will[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consume foods that are appropriate for that, and when the desire for the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realization of Consciousness is predominant, the jiva will take consciousness-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 based foods and maintain its body in that way. Thus, according to either the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 improvement or decline of habits and samskara-based desires of the jiva, in[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (9 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the previously mentioned 12 years, either a completely new god-nature or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 animal-nature prevails in the body, by which, one is transformed into the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 form of a new jiva. For this reason, the saintly scriptural scholars have[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 called these 12 years as one yuga.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is in written in the Vedanta as well as explained in the commentary on[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sloka 70 of the third chapter of this book that when the jiva's capacity of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 awareness evolves, and by which when it is able to realize the vital force[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 within the material body and then the mind within that, eventually evolving[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to possess the ability to operate intellectually, it assumes a human form. In[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this way, up to the time of acquiring the human body, there is no possibility[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the progress of the jiva to go awry in any way, because without having the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ability to function intellectually, there is no type of desire that the jiva wants[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to fulfill; therefore, Consciousness reveals Itself consistently, and the jiva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attains a more evolved state of existence according to natural law. But what[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 a terrible condition befalls the jiva when it becomes aware of the jnanamaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cover! The acquisition of freedom in the power of desire causes the jiva to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become involved in habitual indiscretions, and not to speak of natural[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evolution, from time to time, being bound to one's own engagements by that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 power of desire, the jiva falls and again reincarnates in the form of insects[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and such. If the human being does not use the intellect, or if one does not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 possess that power, then step by step, in 12,000 years the full four-fold[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realization of Consciousness will manifest and thereby the jiva can possess a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 new body of complete bliss. This subject of evolution in time of the material[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world along with the creation of maya to the presiding of only the Kaivalya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Brahman-Consciousness is written in the Manu Samhita. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pitryeratrahanimasah pravibhagastupakshayoh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmacheshta svahah krishnah shuklah svapnaya sharvari[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 daive ratra hani varham pravibhagastayoh punah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahastatrodagayanam ratrih syaddakshinayanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chatvaryahuh sahasrani varshanantu kritam yugam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasya tavacchati sandhya sandhyamshashcha tathavidhah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 itareshu sasandheshu sa sandhyamsheshu cha trishu[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ekapayena vartante sahasrini shatani cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yadetat parisamkhyatamadadeva chaturyugam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etaddvadashasahasram devanam yugamuchyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 daivikanam yuganantu sahasram parisamkhyaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmamekamaharjneyam tavati ratrireva cha[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One lunar month is one "aho ratri" of the plane of the father, meaning this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 physical body given by the father. Within that, the dark fortnight is the day,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning that this physical body is awake and active, and the bright fortnight[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is night, meaning that only that which is necessary to function does so in a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 way that is like sleep. This matter can be clearly understood by observing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the work of honey-bees. They have no intellectual capacity; they accomplish[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 everything bound to natural law. They rest during the bright fortnight and[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (10 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 once the full moon has passed, they return to work. And they work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tremendously throughout the dark fortnight. Once the new moon passes,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they return to their abodes for rest. And they only maintain the minimal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 functioning of their lives - only eating and such - throughout the bright[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fortnight.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, 12 orbits around the sun, meaning one solar year is one aho ratri[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the plane of the gods, meaning the body of providence or the subtle body.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Within that, the summer solstice marks the day of the subtle body, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the time of awakened activity, and the winter solstice marks the night,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning the state of sleep and the time of rest, when only minimal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 functioning is maintained.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kulukabhatta, the primary interpreter of the Manu Samhita, has explained[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the word "varsha" [year] as "daiva varsha" [year of the subtle body], but one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 can see no reason for this. There is no mention of "daiva varsha" anywhere[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in this, instead it seems to clearly indicate the physical year. Therefore, I[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 will explain the meaning of this sloka as would be naturally understood.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 4,000 solar years make one Satya Yuga. Its dawn, meaning the transitional[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 period of its beginning is 400 years, and its dusk, meaning the transitional[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 period of its end is 400 years. In this way, 4,800 years comprise one Satya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Yuga. The Treta Yuga and the others and their dawns and dusks are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 comprised of the number of years calculated by progressively subtracting[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one from the digit in the "thousands" and "hundreds" place, respectively, as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 delineated to the Satya Yuga and its transitional periods. This means that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Treta Yuga is 3,000 years in duration and its dawn is 300 years long, as well[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 as its dusk also being 300 years in length. Dvapara Yuga has 2,000 years, its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dawn being 200 years and its dusk at 200 years in length. Kali Yuga consists[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of 1,000 years and its dawn is 100 years and its dusk is 100 years. Thus,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 along with the transitional periods, one complete Treta Yuga is 3,600 years[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 long; the time of Dvapara Yuga is 2,400 years; and the time of Kali Yuga is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 1,200 years. The above-mentioned 12,000 years comprising the four yugas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 make one yuga for the gods, meaning the body of providence or the subtle[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body, meaning that one part, two parts, three parts and eventually all four[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 parts of Consciousness are gradually realized and the entire subtle body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dissolves mind, intellect etc. and resides in a blissful state. In this way, one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 thousand maha yugas in the time of the subtle body, meaning 12,000,000[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 years - by progressive elevation, even the causal body and maya are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dissolved and the Kaivalya-form, or only the Pure Brahman-Consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Form is existent. These 12,000,000 years of evolutionary time together are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 called one "day of Brahma." Having attained the state of Kaivalya and at the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 same time being devoid of Maya, the time of complete rest naturally occurs,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and as no action is performed to maintain the Self, gradually maya manifests,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and in 12,000,000 years again the material existence becomes predominant.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For this reason, these 12,000,000 years together are called one "night of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahma." This is what is known as one "aho ratri" of Brahma, or total[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (11 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dissolution and creation.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But what misfortune for the human being and what trickery by God![m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without the help of this knowledge, there is no possibility of realizing the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anandamaya covering, and this knowledge is itself the step to bliss [ananda].[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 So is it the way of things that the human within the jiva is worthless and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 capacity to operate intellectually is just some ironic mockery? That can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 never be, because the jiva acquires this human body endowed with this high[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge after traveling through eight million four hundred thousand[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yonis. It is only the misuse of this high knowledge with selfish desires that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 causes the jiva to be bound like a silkworm endlessly spinning its own[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 suffering. If one knows the proper use of this knowledge then one can go[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beyond this horrific vaishnavi chakra maya, meaning that one can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 successfully go beyond even the laws of one's nature. The progress[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mentioned above which would take 12,000 years -- that complete four-fold[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realization of Consciousness, the revelation of the anandamaya kosha and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kaivalya or Full God-ness,, pervading the Universe, can be attained in a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 short time through sadhana. This subject has been extensively explained in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the sloka 70 of the third chapter of this book.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now the significance of the mentioning of the word "yuga" twice shall be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 explained. One mentioning of "yuga" is to explain at what kind of time or in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 what kind of condition this Brahman-Consciousness is fully manifest. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reason for the other mentioning of "yuga" is to explain what kind of work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 leads to the emergence of that Consciousness. About the first - as to the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 matter of the condition in which Consciousness manifests - it has been[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 commented upon as thoroughly as possible. For the moment, the second[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 significance, meaning - what kind of method can the jiva use by which it can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 go beyond the vaishanavi chakra maya and thereby attain Consciousness-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manifesting Full Brahman-ness in a short time, is being explained below.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Besides the above-mentioned definition of "yuga," there is another meaning.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In that, "yuga" refers to "yugma," meaning - pair (yugmantu yugalam yugam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ityamarah). Now, one needs to see the meaning of "yugakriya" as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "yugmakriya" or paired kriya. This is what the Supreme Vishnu-seeing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vaishanavas have called the practice of "yugal [paired] mantra." "Mana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 trayate ity mantra" -- that by which the mind is liberated from maya is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "mantra." This subject has been written about in the introduction of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 book. This type of meaning for the word "mantra" is also written in Tantra.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmadi krimi paryantam praninam pranavartanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nishvasashvasarupena mantrohayam vartate priye[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 At the Divine Goddess' question, Lord Shiva says, "Beloved! The in-breath[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and out-breath, which together hold the life of all living things of Brahman,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 even that of a worm, are called 'mantra'."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (12 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now it can be clearly understood that this pairing of in-breath and out-breath[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is the "yugal [paired] mantra." No one can live in this world by only taking[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the in-breath or only expelling the out-breath. This Universe is manifesting[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bound to this yugal mantra. Its absence causes the world-Brahmanda to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 disappear. Therefore, the way to dissolve this world-Brahmanda in the mind,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and even further, to merge the mind and intellect into the Self, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman, is the awakening through the practice of this yugal mantra in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 form of the in-breath and the out-breath. This subject is written about in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 every book of the vaishnavas. It is because of the need to be aware of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mantra that the jiva again and again travels through birth after birth in one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body after another, leaving behind the conditions of ignorance and fulfilling[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the total force of the acquired samskaras (resultant force), and eventually[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 becomes aware of mantra. Awakening this mantra in a certain way, by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 practicing according to the instructions of Sadguru, and establishing it in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stillness, the entire Universe, including mind and intellect, dissolves and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pure, Complete Consciousness-state is realized. The saintly scholars of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogic scriptures call this practice the "kriya of pranayam." It is also written[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the Patanjal Yoga Sutras that -- the stilling of the movement of this yugal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mantra of in-breath and out-breath, meaning the stilling of restlessness, is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 callled "pranayam." As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shvasaprashvasayorgati vicchedah pranayamah -- Sadhanapada - no. 49[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, ending the restlessness of mantra and establishing pranayam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 causes all mechanisms of the body to be united with Consciousness, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 when that happens, the jiva can leave the functioning of the body to those[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 limbs and organs on their own, and the jiva as the Self can exist separate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from the body. This type of existence is what is called the "jivanmukta"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 state [liberated while having a body]. Teaching his disciple King Janaka[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 about the matter of this liberation, Maharshi Ashtavakra said the same thing.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na prithvi na jalam nagni na vayu dourna va bhavan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 esham shakshinamatmanam chidrupam viddhi muktaye[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yadi deham prithakakritya chiti vishramya tishthami[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adhunaiva sukhi shanta bandhomukta bhavishyashi -- Ashtavakra Samhita -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 1 pra/ 3/4[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "You are not made of earth, water, fire, air, ether - any such elemental[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 matter. If you desire liberation, then become aware of the Witness of all of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these elements, meaning the One in whose vision all work and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 appearance and disappearance of these elements are happening, that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness - Atman - the Self. If you can know the Self in this way and,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being unattached to these quintelemental physical phenomena, if you can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reside separately from the body in the Atman as Consciousness, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 resting self in the Self, then, filled with Tranquility and Supreme[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (13 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Contentment, you will instantly be liberated from the bindings of samsara."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, I will explain below about the practice of yugal mantra, meaning the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kriya [technology] of pranayam and how, by such, it is possible to go beyond[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the vaishnavi chakra maya, meaning -- how to do the work that will in a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 short time actualize the four-fold, complete awareness of Consciousness that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is realized in the normal course in the span of 12,000 years, meaning also --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 how to realize the Kaivalya, or Consciousness-alone, state which in the usual[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 course of time takes 12,000,000 years.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of the special quality of power in 12 places of the orbit around the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sun, those places and the stars corresponding to it have been designated as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the 12 signs of the zodiac by astrological scholars, and they ascribed the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 qualities of certain earthly creatures and other things to those signs and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 called them the sign of the ram [Aries], the sign of the bull [Taurus] etc. In[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that cycle of the zodiac, the moon, beginning on the first day of the bright[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fortnight, travels through six signs of the zodiac until the full moon, when[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the moon is at its furthest point away from the sun. And again, beginning on[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the first day of the dark fortnight, it goes through the other six signs until the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 new moon, when the moon is at its closest point near the sun. This moving[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 away to the furthest point and moving back to the closest point to the sun,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 having gone through all 12 signs of the zodiac, is called one lunar month. In[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this way, the movement of 12 signs of the zodiac with the sun, beginning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with one and ending back at that same one, constitutes one solar year. In one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 solar year, some of the 12th lunar month is left over, because of which, in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 three years, an extra lunar month is born. The ephemeris scholars call this the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intercalary month. Thus, 37 lunar months comprise three solar years. It is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 written in astrological treatises that if the sun is beneficent at the time of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one's birth, meaning if the human being who is born into the body is carrying[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the good parts of the solar materials, then that being will be of great[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nobleness and wisdom. If the sun is maleficent during the time of one's birth,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning if the human being who is born into the body is carrying the bad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 parts of the solar materials, then that being will be tremendously egotistical[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and devoid of responsible behavior. In this way, observing the relationship of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the good parts of solar materials to knowledge, or consciousness, and seeing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that completely the same exact connection and results are true pertaining to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogakriya and the emerging sun within the body by it as to the realization of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge, or Consciousness, along with much other evidence, the saintly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogic scholars have stated that the sun arising by Kriya within the miniature[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe of the body is a part of the sun in the cosmos and they have called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it the human consciousness. In the same way, if the moon is beneficent at the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time of one's birth, meaning if the human being born into the body is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 carrying the good parts of the lunar materials, then that being has a calm and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 steady nature, and he or she is of a happy mind, pleasant to people, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 passes life always in the company of good persons. If the moon is maleficent[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 at the time of one's birth, then that person is of a restless nature and is always[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unsatisfied, a nuisance to people, and he or she passes life in the company of[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (14 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bad persons. Thus, observing the relationship of the good parts of the lunar[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 materials to the state of mind and its exact representation in the relationship[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the moon in the body, emerging from yogakriya, to the state of mind -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning the restlessness of the moon is the restlessness of the mind, and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stillness of the moon is the stillness of the mind and much other evidence -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the saintly yogic scholars have stated that this moon in the miniature[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda of this body revealed through yogakriya is a part of the external[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 moon of the cosmos and they have called this the human mind. Observing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the sushumna as the path of consciousness, and six special locations of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 power within the sushumna manifesting the radiance of consciousness all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 around those spots as lotus-like petals - from which consciousness spreads[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and presides as different gods in the sixty thousand nadis fulfilling every task[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the body - the saintly yogic scholars have termed the likenesses of those[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 special places in the sushumna as four-petaled, six-petaled, ten-petaled,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 twelve-petaled, sixteen-petaled and two-petaled lotuses; and they have[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 understood that the sushumna is the path of the orbit of the jiva-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness sun and the lotuses are the points of the zodiac.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Supreme Yogi Lord Shiva and other great beings have taught that,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 according to Sadguru's instructions, uniting the moon-like sattvic mind to the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 totality of rajoguna manifesting in the prana vayu [prana airs] and working[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this united form within the sushumna, traveling the six lotuses from the two-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 petaled to the Muladhar, the furthest point from the Sun - the jiva-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness revealed in the Sahasrara - and again traveling through the six[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 lotuses from the Muladhar to the two-petaled lotus - the nearest point to the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sun revealed as Consciousness - one month's work [evolution] is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 accomplished. This means that within this short time all blood and flesh in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body is purified of material coagulation; thus, related addictions are also[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purified and the body begins to be prepared for the Holy Consciousness-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 substance. In this way, shooting the prana united with mind to the Muladhar[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and again drawing it from there is called one "kriya of pranayam" in yogic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scriptures. By this, samskaras are removed from consciousness and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happiness is maintained. In the Patanjal Yoga Sutras it is also written that joy[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 at the time of pleasure for the jiva, compassion at the time of sorrow,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 satisfaction at doing good work and rejection of wrong work bring[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cheerfulness of mind. But that is external and remains only for a while,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because the mind, within a short time, being a slave to the previous[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samskaras, becomes unhappy again. Therefore, in order to have happiness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 for a long time, one should cheer up one's inner being by the samskara-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purifying Kriya. By the Kriya of throwing, meaning shooting of the prana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vayu downward and again drawing it, or yugal mantra, the samskaras are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 removed and this happiness remains for a long time. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 maitrakarunamuditopekshanam sukhaduhkha punyapunyavishayanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhavanashchittaprasadanam - no. 33[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pracchardanavidharanyabhyam va pranasya - no. 34 -- Samadhipada[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (15 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Practicing yugal mantra, or the kriya of pranayam at one sitting, including its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dawn and dusk, 12 times, meaning 14 times, accomplishes the work of one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 solar year. This means that the material coagulation concerning arteries,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 veins and nerves, and thereby also the material coagulation of the body of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 providence or the subtle body and its ten senses and five pranas are cleared.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, their addictions are also purified and the body is prepared to receive[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Holy Consciousness-substance. This is called "jada shuddhi." With its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dawn and dusk, doing this Kriya 37 times, meaning 39 times [at one sitting][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 accomplishes the work of three solar years, meaning the work of one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "khanda yuga." Thus, the material coagulation in sperm, marrow, all physical[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 elements and thereby the material coagulation in mind and intellect are also[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purified, and the body is further prepared for the realization of the Holy[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-substance. This is called "khanda shuddhi" or "nadi shuddhi."[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And doing this Kriya, with its dawn and dusk, 148 times, meaning 150 times,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 accomplishes the work of 12 solar years. This means that the material[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 coagulation of even the consciousness-nature, or the causal body, is cleared.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, purified of all addictions, the body begins to realize the longed-for,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 highest Holy Consciousness-substance. This is referred to as "bhuta shuddhi"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in all Tantric scriptures. By this, the work of the twenty-four elements are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fulfilled in a short time and it becomes possible to reside in bliss even while[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in this elemental body. Performing bhuta shuddhi just once this way brings[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 complete happiness to the mind and that happiness remains for a long time.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If there are no changes in the normal course, then, within a short time, no[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kind of unhappiness can come to the mind.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It has been discovered in the scientific world that if electrical waves travel[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 around all sides of an object, then that object becomes imbued with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 qualities of attraction and repulsion and is transformed into the form of a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 magnet, and that the electrical waves do not enter the object; instead, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 remain floating above it. The work of the telegraph is carried out by this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 method. One can observe by an electrometer that when an electrical[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 conductor is heated from one side, from the other side, an electrical flow[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 occurs and moves in the direction of the heated side. The earth is a massive[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 electrical conductor. Whichever side the sun is on is heated. Therefore, from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the other side of the earth an electrical flow moves towards the heated side.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 And because the earth is rotating towards the east, that heated section is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 continuously going west. Therefore that electrical flow is also encircling the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 earth in a westward direction. In this way, because electricity is perpetually[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 spinning around the globular earth, the earth is imbued with the qualities of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attraction and repulsion and is existing as a giant, highly powerful magnet.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For this reason, the magnetic needle of a compass is always attracted towards[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the north and south.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This electrical flow around the earth does not always travel with the same[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 force. Its intensity decreases and increases. At midday, when the sun is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 directly above the head and at midnight, when the sun is directly below -- at[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these times, because of the heated areas of the earth being directly above and[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (16 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 directly below, the enjoined electrical fflow cannot have much intensity in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the direction of east or west; but, because the earth is perpetually turning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eastward and thereby the heated section is always moving westward, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 electrical flow around the earth also maintains motion towards the west. At[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prangnatakal, meaning the time from midnight until midday, when the earth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is being heated on the easterly side, there is another flow of electricity in that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 direction, and thus the above-mentioned perpetual flow of electricity[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 connected with the rotation of the earth towards the west is diminished, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it continues its westward flow with very low intensity. And at the time of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pashchannatakal, meaning the time from midday until midnight, the earth is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 heated in the westerly side and there is an electrical flow in that direction,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 causing the above-mentioned perpetual electrical flow connected with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rotation of the earth to move westward with double the intensity.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, because of an electrical flow perpetually moving westward around the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 earth and thereby causing the earth to behave like a magnet, the great sages[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of India forbid lying down with the head pointed towards the north or the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 west. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prakshiro bhavati vidya valamayushcha dakshine[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pashchime pravala chinta hani mrityumathottare[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Lying down with the head towards the east brings about knowledge and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 wisdom; lying with the head to the south increases strength; lying with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 head towards the west causes turbulence in thought; and lying with the head[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 towards the north brings death closer. The reason for this is that lying with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the head towards the west causes the perpetually westward moving electrical[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 flow to draw all of the impurities of the body to the head, which is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 primary place of consciousness, and thereby all of these together cause the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness to become impure by which it falls into a stupor of ignorance[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or unawareness. Because of that, meaningless imaginary things arise in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 head and the jiva becomes immersed in turbulent thoughts. But lying with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the head pointing east causes the opposite action to happen and the primary[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 place of consciousness - the head - is cleaned of impurities, and wisdom or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge is revealed. Similarly, because the section north of the equator is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 predominant in magnetic attraction flowing towards the north, lying with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 head towards the north causes all of the airs to rise to the head depleting one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of strength, and thereby, the body gradually becomes weak and problems[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 arise within it, and death comes ever closer. But lying with the head towards[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the south causes the opposite action to take place, meaning the airs move[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 downward which increases one's strength, making the body robust and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 giving it long life.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, the decrease and increase of intensity of the electrical flow[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 around the earth during the prangnatakal and pashchannatakal brings about[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 significant change in the enjoined subtle world. And the physical world is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 also similarly changed significantly according to the changes in the degree of[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (17 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 heat during the day and night. Thus, from 66/30 north of the equator to 66/36[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 south, covering 133 parts in this middle section of the earth, in a span of 24[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hours, meaning one aho ratri, the physical part and the subtle part of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 everything, both go through a change twice - the total being four times. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 plane of the gods, meaning the northern part of the world from 23/30 in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 north and the plane of the monsters, meaning the southern 23/30 have six[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 months of day and six months of night; the condition of the physical things[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 presiding there do not go through any change within 24 hours; only the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 subtle bodies of those things go through a change only twice because of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 decrease and increase of the intensity of the electrical flow during the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prangnatakal and the pashchannatakal; and because there is no increase or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 decrease in the electrical flow or in the heat inside the earth, no change takes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 place in any matter present there.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, the best and most pure place to practice this yogakriya is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asana within a cave. The next best place for asana is in the plane of the gods[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the northern part. The southern part is filled with water, so the point is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 moot. And there are very few places that are pure for asana in the middle[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 section on the earth. For this reason, even a little of the kriya practiced in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 other places has to be done by those residing in the middle section on the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 earth with great care and much effort in regards to the asana -- in a place not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 too hot, not too cold, not draughty, on a deerskin upon which there should be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 a cloth with a material that iis a non-conductor etc. Therefore, the particulars[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Kriya for the residents of the middle section on the earth, where there are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not many pure places for asana, are being explained in a condensed manner.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If the residents of earth's middle section do bhuta shuddhi once at dawn, then[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they do not need to do any more purifying Kriya during the prangnatakal,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning the time from when the sun is low in the east until midday, because[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 there is no change in natural states at this time. Therefore, unless one makes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 oneself impure, no impurities will be born on their own. Because of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 above-mentioned reason, if one does bhuta shuddhi at midday, then there is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 no need to do any purifying Kriya until dusk. In this way, if one does bhuta[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shuddhi once at dusk, then there is no need to do any purifying Kriya until[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 midnight, meaning the time when the sun is low in the west. And if one does[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhuta shuddhi once at midnight, then there is no need to do any type of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purifying Kriya until dawn. Unless one makes oneself impure, there is no[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 possibility of any kind of impurity arising on its own at this time. Thus, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogis of the earth's middle section have to do bhuta shuddhi four times a day.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But for householders, the prescript is for Kriya at dawn, midday and dusk[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 only. Kriya at midnight is not as imperative. The reason for this is that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 householders have to labor at many different kinds of work during the day[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and need more rest at night. Otherwise, it is possible that the body will[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become weak, giving rise to disease and making the mind depressed. And if[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 at the time of complete rest one can have sound sleep, then no natural change[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 can touch their minds. But, if there is not that much labor, or if the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness is at peace causing very little depletion from the body, and[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (18 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 thus if it is not necessary to get as much rest, or if one for some reason is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 remains awake at night, then Kriya at midnight is also very necessary. Thus,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 if the householder life requires a good amount of labor and rest, one should[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perform bhuta shuddhi Kriya at the three transitional periods of dawn,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 midday and dusk every day. In this way, doing Kriya at the three transitional[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 periods regularly every day, in a little more than a lunar month - in 34 days -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and even if Kriya is not done one or two times because of important[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 occasions or some events in householder life then in 36 days, one completes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 100 bhuta shuddhi Kriyas. It has already been shown that the amount of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evolution in the realization of Consciousness that would take 12 physical[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 years can be accomplished by one bhuta shuddhi Kriya. Therefore,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 completing 100 [bhuta shuddhi] Kriyas in 36 days accomplishes the work of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one Kali Yuga's length of 1,200 years. Then the Dvapara yugavastha is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attained and one can perceive the existence of the subtle body, the second[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aspect of Consciousness. In this way, the work of four yugas of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-realization that would normally take 12,000 years are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 accomplished by sadhakas in 360 days or one solar year, by which all four[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aspects of the beyond-creation Brahman-Consciousness is fully realized.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Later, according to Sadguru's instructions, by Omkar Kriya etc. one can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realize the different luminous levels of Consciousness in 3 years or 39 lunar[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 months, and thereafter accomplish the work of 12,000,000 years or one kalpa[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in 12 years, attaining Kaivalya, or seeing the Self as pervading all things of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Cosmos, and thus realizing Brahman. The saints have said that if[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhakas do not go astray in a wrong direction, even progressing in Kriya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 slowly can bring the attainment of Kaivalya or Brahman in 36 years, or 39[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 years if some occasions or events of householder life hinder progress. But[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 diligent sadhakas can also complete this work and attain Kaivalya or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman at a high speed of even less than 12 years.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Once sadhakas attain this all-pervading, all-powerful, all-knowing state, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 have nothing in the Cosmos that they lack or that they want. If in this state[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one remains without doing Kriya, then ignorance and delusion gradually[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 emerge again and cover up the revelation of Consciousness. This has been[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stated in the 24th sloka of the third chapter of this Srimad Bhagavad Gita.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, even after the attainment of this Kaivalyavastha or Brahman, in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 order to preserve oneself, one must perform Kriya regularly.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, if one can understand that one meaning of the word "yuga" is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 condition of Satya, Treta etc., and that the other definition of the word is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 way of attaining those conditions via yugal mantra, and if one can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 understand that it is for the reason of instructing in the two meanings that this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 word "yuga" is mentioned twice in this sloka, then it does not take long to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 understand the actual meaning of this sloka. Then the meaning becomes thus:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 destroying the evil tendencies in sadhakas, in order to establish dharma,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning the revelation of Consciousness, by the practice of yugal mantra,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning pranayam, by which, upon gradual attainment of the states of Satya,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Treta etc., the Brahman-Consciousness fully reveals Itself. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (19 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   janma karma cha me divyamevam yo vetti tatvatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   tyaktvadeham punarjanma naiti mameti soharjuna -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Those who about My creation and work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Understand, are saved by that knowing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Dying they are not reborn[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   They attain Me, listen prince of Kunti -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The manifestation of this visible world from that Infinite Consciousness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   meaning the creation element mentioned in the seventh sloka of this chapter,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   and the method to realize this Consciousness, meaning the way to go beyond[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   this vaishnavi chakra maya and attain Brahman as stated in the eighth sloka[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   of this chapter -- the one who has become aware of all of this perfectly by his[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   own realization does not have to take another body upon discarrding the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   present one. He can maintain the body and be beyond all desire. Thus he is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   filled with Pure Consciousness and merges himself in this all-pervading[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Infinite Consciousness and attains Brahman. -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   veetaragabhayakrodha manmaya mamupashritah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   bahavo jnanatapasa puta madbhavamagatah -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Knowing thus My creation and work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Renouncing affinity, fear and anger[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Many surrender their minds in Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In my refuge they remain always[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In the practice of Knowledge given by Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   They have become purified and have merged into Me -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Being a householder itself means that there will be great affinity towards[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   sound, touch, form, taste, smell and such sense-oriented things, and because[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   there is a lack of enjoyment of those things in the path of Knowledge, a great[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   deal of anger towards that, and in order to be pacified, people of the world[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   remain fearfully bound to the enjoyment of sense-objects. But sadhakas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   renounce the above-mentioned affinities, fear and anger, and remain one-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   pointedly in the Kutastha, discerning all these worldly enjoyments to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   trivial; and by attaining Knowledge by the Consciousness-revealing Kriya,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   filled with Full-Consciousness, they are merged in Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Consciousness. -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (20 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ye yatha mam prapadyante tam stathaiva bhajamyaham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mama vartmanuvartante manushyah partha sarvashah -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As one meditates upon Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 So I give accordingly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus the perspectives of people are many, Partha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But all are worshipping Me -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In accordance with the reverence and devotion with which one performs[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kriya will be the quality of the revelation of Consciousness. The great[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sadguru-initiated sadhaka Tulsidas' couplets also contain this statement. As[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [Hindi][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ram jharokhe bayeth kar savko majura ley[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jaysa jako chakri taysa tako dey[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [Lord Ram sits at the window receiving all workers[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As one's work is, so is the remuneration is given][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The all-pervading Consciousness resides within everyone as the Witness and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bestows realization according to the work done.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Surrendering life and mind to the Kutasthachaitanya and keeping in mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this understanding of Atman-Consciousness, the sadhakas take refuge in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-revealing Kriya yoga. -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kangkshyantah karmanam siddhim yajanta iha devatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kshipram hi manushe loke siddhirbhavati karmaja -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Praying for fruits of desire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The human beings worship the gods[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus the fruits of their work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Are acquired quickly, listen mighty one -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pleasure is experienced from sense enjoyments immediately, but very[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 quickly after that, the pleasure is beset by endless suffering. Ordinary[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 persons, being short-sighted and not understanding that, remain engaged in[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (21 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the service of the senses in the lust for those easily acquired, momentary[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pleasures. -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chaturvarnyam maya srishtam gunakarmavibhagashah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasya kartaramapi mam vidhyakartaramavyayam -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With sattva, raja and tama gunas, and karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I created the four varnas*[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 While being the Creator, I am not the Creator[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Know this -- I have no attachment -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [*Translator‚Äôs note: ‚Äúvarnas‚Äù in this case refers to what is usually understood[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 as class or caste divisions in Hindu society][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 According to the prarabdha acquired because of seeking different kinds of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happiness, human beings become imbued with sattva, raja etc. and many[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 qualities and are thereby separated into the four varnas [forms] of "brahmin,"[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "kshatriya," "vaishya," and "sudra." As in - human beings dominated by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sattva guna and living in the state of Eternal Consciousness are called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "brahmin"; sattvic-rajoguna-predominant human beings who are engaged in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 battle of performing the evil-tendency-destroying, Consciousness-revealing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kriya are called "kshatriya"; tamasic-rajoguna-predominant human beings,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who are concerned with the upliftment of the bodily field and thus are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 involved in scriptural study and following rituals, are called "vaishya"; and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tamoguna-predominant human beings, the ignorant ones always in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 service of the senses, are called "sudras." Although it is because of the quest[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Consciousness-ecstasy that such conditions occur, Consciousness does not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 preside more or less over any such states. Consciousness is Eternal-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Substance and is present the same in every place and condition. And neither[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is the Supreme Consciousness the Creator of these small sovereignties -- it is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 only because of the fluctuations of the external dressing that make it seem as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 if the Consciousness is manifesting moore or less and thus giving emergence[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to the many different varnas. Just as the phantasmagoric shadow play[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [cinema] from the increase and decrease of light seems to cause many kinds[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of events, the light or lamp is not involved in any of the action and cannot be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 called as their creator - the many different, changing conditions of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 covering in front of the light is making the events seem to happen - in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 same way, although these varnas have come about because of the gradation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Consciousness-realization, that Eternal Consciousness is not their Creator.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This is happening because of the fluctuations in the covering over[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness in the form of ignorance and unawareness. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (22 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na mam karmani limpanti na me karmaphale spriha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ity mam yohabhijanati karmabhirna sa badhyate -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who knows me in this way, Dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That one is never bound by the fruits of karma -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of no desire or attachment arising in Atman-Consciousness, one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cannot be bound by any karma in that state. The one who can perform all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 work while being aware of Atman, meaning knowing oneself to be Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness, can see that all work is being done by vaishnavi maya chakra[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or natural law; and knowing the Self to be uninvolved from all action[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [karma], he desirelessly performs Atman-Kriya. He does not again have to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 be reborn because of the bindings of karma. -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evam jnatva kritam karma purvairapi mumukshubhi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kuru karmaiva tasmatvam purvaih purvataram kritam -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Do karma having discarded the ego[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Not doing so is the cause of imprisonment to karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing this in the past desiring liberation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Is how the sages were in the sadhana of karma -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One can attain liberation by doing Kriya while being ego-less, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowing oneself as Consciousness and being uninvolved in all karma.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Having known this, sages such as Janaka who desired liberation performed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmayoga in that way and acquired the fruit desired-for. Therefore, one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 should perform karmayoga in the ego-less manner that sages such as Janaka[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 have done, because by that, the jiva can be easily liberated from the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sufferings of samsara and attain Kaivalyapada. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kim karma kimakarmeti kavayohpyatra mohitah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatte karma prakshami yajnatva mokshsehshubhat -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Wanting to know the distinction between karma and akarma [inaction][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Many analysts have become confused by this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 What that is I will tell you, listen Falguni[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Which will free you from samsara -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (23 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Even great pundits become confused trying to discriminate between which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karma is dutiful and which is not dutiful, and are unable to so discern.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, one should remain absorbed in the Kutastha with a still mind and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become aware of the distinction between these dutiful and non-dutiful[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 actions. Understanding the secret matter of this and practicing regularly, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva can be liberated from the bindings of this worldly life. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmanohyapi boddhavyam boddhavyancha vikarmanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 akarmanashcha boddhavyam gahana karmano gatih -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One should know the essence of karma according to establishment[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Should know what karma is not of that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing akarma in that way[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The reason karma moves the same -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Being free of doubt and focused in the Kutastha in this way, when one wants[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to know about karma and akarma, one becomes aware of: the karma to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perform which is according to the rules of the sadhana of liberation and what[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 its form is; the action that is forbidden; and what is the renunciation of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karma. One should be particularly aware of the secret of this. One should not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 base one's discernment on popular theories prevalent, because the hidden[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 truths of karma according to established rules, forbidden karma and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renunciation of karma are quite unknown. Not to speak of ordinary people,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 even great pundits are unable to understand these matters. This has been[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stated in the previous sloka. -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmanyakarmayah pashyedakarmani cha karma yah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sa buddhiman manushyeshu sa yuktah kritsnakarmakrit - 18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The ignorant's renunciation of karma is the cause of enchainment[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore take up karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing this matter, the one who becomes steadfast[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Worshipping the Lord is taken up -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who, upon experiencing himself as separate from the quintelemental[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body and seeing that he is uninvolved in the work being done by the body[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (24 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and the senses, observes himself to be a non-doer who is satisfied and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 detached to the action performed by the body and the senses, and who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 understands this non-doing and satisfied detachment as one's true state of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 work in which he performs Kriya, he is the highest among human beings[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who truly understands the workings of things. He can live always united with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness - meaning being in samadhi while awake - while performing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all action and remaining uninvolved from all karma. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yasya sarve samarambhah kam samkalpa varjitah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanagnidagdha karmanam tamahuh panditam budhah -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one whose actions are not attached to results[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dutiful work free from ambition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the fire of Knowledge the one who burns karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I save him and he is known as a sage -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who performs Atman-Kriya desirelessly and free of ambition has all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of his karma burned in the fire of Knowledge begat of Kriya, meaning that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the jiva as a non-doer does not have to be bound to reaping the fruits of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karma. The knowers of Brahman refer to these types of Kriyavans as all-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowing sages. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tyaktva karmaphalasangam nityatripto nirashrayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmanyabhipravrittohpi naiva kinchit karoti sah -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Renouncing attachment to karma and the fruits of karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the bliss of Knowledge are the content, who need no shelter[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Even if it happens as he performs that karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 His karma remains always the same -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who, having renounced karma and its fruits, remains in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 contentment of Eternal Bliss and does not take refuge in any matter of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body or the senses - meaning that he is uninvolved in body-oriented subjects,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 even though his body or senses are engaged fully in all kinds of karma - does[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not perform action, meaning that because he is separate from all of those[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bodily senses, he resides in detachment and satisfaction. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nirashiryatachittatma tyaktasarvaparigrahah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (25 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shariram kevalam karma kurvannapnotikilvisham -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Renouncing all desire and keeping the mind for the function of body only[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Discarding affinity for all things[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Working to only keep the body maintained[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Doing this one does not incur karmic fruits -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one whose mind and spirit are disciplined and desireless and, by which,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 has renounced all cravings, doing only the necessary karma for the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 maintenance of the body, there is no possibility of harm coming to him,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because by non-doing, there is no relationship to the future fruits of those[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 actions, and thus he is not bound to the fulfillment of results. -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yadricchalabhasantushto dvandvatita vimatsarah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samah siddhavasiddhou cha kritvapi na nibadhyate -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who is satisfied with whatever he gets[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Withstands cold and heat and is no one's enemy[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Success and failure are the same to him[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He is not bound and performs karma -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who is completely satisfied with whatever comes to him easily, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one who is not distressed by cold, heat, sorrow etc., the one who has no[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enmity towards anyone, the one who is neither elated by success nor[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 despondent in failure and remains the same always, he is not bound to the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fruits of any karma, because even though he is engaged in every kind of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 worldly action, he is in a state of non-doing and resultlessness. -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gatasangasya muktasya jnanavasthita chetasah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajnayacharatah karma samagram praviliyate -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without lust, free of affection[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one whose mind is in Knowledge alone[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Performing karma as such is refuge for people[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one whose karma is the same for everyone -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (26 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Establishing the mind in Knowledge and performing Atman-Kriya in a state[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of a non-doing, and being free of dutifulness, non-dutifulness, dharma and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 non-dharma, all prarabdha karma is gradually eroded away and completely[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dissolved. -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmarpanam brahmahavi brahmagnou brahmanahutam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmaiva tena gantavyam brahmakarma samadhina -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman is the oblation, Brahman is the fire, Brahman is the clarified butter[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman is the one for whom the priest worships[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who knows that Brahman is in all action[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He will attain Para Brahman -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Having observed the world-Brahmanda as filled with Infinite Consciousness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning filled with Brahman, the all-perceiving sages discerned that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 elements of a yajna [fire sacrifice worship] - the clarified butter, the fire, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 performer of the fire incantations, the offering and the act - are all Brahman.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, the ones who are performing action in the state of samadhi in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman have no desire for any kind of result, and experiencing Brahman in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 everything, by this itself they remain merged in the Supreme Substance of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman. -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 daivamevapare yajnam yoginah paryupasate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmagnavapare yajnam yajnaivopajuhvati -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The yajna that is worship to the gods[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who act do that practice[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing Brahman the same as the fire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The wise ones sacrifice the fire itself -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Hatha yogis, capturing the gods who preside in the senses, acquire the power[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 over all senses by the various yogic methods. Jnana yogis, by yogakriya,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 surrender all to the Kutasthachaitanya revealed in yonimudra, and become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 merged in samadhi. -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shrotradinindriyanyanye samyamagnishu juhvati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shabdadin vishayananya indriyagnishu juhvati -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (27 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All senses such as hearing in the fire of discipline[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The celibate monks subjugate them by the power of Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The united householder offers the senses[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Control in all things by Knowledge -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmacharis [celibate monks], by methods of withdrawal such as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pratyahara, bring all the senses under control and live unaffected by the work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the senses. Householders fulfill all matters present in a state of being free[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of like and dislike and without attachment to anything, and thereby they wear[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 away prarabdha.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Mentioning "grihashrami[s]" [resident[s] of the ashram of the home][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 immediately brings the worldly life to mind, but there are many differences[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 between worldly life and grihashram[s] [home as ashram[s]]. Through[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evolution and the gradual revelation of prana and mind, the jiva progresses[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 into plants, animals, birds and many such forms. Then, when the power of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intellect is realized, it transforms into the form of a human being. Until this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [human] state finds refuge, up to that time it takes birth again and again due[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to the intellect-generated prarabdha of many kinds causing the need to fulfill[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desires, and according to the fluctuations of mind in oneself, the jiva is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bound to the manifestations of those tendencies as laughter, tears, running[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 around etc. by which it is ever anxiously engrossed in passing life in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 way, eventually ending in the jaws of time. Some think of themselves as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 worthless and are engaged in satisfying others such as wife, children etc.,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 whom they believe to have power over them. Some think themselves to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the ones with power and become greatly involved in showing themselves off.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Some see themselves as kings and rulers and spend time in war and strife.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Some think of themselves as clever ministers of government and pass their[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 lives in mental pursuits in order to rule the world-Brahmanda. But the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 strange thing is that throughout time, those who wear the outfits of lordship[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 never take a look at themselves. That I am floating in the current of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prarabdha, that I have no place to stand, that if this body is destroyed right[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 now, who knows what will happen to this costume and power and who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knows where prarabdha will take one and throw one into who knows what[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kind of great convolution - not even once do they look at all these things.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, because of this kind of lack of self-examination causing one to exist in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 a state of being without a spiritual home and thereby being always engaged[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in work towards others, the scriptural scholars have called this condition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "nirashraya" [without refuge].[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Once observation falls upon oneself, the jivas look to take refuge in order to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 be rescued from this ocean of prarabdha. These shelters - ashrams - are of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 four types: brahmacharyashram, grihasthashram, banaprasthashram and[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (28 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sannyasashram. In times past, care would be taken to start the son of a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 householder in the practice of brahmacharya once the age of seven had[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 passed. If the child was well-mannered, calm, good at studies, and able to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 leave his mother and father to live in an acharyashram, then he would be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enrolled in an acharyashram. A sacred thread was given to the children at the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time of leaving for the acharayashram, signifying their purity. This sacred-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 thread ceremony is called "upanayan." Living in an ashram such as this,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 children would study the Brahman-Knowledge-illuminating Vedas etc.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 according to the instructions of the acharya, and would spend the days in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 discipline of brahmacharya with its various edicts and formalities. Not to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 speak of the company of women or of blindly ignorant sudras, there was no[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chance of even seeing them. This is called "brahmacharyashram." The eighth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 year was understood to be the best time for a child to attain "brahminness."[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Even the ages of up to nine or ten years were considered suitable for children[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to receive the education of brahmins. But if the tenth year had passed and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 upanayan was performed on the eleventh year, the acharyas would not teach[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that child the Vedas and such scriptures; instead, the education appropriate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 for kshatriyas - the political, governmental and military education - was[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 given for the sustenance of livelihood. If the eleventh year had passed and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 upanayan was performed on the twelfth year, then instead of teaching the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 child the subtle and intricate intellectual matters of governmental work, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 education appropriate for vaishyas - commerce and trade - was given for the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sustenance of livelihood. But if the child had not been enrolled in an[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 acharyashram within the twelfth year, then the maturation of sperm would[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cause the senses to become restless and the child would become devoid of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 patience, and therefore it would not be possible for the to acquire knowledge.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This is called "the death of Savitri," and because of this, one would not be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 accepted in an acharyashram once the twelfth year had passed. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 garbhadharnadashtame janmato va, moujibandhah sashyate brahmananam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajanyanamnuynamekadashehabde vaishyanantu dvadashehabde vadanti[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The eighth year from the day of birth is the suitable time for upanayan for[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmins, meaning the suitable time for the child to have the upanayan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ceremony in order to acquire brahminness - the eleventh year for kshatriyas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and the twelfth year for vaishyas.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, according to individual capacity - some in three years, some in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 twelve - children would gain knowledge from the acharya and become fit to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 live in a disciplined, steadfast and desireless way in the temptation-filled[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 society, and understanding that by living with and taking care of mother,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 father and relations, and leading the happy, married life of a householder, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva could wear away prarabdha and attain peace very easily, they would[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 once again return home. This is called "samavartan." Thus, having acquired[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 special knowledge as to one's personal vocation, the youth would take up the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 making of a livelihood and the work of a householder while practicing the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 guru-instructed methods such as "sandhya vandana." Those who wear away[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (29 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 their prarabdha in this way by fulfilling the matters of desire while being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 engaged in the work of the householder are called "grihasthashrami[s]."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, the twice-born would leave the brahmacharyashram, marry at the age[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of twenty-four and have a child by the age of twenty-five. The child would[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 be raised and educated, and would go through the upanayan ceremony. And[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 when the child was ready after having been trained in a brahmacharyashram,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the man would oversee his son's marriage in his son's twenty-fourth year and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 would stay one more year to see the birth of his grandson, after which, at[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 around the man's fiftieth year, he would renounce the household and leave to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 live in the forest. This is called "banaprastha ashram." In this way of life,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 people would often leave the jungle in search of a Sadguru and travel from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pilgrimage to pilgrimage. Then, if they were able to obtain the grace of some[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 saint, they would renounce all restlessness and try to establish themselves in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman-Consciousness. This is what is called "sannyasashram." People in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ashram completely renounce the body, senses, prana-substances and all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fluctuations of consciousness, and thus attaining Supreme Tranquility, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 merge with the Brahman-Substance.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who would not have had the upanayan service done for them would be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 work as ignorant sudras in the service of the three varnas of brahmins,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kshatriyas and vaishyas. Then, if a son or daughter of the family or such[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 someone would be able to take over the householder duties, they would also[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 for the sake of their own liberation seek out the refuge of some saint and go[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 on pilgrimages; and when the Unseen would be pleased and they would[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 receive the grace of some saint, by performing many kinds of yogakriyas,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they would control their minds, and upon achieving that, they would merge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with that Supreme Brahman-Substance.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The "grihasthashram" that was mentioned previously is not the worldly life.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This ashram is the second type of the four types of ashrams. It is in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 refuge of this that jivas are able to live in great happiness and complete the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fulfillment of the terrible prarabdha and thus ascend to Supreme Tranquility.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This is the highly excellent path to take for the elimination of prarabdha. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvanindriyakarmani pranakarmani chapare[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atmasamyama yogagnou juhvatijnanadipite -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Intellect is the dharma by which the listeners listen[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The organs of action are of the speakers' speech[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Prana is the matter of the airs flowing within[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The serpent, the external airs and expulsion[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Burn in the fire of Knowledge and self-discipline[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The meditating yogis sacrifice all of this -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (30 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By the self-discipline of dharana, dhyana and samadhi, through which one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 lights the fire of discriminating knowledge, and being immersed in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experience of the object of meditation - the Supreme Brahman-Substance,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the devoted meditators dissolve sight, sound etc. of the organs of perception,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 speech etc. of the organs of action, and even the work of inhalation and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 exhalation of pranic functions, and thus eradicate all restlessness of the body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and senses. -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dravyayajnastaposhajna yogayajnastathapare[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 svaddhyayajnanayajnashcha yatayah samshritavratah -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Some give things in yajna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Some burn their austere practices[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Yogis do the yajna of kevala samadhi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmins offer recitation of Vedas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In that some do the yajna of knowledge arising[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 These difficult things have the name of yajna -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With steadfast determination and great care, the sadhakas free their bodies of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ailments through medicinal things, and following edicts and difficult[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 practice, stabilizing themselves in yogakriya by which all fluctuations of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness are stopped, and studying the scriptures of liberation, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realize Knowledge. -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   apane juhvati pranam pranohpanam tathapare[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   pranapanagati ruddhah pranayama parayanah -29-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   apare niyataharah pranan praneshu juhvati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   sarvehpyete yajnavido yajnakshayita kalmashah -30-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   yajnashishtamritabhujo yanti brahma sanatanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   nayam lokohstyayajnasya kutohnyahh kurusattam -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Offering apana into the prana at the time of purak[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   At the time of rechak offering prana into apana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In kumbhak the movement of prana and apana stop[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Some do this yajna of pranayam -29-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Eating little and weakening the senses[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Some do sacrifice in prana like this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The wisdom of yajna is because of yajna[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (31 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Destroying all sins and attaining Vishnu -30-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Finishing yajna they drink immortal ambrosia[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Easily they realize the Universal Para Brahman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This plane is not for the one who does not do yajna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Listen great one, what more can I say to people -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By rechak Kriya, sadhakas take the pranavayu residing above in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sushumna and offer it as oblation into the apanavayu residing at the bottom[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the spine, and again by purak Kriya they lift the apanavayu from below[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and merge it into the pranavayu above. This has been mentioned in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogashastras as "kevali pranayam." By this, the movement of prana and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 apana stops naturally and on its own, stilling the mind and all prana,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manifesting eternal happiness and illuminating the lamp of Knowledge.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When the mind and prana are still in this way, the inhalation and exhalation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the physical airs, speech, body, sight - all of these things - also become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 still. One can ascertain the level of consciousness-absorption by these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 physical signs. This matter is written about in the yogic scriptures. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatha yatha sadabhyasanmanasah sthirata bhavet[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vayu, vakkaya drishtinam sthiratashcha tatha tatha[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Extinguishing all such internal and external restlessness and attaining[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stillness, all hindrances and problems disappear within, and the eternal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happiness of consciousness is manifested; and by the revelation of all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 awareness, the knowledge of discrimination is brilliantly illuminated.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Some sadhakas practice disciplines regarding food and they merge the pranic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 faculties into each other by that practice. These matters of food are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 particularly expounded upon in the yogic scriptures. Here, one or two of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 things about this written in the Mahabharata as part of a conversion with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bhisma is shown below. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kanam takshaneyuktah pinyakasya cha bharata[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 snehanam varjaneyukto yogi balamavapnuyat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhunjanoyavakam ruksham dirghakalamarindam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ekaharo vishuddhatma yogibalamavapnuyat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 panchan masan ritumshchaiva samyatsavanahastatha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 apah pitva payomishram yogibalamavapnuyat[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Putting aside oily/fatty food that may be dear, for the sake of purification at[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the end of the day, yogis gain yogic power by eating ground cereal in a paste.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Yogis also gain yogic power by drinking milk mixed with water every day[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 for one fortnight, one month, one season - meaning two months - or one year.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Although every sadhaka does not have to follow the rules of eating in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manner mentioned above, still, everyone who wishes to practice the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (32 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-revealing Kriya must use temperance in food - become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "mitahari[s]" - in order to eliminate impurities in the mind. Just a little bit of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 negligence in this causes the appearance of many kinds of diseases and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 negativity in the mind, by which Consciousness becomes covered up and one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 falls from practicing Kriya. This has been specifically stated in yogic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scriptures. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mitaharam vinayastu yogarambhancha karayet[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nanaroga bhavettasya kinchidyoga na siddhati[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Many types of ailments arise in the yogi who performs any kind of yogakriya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 without being a mitahari, and none of his work is successful. Now, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 teaching in regards to the matter of mitahar [eating temperately] as given in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogic scriptures is expressed below. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 annena purayetardham toyena tu turiyakam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 udarasya turiyam samrakshayet vayuchalane[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shuddham sumadhuram snigdam udaradhvana varjjitam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhujyate surasam pritya mitaharamimam viduh[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Food such as rice should occupy half of the stomach (medham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 havishyamityuktam prashastam sattvikam laghu), meaning sacredly prepared[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sattvic and light substances; one-fourth of the space should be for liquids,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and one-fourth should be empty so that air may breathe. The food to eat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 should be pure, tasty, sweet, gentle and by which air does not spread in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 belly, and should be eaten in a peaceful state of mind. This is called mitahar.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The previously mentioned Kriyavan sadhakas of all types destroy all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tendencies of self-ruin by the path of Kriya as directed by their individual[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gurus, and attaining nectarous Tranquility at the end of Kriya, they remain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 absorbed in the Eternal Universal Brahman-Substance. But the persons[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 without Kriya - not to speak of the afterworld, meaning the Greatest Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Spiritual Happiness of the Bliss of Brahman - are not even able to obtain the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 little happiness of the human world, meaning that they are not able to have[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happiness in the matters of the body. In the Patanjal philosophical treatises[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this subject is written about in this way, as in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogashchitta vritti nirodhah - no. 2[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tadadrashtu svarupehavasthanam - no. 3[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vritti svarupyamitaratra - no. 4 -- Sadhanapada[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The ending of the fluctuations of consciousness is what is called "yoga." By[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this, sadhakas residing in its still and tranquil state are able to clearly and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 deeply know the nature of all things in the world. In other cases, human[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beings become tremendously involved in the manifestations of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fluctuations caused by restlessness. The fulfillment of prarabdha, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the fulfillment of desires associated with the fluctuations, meaning that if the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fluctuations are of an unpleasant nature, then immediately despondency sets[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (33 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in and one becomes filled with anxiety and sorrow; and when those matters[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of fulfillment are of a pleasant nature then a great attraction comes and all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 those prarabdha karmas are enjoyed through dancing, laughter etc., and one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is not even aware of how it is happening. And one does not understand all of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the changes that are taking place because of partaking in those things; one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 only is totally involved in the indulgence of physical enjoyments like an[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 animal. The significant thing here is that because lower life-forms do not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 possess the power of intellect, they steadily evolve into higher and higher[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 states according to natural law. But these people go beyond natural law by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the use of intellect; some evolve higher, and some fall and again have take to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 take the forms of insects etc. For them nothing is stable. -29, 30 and 31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evam bahuvidha yajna vitata brahmano mukhe[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmajan viddhitan sarvanevam jnatvavimokshyase -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus there are many ways of performing yajna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Numerous forms explained in the Vedas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All yajna is performed due to karma, know that, victorious one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing you will certainly be liberated -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The wise, Brahman-realized beings have spoken about many types of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 methods of yajna - meaning the matters of yogakriya. Knowing all of these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 things and performing yajna according to injunctions, the jiva can be free[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from this worldly life. -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   shreyan dravyamayadayajnaja jnanayajnah parantapa[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   sarvakarmakhilam partha jnane parisamapyate -33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Better than the offering of things in yajna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Is the offering of knowledge, O son of Kunti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   With the fruits, all karmas dissolve[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In Brahman-Knowledge, listen Dhananjaya -33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Jnanayoga is the highest of all yogas of kriya [using technique], higher than[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   yogas of kriya based on material things. It is so because all kinds of yogas of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   kriya are only necessary so that one may realize Knowledge. And when[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Knowledge is revealed in Its Highest Form, meaning when prajna [aggregate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   of faculties of inner wisdom] becomes still, no type of yogas of kriya are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   necessary. All kriyas [techniques/processes] end in that prajna and one[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (34 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attains the immortally nectarous Tranquility. -33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tadviddhi pranipatena pariprashnena sevaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 upadekshyanti te jnanah jnaninastattvadarshinah -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Go to the wise, Partha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With single-mindedness, humbly inquire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In initiation you will become disciplined in Brahman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Easily you will have the Knowledge of Para Brahman -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One should do reverent service to those wise ones who are Self-realized and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman-realized, and humbly ask them questions in regards to Atman,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning questions such as - "What is Atman? To what are we bound? And[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 how can we be free of this imprisonment?" and other inquiries such as these;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and they will teach the way of liberation in the form of all these yogas of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kriya. -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yaja jnantva na punarmohamevam yasyasi pandava[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yena bhutanyasheshena drakshyasyatmanyatho mayi -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing such you will never again be deluded[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 You will see all as Me -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When prajna is established by this yogakriya, one is never again under the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stupor of ignorance. After understanding the nature of all things of creation,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 through this prajna, as being in the Self, the jiva realizes that the Self is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Infinite Consciousness, and the Creator and Sustainer of the Universe, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 thus it attains liberation from being bound to earthly existence. -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 apichedasi papebhyah sarvebhyah papakrittamah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvam jnanaplavenaiva vrijinam santarishyasi -36-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yathaidhamsi samiddhohagnirbhasmasat kurutehrjuna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanagnih sarvakarmani bhasmasat kurute tatha -37-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If one is the worst of all sinners[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By the boat of Knowledge he can cross to the other shore -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (35 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The way blazing fire burns wood to ashes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The fire of Knowledge burns away the body of sin in the same way -37-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Even the worst sinners can be easily liberated from imprisonment of earthly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 existence by establishing prajna through the Guru-instructed yogakriya. Just[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 as the blaze of fire burns all wood to ashes, in the same way, by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revelation of Knowledge, through which one experiences the world-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda in oneself and all creation of Brahman as if in the palm of one's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hand, and because of the tranquility of consciousness and the state of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desirelessness attained by that, like burned seeds, all karmas become devoid[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of all germinating power. Thus, because no fruits are born from those karmas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to be fulfilled in the future, the jiva is no longer bound to take birth again and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 again in samsara. -36 and 37-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nahi jnanena sadrisham pavitramiha vidyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tat svayam yogasamsiddhah kalenatmani vindati -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For purification, nothing is higher than Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The blessed attain perfection through yoga in the course of time -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There is nothing more sacred than the supremely purifying Knowledge for[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the revelation of Consciousness residing in the body. This Knowledge, via[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Sadguru-initiated Kriya, ends the fluctuations of consciousness and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reveals the Self. -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shraddhavana labhate jnanam tatparah samyatendriyah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanam labdha param shantimachirenadhigacchati -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One whose mind is one-pointed and victorious over the senses[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That one becomes the vessel of Knowledge -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The sadhakas who are reverent, Kriyavans, and victorious over the senses are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the ones who are able to realize this Self-Knowledge. When Self-Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is established, the jiva is liberated from the bindings of mundane existence[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and attains Supreme Peace. -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (36 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ajnashchashraddadhanashcha samshayatma vinashyati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nayam lokohsti na paro na sukham samshayatmanah -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who is looking outwards and full of doubt[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The two worlds are ruined for him - he has no happiness -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For the persons without Kriya who are always thinking of receiving initiation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from Guru at some convenient time in the future, or the ones who have been[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 initiated but are not reverent towards the practice, or the ones who are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reverent but are doubtful of the possibility of success by the practice - for[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 them all work is corrupted; no work is successful. The doubtful persons are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not able to understand the matters of the physical and subtle bodies through[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the experience of Supreme Bliss of Brahman within. Those who are engaged[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in such doubtfulness remain bound to the pleasures of ordinary things such[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 as food etc. -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogasamnyastakarmanam jnana samcchinna samshayam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atmavantam na karmani nivadhnanti dhananjaya -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Surrendering karma to God is sannyas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who does so quickly passes through karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who is disciplined in Atman and without doubt[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 How can the ashes of karma bind him -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, if the jiva can, by the Guru-instructed Knowledge of liberation as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stated in the scriptures, tear up all doubt and, by the performance of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogakriya with certainty of mind, eliminate all karma - meaning all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 restlessness of the senses and pranic faculties - and reside contentedly in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman-Consciousness, then the jiva is not bound to any type of karma of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body or of the senses. -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasmadajnana sambhutam hritstham jnanasinatmanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chhittvainam samshayam yogamatishthottisshtha bharata -42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, when doubt appears towards Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Cut it by the sword of discrimination of the Atman in the body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Listen Bharata, perform karma[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (37 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Get up and fight now, virtuous and wise one -42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, discarding laziness and cutting up all doubt in the heart by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sword of the Sadguru-initiated Knowledge, one should perform yogakriya. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 SUMMARIZED DESCRIPTION OF CHAPTER 4:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 According to the teaching of the preceding chapter, experiencing the Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness and focusing the mind with devotion in That, it can be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 understood that the all-pervading Eternal Consciousness is within the human[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body firstly as the sun-consciousness, by which It becomes present at the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 door of sushumna in the Ajna chakra, from the Ajna chakra It is then present[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the other chakras existing in the sushumna, and from them It is spread in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the subtlest of ways within the nadis throughout the body, and is manifesting[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body as it appears. Later, it becomes known in the fire element that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 when the sun is revealed by the practice of Kriya, by that the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya is experienced. Thus - how is it possible that the sun is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 present due to the Kutasthachaitanya? Then it is experienced in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya that although Consciousness is without birth or death and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is the ruler of the Universe, because of Its presence in Prakriti, It reveals[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Itself with the elements again and again in the body. Ordinary people are not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aware of this. But once Kutasthachaitanya is established, then all is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experienced. When unawareness of Consciousness covers Prakriti, it faces[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 outward and the world-Brahmanda is created within. Through pranayam, all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of those faculties are extinguished and by the gradual evolution of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 condition of being, the Infinite Consciousness is revealed within and one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 merges into the Brahman-Substance. One no longer has to take birth in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samsara again and again. Whatever type of karma [action] one does yields[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that type of result. Not being able to understand the consequences in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 future, ordinary people become engaged in the service of the senses, lusting[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 after the acquisition of instantaneous pleasure. But, understanding the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eternity of the Bliss of Brahman, sadhakas renounce like and dislike and by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fearless and one-pointed practice of meditation, they attain the Knowledge of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman and remain in a state of oneness with the Brahman-Substance. It is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 true that the four varnas such as "brahmins" etc. are created because of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gradation of the manifestation of Consciousness, but Consciousness is never[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 less in some place nor more in another; It is present the same everywhere.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This idea of the manifestation of Consciousness as being more in one place[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and less in another is not created by Consciousness; this idea exists because[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of ignorance. In this way, all karma is of ignorance, and understanding that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman-Consciousness is completely uninvolved in that [karma], the sages of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the past attained liberation. Therefore, one should desirelessly remain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unattached from all types of karma. Among karma [action], some should be[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (38 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 done and some should not be done -- the understanding of this and the way[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of residing in non-attached tranquility from all karma -- the secrets of these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are veery difficult to know. Even very great and knowledgeable beings are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unable to comprehend these things. Therefore, instead of relying upon[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ordinary intellect, one should discern among these things from a state of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind that is completely controlled and focused. The one who knows heat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and cold or success and failure to be the same, who is not a slave to any[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 senses of the body, who has renounced all cravings and is satisfied with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 whatever comes effortlessly, who works to simply maintain the workings of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body with disciplined mind, desirelessly and without confusion and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 doubt, all of this person's work is devoid of the bindings of future results and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [his work] is transformed into "akarma" [non-action]. And the one with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 akarma, meaning the one with the purpose of having no attachment to results[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of any karma, who takes up yogakriya in the Kutastha with disciplined and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 focused mind, is the truly intelligent being. Even while engaged in all types[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of work, he remains in samadhi of the Consciousness of the Self. The seers[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Oneness know this world-Brahmanda to be completely filled with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman, and thus, they practice experiencing Him in all types of work.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Hatha yogis practice the control of the senses by certain techniques. Jnana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogis surrender every karma to Kutasthachaitanya and try to live in non-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attached tranquility. Brahmacharis try to pacify the senses by pratyahara[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [withdrawal] etc. Those disciplined in meditation practice the surrender of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the work of all senses and even the workings of prana itself to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya. Asectics take extreme vows and by the use of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 medication and difficult practices, try to steady the body, and by certain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogic practices and studying scriptures of liberation, they try to illuminate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge within themselves. Other yogis practice the stillness of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge by rechak and purak of pranayam, stopping the movement of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prana and apana. And some others try to extinguish the outgoing faculties by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 disciplined eating. The fruits of all of these yogic practices can be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 successfully attained by Kriya, and when Knowledge is illuminated by this,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all kriyas [methods] are finished. After reverently serving and asking[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 questions regarding these things to the wise ones of Self-Knowledge, when[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one receives the answers and practices accordingly, one can no longer be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stupefied by maya. By this, sadhakas become free of everything and sinless,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aware of all things in the Universe within themselves, and finally seeing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 themselves as the Infinite Consciousness, they attain the Infinite Bliss of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman-Substance. But those without Kriya are not able to be successful in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 acquiring even the happiness of the physical world, far be it to speak of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 spiritual Bliss of Brahman. There is nothing more pure and higher than[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge in this world; this Knowledge of the Self is revealed by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogakriya. Just as the blaze of a fire burns dry wood all into ashes, in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 same way this Knowledge burns the seeds - rendering them fruitless for the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 future - of all karma of even the worst of sinners, and thus liberating them[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from the ocean of samsara. The reverent, one-pointed and disciplined[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhakas in yogakriya gain Knowledge and attain liberation, and all work of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the ignorant ones practicing yogakriya with irreverence or with doubt[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter4.html (39 of 40)4/18/2006 2:42:03 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become corrupted. The apprehensive ones engaged in doubt have to remain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bound to all kinds of physical, subtle and other kinds of ordinary pleasures.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With the sword of Sadguru-initiated Knowledge cutting apart all doubt in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 heart, and residing non-attached and contentedly in Atman-Consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 through the performance of yogakriya, jivas can become liberated from all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karma. Therefore, one should abandon all laziness and, with a mind that is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 free of doubt, perform this yogakriya.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the fourth chapter of the yogashastra upanishad Srimad Bhagavad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gita with analysis via various scriptures of this country and the West, along[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with spiritual commentary.[m
[32m+[m
