[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 CHAPTER FIVE[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 SANNYASYOGA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sannyasam karmanam punaryogancha shamsasi[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       yacchreya etayorekam tanme bruhi sunishchitam -1-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition                          Arjuna said I beseech You Krishna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Previously You described sannyas[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            Then again You spoke about karmayoga[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     I cannot understand what You are saying[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   Make me certain for once[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  Taking which path I may cross over -1-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction                     Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        When all that is explained in the previous chapter is experienced via the[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        Kutasthachaitanya, a question arises in the force of the fire element: "O[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        Kutasthachaitanya! Once I see that all karma must be equally extinguished;[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        then again I see that performing Kriya in order to stop the fluctuations of[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5                        consciousness is the imperative duty. Therefore, please show me with[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        certainty which is the best of the two." -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        sannyasah karmayogashcha nihshreyasakarabubhau[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tayastu karmasannyasat karmayogo vishishyate -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Govinda said listen attentively Partha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The renunciation of karma and the doing of karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For liberation, there is no conflict between the two[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter5.html (1 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:04 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  From sannyas, again karma is greater[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  Devotion is related to desireless karma[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  As instructed in the scriptures for the purification of consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  Therefore, karma is greater than jnana[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  Without the purification of consciousness there is no jnana -2-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  When the mind is fixed in the Kutasthachaitanya, an experience occurs that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eradicating karma equally, and the performance of karma [action] in order to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stop the fluctuations of consciousness are both great and will bestow[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 liberation. In that, the consciousness-fluctuation-stopping performance of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karma [action] in the form of Kriya yoga is the greatest. -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jneyah sa nityasannyasi yo na dveshti na kankhati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nirdvandvo hi mahabaho sukham bandhat pramuchyate -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without dislike and without craving[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Feeling cold, heat, pleasure, sorrow as the same[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That true sannyasi is spoken of in the Vedas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Effortlessly untangling the bindings of life -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who lives in peaceful non-attachment and whose consciousness is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beyond all conflicts of dislike and want, pleasure and sorrow etc., and who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 performs all karma [action] with the physical organs in order to simply[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 maintain the normal functioning of the body from that state of being -- he is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the true sannyasi, meaning a renunciate of all types of karma, and he can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 easily and in great happiness become liberated from the world. -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samkhyayogou prithagbalah pravadanti na panditah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ekamapyasthitah samyagubhayorvindate phalam -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yat samkheyaih prapyate sthanam tadyogairapi gamyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ekam samkhyancha yogancha yah pashyati sa pashyati -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The ignorant say the sannyas and karmayoga are different[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Performing one, one gets the fruit of both[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The fruits of karma bring corruption to the purification of consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Destroying pravritti one becomes united -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That which is of the sannyasi is the path of the yogi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The great ones know the methods to be the same samkhyayoga -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter5.html (2 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:04 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The sannyasyoga of the discipline of knowledgeable ones, meaning the yoga[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of non-doing, and the Kriya yoga of kriyavans -- performing either one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 completely can lead to the attainment of Kaivalyapada and Tranquility. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledgeable ones ascerttain that both are the same. The childish and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ignorant see them as different. By both - the performance of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness-fluctuation-stopping Kriya yoga, or residing in the state of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tranquil non-attachment from the renunciation of all karma - one can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experience Full Consciousness and be liberated from enchainment of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world. Because they yield the same result, they are the same thing. The one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who has understood this is a true jnani and judicious. -4 and 5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sannyasastu mahabaho duhkhamaptumayogatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogayuktomunibrahma nachirenadhigacchati -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who does sannyas without doing karma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Disaster befalls him in sorrowful partaking[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Yogis surrender karma to God[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Being wise, it is he who ascends samsara -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Trying to renounce all karma equally and thus trying to reside in non-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attached tranquility without purifying consciousness by the consciousness-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fluctuation-stopping Kriya only causes sorrow. But purifying consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by yogakriya and thereby achieving steadiness of mind, one can easily[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eradicate all karmic restlessness, and by experiencing Full Consciousness in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 oneself, one can attain Kaivalyapada. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogayukto vishuddhatma vijitatma jitentriyah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvabhutatma bhutatma kurvannapi na lipyate -7-[m
[32m+[m
