[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Seeing, hearing, touching, smelling and tasting comprise the functions of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 five organs of perception. Speaking, holding, moving, urinating and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 excreting comprise the functions of the five organs of action. Pranic work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 such as inspiration, expiration etc. comprise the functions of the five airs.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Steadfastness, unfolding etc. are the functions of the inner senses of mind,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and dreaming etc. are of the intellect. Because kriyavan sadhakas reside[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 separately from the body and senses, they experience that the ten sense-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 organs of the body, the five pranas, mind and intellect are carrying out all the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 work mentioned above via the seventeen forms in the subtle body; the Self is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not involved in any of this. -8 and 9-[m
[32m+[m
