[32m+[m[32m                                 In the delusion of samsara, people cannot find the way out -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By researching the science of creation one can know that from the gods to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mobile and immobile matter, all things are following their own nature and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are being created accordingly in new and different forms. And being bound[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter5.html (6 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:05 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to such nature, one form is being discarded and again a new one is being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 created. But Atman-Consciousness is eternal and immutable, and is present[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the same way everywhere. This has been clearly explained in previous[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 slokas of this book. Now, it is being revealed in sloka that the beneficent or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 maleficent works by the Prakriti-deviation-culture of body, mind, intellect[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and sensory functions are affecting in their various ways only the nature of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jivas. No diminution or expansion happens to the Atman-Consciousness by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this. It is eternal and immutable. Ignorance, meaning Prakriti, is not in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness and is engaged in acquiring externally. From such deviation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 many types of things have arisen and they are keeping the Consciousness in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the form of Knowledge in jivas covered in stupor. Because of this, jivas have[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become deluded, and unable to realize this, they are bound to this worldly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 life. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanena tu tadajnanam yesham nashitamatmanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 teshamadityavajjnanam prakashayati tatparam -16-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tadbuddhayastadatmanastannishthastat parayanah[m
