[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One whose ignorance is destroyed by this Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He is revealed the God-Substance[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As the rising sun dispels darkness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the same way their bindings are destroyed -16-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who absorbs mind and intellect in that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Firmly and solely are they in the Refuge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Extinguishing all sin by Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ending birth and death, they leave -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 What attachment to partaking/enjoyment [bhoga] and salvation, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 liberation, are -- if they are not clearly explained, then there is a significant[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 possibility of confusion arising in trying to understand sevveral circuitous[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 slokas of this chapter. Therefore, what is written in Patanjal Darshan about[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the aforementioned bhoga and salvation from it are being explained below.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Purusha, meaning jivatman, is the immutable Consciousness-Substance.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Prakriti, being in the presence of this Consciousness and being Its mirror,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 creates a new type of substance, as iron is energized in the presence of a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 magnet, and by this manifests as the numerous elemental and sensory objects[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and their workings. All of these elemental and all internal and external[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sensory matter - up until the Absolute - are imbued with the three gunas:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revelatory sattva, active rajas, and veiling and inertia-producing tamas. These[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 comprise what is called "drishya" [scene, or that which is seen/perceived]. In[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this way, Prakriti, a reflection of Consciousness manifesting as the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter5.html (7 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:05 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 innumerable things, is experienced in the jiva-consciousness. This is why the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva-consciousness is usually called "drashta" [perceiver/witness]. When in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 order to perceive these perceptible things [drishya padartha] the jiva-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness joins Prakriti-Shakti, sound, touch, sight, taste, scent, pleasure[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and pain etc. manifest as the innumerable things and are experienced by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva. This is what is called the jiva's "bhoga."[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, all of these perceptible things or the matters of bhoga are only[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mutations of Consciousness by the Prakriti-Shakti union. Thus, this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness is the Soul-Self of these innumerable perceptible things. Just[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 as the intoxicated state of mind caused by drinking liquor seems to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pleasure to the drinker of liquor, in the same way, the state caused by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 partaking [bhoga] in sensory matters seems to be pleasure for the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 undiscriminating. But if one does a little thoughtful analysis, one can see that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it is because of being under the power of this need to partake/enjoy [bhoga][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that jivas are unable to have peace. Just as throwing clarified butter in fire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 causes the fire to burn more instead of extinguishing it, in the same way,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 instead of peace, the partaking/enjoying causes desire and cravings to grow,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and by that jivas become intensely engaged in fulfilling desires, incurring[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 great suffering. (‚Äúna jatu kamah kamanamupabhogena samyati.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 habishakrishnavartmaiva bhuya evabhivardhate.‚Äù) Thus, sorrow is the end[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 result of all bhoga. One suffers greatly by constantly thinking about and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 trying to maintain and protect the things to be enjoyed [matters of bhoga].[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, this bhoga is accompanied by sorrow, or suffering. The samskaras[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [tendencies] that are born of this bhoga are also full of suffering. For[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 example, the samskara arising from becoming attached to the bhoga of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 seating in a plush velvet seat in a beautifully perfumed place causes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 displeasure at sitting in any other condition in the world. Staying even a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 moment at any place causes great suffering. Because these momentary and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fleeting enjoyments are imbued with the sattva, rajas and tamas gunas, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are often at odds with each other and this also brings tremendous suffering to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the jiva. Knowing all bhoga to be filled with sorrow because of these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reasons, the discriminating ones take care to renounce all partaking/[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyment of sense objects.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By delusion, ignorance and unawareness, the five kleshas [afflictions] with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 affinity, hate etc. arise in the perceptible matters of the jiva, and in order to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fulfill the experiences of partaking accordingly, the jiva-consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 remains in a distorted state, bound to the power of Prakriti. Stilling the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fluctuations of consciousness by yogakriya and thereby being the perceiver/[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 witness, the source of the five kleshas, meaning the field of ignorance,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 delusion or Prakriti, from which all bhoga has arisen, is revealed, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experiencing the Substance hidden within all bhoga, or that Consciousness as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Self in them, jivas are no longer bound to Prakriti for the purpose of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhoga. In this way, when ignorance is destroyed and attachment is no more,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all distortion vanishes, and the entire Cosmos is revealed as the Jiva-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-Self. This is what is called salvation or liberation in the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter5.html (8 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:05 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scriptural treatises.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, those who can understand the secret matter of these things that are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perceptible -- which act as the provider of bhoga for the undiscriminating[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ones -- those discriminating ones are prepared for the gift of liberation. In[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this way, jivas experience themselves as the Self in all things in the world-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda and realize themselves as pervading all things in the Universe.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, in the Cosmos, there is no experience of a second anything[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 separate from the Self. This type of state is called the Purusha's or jiva's[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "kevalatva" or "Kaivalya" state of existence. When this state is attained, then[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all bhoga and desires are devoid, and jivas do not ever again have to take[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 birth in this samsara.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "prakashakriyasthitishilam bhutendriyatmakam bhogapavargartham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 drishyam" - 2-18[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "drashadrishimatrah shuddhohpi pratyanupashyah" - 2-20[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "swaswamishaktyah swarupopalabdhihetuh samyogah" - 2-23[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "tadartha eva drishyatma" - 2-21[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "parinama tapasamskara duhkaigurnavrittivirodhaccha sarvameva duhkham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vivekakinah" - 2-15[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "tasya heturavidyah" - 2-24[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "yogashchittavritti nirodhah" - 1-2[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "tadadrashtuh svarupehvasthanam" - 1-3[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "avidyakshetramuttaresham prasupta tanuvicchinnodayanam" - 2-4[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "anityashuchiduhkhanatmasu nityashuchi sukhatma khyatirvidya" - 2-5[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "tadabhavat samyogabhabvohanam tadvasheh kaivalam" - 2-25[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, it can be clearly understood in these two slokas that as jivas gradually[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realize Atman-Consciousness by the Sadguru-instructed Kriya and thereby[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eradicate the manifestation of this greatly destructive unawareness, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ignorance, that all-revealing Knowledge like the sun reveals this infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe and the entire Cosmos, and thus they gradually experience that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Supreme Substance Infinite Consciousness. In this way, having eliminated[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the presence and effect of ignorance, when by doubt-free and steady[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perception that Infinite Consciousness is experienced, the wise and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 discriminating sadhakas, remaining self-disciplined and keeping the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness engaged in Atman and apart from all bhoga, take refuge in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that Infinite Consciousness and become liberated from this horrific,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 destructive suffering of samsara. These types of "jivanmukta" [liberated[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 while alive in the body] sadhakas never again have to be bound to take birth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the world. -16 and 17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vidyavinayasampanne brahmane gavi hastini[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shuni chaiva shvapake cha panditah samadarshanah -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter5.html (9 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:05 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The humble, the wealthy, the brahmin, knowing the four Vedas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who does not see any difference in the outcast[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Elephant, cow, dog, and such - sees them as the same[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He is the wise scholar with pure nature -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Although a cow, an elephant, a dog and such classes of nature, the highest[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmin of yogakriya with supreme knowledge, the humble and the wealthy,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and low beings of inferior activities, have tremendous differences even in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one race or class because of diverse tendencies, the wise understand that all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these are only variants of Prakriti, and, experiencing that all-pervading[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness as the Soul-Self equally in all perceptible things, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consider all of them to be the same. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ihaiva tairjitah svargo yesham samye sthitam manah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nirdosham hi samam brahma tasmadbrahmani te sthitah -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this body while alive he is victorious over samsara[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who behavior is unchanging everywhere[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The flawless, same Brahman is spread throughout all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He is the form of Brahman, the one who has this equanimity of intelligence -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If Prakritic distortions do not arise in the mind, meaning that if jivas do not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become corrupted by uniting with Prakriti-Shakti, then jivas experience all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 things in the Universe as equal, and attaining that unalloyed, equanimous,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 supreme condition of Brahman, they gain victory over birth and death even[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 while in the body, meaning that birth and death come under their power and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become slaves to their whim. This is called "jivanmuktavastha." -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na prahrishyet priyam prapya nodvijet prapyachapriyam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sthirabuddhirasamudho brahmavid brahmanisthita -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 No contentment from gaining the thing loved[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 No sorrow from getting the unwanted[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing the Brahman-Substance with still consciousness, devoid of delusion[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The yogi to whom the great and dear is Param Brahman -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
