[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The force that arises from lust and anger[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who is stern in withstanding that force[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That yogi, shedding the body at the end-time[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Effortlessly receives liberation, so says wisdom -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who after death, meaning that the one who is as a dead body even[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 before death, meaning that the one who resides separately from the mind-,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intellect- and sense-connected body and who is not perturbed by the lust- and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anger-force-connected pleasures or sorrows of any type -- he is said to be the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one who is united with the Self, and he is the one who attains that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indestructible-Peace-filled, Suprreme Happiness-filled Kaivalyapada.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Maharshi Vashishthadeva has also expounded upon this. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prane gate yatha dehah sukha duhkham na bindati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatha chet prahayuktehpi sa kaivalyashrame baset[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As a dead body while alive, the ones who are unmoved by any pleasure or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sorrow of the mind, intellect, body and the senses, are the ones who are said[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to be residing in the house of Kaivalya. -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yohntah sukshohntararamastathantarjyotireva yah[m
