[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Devoid of lust and anger, the one whose mind is pure[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Who can be in judgment of his liberation in the after-world[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The relationship to unawareness while there is life[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As Brahman and jivanmukta, is not bound by karma -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If sadhakas can be liberated from the lust- and anger-force connected[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pleasure and sorrow in the previously mentioned way, then they can at any[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time, meaning even in this alive state, attain Kaivalyapada. This is what is[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter5.html (13 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:05 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 called the jivanmuktavastha. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sparshan kritva bahirbahyamshchakshushchaivantare bhruvouh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pranapanou samou kritva nasabhyantaracharinou -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatendriyamanobuddhi munirmokshaparayanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vigatecchabhayakrodho yah sada mukta eva sah -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Do not ever keep the mind in material things[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Half-closed eyes look at one point[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Prana and apana, above and below, the two are spread[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bring them together in the middle of the nose -27-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Control yourself the senses, intellect and mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Renouncing the pleasure of heaven, leading to liberation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who is ever without desire, fear, anger[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He is eternally free, know that he has attained -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those sadhakas, having taken up the path of liberation, who have renounced[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all sensory bhoga of sound, touch etc. and who by focusing on the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 connecting point of the eyebrows equalize prana and apana within the nose,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who have immersed the senses, mind and intellect into the Atman, and who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are devoid of all distortions of Consciousness, such as desire, fear and anger[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- they, at all times, attain liberation even in this alive state. Sadhakas call[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that type of state jivanmuktavastha. -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhoktaram yajnatapasam sarvalokamaheshvaram[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 suhridam sarvabhutanam jnatva mam shantimricchati -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing the Lord of All as receiver of yajna and all good work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Realize Me and quickly attain liberation -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By the aforementioned Kriya, when sadhakas see Infinite Consciousness as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being in everything - up to the Ultimate - as the receiver of all yajna, spiritual[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 practices, etc. Who is residing as the liberation-bestowing Lord in the form[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Paramatman -- when this is realized, they see all things of the Cosmos as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Self. Thus, they have the Universe-pervading experience that there is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nothing other than Atman-Consciousness in the Universe. This is what the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 great sages have called "Kevalatva" or "Kaivalyapada." -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter5.html (14 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:05 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 SUMMARIZED DESCRIPTION OF CHAPTER 5[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When sadhakas are in the state of absorption in the Kutastha, many[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 wonderful facets of the yoga of performing Kriya and the yoga of renouncing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all action, as expressed in previous chapters, are experienced; then a desire to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 know which is the greater of these occurs in the energy of the rajoguna. At[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this, an experience happens by Kutasthachaitanya that performing yogakriya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and renouncing all karma by residing in a state of non-doing - when either is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 practiced with complete focus - one can attain Kaivalyapada. The wise see[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 both as of the same stature; only the immature and ignorant think that these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 two are different. Even if the organs of perception - sight, hearing, touch,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 smell, and taste, the organs of action - speech, receiving, motion, excretion[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and urination, the inner organs - mind, observation, understanding, intellect[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and dreams are all engaged in their respective work, Kriyavan sadhakas as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman-Consciousness reside separately from the sense-body in tranquil non-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attachment. This is because they are devoid of conflicts brought about by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 affinity and dislike etc., and they are not attached to those works. Therefore,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 even though they work, they are renunciates of all work and ever the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sannyasis. In this way, the condition of sannyas can be attained with ease.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 But trying to attain this state without yogakriya leads only to suffering.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, although either the performance of Kriya or the renunciation of all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 action are both liberation-endowing, the performance of Kriya is better.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman-Consciousness, the Lord of this miniature Cosmos of the body is not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 involved in any work. It does not cause any other to be involved, nor does It[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 have any craving to enjoy any karmic bhoga. Therefore, no diminution or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 expansion happens to Atman-Consciousness due to the routine workings of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body; only the prakriti of the jiva is affected. Atman-Consciousness is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eternally immaculate and eternally immutable. All worldly work is being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 done by Its natural law through Maya. Other than partaking due to one's own[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desire, no one has to be a recipient of its fruits. By ignorance or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unawareness, wisdom is veiled, and because jivas are connected to that and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enraptured by that, they cannot understand this. By yogakriya this ignorance[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is destroyed and when the all-exposing sun-like Knowledge of Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness is revealed, all of these things are understood. Then sadkakas,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by having worn away prarabdha, for the sake of self-purification having[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renounced all desires to partake/enjoy, being united and immersed in Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness, residing in Supreme Happiness in the city of nine gates or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body, not being enmeshed as the Self during all works of the world nor[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 causing anyone to be enmeshed in such, having renounced all karma, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 accomplishing all work at hand by the body, mind, intellect and the senses[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 alone, live liberated from the sufferings of samsara. But jivas without Kriya,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being under the stupor of ignorance, see themselves as doing all the works by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body etc., and thereby desiring to enjoy the fruits of such work, remain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bound to this samsara. When Self-Knowledge is revealed, the differences in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 a cow, an elephant, a dog and such classes of nature, or the differences[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 between a highly educated and humble Kriyavan brahmin or a low-kriya[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter5.html (15 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:05 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [disrespectful action] oriented base person and the differences even within[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one class with the innumerable permutations of Prakriti manifesting --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 despite the differences, the sadhakas experience the Self in all things as the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unalloyed and immutable Brahman-Consciousnesss existing everywhere[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 equally. Thus, they are not overly elated at gaining something desirable, nor[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are they despondent over having gotten something undesirable. In this way,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 having destroyed all distortions and ideas of dissimilarity in the mind, with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 steadiness of perception, sadhakas are freed from all delusions in the world,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and having eradicated and become victorious over birth and death, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attain that immutable and all-pervading state of equanimity of the Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 State. The wise know that all of these fleeting and momentary pleasures of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhoga, which are of the sense-objects, are the wellspring of all suffering, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they are not attracted by them. If attachment to all these lust- and anger-force-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 produced desires of bhoga can be checked and ended, then jivas can gain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happiness within, and being immersed in Atman-Consciousness, in the end,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 having become one with that Infinite Consciousness, attain the indestructible[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happiness of Tranquility. Understanding all this, Kriyavans and sadhakas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who know the Self eliminate all conflict and doubt, renounce all partaking/[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyment associated with sense-objects, discipline the mind, intellect and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the senses, become free from the forces of lust, anger etc. by having attained[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 liberation, with a consciousness devoid of desire, fear and anger, focus[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 wholly within where the eyebrows unite and where Consciousness in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 form of Light is revealed, equally still prana and apana, gain complete[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 steadfastness within, attain the highest samadhi of asamprajnata state,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eradicate the greatly destructive ignorance and all samskaras, and realizing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 oneself to be that Infinite Consciousness in all elements as the Self who is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyer of all spiritual work, they become one with all things, pervading all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the Cosmos and attain the indestructible Supreme Happiness of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kaivalyapada.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the fifth chapter of the yogashastra upanishad Srimad Bhagavad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gita with analysis via various scriptures of this country and the West, along[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with spiritual commentary.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                   Yoganiketan, Portland Maine , USA ¬© 2002[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All Rights Reserved by Yoganiketan for any material published on this[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                                          website.[m
