[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter5.html (16 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:05 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 CHAPTER SIX[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 DHYANAYOGA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome          Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page    anashritah karmaphalam karyam karma karoti yah[m
[32m+[m[32m              sa sannyasi cha yogi cha na niragni rnachakriyah -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to[m
[32m+[m[32mthe present   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32mEnglish[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition       Doing dutiful karma, not paying attention to the fruits of karma [action][m
[32m+[m[32m              That is the sannyasi yogi who knows the essence of all things[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami         All fruits of all yajna, are his that Kriyavan[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's  Renouncing, karma yoga - is all the same to him -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to[m
[32m+[m[32mthe Bengali   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition[m
[32m+[m[32m              As consciousness stays immersed in Kutasthachaitanya, even more is experienced - that:[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction  the one who, having renounced all craving for all types of results, continues to do all[m
[32m+[m[32m              karma [action] -- he is the definitive sannyasi, and he is also the definitive yogi. Yajna by[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1     fire, or renouncing different kinds of work annd being without action and sitting under a[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2     tree does not make a sannyasi or yogi. -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4     yam sannyasamiti prahuryogam tam biddhi pandavah[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5     na hyasamnyastasamkalpo yogi bhati kashchan -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7     Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m              Know this word to be verily true, son of Pandu[m
[32m+[m[32m              What is a yogi who cannot renounce the fruits -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m              Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (1 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8   Renouncing all human and physical karma and the craving for their fruits equally, no[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9   types of concern arise in the mind; therefore, there are no corruptions of consciousness.[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 10  That is what is called the cessation of fluctuations in consciousness [chittavritti nirodha].[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 11  As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 12  shlokarddhantu prakshyami yaduktam tatvadarshibhih[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 13  sarvachinta parityage nishchinto yoga ucchyate - Jnanasamkalinitantra -no. 61-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 14[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 15  "yogashchittavrittinirodhah" - Patanjaladarshane Samadhipadah -no. 2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 16[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 17  In the yogic scripture of Hara Gauri Samvad, to the Divine Goddess' question of "What is[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 18  yoga?" - the Lord Mahadeva has said that I am only speaking half of what the seers of[m
[32m+[m[32m            essence and realized in this subject of yoga - listen. Having abandoned all thought and[m
[32m+[m[32m            being in the state of tranquility is called yoga. It has also been stated in the Patanjal[m
[32m+[m[32m            Darshan that yoga is the state of the cessation of the fluctuations in consciousness.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m            Therefore, the renunciation of all karma, and yoga, or the cessation of the stopping of the[m
[32m+[m[32m            fluctuations in consciousness, are both the same thing. Not renouncing all types of karma[m
[32m+[m[32m            enjoined with the craving of results and performing action with all kinds of strong desires[m
[32m+[m[32m            cannot in any way bring about the cessation of the fluctuations in consciousness.[m
[32m+[m[32m            Therefore, it is not possible for these types of renunciation-less sadhakas to have yogic[m
[32m+[m[32m            union, or to be in samadhi. -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      aruruksho muneryogam karmakaranamuchyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                      yogarudhrasya tasyaiva shamah karanamuchyate -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The one who wants to ascend in yoga[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Desireless action is his way[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Ascending will bring him liberation[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Remaining in God only, the great bridge to Tranquility -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Sadhakas wishing to stop fluctuations in consciousness should perform the Sadguru-[m
[32m+[m[32m                      instructed yogakriya. But when the cessation of fluctuations in consciousness has been[m
[32m+[m[32m                      attained, in order to extinguish all those causes of fluctuations in consciousness, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                      should remain in the highest unknowable samadhi and by that practice non-attachment[m
[32m+[m[32m                      again and again, and end all types of physical and human karma. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      "viramapratyayabhyaspurvah samskarasheshohanyah" - Patanjaldarshane Samadhipadah -[m
[32m+[m[32m                      no.18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Practicing supreme non-attachment again and again, which is the form of the means of[m
[32m+[m[32m                      coming to rest and thereby ending all samskaras, that highest of all asamprajnata samadhi[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (2 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mstate becomes present. -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32myada hi nendriyartheshu na karmasvanuyajjate[m
[32m+[m[32msarvasamkalpasannyasi yogarudhrastadochate -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNot addicted to things, mind devoid of want[m
[32m+[m[32mOne can say this when firmly established in yoga -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAll those sadhakas who do not become addicted to sense-objects and sense-actions -- they[m
[32m+[m[32mare the renunciates of all types of desires who reside quietly as sannyasis, and it is their[m
[32m+[m[32mfluctuations of consciousness that have ceased. - 4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32muddharedatmanatmanam natmanamavasadayet[m
[32m+[m[32matmaiva hyatmano bandhuratmaiva ripuratmanah -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHis own salvation will be done by the jiva himself[m
[32m+[m[32mBy not being in the destructive lie of delusion -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIn this Universe, one is one's own friend, meaning benefactor, and one is one's own[m
[32m+[m[32menemy, meaning malefactor. Without effort by oneself, no one can do good or harm to[m
[32m+[m[32manyone. Therefore, to save oneself from this endless, suffering-laden sorrow of life in the[m
[32m+[m[32mworld, one has to make the effort oneself. One should not in any way become weary in[m
[32m+[m[32mthe matter of Atman-Consciousness.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis matter is very clearly expressed in a song by the Baul sect of the Vaishnava side. A[m
[32m+[m[32msection of it is presented below. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m"(Come brother) see one's own form by oneself[m
[32m+[m[32mOneself has to cross over by oneself being the boatman[m
[32m+[m[32mOneself is the criminal, oneself is the lord, oneself is intelligence and might[m
[32m+[m[32m(If one can) oneself goes (if not) oneself is does not go[m
[32m+[m[32m(O brother) oneself is all[m
[32m+[m[32m(See brother) oneself is Brahman, oneself is Shambhu, oneself is Srihari[m
[32m+[m[32m(Come brother) see one's own form by oneself"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m-5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (3 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mbandhuratmanastasya yenatmaivatmana jitah[m
[32m+[m[32manatmanstu shatrutve vartetatmaiva shatruvam -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe one who can be victorious over oneself[m
[32m+[m[32mKnow certainly, that one's Atman is friend[m
[32m+[m[32mThe one who cannot win over himself[m
[32m+[m[32mHe becomes his own enemy, son of Pandu -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe one who has saved himself from being enslaved by mind, intellect, senses etc., and[m
[32m+[m[32mwho is free and established in Atman-Consciousness, meaning the one who has been able[m
[32m+[m[32mto be successful in maintaining one's true identity -- that one is the supreme benefactor of[m
[32m+[m[32mhimself and his own friend, and the one who, by having broken away from Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32mConscioousness, is controlled by tendencies under the enslavement of all types of desire-[m
[32m+[m[32mfilled mind, intellect, senses etc. -- these types of beings, who have resigned to make effort[m
[32m+[m[32min the attainment of Atman-Consciousness, are themselves their own malefactors and their[m
[32m+[m[32mown supreme enemy. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mjitamanah prashantasya paramatma samahitah[m
[32m+[m[32mshitoshnchasukhaduhkheshu tatha manapamanayoh -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mKeeping unattached from the influence of things[m
[32m+[m[32mThe one whose mind is eternally on Paramatman[m
[32m+[m[32mCold, heat, pleasure, sorrow, eminence, shame[m
[32m+[m[32mWhen any happens, there is no birth of want; all are same -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhen cold, heat, pleasure, sorrow, eminence, shame etc. and many such types of suffering-[m
[32m+[m[32mcausing matters of the world - appear -- those who maintain themselves in their true[m
[32m+[m[32midentity and are established in Atman-Consciousness -- those sadhakas, who arre devoid[m
[32m+[m[32mof like and dislike and in tranquil consciousness, do not thereby partake in any type of[m
[32m+[m[32mcorruption and thus are able to directly attain the incorruptible state of Paramatman. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mjnanavijnanatriptatma kutastho vijitetindriyah[m
[32m+[m[32myukta ituchyate yogi samaloshtrashmakanchana -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mKnowledge, Science [beyond knowledge], certainty in doing the two[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (4 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mUncorrupted consciousness, senses in control[m
[32m+[m[32mThe one who is called a liberated yogi[m
[32m+[m[32mA clod of earth, a stone, gold are all the same to him -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mKnowledge, meaning knowing about things in treatises by the proofs realized by others,[m
[32m+[m[32mand Science, meaning experiencing by oneself beyond all those attained proofs and[m
[32m+[m[32mknowing by oneself -- the one who has satisfied oneself by such, the one who has[m
[32m+[m[32mbrought the five organs of perception, the five organs of actioon, mind and all of these[m
[32m+[m[32msenses under one's own power, and the one to whose mind gold, a clod of earth, a stone[m
[32m+[m[32metc. - all things to whom are the same - meaning discerning them as only permutations of[m
[32m+[m[32mmanifesting Consciousness, and therefore, the one whose consciousness is not the slightest[m
[32m+[m[32mbit perturbed by all kinds of things happening in the present -- it is that sadhaka whose[m
[32m+[m[32mfluctuations of consciousness have ceased. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      suhrinmitraryurdasinamadhyasthadveshyabandhushu[m
[32m+[m[32m                      sadhushvapi cha papeshu samabuddhirvishishyate -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The good-hearted, the boon companion, the non-caring, and friend[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The centrist, the hateful, and enemy[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The sage always remains in one's own dharma[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The great sinner abandons the path of righteousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The one to whom all of these are the same[m
[32m+[m[32m                      That venerable yogi is filled with the Supreme -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The good-hearted [suhrida], meaning naturally well-wishing, the boon companion [mitra],[m
[32m+[m[32m                      meaning well-wishing because of affection, "ari", meaning enemy, the non-caring[m
[32m+[m[32m                      [udasina], meaning one who is not either in good or non-good, the centrist [madhyastha],[m
[32m+[m[32m                      meaning one who is in the middle of both good and bad, the hateful [dveshya], meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                      one who is habitually wishes malefaction, the friend [bandhu], meaning one who wishes[m
[32m+[m[32m                      beneficence through relationship, the sage [sadhu], meaning one who is a virtuous[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Kriyavan of scriptural edicts, and the sinner [papi], meaning one who indulges in[m
[32m+[m[32m                      depravity -- the one to whom all of the many such types of human beings are known as the[m
[32m+[m[32m                      same, meaning the one in whom not even the sligghtest affinity or repulsion arises in[m
[32m+[m[32m                      regards to all these -- he is the supremely great master yogi.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The matter written about in the aforementioned three slokas are expressed by Vaishnavas[m
[32m+[m[32m                      as "the net of illusory magic [kuhakjal]," and they say that the beings of Self-knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                      whose minds are profoundly deep and steadfast, whose selves are immersed in the Self[m
[32m+[m[32m                      and who are wandering about in the Unfathomable Infinite Consciousness cannot even be[m
[32m+[m[32m                      touched by this kuhakjal. But the human beings of limited understanding who are under[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (5 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mthe power of like- and dislike-joined greed, and who are immersed in the ocean of desire-[m
[32m+[m[32mfulfillment become caught in the hooks and webbings of this net of Maya and have to[m
[32m+[m[32mpartake in the endless suffering of samsara. To show how the Vaishnavas of the Baul sect[m
[32m+[m[32mexpress this, part of a song of theirs is presented below.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m"In the waters of the world, so terrifying is the kuhakjal[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mO brother, the big fish with teeth[m
[32m+[m[32mNot for it is it so[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIn the waters of the world, so terrifying is the kuhakjal[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mO brother, the fish that moves in the unfathomable waters[m
[32m+[m[32mDoes it die by this?[m
[32m+[m[32mOnce it finds small fish, Maya's hooks[m
[32m+[m[32mImmediately bind it[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIn the waters of the world, so terrifying is the kuhakjal[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mO brother, the bait of greed in the ocean of bhoga[m
[32m+[m[32mThe one who lusts for it[m
[32m+[m[32mHe is pierced by the fish-hook, caught in the webbings[m
[32m+[m[32mStrung up in humiliation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIn the waters of the world, so terrifying is the kuhakjal"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m-9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32myogi yunjita satamatmanam rahasi sthitah[m
[32m+[m[32mekaki yatachittatma nirashiraparigrahah -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThink always of the longed-for Lord[m
[32m+[m[32mAlways be by yourself in a solitary place[m
[32m+[m[32mKeep consciousness and mind under the power of Atman[m
[32m+[m[32mRenounce all want; do not take anyone's wealth -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWith non-attachment and devoid of accepting anything, and disciplining the mind in[m
[32m+[m[32mAtman, in a solitary and silent place, Kriyavan sadhakas are continuously engaged in Self-[m
[32m+[m[32mKriya. -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mshuchau deshe pratishthapya sthirasanamatmanah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (6 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mnatyucchritam natinicham chelajinakushottaram -11-[m
[32m+[m[32mtatraikagram manh kritva yatachittendriyakriyah[m
[32m+[m[32mupavishyasane yunjad yogamatmavishuddaye -12-[m
[32m+[m[32msamam kayashirogrivam dharyannachalam sthirah[m
[32m+[m[32msamprekshya nasikagram svam dishashchanavalokayan -13-[m
[32m+[m[32mprashantatma vigatavibrahmacharivrate sthitah[m
[32m+[m[32mmanah samyamya macchitto yukto asita matparah -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSolitary; take your body[m
[32m+[m[32mSit in a purified place[m
[32m+[m[32mUnder skin, spread a seat of kusha grass[m
[32m+[m[32mOn top of that spread a soft piece of material[m
[32m+[m[32mKeep mind and senses one-pointed[m
[32m+[m[32mSitting in asana you will later know Atman[m
[32m+[m[32mBody, neck, head and such - do not move anything[m
[32m+[m[32mFocus your sight at the root of the nose; do not look in any direction[m
[32m+[m[32mBe in profound peace and in a chaste way[m
[32m+[m[32mBoth mind and consciousness in Me -11, 12, 13 and 14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhat are the aspects of Kriya yoga in these four slokas? How does one practice them, and[m
[32m+[m[32min what ways can one be careful about the obstacles associated with these? These have[m
[32m+[m[32mbeen subtly indicated here. Thus: what is known is yoga; what are known as its aspects;[m
[32m+[m[32mand which are its obstacles as well as how can one save oneself from those obstacles --[m
[32m+[m[32munderstanding all of these makes it easier to clearly comprehend these slokas. For that[m
[32m+[m[32mreason, before explaining these sllokas, I present below in a condensed manner what is[m
[32m+[m[32mwritten about those subjects in the supremely high yogic treatise, Patanjal Yogasutra, as[m
[32m+[m[32mwell as in other primary and important scriptures.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mShiksha, Kalpa, Vyakarana, Nirukta, Cchanda, Jyotish - having studied these six Vedic[m
[32m+[m[32maspects and thereby having become prepared to recite the Vedas, when one analyzes the[m
[32m+[m[32mprofound statements made in them such as "tattvamasi," "sohham," "ekamevadvitiyam,"[m
[32m+[m[32m"sarvakhalvidam brahman" etc., one comes to know that, just as the one water element in[m
[32m+[m[32mthe creation, meaning liquid substances, by being mixed with complementary qualities[m
[32m+[m[32mmutate and appear as oil and many such types of substances, in the same way, only the[m
[32m+[m[32mone Brahman-Consciousness, meaning Paramatman, mutates through Maya and appears[m
[32m+[m[32mas this whole creation with its beings that are of the land, of the air, of the water etc. along[m
[32m+[m[32mwith streams and rivers, oceans, mountains etc. - as this infinite Universe. And just the[m
[32m+[m[32msame as when those oil-like substances mix with water, instead of permeating the water[m
[32m+[m[32mremain separate, similarly the Maya-enjoined creation-substances are always in the[m
[32m+[m[32mInfinite Brahman-Consciousness, although mixed with It, they cannot permeate the entire[m
[32m+[m[32mUniverse, and thus, discerning themselves to be a tiny part of creation, they remain as[m
[32m+[m[32mseparate things in creation. Just as by applying some appropriate method to medicine such[m
[32m+[m[32mas liquor potass, or other such substance, the compound liquid can be broken up and[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (7 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mimmediately it will permeate all of the water, similarly, if by some technique, among all[m
[32m+[m[32mthings in this infinite Universe, the fluctuations of consciousness is stopped and the[m
[32m+[m[32minfluence of Maya is destroyed, then, mixing with this Infinite Consciousness, one[m
[32m+[m[32mpervades the entire Cosmos, becoming omniscient and omnipotent, and attaining Kaivalya[m
[32m+[m[32mor Brahman. In this way, the cessation of Maya-caused fluctuations of consciousness,[m
[32m+[m[32mmeaning ordinary actions, like the union of the oil-like substance with water like liquor[m
[32m+[m[32mpotass etc, is for the union of all things in the Universe with that Infinite Consciousness,[m
[32m+[m[32mmeaning the reason for yoga, which is why the great scriptural saints call the cessation of[m
[32m+[m[32mthe fluctuations in consciousness "yoga" [union], and the techniques/methods that one[m
[32m+[m[32mneeds to apply to stop those fluctuations in consciousness are called the "anga" - body,[m
[32m+[m[32mlimbs or parts - of yoga. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32myogashchittavritti nirodhah - Samadhipada - no. 2[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAlthough the above-mentioned limbs or parts of yoga to be practiced in order to stop the[m
[32m+[m[32mfluctuations in consciousness are of many types, in the Patanjal philosophical treatises[m
[32m+[m[32mthose have been divided into eight parts and given these eight names: yama, niyama,[m
[32m+[m[32masana, pranayam, pratyahar, dharana, dhyan and samadhi. Among these, the last -[m
[32m+[m[32mdharana, dhyan and samadhi - having nothing to do with external sadhana, are called[m
[32m+[m[32minternal parts. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32myamaniyamasanapranayamapratyaharadharanadhyanasamadhiyohashtavangani -[m
[32m+[m[32mSadhanapada - no. 29[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNow, I present below the manner in which the above-mentioned parts of yoga are written[m
[32m+[m[32mabout in the book named "Yogasutra" by Maharshi Patanjal:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mahimsasatyasteyabrahmacharyaparigraha yamah - Sadhanapada - no. 30[m
[32m+[m[32mshouchasantoshatapasvadhyayeshvarapranidhanani niyamah - Sadhanapada - no. 32[m
[32m+[m[32msthirasukhamasanam - Sadhanapada - no. 46[m
[32m+[m[32mtatah dvandanavaghata - Sadhanapada - no. 48[m
[32m+[m[32msvasvavishayasamprayoge chittasya svarupanukara ivendriyanam pratyaharah -[m
[32m+[m[32mSadhanapada - no. 54[m
[32m+[m[32mtasmin sati shvasaprashvasayorgatirvicchedah pranayamah - Sadhanapada - no. 49[m
[32m+[m[32mtatah kshiyate prakashavaranam - Sadhanapada - no. 52[m
[32m+[m[32mdharanashu yogyata manasah - Sadhanapada - no. 53[m
[32m+[m[32mdeshabandha chittasya dharana - Bibhutipada - no. 1[m
[32m+[m[32mtatrapratyayenaikatanata dhyanam - Bibhutipada - no. 2[m
[32m+[m[32mtadevarthamatranirbhasam swarupashunyamivasamadhih - Bibhutipada - no. 3[m
[32m+[m[32mtrayamekatra samyama - Bibhutipada - no. 4[m
[32m+[m[32mayamantaranga purvebhyah - Bibhutipada - no. 7[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRenouncing envy, greed, taking things of others and such things that cause mental[m
[32m+[m[32mrestlessness, being on the path of truth in chastity, and thereby extinguishing the[m
[32m+[m[32mperturbations in consciousness is called "yama." By this method, all destructive[m
[32m+[m[32mtendencies are eradicated. This matter has been explained in the fourth, fifth and sixth[m
[32m+[m[32mslokas of the first chapter of this book.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (8 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf, after experiencing Consciousness-Self, the human consciousness is unable to attain the[m
[32m+[m[32mBliss of Atman, then, as the joys of bhoga are now scattered about, it adopts many types of[m
[32m+[m[32mtendencies. This condition produces physical ailments, "styan" - meaning mental[m
[32m+[m[32mproblems, confusion/doubt - meaning the inability to discern between good and bad,[m
[32m+[m[32minadvertence - meaning the non-caring aloofness of mind and the lack of enthusiasm,[m
[32m+[m[32mlaziness - meaning the lack of activity, incessant worry over this or that happening,[m
[32m+[m[32menvisioning imaginary things - meaning delusion, a scenario of not being able to attain -[m
[32m+[m[32mmeaning a type of insufferable condition that says "something seems to be obviously[m
[32m+[m[32mavailable but I can't seem to get it," unsettledness - meaning the lack of stability -- many[m
[32m+[m[32mtypes of sufferings such as these become present. In the book named "Yogasutra" by[m
[32m+[m[32mMaharshi Patanjal, these have beenn called obstacles, meaning impediments. It is also[m
[32m+[m[32mwritten in the aforementioned book that the threefold suffering - meaning the physical[m
[32m+[m[32msuffering caused by the shock or attack from humans or animals or some other physical[m
[32m+[m[32mthing, the suffering of the subtle level caused by the corruption of the subtle body due to[m
[32m+[m[32mlapse in proper discipline, and spiritual suffering associated with the experience of [not[m
[32m+[m[32mfully attaining] the Bliss of Atman - causes depression, meaning despondency associated[m
[32m+[m[32mwith unfulfilled desire, "angamejayatva," meaning the shakiness of body and limb, along[m
[32m+[m[32mwith inhalation and exhalation, and by these things the human consciousness remains in a[m
[32m+[m[32mdisturbed state. Thus, to eradicate all of these, one should practice "ektattva" [one unified[m
[32m+[m[32mthing]. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mbyadhistyanasamshayapramadalasyabiratibhrantidarshanalabdhabhumikatvanavasthitatvani[m
[32m+[m[32mchittavikshepastehantarayah - Samadhipada - no. 30[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mduhkhadaurmanasyangamejayatvashvasaprashavasa vikshepasahabhuvah - Samadhipada[m
[32m+[m[32m- no. 31[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mtatpratishedhartamekatattvamabhyasah - Samadhipada - no. 32[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNow, what is this which is called "ektattva," and how one can practice it, is being[m
[32m+[m[32mexplained. To speak about this, first it is necessary to speak about the nature of mind,[m
[32m+[m[32mmeaning its character. By nature, the mind cannot just reside in a condition of emptiness[m
[32m+[m[32mwithout holding on to something, and it loves bliss so much that it does not hold on to[m
[32m+[m[32manything that does not give it any joy. If for some reason it has to hold on to such a thing,[m
[32m+[m[32mthat is for only a short while. As quickly as it can, it will abandon it and run after another[m
[32m+[m[32mthing that will be joyful. Knowing these two characteristics, it can clearly understood that[m
[32m+[m[32mif it is possible to keep the mind happy in something, something from which there can be[m
[32m+[m[32mno fear of unhappiness, then it remains in that thing in bliss, and no longer does it try to go[m
[32m+[m[32mafter other things. As soon as the mind is no longer restlessly going from one thing to[m
[32m+[m[32manother thing, and is steadily holding on to one thing by which it is happily residing,[m
[32m+[m[32mektattva is being practiced. For the practice of this ektattva, two slokas about keeping the[m
[32m+[m[32mmind happy and five slokas about keeping the mind steadfast - these seven sutras are[m
[32m+[m[32mwritten in the Patanjal philosophical treatises. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mmaitrikarunamuditopekshanam[m
[32m+[m[32msukhaduhkhapunyapunyavishayanambhavanashchittaprasadanam - Samadhipada - no. 33[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (9 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mpracchardanavidharanabhyam va pranasya - Samadhipada - no. 34[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe human consciousness of the jiva is happy at merriment in pleasure, pathos in sorrow,[m
[32m+[m[32menthusiasm for beneficent work, and rejection of maleficent work, but these external joys[m
[32m+[m[32mremain only for a very short time. The reason for this is that because of being attached to[m
[32m+[m[32mprevious samskaras [acquired tendencies], the consciousness, immediately afterwards,[m
[32m+[m[32magain gradually becomes unhappy. Therefore, in order to make the happiness just[m
[32m+[m[32mmentioned long-lasting, one must practice a kriya [technique/work] that purifies[m
[32m+[m[32msamskaras and creates inner happiness. When, by Sadguru's instructions, the flinging out,[m
[32m+[m[32mmeaning shooting out, of prana-air, and again its drawing back, meaning attraction -- by[m
[32m+[m[32mthe Kriya of this rechak and purak, there is samskara-purification, and happiness remains[m
[32m+[m[32mfor a long time. This subjectt has been explained in the eighth sloka of the fourth chapter.[m
[32m+[m[32mThese sutras teach on the way of keeping the mind happy, while the latter five slokas teach[m
[32m+[m[32mon how to keep the mind from going after things and thereby cast off restlessness, and[m
[32m+[m[32mthus remain in steadfastness. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mvishayavati va pravrittirutpanna manasah sthiti nibandhini - Samadhipada - no. 35[m
[32m+[m[32mvishoka va jyotismati - Samadhipada - no. 36[m
[32m+[m[32mvitaraga vishayam va chittasya - Samadhipada - no. 37[m
[32m+[m[32msvapnidrajnanalambanam va - Samadhipada - no. 38[m
[32m+[m[32myathabhimatadhyanat va - Samadhipada - no. 39[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mKeeping the mind happy by the above-mentioned type of technique, the all-pervading[m
[32m+[m[32mSound of Space, the touch of the prana-air within, the sight of the inexhaustible Light, the[m
[32m+[m[32mNectarous Ambrosia flowing from the Sahasrara, inner divine scent etc. - when any such[m
[32m+[m[32mtype of inner experience arises in consciousness, the mind no longer goes after external[m
[32m+[m[32mthings and remains steadily in that. Among these, one of the highest methods is this:[m
[32m+[m[32mcoming to the place of ahamkara through the door of sushumna by Sadguru's instruction,[m
[32m+[m[32mhere one experiences: from the plane of the sun - an incredibly powerful, and from the[m
[32m+[m[32mplane of the moon - an incredibly lovely, and together - a Light of such sublime beauty[m
[32m+[m[32mthat experiencing it casts away all types of suffering and grief from the mind. For this[m
[32m+[m[32mreason, this has been called by great saints as "vishokajyoti" [the Light that ends grief]. If[m
[32m+[m[32mthis vishokajyoti is revealed and consciousness is surrendered in it, then the mind becomes[m
[32m+[m[32mcompletely steadfast and still.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHaving explained in these two sutras [Samadhipada - no. 35 and 36] about the method by[m
[32m+[m[32mwhich the mind can be tied to a certain thing and thereby gain steadiness, it is being[m
[32m+[m[32minstructed in the next two sutras [Samadhipada - no. 37 and 38] on how one can disengage[m
[32m+[m[32mthe mind from things and keep it still. By determining between imperishable and[m
[32m+[m[32mperishable things and allowing non-attachment to arise in relation to things of sound,[m
[32m+[m[32mtouch, sight, taste, smell etc., and disengaging the mind from all those things, the mind[m
[32m+[m[32mnaturally becomes still by itself. The way to make this condition more permanent is this:[m
[32m+[m[32mby the aforementioned technique received from Sadguru, the mind becomes happy and[m
[32m+[m[32mwisdom is established revealing: "there is no existence of anything in this Universe other[m
[32m+[m[32mthan Infinite Consciousness, but because jivas are covered in ignorance and are living as if[m
[32m+[m[32masleep, it is being imagined that there are many kinds of things that have subsistence and[m
[32m+[m[32mare being experienced." Realizing this experience with certainty, the mind becomes[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (10 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32munwaveringly still. Having instructed these four sutras to the Sadguru-graced sadhakas, in[m
[32m+[m[32mthe fifth sutra [Samadhipada - no. 39], teaching is being given on what to do to attain[m
[32m+[m[32mstillness of mind in sadhana if it is not possible to acquire the grace of Sadguru or the[m
[32m+[m[32maforementioned method. If one is not successful at being able to have the aforementioned[m
[32m+[m[32mtype of technique, then enjoining the mind's focus on any one thing which can deemed[m
[32m+[m[32mappropriate according to one's country, time and personal condition will also make the[m
[32m+[m[32mmind still. In this way, stilling the mind by some method and practicing keeping it in[m
[32m+[m[32mequipoise is called "practicing ektattva" in yogic scriptures. It has been expressed as[m
[32m+[m[32m"doing sadhana with a unified mind" in the Srimad Bhagavad Gita.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNow, if one reads these four slokas [Gita 6:11 through 6:14] intently, it can be clearly[m
[32m+[m[32munderstood that He has instructed to practice all of the aforementioned parts of yoga[m
[32m+[m[32maltogether at the same time in the manner of ektattva which is antidote to the obstacles to[m
[32m+[m[32myoga. The aforementioned four slokas are being explained below.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBy practicing ektattva, the counteraction to the obstacles to yoga - such as physical and[m
[32m+[m[32mmental problems, confusion etc. - unifying the mind, renouncing envy, fear etc.,[m
[32m+[m[32meliminating restlessness of mind through chastity, devoting oneself to God with a tranquil[m
[32m+[m[32mmind, disciplining oneself in cleanliness and such other niyamas, seating oneself in a[m
[32m+[m[32msanctified place on a seat which has kusha grass as its base, on top of which there is skin[m
[32m+[m[32mof deer or such animal, and on top of which there is some good quality cloth, sitting not to[m
[32m+[m[32mhigh and not too low, using a method of sitting that will keep the body, head and neck[m
[32m+[m[32mwithout movement and balanced as well as in comfort, withdrawing sight from all sides[m
[32m+[m[32mand putting it at the root of the nose, extinguishing all restlessness of the senses, preparing[m
[32m+[m[32mthe mind for concentration by purifying oneself, practicing the yogic technique of[m
[32m+[m[32mpranayam for the elimination of ignorance which covers Consciousness, concentrating the[m
[32m+[m[32mmind in Kutasthachaitanya and intently remaining enjoined in Its meditation,[m
[32m+[m[32mconsciousness becomes one with It. When by this type of absorption wisdom is realized,[m
[32m+[m[32msadhakas experience the Consciousness-Self as the Supreme Being, and live in Total[m
[32m+[m[32mAwakenedness united with that Atman-Consciousness. -11, 12, 13 and 14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      yunjannevam sadatmanam yogi niyatamanasah[m
[32m+[m[32m                      shantim nirvanaparamam matsamsthamadhigacchati -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      In devotion keeping mind on Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Effortlessly that yogi will cross the ocean of samsara -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      By the completely focused practice of the aforementioned parts of yoga, sadhakas[m
[32m+[m[32m                      continuously remain in union with Atman-Consciousness, and thus becoming permeated[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (11 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32min the Infinite Brahman-Consciousness, attain the form the Supreme Nirvana, the Abode[m
[32m+[m[32mof Tranquility - Kaivalya. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mnatyashnatastu yogohsti na chaikantamashnatah[m
[32m+[m[32mna chatisvapnashilasya jagrato naiva charjuna -16-[m
[32m+[m[32myuktaharaviharasya yuktacheshtasya karmasu[m
[32m+[m[32myuktasvapnavabodhasya yoga bhavati duhkhaha -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mEating too much or not eating[m
[32m+[m[32mExcessive sleep or keeping awake [without much sleep], yoga is not for him -16-[m
[32m+[m[32mFood, recreation, or sleeping or being awake[m
[32m+[m[32mOther types of activities, or moving about[m
[32m+[m[32mPerforming all these in moderation[m
[32m+[m[32mThat one attains yoga siddhi - the Supreme Nirvana -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThose who either eat too much or constantly fast, as well as those who sleep excessively[m
[32m+[m[32mor generally remain without much sleep are not able to have the revelation of[m
[32m+[m[32mConsciousness. Therefore, to unite with Consciousness, things such as eating, recreation,[m
[32m+[m[32msleep, being awake, and all present work to be done, should be carried out in an orderly,[m
[32m+[m[32mmoderate and balanced manner. If one is in Self-Kriya being able live in this moderate[m
[32m+[m[32mand balanced way, then all suffering is destroyed and consciousness becomes one with[m
[32m+[m[32mAtman-Consciousness. -16 and 17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32myada viniyatam chittamatmanyevavatishthate[m
[32m+[m[32mnisprihah sarvakamebhyo yukta ityuchyate tada -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe one whose consciousness is stilled in Atman[m
[32m+[m[32mHe is called in the scriptures as a yogi who is devoid of lust and desire -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe state of being where consciousness is devoid of all types of wanting for desirable[m
[32m+[m[32mthings, and is completely absorbed and stilled in Atman-Consciousness is what is called[m
[32m+[m[32mby the great saints as "the condition of being seated in yoga" [yogarudhavastha]. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32myatha deepo nivatastho nengate sopama smrita[m
[32m+[m[32myogino yatachittasya yunjato yogamatmanah -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (12 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj    www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe way a lamp burns in a place devoid of wind[m
[32m+[m[32mStays steady and does not waver[m
[32m+[m[32mThe one whose mind is steady in the same way[m
[32m+[m[32mHis yoga will bring him his salvation -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe saints who are knowledgeable in yoga compare the consciousness of a sadhaka seated[m
[32m+[m[32min yoga [yogarudha] to a lamp, the flame of which burns steadily and without perturbation[m
[32m+[m[32min a place devoid of wind. This means that as the lamp remains steady and without[m
[32m+[m[32mperturbation in a place devoid of wind, the consciousness of sadhakas seated in yoga and[m
[32m+[m[32munited with Atman-Consciousness also reside in that state of motionless steadiness. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      yatropraramate chittam niruddham yogasevaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                      yatra chaivatmanatmanam pashyannatmani tushyati -20-[m
[32m+[m[32m                      sukhamatyantikam yattadbuddhigrahyamatindriyam[m
[32m+[m[32m                      vetti yatra na chaivayam sthitashchalati tattvatah -21-[m
[32m+[m[32m                      yam labdha chaparam labham manyate nadhikam tatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                      yasmin sthito na duhkhena gurunapi vichalyate -22-[m
[32m+[m[32m                      tam vidyadduhkhasamyogagamviyogam yogasamjnitam[m
[32m+[m[32m                      sa nishchayena yoktavyo yogohnirvinnachetasa -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The place where yogic service is done with steadfast consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                      In that place effortlessly Atman is seen -20-[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The one with no danger of wanting pleasure[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The senses are under his power[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Surrendering mind and intellect to the Atman[m
[32m+[m[32m                      That one sees the True Eternal Form of Atman -21-[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The one who realizes Atman's True Form[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Other acquisitions, heat, cold, he does not need[m
[32m+[m[32m                      There is no relationship to pleasure and sorrow[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Know that this is the sign of yoga as decreed -22-[m
[32m+[m[32m                      That with which there is no connection of sorrow[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The unengaged consciousness certainly attains that yoga -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The state where consciousness, by the performance of yogakriya, arrests its own[m
[32m+[m[32m                      fluctuations and transcends all things; the state where sadhakas, experiencing their own[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Consciousness-Self, are content in That Itself, and thereby attain the Eternally Permanent[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Bliss of Brahman which is beyond the senses and even the intellect's grasp; compared to[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Which any joy of the highest nature of the world cannot be considered as any kind of joy[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (13 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mat all; the state, if attained, where no profound suffering that may be present can unnerve[m
[32m+[m[32mthe mind, and no other sorrow can even appear -- this state of being is what is called yoga.[m
[32m+[m[32mTo attain this state, one should, with an assured intellect and an unrelentingg[m
[32m+[m[32mconsciousness, perform Kriya as instructed by Sadguru. -20, 21, 22 and 23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32msamkalpaprabhavan kamamstyktva sarvanasheshatah[m
[32m+[m[32mmanasaivendriya gramam viniyamya samantatah -24-[m
[32m+[m[32mshanaih shanairuparamed buddhya dhritigrihitaya[m
[32m+[m[32matmasamstham manah kritva na kinchidapi chintayet -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe sadhana of that yoga will not be fruitless[m
[32m+[m[32mIn renunciation, all wants are cast off -24-[m
[32m+[m[32mSubjugate all senses within[m
[32m+[m[32mLittle by little, let go of relationship to things[m
[32m+[m[32mKeep the mind in Atman, do not think about anything[m
[32m+[m[32mStay wholly desireless always -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRenouncing with resolve and extinguishing all desires that arise, drawing within and[m
[32m+[m[32mcompletely controlling all functions of the sense-body, being patient and steadfast of mind[m
[32m+[m[32mand ending connection with all worldly things little by little, establishing the mind in[m
[32m+[m[32mAtman-Consciousness and thereby casting off all thought, reside securely in[m
[32m+[m[32mcontentment. -24 and 25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32myato yato nishchalati manashchanchasamasthiram[m
[32m+[m[32mtatastato niyamyaitadatmanyevam vasham nayet -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhatever place the restless and unsettled mind goes[m
[32m+[m[32mBring it back with surety and subjugate it in Atman -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhen the mind by its nature is influenced by the restless aspect of rajoguna and is thereby[m
[32m+[m[32munsettled, with wherever things it faces and becomes distracted, one should, by the[m
[32m+[m[32mSadguru-instructed Kriya, withdraw the mind from those things and bring it under the[m
[32m+[m[32mcontrol of the Self. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mprashantamanasam hyenam yoginam sukhamuttamam[m
[32m+[m[32mupaiti shantarajasam brahmabhutamakalmayam -27-[m
