[32m+[m[32mArjuna said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (16 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32myohyam yogastvaya proktah samyena madhusudana[m
[32m+[m[32metasyaham na pashyami chanchalatvat sthitim sthiram -33-[m
[32m+[m[32mchanchalam hi manah krishna pramathi balavaddhridham[m
[32m+[m[32mtasyaham nigraham manye vayoriva sudushkaram -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mArjuna said, listen Sri Madhusudan[m
[32m+[m[32mWith equipoise, the yoga about which You spoke now[m
[32m+[m[32mI cannot see patience coming because of restlessness[m
[32m+[m[32mWho has the capacity to perform such a yoga -33-[m
[32m+[m[32mThe cause of want in body and senses[m
[32m+[m[32mWho has the power to win this with steady mind[m
[32m+[m[32mAs a pot cannot hold the wind[m
[32m+[m[32mSimilarly, the mind cannot be kept at bay -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhen all this is experienced in Kutasthachaitanya, an experience happens in the energy of[m
[32m+[m[32mthe fire element that: although it is true that in the momentary tranquility attained by the[m
[32m+[m[32mafter-effect poise [par avastha] of different types of Sadguru-instructed Kriya one[m
[32m+[m[32mexperiences the Universe as the form of that Infinite Consciousness, one cannot see the[m
[32m+[m[32mnaturally restless mind, not being able to be still in one way for any length of time, as[m
[32m+[m[32mbeing steadfast for an extended period. Therefore, O Chaitanya!! [Consciousness] I[m
[32m+[m[32mconsider the complete focusing of this sense-desirous, naturally restless, uncontrollable[m
[32m+[m[32mmind for an extended period of time as impossible as stopping inhalation and exhalation. -[m
[32m+[m[32m33 and 34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      asamshayam mahabaho mano durnigrahachanchalam[m
[32m+[m[32m                      abhyasena tu kaunteya vairagyena cha grihyate. -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Govinda said, listen to what I say, Dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                      What you are saying is all true[m
[32m+[m[32m                      The turbulent and uncontrollable mind is very restless[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Who has the power to coerce it back in[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Wherever the mind goes whether true or false[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Bring it back from those places and establish it in Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                      By non-attachment become disinterested in things[m
[32m+[m[32m                      By these two is the power to control the mind -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      It is necessary to clearly explain the matters of practice [abhyas] and non-attachment[m
[32m+[m[32m                      [vairagya] which are mentioned in this sloka, because these two are the primary aspects of[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (17 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32myogic methods, or it can be said that all yogic methods are only the body and limbs of[m
[32m+[m[32mthese two. Therefore, some of what has been said about these two subjects by the most[m
[32m+[m[32mesteemed sages is being explained below.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mMaharshi Patanjali has written about this subject in the book named "Yogasutra" in this[m
[32m+[m[32mway: that just as when a certain type of substance is mixed with a different type of[m
[32m+[m[32msubstance, a change occurs in the natural condition of the original substance and thereby[m
[32m+[m[32mthat substance transforms to a mutated state, in the same way, when consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32mmingles with external matters of sound, touch, sight, taste and sound etc., it becomes[m
[32m+[m[32mattached to them and a change of its natural condition occurs, because of which it then[m
[32m+[m[32mexists in a distorted condition. Thus, if it is not able to abstain from all those things,[m
[32m+[m[32mconsciousness can never reside in its natural state.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf consciousness is able to abstain from things in order to remain in its natural state, then[m
[32m+[m[32mgradually, four states of being, one after another, arise in consciousness. First, by[m
[32m+[m[32mdiscerning the transitory nature of things and becoming aware of its own corrupted[m
[32m+[m[32mcondition, an effortful state emerges within consciousness, with consciousness wanting to[m
[32m+[m[32mattain its natural state of being. The scriptural saints call this effortful condition the[m
[32m+[m[32m‚Äúyataman avastha‚Äù of consciousness. After this, consciousness gradually continues to[m
[32m+[m[32mdiscard the causes of its distortions. This type condition of consciousness in the scriptures[m
[32m+[m[32mis called ‚Äúvyatirek avastha.‚Äù Then, the distorted conditions in consciousness that still occur[m
[32m+[m[32mbecause of attachment to previous tendencies [samskaras] from time to time even after[m
[32m+[m[32mhaving eradicated all causes [of corruption] are brought into awareness, and the state[m
[32m+[m[32mattained by consciousness from wanting to achieve peace from that is called in the[m
[32m+[m[32mscriptures as "ekindriyavastha." After that, when all distortions and even their samskaras[m
[32m+[m[32mare eliminated, a type of peaceful state of being is obtained where any types of matters[m
[32m+[m[32mrelating to visible things or supernatural intimations -- no kinds of desires for anything can[m
[32m+[m[32marise. Always, consciousness remains in its natural state. This is what the scripturral saints[m
[32m+[m[32mhave called as the "vashikar avastha" of consciousness. Maharshi Patanjali has called this[m
[32m+[m[32mvashikar avastha as having the same meaning as "vairagya" [non-attachment]. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m"drishtanushavikavishayavitrishnasya vashikarasamjnya vairagyam" - no. 15 - patanjal[m
[32m+[m[32myogasutre samadhipadah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mJust as when many children recite loudly and in unison, the recitations of those whose[m
[32m+[m[32mvoices are more physically strong are able to be heard, and those whose voices are subtle,[m
[32m+[m[32mmeaning mellow, are not able to be heard at all, in the same way, because mind[m
[32m+[m[32mexperiences many types of physical things and remains engaged in their momentary and[m
[32m+[m[32mminiscule happiness, it is unable to experience that extremely subtle and internal, Eternal[m
[32m+[m[32mKnowledge and Bliss. Thus, not attaining purity because of the mind totally being in the[m
[32m+[m[32mexperience of happiness from all kinds of material and physical things, that extremely[m
[32m+[m[32msubtle, Infinite Knowledge and Consciousness-Self in the Form of Bliss is not[m
[32m+[m[32mexperienced. Therefore, not being immersed in the corruption-causing external things and[m
[32m+[m[32mremaining in its natural state, consciousness is able to experience that infinite and eternal[m
[32m+[m[32mknowledge and the Consciousness-Self in the Form of Bliss. In this way, practicing[m
[32m+[m[32mresiding in the state of that Eternal and Infinite Form of Knowledge-Bliss of the Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32mConsciousness is what is referred to in the Patanjal Yoga Sutra as "abhyas" [practice]. As[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (18 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m"tatra sthitau yatnohabhyasah" - Samadhipada - no. 13[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIn this way, experiencing Atman-Consciousness, and continuously practicing residing in[m
[32m+[m[32mthe Bliss of Self-Knowledge, the desire for happiness connected with the enjoyment of[m
[32m+[m[32mphysical things is gradually eliminated, and consciousness resides in a state of[m
[32m+[m[32m"vashikar" [independent/sovereign], which is the emergence of what is synonymously[m
[32m+[m[32mknown as vairagya [non-attachment]. And if one can become devoid of the desire for[m
[32m+[m[32mhappiness connected with the enjoyment of physical things, meaning if the[m
[32m+[m[32maforementioned state of "vashikar", or the emergence of what is synonymously known as[m
[32m+[m[32mvairagya, occurs, then that Infinite Consciousness is experienced. Thus, without the[m
[32m+[m[32mpractice of experiencing Atman-Consciousness for a while, the emergence of vairagya is[m
[32m+[m[32mimpossible, and without such vairagya, the experience of Atman-Consciousness is also[m
[32m+[m[32mimpossible; therefore, both are unattainable. To resolve this unattainable condition it is[m
[32m+[m[32messential to take refuge in the Lotus Feet of Sadguru. With regular and disciplined[m
[32m+[m[32mpractice of their directives, as instructed in the 10th through the 14th slokas of this[m
[32m+[m[32mchapter, and engaging in the performance of yogakriya, in the state at the end of Kriya,[m
[32m+[m[32mmore or less, little by little, Atman-Consciousness is experienced for moments at a time.[m
[32m+[m[32mIn this way, experiencing Atman-Consciousness, mind attains stillness in the Bliss of Self-[m
[32m+[m[32mKnowledge. When mind is filled with the Bliss of Atman in such moments, it recognizes[m
[32m+[m[32mthe momentary enjoyment of happiness connected with physical things as extremely[m
[32m+[m[32mtrivial. If one can practice this experience of Atman-Consciousness ceaselessly for a long[m
[32m+[m[32mtime while being fully disciplined, chaste, reverent, devoted and doing good works with[m
[32m+[m[32mnon-attachment, then the state of the Bliss of Self-Knowledge becomes eternally present.[m
[32m+[m[32mMaharshi Patanjali has also written on this matter. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m"sa tu dirghakalanairantaryasatkarasevito dridhrabhumih" - no. 18 - patanjal yogasutre[m
[32m+[m[32msamadhipadah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWith the aforementioned Atman-Bliss-filled state at the end of the yogakriya acquired[m
[32m+[m[32mthrough the grace of Sadguru, having left behind the happiness connected with the[m
[32m+[m[32menjoyment of physical things, by which a type of care arises whereby the[m
[32m+[m[32m"yatamanavastha" is attained - the thread of vairagya appears in consciousness. If one[m
[32m+[m[32mdoes not attempt to corrupt consciousness again by thoughts of things associated with[m
[32m+[m[32msound, touch, sight, taste, smell, etc., and many such types of associations with bad[m
[32m+[m[32mcompany such as these, then by this type of practice, the second level of vairagya[m
[32m+[m[32mgradually arises in consciousness in the form of "vyatirekavastha," and progressively, after[m
[32m+[m[32mthe third level in the form of "ekendriyavastha" emerges, consciousness attains the[m
[32m+[m[32multimate end of vairagya - the "vashikaravastha." It is written in the Patanjal Yoga Sutra[m
[32m+[m[32mthat it is in this "vashikaravastha" that the knowledge of Purusha, meaning the incisive[m
[32m+[m[32mvision of Purusha-Prakriti, is born in the jiva, and from the understanding of that Prakriti-[m
[32m+[m[32mPurusha, the spoken and the unspoken, meaning creation and destruction, or even the[m
[32m+[m[32mdesire to be embodied are extinguished, the jiva attains that Eternal, filled with the Bliss of[m
[32m+[m[32mKnowledge, Brahman-ness. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m"tat parampurushakhyatergunavaitrishnyam" - Samadhipada - no. 16[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (19 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNow, the meaning of this sloka is this: even if mind is brought into stillness momentarily[m
[32m+[m[32mby yogakriya, the always-restless consciousness of the matter-oriented mind again[m
[32m+[m[32massumes its former condition; therefore, to quell the mind, meaning destroying this restless[m
[32m+[m[32mnature of mind, establishing stillness and experiencing the omnipresence of Total[m
[32m+[m[32mBrahman is tremendously difficult - there is no doubt about this. But by attaining the[m
[32m+[m[32mstillness at the end of the yogakriya acquired by Sadguru's grace, and continuously[m
[32m+[m[32mpracticing the experience of Atman-Consciousness with reverence and pure work, the state[m
[32m+[m[32mof Bliss of Self-Knowledge is realized, and the enjoyment of happiness connected with[m
[32m+[m[32mphysical things is understood as extremely trivial, and as the ultimate end of vairagya[m
[32m+[m[32m-"vashikaravastha" - becomes present, one becomes effortlessly aware that all of the[m
[32m+[m[32mCosmos is filled with Total Brahman-Consciousness. -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32masamyatatmana yogo dushprapa ity me matih[m
[32m+[m[32mvashyatmana tu yatata shakyohvaptumupayatah -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mControlling the mind without yoga is never successful[m
[32m+[m[32mWhen the mind is under control this kind of wisdom comes[m
[32m+[m[32mOne who takes care to control the mind[m
[32m+[m[32mThat one finds the path and way in yoga -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIt has been clearly explained in the commentary to the previous sloka that if wants to[m
[32m+[m[32mcontrol oneself, four states of being gradually arise in consciousness which are named,[m
[32m+[m[32m"yataman," "vyatirek," "ekindriya" and "vashikar." Among these states mentioned,[m
[32m+[m[32mMaharshi Patanjali has referred to the state named "vashikar" as being synonymous in[m
[32m+[m[32mmeaning to "vairagya" [non-attachment]. Now, in this sloka, the matters on that which[m
[32m+[m[32mhave been expressed as "vashyatma" or "samyatma" - which have been stated in regards to[m
[32m+[m[32mthe sadhakas whose consciousnesses are absorbed the condition of "vashikaravastha" - are[m
[32m+[m[32mbeing explained below.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIn the state of the Self-revealed Consciousness, it can be known that those who are[m
[32m+[m[32mimmersed in vairagya, meaning those whose consciousnesses have attained[m
[32m+[m[32m"vashikaravastha" -- by performing with great care the Sadguru-given way of yogakriya,[m
[32m+[m[32mthey realize the Self-revealed Consciousness state and arre able to live filled with the form[m
[32m+[m[32mof the Eternal Bliss of Knowledge. But those who are not adjoined in vairagya, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32mthose whose consciousnesses are inclined towards material things -- for them the[m
[32m+[m[32maforementioned state of being is ever unattainable. -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mArjuna said:[m
[32m+[m[32mayatih shraddhayopeto yogacchalitamanasah[m
[32m+[m[32maprapya yogasamsiddhim kam gatim krishna gacchati -37-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (20 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mkacchinnobhayavibhrashtashchhinnabhramiva nashyati[m
[32m+[m[32mapratishtho mahabaho vimudho brahmanah pathi -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mArjuna said, If you please, Yadupati[m
[32m+[m[32mNot victorious over the senses are the reverent great ones[m
[32m+[m[32mIf divine beings fall from the path of yoga[m
[32m+[m[32mNot successful, then what way can they find -37-[m
[32m+[m[32mThis world, the next world, are not[m
[32m+[m[32mWhat suffering they experience, having fallen in hell[m
[32m+[m[32mAs clouds going in many directions by the force of wind[m
[32m+[m[32mIn this way they wander about in samsara -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIt has concluded in sloka no. 70 of the second chapter of this book that: being bound to[m
[32m+[m[32mdesire and in order to enjoy the fulfillment of the matters of desire, jivas take birth again[m
[32m+[m[32mand again; and in this chapter this type of essence has been expressed which says that[m
[32m+[m[32mwhen Atman-Consciousness is experienced by the reverent performance of Sadguru-[m
[32m+[m[32minstructed yogakriya, mind becomes filled with the Bliss of Self-Knowledge and wants to[m
[32m+[m[32mleave behind the pleasures connected with the enjoyment of external things. Upon this,[m
[32m+[m[32mthis type of doubt arises in the fire element that: there are those who acquired the Bliss of[m
[32m+[m[32mAtman by the Sadguru-graced yogakriya, and by being enjoined in reverence of Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32mConsciousness, they wished to leave behind the paltry, momentary happiness connected[m
[32m+[m[32mwith the enjoyment external things; but because of the state of vairagya in the mind[m
[32m+[m[32mbecoming disrupted repeatedly, not being able to remain in Atman-Consciousness, they[m
[32m+[m[32mbecame faulty in their taking care, lackadaisical in their practice and never were they able[m
[32m+[m[32mto reside in the state of the Bliss-filled Eternal Knowledge. O Kutasthachaitanya! What[m
[32m+[m[32mwill be the way for them? Will these types of sadhakas who could not realize that[m
[32m+[m[32mSupreme Brahman-Substance and who, by having desisted sense-enjoyment, cannot take[m
[32m+[m[32mbirth in the desire-oriented creation be eternally in a delusion-drenched state, like broken[m
[32m+[m[32mclouds floating in space until they are destroyed at the time of Final Dissolution? -37 and[m
[32m+[m[32m38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      etanme samshayam krishna chettumaharsyasheshatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                      tvadanya samshayasyasya chetta na hyupapdyate -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      One who is restless on the path of Brahman, who is in a stupor[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Can he be reprieved of again being in samsara[m
[32m+[m[32m                      This doubt in mind is my ruin[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Who else but You can cut through this doubt -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                      Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (21 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mO Kutasthachaitanya! Without You, there is no possibility of ending this conflict; thus,[m
[32m+[m[32mYou are the One Who is able to expel this doubt of mine in every way -- meaning that[m
[32m+[m[32mwhen this type of doubt rises up in the fire element, in order for it to be removed, sadhakas[m
[32m+[m[32mtrust Kutasthacchaitanya in this way . -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32mpartha naiveha namutra vinashastasya vidyate[m
[32m+[m[32mnahi kalyanakrit kashchiddugatim tata gacchati -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mGovinda said, Partha listen to this wisdom[m
[32m+[m[32mNot in this world, nor in the next is he destroyed[m
[32m+[m[32mHow can one who is on the path of sannyas be destroyed[m
[32m+[m[32mEver he is who believes -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mUpon trusting Kutasthachaitanya, this type of experience happens: those who for their[m
[32m+[m[32mown beneficence, meaning for the revelation of Atman Consciousness, have become[m
[32m+[m[32mimmersed in the Sadguru-given yogakriya and have been able to experience even a little[m
[32m+[m[32mexperience of Consciousness -- there is never condemnation for them. That[m
[32m+[m[32mConsciousness-experience of theirs cannot - not in this body, nor after the boddy, nor by[m
[32m+[m[32manything - be destroyed. -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mprapya punyakritam lokanushitva shashvatih samah[m
[32m+[m[32mshuchinam srimatam gehe yogabhrashtohbhijayate -41-[m
[32m+[m[32mathava yoginameva kule bhavati dhimatam[m
[32m+[m[32metaddhi durlabhataram loke janma yadidrisham -42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPerforming this yoga regularly[m
[32m+[m[32mEven if one cannot do that, it is greater than other things[m
[32m+[m[32mLiving in the land of gods for eternity[m
[32m+[m[32mIs born in the house of the pure and holy -41-[m
[32m+[m[32mThe engaged yogi's path is thus[m
[32m+[m[32mListen now to what I say in the middle of all this[m
[32m+[m[32mAfter living in heaven, birth takes place in the house of yogis[m
[32m+[m[32mThis the priceless birth in this world -42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (22 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBecause of not being able to practice residing for long periods of time in the Bliss of the[m
[32m+[m[32mAtman-Self and not being able to fully realize vairagya, meaning that because their[m
[32m+[m[32mconsciousnesses were not yet able to renounce the tendencies and inclinations of external[m
[32m+[m[32mmatter and thereby were not able to attain the vashikaravastha and were not able to[m
[32m+[m[32meternally experience the infinite Bliss of Knowledge-filled Brahman-Consciousness all at[m
[32m+[m[32monce, according to each one's greater or lesser experiences of Consciousness, some such[m
[32m+[m[32msadhakas take birth in houses of high beings who are pure of mind, successful in living[m
[32m+[m[32mwithout lack, and are fit for the yoga of Consciousness; some take birth in the houses of[m
[32m+[m[32mSadguru-graced Kriyavan sadhakas, and some take birth in the houses of those wise ones[m
[32m+[m[32mwho are filled with Eternal Bliss and are absorbed in the yoga of Consciousness. Such[m
[32m+[m[32mtypes of births in this physical world are extremely precious. -41 and 42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mtatra tam buddhisamyogam labhate paurvadehikam[m
[32m+[m[32myatate cha tato bhuyah samsiddhou kurunandana -43-[m
[32m+[m[32mpurbabhyasena tenaiva kriyate hyavashohpi sah[m
[32m+[m[32mjijnasurapi yogasya shabdabrahmativartate -44-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAcquiring wisdom from the previous body[m
[32m+[m[32mBy the habit of past practice, yoga is done bound to that -43-[m
[32m+[m[32mThose whose minds enquire into the path of yoga[m
[32m+[m[32mHe claims nothing in karmayoga[m
[32m+[m[32mWith great care he meditates with determination[m
[32m+[m[32mNo connection to sin remains in his body -44-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHaving taken birth in these types of situations, fixing the mind to Consciousness because[m
[32m+[m[32mof yogic habits from the previous body, they again take care to ascend in the yoga of[m
[32m+[m[32mConsciousness; and some, without effort and by themselves, go beyond all Vedic rituals,[m
[32m+[m[32mand enquiring into the techniques of yoga in order to become united with the Eternal, Bliss[m
[32m+[m[32mof Knowledge-filled Brahman-Consciousness, become engaged in the performance of[m
[32m+[m[32myogakriya as was practiced in the previous body. -43 and 44-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mprayatnad yatamanastu yogi samshuddha kilvishah[m
[32m+[m[32manekajanmasamsiddhastato yati paraam gatim -45-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe yogi who with great effort takes care in yoga[m
[32m+[m[32mPurified and without sin[m
[32m+[m[32mAfter many births that human being becomes perfected[m
[32m+[m[32mThen goes to attain the All -45-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (23 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThrough many births in this way, gradually ascending with great care along with[m
[32m+[m[32mpracticing self-discipline, after all impurities of mind are eliminated, such yogis reside in[m
[32m+[m[32mthe ultimate end of vairagya - vashikaravastha - and attain the Supreme Way, meaning the[m
[32m+[m[32mform of the Eternal, Bliss of Knowledge-filled Brahman-Substance. -45-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mtapasvibhyohdhikoyogi jnanibhyopi matohdhikah[m
[32m+[m[32mkarmibhyashchadhikoyogi tasmadyogi bhavarjuna -46-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe one who performs severe austerities of the body[m
[32m+[m[32mThe yogi is greater than that ascetic[m
[32m+[m[32mThe yogi is beyond the scholars and those who perform actions[m
[32m+[m[32mTherefore, be a yogi, Dhananjaya -46-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThus, as yogis are superior to the austerity performing ascetics, the scriptural scholars[m
[32m+[m[32mwith knowledge from outside sources, or the fire-ceremony-performing Vedic ritualists,[m
[32m+[m[32mone should take refuge in the Lotus Feet of Sadguru and, with the aid of the fire element,[m
[32m+[m[32mperform yogakriya. -46-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32myoginamapi sarvesham madgatenantaratmana[m
[32m+[m[32mshraddhavan bhajate yo mam sa me yuktatamo matah -47-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPoetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mYogis who are devoted to other gods[m
[32m+[m[32mTaking the mind from there and establishing it in Me[m
[32m+[m[32mAbsorbed in reverence, the one who always meditates on Me[m
[32m+[m[32mHe is known as the greatest yogi in the three worlds -47-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCommentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThose who surrender mind, intellect etc. and the inner senses in Atman, and practice[m
[32m+[m[32mresiding in Consciousness-Self with reverence, they very quickly attain that Infinite, Bliss[m
[32m+[m[32mof Knowledge-filled Brahman-Substance. This is what is experienced in the Most[m
[32m+[m[32mSupreme Kutasthachaitanya. -47-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSUMMARIZED DESCRIPTION OF CHAPTER 6[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter6.html (24 of 26)4/18/2006 2:42:06 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf the mind stays immersed in Kutasthachaitanya in the aforementioned manner, then even[m
[32m+[m[32mmore is experienced, such that: when the cessation of the fluctuations of consciousness is[m
[32m+[m[32mexperienced via the practice of yogakriya, the very practice that yogis should do is to[m
[32m+[m[32mprevent the reemergence of that [the fluctuations] and rest in that state [of tranquility]. In[m
[32m+[m[32mthis perspective, yoga and sannyas are not different. Those who are not attracted to the[m
[32m+[m[32msense-oriented things of sound, touch etc. or sense-oriented acts, who have renounced the[m
[32m+[m[32mdesire for their fruits and who have fulfilled only what needs to be dutifully done, those[m
[32m+[m[32mwho have renounced all desire and doubt of body, mind and even up to speech -- they are[m
[32m+[m[32mthe ones who are yogis, and they are the ones who are sannyasis or renunciates. Without[m
[32m+[m[32mthis kind of renunciatioon there is no becoming a yogi or a sannyasi by just renouncing[m
[32m+[m[32maccording to the methods of the Vedas or society [1 - 4]. In this world, one is one's own[m
[32m+[m[32mfriend and one is one's own enemy. When one can remain enjoined in Kutasthachaitanya,[m
[32m+[m[32mone can rescue oneself as one's own friend from all sorrows of the world; this is what the[m
[32m+[m[32mjiva should do; the jiva should not instead break off from Consciousness and become[m
[32m+[m[32menveloped by the sorrows of the world [5 - 6]. Kutasthachaitanya sadhakas, who are[m
[32m+[m[32mvictorious over their senses, experience in this way the Substance beyond scriptural[m
[32m+[m[32mknowledge, become fully content, and residing completely and in profound Tranquility in[m
[32m+[m[32munion with the Supreme Substance, know gold, earth, stone etc. as undifferentiated[m
[32m+[m[32mConsciousness, and thereby are unperturbed by [the seeming differentiations of] friend,[m
[32m+[m[32menemy, saint, wicked, cold, heat, pleasure, sorrow, honor, shame etc. [7 - 9]. With one-[m
[32m+[m[32mpointed focus of mind, alone in a solitary place, following the practices of not taking from[m
[32m+[m[32manyone, chastity, continence, cleanliness etc., sitting on a seat of grass, skin and cloth,[m
[32m+[m[32mkeeping body, neck and head still and steadfastly concentrating by techniques such as[m
[32m+[m[32mfocusing at the root of the nose, and thereby withdrawing all senses and their associations,[m
[32m+[m[32mfastening consciousness in Kutasthachaitanya, and continuously remaining engaged in Its[m
[32m+[m[32mmeditation, become one with that Supreme Nirvana-Form in the Abode of Tranquility, the[m
[32m+[m[32mInfinite Consciousness [10 -15]. This type of yogakriya is not within the capacity of those[m
[32m+[m[32mwho overeat or fast, or those who oversleep or do not sleep at all. If one can perform this[m
[32m+[m[32mwhile maintaining eating, recreation, sleeping, waking, work, effort etc. with regularity,[m
[32m+[m[32mthen all sorrow is eradicated [16 - 17].[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThus ends the sixth chapter of the yogashastra upanishad Srimad Bhagavad Gita with[m
[32m+[m[32manalysis via various scriptures of this country and the West, along with spiritual[m
[32m+[m[32mcommentary.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                       Yoganiketan, Portland Maine , USA ¬© 2002[m
[32m+[m[32mAll Rights Reserved by Yoganiketan for any material published on this website.[m
