[32m+[m[32m                                 CHAPTER SEVEN[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 VIJNANAYOGA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       mayasaktamanah partha yogam yunjanmadashrayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asamshayam samgram mam yatha jnasyasi tacchrinu -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Mind attached always to Me[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            Doing yoga with refuge in Me[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     There is no doubt, listen to this wisdom[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   In that you will know the Supreme of all -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If consciousness is immersed in Kutasthachaitanya in the previously-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        mentioned way, even more is experienced, such that: residing in[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        Consciousness-Self and performing yogakriya with mind deeply absorbed in[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        the Atman, the all-pervading Infinite Consciousness with Its glorious,[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        miraculous, mighty power is revealed in complete clarity. -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        jnanam tehham savijnanamidam vakshyamyasheshatah[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        yajajnatva neha bhuyohnyaj jnatavyamavashishyate -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I will tell you the highest knowledge of the matters in scriptures[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing which, there is nothing left to be known in the world -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter7.html (1 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:07 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  In this way, if one is successful in experiencing the knowledge of Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  Consciousness as mentioned in the scriptures, then nothing remains to be[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  known in creation; the Cosmos is acquired, as if in the palm of one's hand. -[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  2-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  manushyanam sahasreshu kashchid yatati siddhaye[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  yatatamapi siddhanam kashchinmam vetti tattvatah -3-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Among thousands and thousands of people who is fortunate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Engaged in the Knowledge of Brahman with care[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In thousands of those, some know me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Lord of All, the refuge of All, the Supreme God -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Among thousands and thousands of human beings, rarely is there one who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 takes care to seek on the matters of Consciousness, and, even among the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 many of these types of human beings who know the Consciousness-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Substance through their search, rarely is there anyone who, through Spiritual[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge [tattvajnana], is able to experience this all-revealing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya. -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhumirapohnalo vayuh kham manobuddhireva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahamkara itiyam me bhinna prakritirashtadha -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aparayemitastvanyam prakritim viddhi me param[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jivabhutam mahabaho yayedam dharyate jagat -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Earth, water, fire, air, space[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Mind, intellect, ego - these eight[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This is called Prakriti, say all the Vedas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 What is beyond this, I will tell you - listen of that which penetrates Prakriti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Para Prakriti it is called, know this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That which is holding samsara -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The two fundamental aspects which compose this Cosmos, by which the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Cosmos exists, comprise the subject that is being elucidated in this sloka.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now, discussing how this matter has been analyzed in philosophical treatises[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 will make it possible to clearly understand this subject; for this reason, those[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter7.html (2 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:07 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 analyses are being explained below in a condensed form.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the philosophical and scientific treatises of this country and the West, it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 has been concluded that this Cosmos with its innumerable solar systems has[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 been created by two fundamental substances. One is material-substance[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (matter), and the other is Consciousness-Substance (Spirit). Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness (God the Father), or the part/piece of Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness (Son), or Its Cosmos-revealing Kutasthachaitanya (the Holy[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ghost), is the Eternal Substance beyond and before creation (ever existing).[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman-Consciousness, or Its part - jiva, or Its revelatory aspect -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya (God, Son, and Holy Ghost) - these three substances are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not different things; they are one thing only; and, the fundamental causes of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 creation - matter and Consciousness (matter and Spirit) - these two are also[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not separate things from That; they are only Its two Prakriti-aspects, or Its[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Shakti.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Although this material-Prakriti (matter) is not able to do the work of creation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 completely on its own, because of its proximity to Param Purush, like iron in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the proximity of a magnet, it becomes imbued with Consciousness (spirited)[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and is transformed into a new type of substance. This new substance is that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 which is the primary cause of creation - known as "mahat tattva." For this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reason, the saintly scriptural scholars refer to this as "mahattattva." As in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Samkhyadarshan -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "sattvarajastamasam samyavastham prakritiprakritermahan" etc. -- no. 59[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "tat sannidhanadadhishthatritvam manivat" -- no. 94 ity vishayadhayah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Material-Prakriti itself, having been imbued with Consciousness and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 transformed into the form of mahattattva, moves towards Consciousness as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 iron in the proximity of a magnet, and in the process of transforming into[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness, an effort-quality or energetic quality arises. The saintly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scriptural scholars call this energy/effort-endowed part of the mahattattva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "buddhi" [loosely - intellect]. Its function is dharma. That which is known as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "dharma" while residing in the state of the revelation of Consciousness-Self[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 has been explained in the commentary to the fifth sloka of the fourth chapter[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of this book. It is with the help of this energetic-quality-endowed part of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mahattattva - the action of the buddhi - that the revelation of Consciousness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning Kaivalyapada, is attained. Because of the solidifying of the previous[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samskaras [inclinations or impressions] of this very mahattattva, the other[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 parts become somewhat colored and become transformed to work counter to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that [the actions of buddhi], meaning "adharma" [not-dharma], which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 becomes the manifestation of the many types of created forms of things. It is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this contrary functioning part that the saintly scriptural scholars call[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "mana" [loosely - mind]. In this way, the same Consciousness-imbued[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 material-Prakriti, or mahattattva, is itself referred to by the two names of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "buddhi" when enjoined with the effort-energetic quality, which is dharmic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or holy, and when solidified and colored as "mana," which is non-dharmic or[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter7.html (3 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:07 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the created form. As in Samkhyadarshan -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "adhyavasayo buddhih" -- no. 13[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "tatkaryam dharmah" -- no. 14[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "mahaduparagadviparitam" -- no. 15 -- ity pradhana karyadhyayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "mahadadyam karyam tanmanah" -- no. 69 -- ity vishayadhyayah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When material-Prakriti becomes imbued with Consciousness and is thus[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 transformed into the aforementioned form of mahattattva, a type of self-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 consciousness - "I am a separate thing" - arises. The saintly scriptural[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scholars call this extreme type of self-conscious vanity or such[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 transformation of material-Prakriti as "ahamkar." As in Samkhyadarshan -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "charamohamkarah" -- no. 70 -- ity vishayadhyayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "abhimanohhamkarah" -- no. 16 -- ity pradhana karyadhyah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [Translator's note: In the next paragraph, as well as throughout the body of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the book, there are differently written variations of the gunas commonly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 written as "rajas" and "tamas" and their extensions such as "rajaguna" or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "rajoguna." These variations have been transliterated as they have appeared[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in their various forms, including their expressions as multiple words or as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one compound word.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, from a state in which the three gunas are in a neutralized*[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 condition, Prakriti becomes polarized,* and transformed into the dharmic-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and non-dharmic-elements-embodying ahamkar, and because of this, sattva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (neuter), raja (positive) and tamah (negative) - these three gunas arise; and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this rajoguna is endowed with the capacity of action and is mixed with sattva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and tama gunas. In this way, the one polarized Prakriti, transformed into the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dharmic- and non-dharmic-elements-embodying form of ahamkar, is imbued[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with sattva, rajasic sattva, raja, rajasictama and tama, and because of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 imbuing by these five types of gunas, the saintly scriptural scholars refer to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 each guna-embodying part with individual and separate names; meaning: the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tamaguna-embodying part is called "kshiti" or "bhumi" [earth]; the rajasic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tamaguna-embodying part is "ap" [water or liquid]; the rajaguna-embodying[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 part is called "teja" or "anel" [energy/fire]; the rajasic sattvaguna-embodying[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 part is called "marut" [air]; and the sattvaguna-embodying part is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "vyom," "akash" or "kha" [ether or space]. They have delineated [these parts][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by these five names. In Vedantadarshan, these have been expressed as the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 five elements.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [*Translator‚Äôs note: The words ‚Äúneutralized‚Äù and ‚Äúpolarized‚Äù are in English[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the original, but are enclosed in parentheses, indicating them to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 definitions of their Bengali counterparts. The parenthetical occurrences - ( ) -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the previous paragraph of this translation are in the original and the words[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 within them are in English in the original. The bracketed words in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 previous paragraph - [ ] - are the translator‚Äôs, and they are explanations of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sanskrit words appearing before them.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter7.html (4 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:07 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This Universe is built from this permutation of ahamkar, or the five elements[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 which have themselves been converted into the five subtle elements. Beyond[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the aggregate of the five sattvic parts of these five subtle elements is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 eleventh sense - mind; and everyone‚Äôs five sattvaguna parts spawn the five[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 organs of perception, and the five rajoguna parts create the five organs of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 action; and in everyone, the five tamaguna parts create the five matters, or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 just the five working in five ways with each other, manifesting as the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 physical elements in the form of that which can be partaken of for the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purpose of the aforementioned eleventh sense's partaking, and thus, these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [together] make up the construction of the Cosmos in its many different[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 forms. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "tatkaryatvamanyeyam" -- no. 71 -- ity samkhyadarshane vishayadhyayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "ekadasham panchatanmatram tatkaryam" -- no. 17[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "sattvikamekadashakam pravartate vaikritadahamkarat" -- no. 18[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- ity samkhyadarshane pradhana karyadhyayeh[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "gunabhavadvyajamano mahana pradurvabhuvaha" -- ity vayupurane[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "sattvamshaih panchabhistesham kramaddhindriyapanchakam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shrotratvagakshirasana ghranakhyamupajayate" -- no. 19[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "rajohmshaih panchabhistesham kramat karmendriyanitu[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vakpanipadapayupasthabhidhanani jajnire" -- no. 21[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "tadbhogaya punarbhogya bhogayatanajanmane[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 panchikaroti bhagavan pratyekam vishayadikam" -- no. 26[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- ity panchadashyam tattvavivekah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, from the state of the neutralized condition of the three gunas, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one material-Prakriti itself, having become enjoined with Consciousness, is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 endowed with an effort/energy quality by which it becomes the dharmic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "buddhi," then the manifestation-oriented [adharmic] "mana," and thereafter[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the combination dharma and adharma - "ahamkar"; and due to the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 permutation of the three gunas mentioned, and the active capacity of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 energy of rajoguna, "kshiti" [earth or solid], "ap" [water or liquid],[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "teja" [fire or heat], "marut" [air or gaseous] and "vyom" [ether or space] -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these eight forms [including "buddhi," "mana," and "ahamkar"] are imbued[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with the gunas, and by their manifested work has this world-Brahmanda been[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 constructed. But it is because of the presence of the aforementioned[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-Power [Chaitanyashakti] that all of creation, even atomic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 particles, are alive, and thus continue to properly sustain this Universe. A[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 momentary lack of this Chaitanyashakti results in all atomic particles in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world-Brahmanda to become devoid of power, whereupon this vast[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda contracts and the Cosmos becomes completely non-existent.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, this infinite Cosmos with Brahmanda has only been constructed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by the previously-mentioned permutation of the physical-Shakti enjoined[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with the eight qualities, but it is existing in living form upon having taken[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 recourse in this Consciousness-Power. The way that Maharshi Vyasdev has[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter7.html (5 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:07 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 expressed the above-mentioned spiritual essence in these two slokas is being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 explained below.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Earth, water, fire, air, and space, and mana [mind], buddhi [intellect] and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahamkar [ego] - these eight-essence-enjoined material-Prakriti, by whose[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 permutated substance this world-Brahmanda is comprised -- that is only a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 small physical-Shakti of Infinite Consciousness; but there is another[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-Power - Chaitanyashakti - because of taking recourse in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 which this Cosmos is existing in a living form -- that is what is known as the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Supreme Power of the Universe-pervading Infinite Consciousness. -4 and 5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etadyonini bhutani sarvanityupadharaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aham kritsnasya jagatah prabhavah pralayastatha -6-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mattah parataram nanyat kinchidasti dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mayi sarvamidam protam sutre manigana iva -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Listen - the elements that arise from this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In Me dissolve these three worlds -6-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There is nothing greater than Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Know this with certainty, Dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Strung to Me are the three worlds[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The way that jewels are strung to thread -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The material-Prakriti [physical-Nature], by whose mutation all things of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Universe have arisen, and that which, having taken recourse in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-Nature [Chaitanyaprakriti], is existing filled with life -- both[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are only the Power of that Infinite Consciousness; therefore, that Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness is that which is the place oon which this world-Brahmanda[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 emerges, and if this Prakriti-mutation is destroyed either because of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 passage of the ages or by some other cause, then this world-Brahmanda[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dissolves in that very Infinite Consciousness; thus, this all-pervading Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness is also this vast Cosmos' place of dissolution. Therefore,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nothing in this Cosmos is greater than this all-pervading Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness. Like jewels strung to thread, this immense Cosmos with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda is existing because of the Presence of that Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness. -6 and 7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rasohhamapsu kaunteya prabhasmi shashisuryayoh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pranavah sarvavedeshu shabdah khe pourusham nrishu -8-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 punyo gandhah preithivyancha tejashcasmi vibhavasou[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jivanam sarvabhuteshu tapashchasmi tapasvishu -9-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bijam mam sarvabhutanam viddhi partha sanatanam[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter7.html (6 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:07 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 buddhirbuddhimatamasmi tejastejasvinamaham -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am the liquidity of water, the radiance of the sun and moon[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Listen, O Pandava, I am the glowing essence in human beings[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the four Vedas, I am in the form of the Pranava [OM][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the form of sound I am in space -8-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The austere happiness of the ascetics austerity on Earth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am the heat in fire, the life in all -9-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am the intelligence in the intelligent, the Cause of All[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The brilliance of the brilliant, I am Eternal and Beginningless -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All things and even all aspects of those things - internal and external - of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aforementioned enormous Brahmanda-Cosmos and its miniscule part, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 microcosmic form of the body, are existing as manifested because of the all-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 revealing Kutasthachaitanya. This Kutasthachaitanya is present as the all-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pervading, Self-Knowledge-revealing Pranava [OM], as Life in all creatures[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 including human beings, and as the Radiance of the lords and gods of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 subtle world - sun, moon etc. In physical creation, this Kutasthachaitanya is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 present as the sound which is manifesting the very subtle (rarified) all-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pervading space, as the energy/heat-essence which is manifesting the fire-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 like substances, and the pure fragrance which is the essence of the hard[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 (solid) Earth. This Kutasthachaitanya is present as the life-force in all living[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 creatures, as austerity in the ascetic with the capacity to withstand cold, heat,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 conflict etc., as wisdom in the intelligent, as brilliance in the brilliant ones,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and even as the Cause of the reemergence of this Cosmos after its dissolution[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 - even in that, It Is. -8, 9 and 10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 balam balavatasmi* kamaragavivarjitam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dharmaviruddho bhuteshu kamohsmi bharatarshabha -11-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ye chaiva sattvika bhava rajasastamasashcha ye[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 matta eveti tan biddhi na tvaham teshu te mayi -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [*Translator's note: The first line of sloka 7:11 in some renditions of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bhagavad Gita is written as: "balam balavatam chaham kamaragavivarjitam"][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The strength of the strong that is beneficent[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am the lust where there is nothing adulterous -11-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The essences - sattva, rajas and tamas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From Me do all of them emanate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am not in them; I am beyond all gunas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From Me do all things come into being -12-[m
[32m+[m
