[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The desire and the pure, unattached, sattvic strength of the powerful ones,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and the natural ways of all creatures which are necessary for the maintenance[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the body, such as the desire for food etc., and even all of the sattvic,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajasic and tamasic qualities by which this Universe is appearing -- all of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these are existing as manifested because of having taken recourse in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutasthachaitanya; but Kutasthachaitanya is eteernally and gracefully[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 existing by Itself, with no dependence on anything. -11 and 12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tribhirgunamayairbhavairebhih sarvamidam jagat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mohitam nabhijanati mamebhyah paramavyayam -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of the nature of the three gunas, all is forgotten by the world[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Do not know Me; I am beyond the three gunas -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because all creatures of the world-Brahmanda are absorbed in the delusion[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 caused by the previously-mentioned triumvirate of sattva, raja and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tamogunas, they are not able to experience that Immutable, Eternal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-Substance beyond the three gunas. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 daivi hyesha gunamayi mama maya duratyaya[m
