[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Because they take up the path of Consciousness - the most excellent thing of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   life - these four types of sadhakas are the highest. But among them, the one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   who, upon having listened to, thought about, and intensely meditated upon[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   the matters of Atman from the scriptures and the words of Sadguru, acquires[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter7.html (9 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:07 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 non-experiential knowledge of the Self from others and thus takes up the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 path of Consciousness -- he, knowing Atman-Consciousness as the only[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 substance of devotion and the Supreme Way, offers all his affection to It[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with great love, and always taking refuge in It, residing with mind merged in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It, attains the realization of that Infinite Consciousness. -17 and 18-[m
