[32m+[m[32m                                 labhate cha tatah kaman mayaiva vihitan hi tan -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In whatever form, whichever devotee meditates upon Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Intensely desiring [Me] always[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When reverence is born in his steadfast mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With that reverence he worships -21-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am within all those gods[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, I am the fruit of all -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, when the minds of jivas, to obtain the fruits of each one's own[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desire, wish to manifest some senses-ruled bodily joy, or wish to manifest[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happiness through devotion to some part of Consciousness, meaning - when[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the mind's sattvic condition (neutralized state) is transformed and becomes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 active (polarized) with a guna such as rajas, by Kutasthachaitanya, the proper[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reverence appears in jivas‚Äô minds, and upon having the enjoyment of that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 miniscule part of Consciousness, jivas are bestowed capability. In this way,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 having obtained some capability from Kutasthachaitanya, the rich rewards[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that jivas receive from having executed such work are also for the purpose of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 satisfying jivas' minds, meaning - for the purpose of establishing the mind[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 again in its natural state, and such happens also by Kutasthachaitanya. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 extensive description of this appears in the commentary to the 70th sloka of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the second chapter of this book. -21 and 22-[m
[32m+[m
