[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvabhutani sammoham sarge yanti parantapa -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the physical body is pleasure born[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All jivas become attached because of desire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In those things from sorrow is loathing born[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With self-effort, Knowledge destroys pleasure, sorrow, afflictions[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this net of delusion is one happy or miserable[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Caught in illusion, the jiva is taken by Time -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Possessing a physical body in creation, because of affection towards[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 favorable matters and repulsion towards unfavorable matters regarding that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body, jivas remain entranced by the many types of afflictions such cold, heat,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pleasure, sorrow, etc. -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yesham tvantamatam papam jananam punyakarmanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 te dvandvamohanirmukta bhajante mam dridhatah -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That sanctified person who has no sin[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without sin, cold, heat, pleasure, sorrow[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In steadfast devotion, he meditates upon Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Easily he goes to the Supreme Abode -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Among the Sadguru-initiated Kriyavan sadhakas, those who have been able[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to tear away the veil that covers Consciousness -- they are the ones who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become liberated from the above-mentioned problems of cold, heat, pleasure,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sorrow, etc., and with oone-pointed mind, establish themselves in that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Infinite Consciousness. -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jaramaranamokshaya mamashritya yatanti ye[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 te brahma tadviduh kritsnamadhyatmam karmachakhilam -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter7.html (13 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:07 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 To conquer birth, old age and death[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Always they meditate, contemplate upon Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Later, gradually knowing Para-Brahman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Effortlessly they know all, having become Self-Realized -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who, in order to attain liberation from the many types of distressing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sufferings of samsara such as old age, death etc., take refuge in that Eternal,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bliss-of-Knowledge-filled Infinite Consciousness and reside in That --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gradually becoming purified in heart and experiencing Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness as the Soul of this entire Universe, as a resullt of that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhana, they come to know all workings of the Universe. -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhibhutadhidaivam mam sadhiyajnancha ye viduh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prayanakalehpi cha mam te viduryuktichetasah -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In gods and yajna and all elements[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is Me they know in those different forms[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Owing nothing at the time of their death[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Easily they find Me in all -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, those who are able to experience that Eternal Bliss-of-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge-filled Infinite Consciousness as the Lord of the quintelemental[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 physical body, the subtle body and all works -- they are the ones who,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because of always residing in Atman-Consciousness, experience that Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness at the time of leaving the body and remain filled with Eternal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bliss. -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   SUMMARIZED DESCRIPTION OF CHAPTER 7[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   If mind is absorbed in Kutashta in the previously mentioned way, it is known[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   that there are very few people in the world who take care to attain the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   revelation of Consciousness-Self; rarely is there one who is able to do that.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   How that person comes to know that Glorious Infinite Consciousness and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   thereby becomes aware of all things in the Universe is being explained [1-3].[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Creation, samsara - all - having been constructed by a small, material-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Prakriti aspect - these eight types of essences: earth, water, fire, air, ether,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   mana, buddhi and ahamkar - of that Infinite Consciousness, are existing as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   alive because of being imbued with another Supremely High Prakriti of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Consciousness. Both of these Prakritis have emerged from that Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Consciousness, and they also dissolve in That; there is nothing greater in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Cosmos beyond That; like jewels strung on thread, this Cosmos is existing[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter7.html (14 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:07 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 on That [4-7]. This Kutasthachaitanya makes all physical elements appear in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 creation. It is present in that as sound, as radiance in the presiding lords of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the subtle world, such as the sun and moon, as life in living creatures, as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 might in the mighty, as the wish for jivas to create bodies, meaning the life-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 force, as the humanhood in human beings, and as OM, the revealer of Self-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge; even at the culmination of dissolution, it is That who exists as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Seed for the reemergence of the Cosmos. This cause of creation,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 preservation and dissolution - the sattva, raja and tamagunas - is also[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 emanating from Kutasthachaitanya, but It is gracefully residing as Eternal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and Immutable [8-12]. Ignorant human beings, being entranced by the Mayic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 three gunas, remain bound, with demonic nature, in the experience of ego-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 self-consciousness. Even though this three-guna-filled Maya is difficult to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 traverse, by the performance of Sadguru-initiated Kriya, it can be easily[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 crossed [13-15]. The sick, those who crave material enjoyments, the seekers[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Truth and the wise -- these four types of human beings are of the highest;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they take up the path of Consciousness. Among them, the wise ones aree the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 highest of all; this type of birth is priceless in this world. After many[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 lifetimes of accumulating good samskaras, by always remaining absorbed in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-Self with complete love and devotion, they easily attain the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realization of Infinite Consciousness [16-19]. Being infatuated with each[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one's own samskara-bound desires and in order to fulfill them, jivas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 accomplish the very temporal enjoyment of bodily pleasure ruled by some[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sense, or some other small part of Consciousness through reverence to ego-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 self-consciousness, and because of that, they experience the joy of that. In[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that, the inner power of the body becomes scattered and soon, one has to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 immersed in the ocean of sorrow. But, upon the revelation of Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness, all enjoyment of the body, senses and all parts of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness are fulfilled in their totality, and the Bliss of Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manifests as Eternal and Endless [20-23]. Being with a body made by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Maya-united created-substances, human beings become stupefied by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 favorable and unfavorable matters - like and dislike - concerning that body,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and because of that, unable to experience that Immutable Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness upon which all elements of the present, past and future appear[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and disappear, they deem it to be unmanifested and manifested [24-27].[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those Kriyavan sadhakas whose Consciousness-covering veil has been torn[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 off -- they, in order to be liberated from the sufferings of samsara such as old[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 age, death, etc., take refuge in Atman-Consciousness with one-pointed and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fully engrossed mind, and going above the physical aspect, the subtle aspect,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and yajna, they come to know that Brahman-Consciousness, all spiritual[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 things, and all the workings of the Cosmos by meditating upon them, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 thus they discard their bodies while being merged in the Eternal, Bliss of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge [28-30].[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the seventh chapter of the yogashastra upanishad Srimad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bhagavad Gita with analysis via various scriptures of this country and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 West, along with spiritual commentary.[m
[32m+[m
