[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and even ego has been clearly explained in the eighth sloka of the fourth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chapter. Now, the significance of this sloka is this: those who, in the above-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mentioned way by the Grace of Sadguru, have gone beyond the Wheel of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Maya and completed one kalpa - meaning the Kriya of one day of Brahma -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in their own elemental bodies, and thereby experienced the dissolution of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 each one's mana, buddhi, chitta and ahamkar, and then inverting it, have[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 been able to be again present in a body-form -- they are the ones that the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 saintly scriptural scholars call "ahoratrajna" [knower of "aho ratri"]. -17-[m
