[32m+[m[32m                                 The One who pervades all creation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 On Whom the world is spread[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Param Purusha - He is Most Merciful[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Devotion to Him and no other - attains Him, Dhananjaya -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The One Who is residing as Omnipresent in this creation and Cosmos, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One with whose recourse the totality of all elements up to the ultimate exists[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- that Complete Infinite Consciousness can be attained by one-pointed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 devotion; there is no other way to experience That. --22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatra kale tvanavrittimavrittinchaiva yoginah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter8.html (10 of 15)4/18/2006 2:42:08 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prayata yanti tatkalam vakshyami bharatarshabha -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The way of death in which the yogi is never reborn[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dying in the way when there must again be rebirth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I will you the difference in them; listen, great one of Bharat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dying remembering Me is always the same -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The kind of way that yogis are once and for all liberated from samsara, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the kind of way by which they have to again take birth in samsara is being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 explained in summarized form. -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 agnirjyotirahah shuklah shanmasa uttarayanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatraprayata gacchanti brahama brahmavidojanah -24-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhumoratristatha krishnah shanmasa dakshinayanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atra chandramasam jyotiryogi prapya nivartate -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the bright fortnight during the day of the summer solstice[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Close to fire and in the presence of the sun[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who discards life by yoga[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing Brahman, attains Brahman -24-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the dark fortnight at night in a dark place[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If in the winter solstice the karmi releases life[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For a long time enjoys heavens and chandraloka and such[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Then again takes birth in this samsara -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In previous commentaries it has been explained that sadhakas call the upper[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 part of this body as "north" and the lower part of this body as "south"; and in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the 69th sloka of the second chapter it has been stated that because at the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time of the awakened state of the phenomenal world - meaning the day-part[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Brahma - Atman-Consciousness is covered by a corrupted state, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhakas of Self-Knowledge perceive that time to be "night"; and at the time[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 which is the night-part of Brahma - because at this time the entire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 phenomenal world is dissolved and Atman-Consciousness is revealed in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Totality, the sadhakas of Self-Knowledge perceive this time as "day." Now[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the meaning of this sloka is this: the time when Consciousness-Self, as Fiery[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Energy and as Radiant Light, having annihilated the elemental aggregates,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pierces through the six chakras and rises above -- that is the time which is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 most excellent. It is at that time that Brahman-realized sadhakas discard their[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bodies and bbecome the Beingness of Infinite Consciousness. All those[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter8.html (11 of 15)4/18/2006 2:42:08 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhakas who, being attached to the fulfillment of desire, have been unable[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to dissolve the aggregate of elements and thus have been unable to realize[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman-Consciousness -- they become covered with the darkness of illusion,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and at the time of leaving the body, unconsciously descend through the six[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chakras, because of which thoughts of sense-objects arise, and they again[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 take birth in samsara. -24 and 25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shuklakrishne gati hyete jagatah shashvate mate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ekaya yatyanavrittimanyayavartate punah -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Whoever is a sinner always goes to hell[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Devotees always get Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The white and black ways are always in this world[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By one path there is liberation, in the other not -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For all phenomena of this world up to the ultimate, there always exists two[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 types of paths: white - meaning higher - and black - meaning inferior. By[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 taking one of these paths sadhakas attain Nirvana once and for all; and by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 taking the other path, they have to again take birth in samsara. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 naite sriti partha janan yogi muhyati kashchana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasmat sarveshu kaleshu yogayukto bhavarjuna -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who know these two paths, Partha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Such yogis are never deluded[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Discard all other karma for good[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Take up yoga; be liberated by that -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Being established in Atman-Consciousness, if sadhakas are able to become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aware of both of these white and black paths, then nothing can delude them[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in this world; therefore, to attain liberation from the sufferings of samsara,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one should always abide in Atman-Consciousness. -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vedeshu yajnashu tapahsu chaiva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 daneshu yat punyaphalam pradishtam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atyeti tat sarvamidam viditva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogi param sthanamupaiti chadyam -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter8.html (12 of 15)4/18/2006 2:42:08 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The recitation of the Vedas, penance, yajna offerings - the fruits of each of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Now you know that the yogi wins over all these[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Before All, Eternal - the Highest is My Abode[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He attains it easily and is not reborn -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Whatever beneficence and joy can be obtained by studying all the Vedas,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 performing all types of yajnas, all types of austere penances, and all types of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renunciation -- the sadhakas established in Atman-Consciousness experience[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all that in the Supreme Atman-Bliss, which is beyond all those practices, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in the end, they even go beyond Prakriti and attain the Highest Nirvana and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman-ness. -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   SUMMARIZED DESCRIPTION OF CHAPTER EIGHT[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   After the previously-mentioned type of experience in Kutasthachaitanya, this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   type of question arises in the energy of the fire element: what are Brahman,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   adhyatma, adhidaiva, adhibhutkarma and adhiyajna? And in what way do[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   they exist in this body? And how do sadhakas with absorbed minds, filled[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   with the total realization of Brahman, leave their bodies? [1 - 2] Answering[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   that, this type of experience happens in the Kutasthachaitanya of sadhakas:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   The Imperishable Infinite Consciousness which is beyond creation is what is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   known as Brahman; and within creation, His causal-body-based life-element[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   without permutation is adhayatma; the ever-transforming form of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Cosmos is His physical essence adhibut; and His inner-residing, Lord of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   creation form as the subtle essence is called adhidaiva. The sum total of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   phenomena, rising out of the Consciousness-Being - the Omkar Sound - is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   the only Self-Kriya; and the One, taking Whose recourse brings about the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   emergence of that Omkar Sound -- that Kutasthachaitanya is the One Who is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   adhiyajna. He abides in this Cosmos as the Highest of All [3 - 4]. At the time[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   oof leaving the body, the thoughts that become established in the mind of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   jiva because of the united power of many types of samskaras -- attached to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   and according to that conglomeration, the jiva takes birth in samsara.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Therefore, if Brahman-realization is established at that time, then Brahman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   ness is what is attained. There is absolutely no uncertainty about this.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Therefore, one should always remain in Kriya with mind surrendered in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Kutasthachaitanya [5 - 7]. The one who, by yogic practice, with devoted[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   heart and by the Sadguru-bestowed method, holds prana between the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   eyebrows and abides in that Omniscient, Ruler of All, Lord of the Universe,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   beyond the buddhi and even the supremely subtle Prakriti, the Supreme,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Beginningless, Perfect, Self-Revealed Infinite Consciousness, and leaves his[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   body thus -- he becomes Brahman [8 - 10]. The practitioners who are devoid[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   of affinity etc., withdraw their senses, still the fluctuations of mind, merge[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter8.html (13 of 15)4/18/2006 2:42:08 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prana into the Brahmarandhra with certain dharana methods, and by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 constantly meditating on the all-Cosmos-pervading, sum total of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 physical, subtle, causal phenomena, the Ishwar-Consciousness Word of OM[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- they leave their bodies and attain that Abode of Kaivalya, the Immutable[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 subject spoken of by the realized ones [11 - 13]. Even after attaining[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmaloka, because of Supreme Contentment being still unsatisfied, such[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jivas again and again take birth in creation; but the sadhakas who with one-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pointed mind remain engrossed in the meditation of Atman-Consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and thus attain that Beingness of Eternal Consciousness -- they never again[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 have to return to this samsara, the abode of sorrow [14 - 16]. The Cosmos[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manifests for millions of years in the day of Brahma and for millions of years[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 it remains in a dissolved state in the Inexpressible Nature during the night of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahma. The sadhakas who, having crossed over the Wheel of Maya through[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the sacrament of Sadguru and with one-pointed devotion, have experienced[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that All-pervading Supreme Substance of Atman Consciousness - the One[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Who is Immutable throughout the repeated creation and destruction of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 phenomenal aggregate, and the Sustainer of the entire Cosmos -- they never[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 again have to become slaves to creation [17 - 22]. Because they are deluded[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with the fulfillment of desire, inferior jivas are unconscious, due to which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they become attached to sense-objects and thereby have to come back to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samsara; and elevated sadhakas, because they remain in the Fiery and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Powerful, Radiantly Effulgent, Self-Revealed Atman Consciousness, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fully satisfy all sensory desire and having no need to come back to samsara,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they abide in the Indestructible Peace. These two types of good and evil[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ways are always present in the world [23 - 26]. The little bit of joy that is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 obtained through the study of the Vedas, yajna, austere penance, charity etc.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- because sadhakas by the Sadguru-graced method reside in that Atman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness - the abode of the totality of all those joys, nothing is able to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 delude them [27 - 28].[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the eighth chapter of the yogashastra upanishad Srimad Bhagavad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gita with analysis via various scriptures of this country and the West, along[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with spiritual commentary.[m
