[32m+[m[32m                                 CHAPTER NINE[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 RAJAGUHYAYOGA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       idantu te guhyatamam pravakshyamyanusuyave[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanam vijnanasahitam yajjnatva mokshasehshubhat -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I say to you, when empty of seeing blame is one wise[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            With devotion, the Knowledge of Self[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     Says Govinda this is deeply hidden[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   Knowing it you will cross the impure, material world -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When sadhakas, by complete absorption of the heart in Kutastha, become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 empty of hate, condemnation and such evil tendencies, thereby attaining the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experience of that Infinite, Incomprehensible, Supreme Consciousness-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Substance written about in scriptures -- when this direct Knowledge is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realized, they are able to be liberated from the life- and death-oriented,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 suffering-filled ssamsara. -1-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        rajavidya rajaguhyam pavitramidamuttamam[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        pratyakshavagamam dharmyam susukam kartumavyayam -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        With devotion, the Knowledge of Self[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        Of all secrets this is the highest of great wisdom[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        It is known clearly, with easy practice[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        Imperishable fruit it gives, the highest of dharma -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (1 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  This Infinite, Incomprehensible experience of Atman-Consciousness is the[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  greatest of all knowledge and the bestower of the highest Bliss; It is attained[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  with easy practice; It's fruit is directly experienced and permanent. -2-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  ashraddhahah purusha dharmasyasya parantapa[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  aprapya mam nivartante mrityusamsaravartmani -3-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  Poetically:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who has no reverence for this incomparable dharma[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Not attaining Me, he gets the falseness of samsara -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Human beings who are irreverent, devotion-less, engaged in evil doings,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being devoid of the Eternal Bliss-of-Knowledge from the experience of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman-Consciousness, and being enmeshed in the craving for pleasure and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyment, are again and again enslaved by life and death in this samsara. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 maya tatamidam sarvam jagadvyaktamurtina[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 matshtani sarvabhutani na chaham teshvavasthitah -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From Inexpressible Form - I have created[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The expanse of samsara in expressible form[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All work of Mine are in Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Like the sky, I am not in them -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Beyond the senses, Consciousness-Self is pervading this entire Cosmos; the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 totality of the Cosmos is existing, up to the ultimate, because of being in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman-Consciousness; Atman-Consciousness' existence is not by being in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 any created thing. -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na cha matsthani bhutani pashya me yogamaishvaram[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhutabhunna cha bhutastho mamatma bhutabhavanah -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Look, Pandava, nothing is in Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 My Glory is causing all happenings[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All are obeying My Being[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (2 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Not being in anything nor holding anything -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The mystery of creation is such that, even though that Infinite Consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is the Self in all created things and is manifesting them by holding them and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ruling over them, It is not bound to the created things and is residing as not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in them; and even though these created things are internally and externally[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 soaked in Consciousness, they become un-Conscious and endlessly travel[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 through samsara via birth and death. -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yathakashashtito nityam vayuh sarvatrago mahan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatha sarvani bhutani matsthanityupadharaya -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As air is in the sky and everywhere[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In that way are all things in Me -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Just as air within the omnipresent sky can travel everywhere and is powerful,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 but exists separately and unmixed with anything, it that way, this Universe,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 although residing in that Unattached Infinite Consciousness, is bound by un-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness and existing in that way. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvabhutani kaunteya prakritim yanti mamikam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kalpakshaye punastani kalpadou visrijamyaham -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 At the time of dissolution, all things dissolve in Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 At the beginning of Kalpa, I create them again -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 At the end of the Kalpa - meaning at the time of dissolution after thousands[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Maha Yugas - all created things existing in this Universe, up to the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ultimate, with the three gunas equalized, dissolve into that Infinite Nature of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Infinite Consciousness, and at the beginning of the Kalpa - meaning at the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time of creation - the three gunas become distinguished from each other and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are transformed into the innumerable forms of created things. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   prakritim svamavashtabhya visrijami punah punah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   bhutagramamimam kritsnamavasham prakritervashat -8-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (3 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ruling Prakriti while unseen[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I create all things again and again -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, all things existing in the Universe, up to the ultimate, because[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they are bound by the power of previous samskaras, adopt the three gunas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 according to their particular condtions, and again manifest in the form of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 created things. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na cha mam tani karmani nibadhnanti dhananjaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 udasinavadasinamasactam teshu karmasu -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Indifferent, I am not attached to anything[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For this reason, no one can bind Me -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because Consciousness is not attached to anything in all of this creation,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness resides as not in it and abides in aloofness. -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mayadhyakshena prakritih suyate sacharacharam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hetunanena kaunteya jagadviparivartate -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 As many mobile and immobile creatures as there are in the world[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of My proximity are brought forth by Prakriti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For this reason, listen son of Kunti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Effortlessly the Cosmos is created again and again -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Simply because of Consciousness‚Äò presiding, by the three gunas of Prakriti,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this Cosmos of mobile and immobile creatures, even though they are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dissolved over and over, are created again and again. -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avajananti mam mudha manushim tanumashritam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 param bhavamajananto mama bhutamaheshvaram -11-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 moghasha moghakarmano moghajnana vichetasah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rakshasimasurinchaiva prakritim mohinim shritah -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (4 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I have taken on the human body[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 For this reason the ignorant disregard Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 They do not know that I am the Lord of All[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 They are without devotion, all is My play -11-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Quickly the ignorant will receive the result of his indulgence[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Serving other gods than Me, his hopes are useless[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Like demons and monsters, deluded[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Whatever he does is contrary to happiness -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those human beings who have become stupefied by the want of enjoyment[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because of their nature being permeated with affinity and repulsion etc., who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are engrossed in the activities that bring about the useless hopes of happiness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and useless partaking in samsara, and who have become unconscious by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 useless arguments of scriptural knowledge -- those unwise ones, not being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 able to experience the Supremeness of Atman-Consciousness - meaning that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 only Consciousness exxists indivisibly as this entire Cosmos and the world-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmanda up to the ultimate, think that the abidance of Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness in the human body is insignificant and do not give that any[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attention. -11 and 12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mahatmanastu mam partha daivim prakritimashritah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhajantyananyamanaso jnatva bhutadimavyayam -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Partha, those who are the sattvic great saints[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing the Lord of the Universe, meditate upon Me -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing that only Consciousness-Self is the Indestructible and Eternal[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Substance and the Cause of the totality of all things up to the ultimate, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 great saints take refuge in Its elevated prana-of-the-world-form astral nature[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and worship [upasana] with one pointed devotion while abiding in the Self. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   satatam kirtayanto mam yatantashcha dhriravratah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   namasyantashcha mam bhaktya nityayukta upasate -14-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   jnanayajnena chapyanye yajanto mamupasate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   ekatvena prithaktvena bahudha vishwatomukham -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Some worship Me through chanting[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Some worship Me with many rites[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (5 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 To know Me they take steadfast care[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 They devote themselves and prostrate themselves -14-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing the Universal Form of Vasudeva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thinking as separate or thinking as one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In this way, many devotees worship[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Some in sensory ways, some with service -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In these two slokas, the practice of "upasana" [commonly: worship], as has[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 been understood by great knowledgeable saints, towards that Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness has been written about .. Therefore, what "upasana" is, who is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 decreed to be worshipped, and what is even the need for it -- these matters[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 should be addressed first. "Upasana" - this word is comprised of "up" and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "aas." "Up" means "nearness" andd "aas" is used to mean "establishing."[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus, the meaning of the word "upasana" can be understood to be: "being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 near." Now, who should be worshipped and for what reason or its necessity[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etc. is being gradually explained.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The only necessity for the jiva, meaning the being, is the cessation of all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 types of sorrows from the adhibhautic [physical], adhidaivic [subtle] and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adhyatmic [causal] essences. For this reason, the extinguishing of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 threefold sorrow is what has been called in Samkhyadarshan as the purpose,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or necessity, of the being. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 trividhaduhkhanivrittirartha purushanam - 1:1[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 To negate adhibhautic sorrow, the jiva again and again partakes in the usage[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of cuisine, haberdashery etc.; to end adhidaivic sorrow, it partakes again and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 again in the desirable things of sound, touch, sight, taste, smell etc.; and to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stop adhyatmic sorrow, the jiva again and again engages in activities such as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being in the company of the opposite sex. Because all these sorrows are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 temporarily ended by partaking in these desired things, these enjoyments are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 thought to be accomplishments necessary for the being's life-purpose. But[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the wise have said that no type of sorrow born of desire is permanently[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 extinguished through the partaking of things of desire; whatever [cessation][m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happens stays only momentarily; immediately afterwards, like the ghee[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 oblation in fire, the sufferings burst afire again, this time with twice the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 force. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "na jatu kamah kamanamupabhogena shamyati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 havisha krishnavartmaiva bhuya evabhivardhate"[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If the jiva knew that by the partaking of these things of desire the force of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 triumvirate of sorrows would increase twofold, then it would never be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 engaged in that. The jiva does not want this kind of way of being. The type[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of negation of the triumvirate of sorrows that it wants is such that they can[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 never appear again. The jiva prays for the supreme substance of cessation,[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (6 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning the Supreme Nirvana. In Samkhyadarshan it has also been stated[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that the total ending of these three sorrows is the most important goal of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being or jiva. This supreme purpose of the being is the jiva's prayer. As in -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tribidhaduhkhatyantanivritti paramapurusharthah - 1:2[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In all types of philosophical scriptures, this has been concluded with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 certainty: that if one dies, then one must take birth, and if one takes birth, one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 will surely die. Therefore, the jiva, bound in this creation-samsara, cannot[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attain the Supreme Nirvana or the highest purpose of being while being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enslaved by birth and death. To attain this, it is necessary to liberated from[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 life and death. As in Samkhyadarshan -[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na drishta drishtattat siddhih nivrittehpanurattidarshanat - 1:3[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 utkaryadapi mokshasya sarotkarshah shrute - 1:5[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It has also been concluded by all types philosophical scriptures that: if the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jiva cannot abide in Kaivalyapada by not establishing himself in that Infinite[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness beyond creation, then he cannot ever attain that supreme[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purpose - meaning the complete cessation of all types of adhibhautic,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adhidaivic and adhyatmic sorrows - that Supreme Nirvana. Therefore, to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 accomplish this highest purpose, it is extremely necessary to do upasana of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciouness - meaning being near to Spirit. The eminent sages have[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 decreed this upasana of Consciousness as the only process to attain the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 highest purpose. Maharshi Vedavyas, in the 35th sloka - pertaining to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmayoga - of the third chapter of this book, has also said this: that it is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 good to die during doing upasana of Consciousness; one should not do[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 upasana to anything else; that is extremely dangerous.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is by taking up the paths of devotion [bhakti] and wisdom/knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [jnana] that one can practice upasana of Atman-Consciousness. In these two[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 slokas, Maharshi Vedavyas has taught us in one sloka the practice of upasana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by the way of devotion, and in the other, the way of wisdom/knowledge.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The sadhakas on the path of bhakti, after having become devoid of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 restlessness, having become steadfast, with one-pointed devotion and heart[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 completely engrossed, and always being engaged in the discussion of Spirit,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 stop being externalized and turn towards Atman, and thus always abide in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that Consciousness-Self. -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The sadhakas on the path of jnana, take their personal realizations - greater[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or lesser - revealed by yogic methods, where some experience the existence[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of Atman-Consciousness as separately residing in all the created things in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 forms of Brahma, Rudra etc., some experience the existence of the only[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 worshippable thing as Infinite Consciousness and oneself as the worshipper,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and some experience even oneself to be a part of that All-pervading[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness, and thereby knowing all things of creation to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unsubstantial and experiencing that only Atman-Consciousness exists, do[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (7 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 upasana to that Infinite Consciousness. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aham kraturaham yajnah svadhahamahamoushadham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mantrohhamahamevajyamahamagniraham hutam -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Listen, O Arjuna, to My words[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The description that I am All[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The fire rituals, pancha yajna and all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The nectar, the panacea are all My Form[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Mantra, ghee, fire, oblation are My Form[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing this one escapes the dark well of the world -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That Infinite Brahman-Consciousness is Itself the fulfilling medicinal things[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of this world such as food etc., the fulfilling funeral of the ancestral world,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and the fulfilling works of oblation and its ritual procedures - such as fire,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mantra and burnt offerings - of the subtle world, and It is even present as all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 types of Vedic fire-practice- and conception- based yajna etc. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pitamahasya jagato mata dhata pitamahah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vedyam pavitramomkar rik sama yajureva cha -17-[m
