[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The father, grandfather and mother of the world[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All these are Me, the bestower of the fruits of yajna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am the Pure Pranava of Knowledge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am all of the Vedas, listen O Pandava -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That Infinite Consciousness is this Universe's father, mother, grandfather and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Lord, and it is He Who is the Vedas - Rik, Sama, Yaju etc. and what is to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 known from them - Param Brahman, and the destroyer of all sins - the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pranava - the mighty resonance of Omkar - are simply Its Being. -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gatirbharta prabhuh sakshi nivasah sharanam suhrit[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prabhavah pralayah sthanam nidhanam bijamavyayam -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the world of the fruits of karma, I am the governor[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I see good and evil and keep order[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (8 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the place of enjoyment I am all goodness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I create the world and again destroy it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am the seed of all, the supporter of the Cosmos[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There is nothing besides Me in the three worlds -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That Infinite Consciousness is Itself the savior, supporter and Lord of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 goodness of all jivas up to the ultimate; It is He Who is the Witness of all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fruits of good and bad karma and their fulfillment; it is He Who is the Cause[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of this Cosmos' and samsara's creation, preservation and destruction. More[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 than that, it is He who is the profound Cause of this Cosmos' appearance and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 its dissolution. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tapamyahamaham varsham nigrihnamyutsrijami cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 amritachnaiva mrityushcha sadasacchahamarjuna -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am the heat as the sun, the rain of the clouds[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sometimes attraction, sometimes creation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The life in all, and the destruction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In every place I am in the physical and subtle forms -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That Infinite Consciousness Itself cools the world by rain from clouds, and it[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is He Who magnetizes as the sun and heats the world; it is He Who is the life[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and death, Lord of creation and Lord of destruction of this world; more than[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that, it is only He Who is residing in this unsubstantial, temporary and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 insignificant created matter which has emerged from that Beginingless,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Eternal Substance. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 traividya mam somapah putapapa[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajnairishtva svargatim prarthayante[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 te punyamasadya surendraloka[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mashanti divyan divi devabhogan -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The brahmin studies Rik, Yaju, Samavedas[m
