[32m+[m[32m                                 They do not stay in heaven forever and get suffering -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (9 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The soma-juice drinking brahmins who have studied the Rik, Sama and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Yajurvedas, by their Vedic rituals and worship of many sense-oriented types[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of gods, pray to Infinite Consciousness for heaven. After leaving the body,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 they acquire heaven and according to their karma, they satisfy the high types[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of heavenly bhoga. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 te tam bhuktva svargalokam vishalam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kshine punye martalokam vishanti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 evam trayidharmamanuprapanna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gatagatam kamakama labhante -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus enjoying much after a long time[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Benefits gone, again they are born on earth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Following the Vedas, all these desirous ones[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Come and go again and again from birth to birth; the enchainment remains -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 After enjoying immense amounts of heavenly pleasures, once the benefits of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 good works are gone, the aforementioned brahmins who subscribe to the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 three Vedas again return to the mortal realm. The Vedic ritualists, bound to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desire, continue forever to come and go in samsara again and again. -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ananyashchintayanto mam ye janah paryupasate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tesham nityabhuyuktanam yogakshemam vahamyaham -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who know that there is no one but Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Worship and contemplate Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The true yogi for whom there is nothing else[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I make the effort to bring that one to Union[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I take care of his needs present[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Destroy his sorrows, and more, I give him the treasure of liberation -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All those sadhakas who with one-pointed heart only do upasana on Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness -- their Consciousness-Self Itself manifests and preserves[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 their Awakened State; thus they are always united with Spirit. -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yehpyanyadevata bhakta yajante shraddhayanvitah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tehpi mameva kaunteya yajantyavidhipurvakam -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (10 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who worship other gods[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 They also worship Me, this is truly said[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Without the prescript of liberation attainment those people worship[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus contrary to the rules they worship -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All those reverent devotees who do upasana of other gods and not[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness -- it is the Atman [to Whom they worship], Who is not bound[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to rules, meaning that they also worship the Self. -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aham hi sarvayajnanam bhokta cha prabhureva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na tu mamabhijananti tatvenatashchya vantite -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am the enjoyer of all yajna, the Lord of all forms[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who do not have the special Knowledge of Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Doing penance and yajna they still descend[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the illusory dreadful samsara, and do not find the way -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Self is the Lord of all rituals and methods, and It is their enjoyer. It is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 because of not knowing the Truth of the Self through Knowledge that jivas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 again and again come and go in the creation-samsara. -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yanti devavrata devan pitrin yanti pitavratah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhutani yanti bhutejya yanti madyajinohpi mam -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Worshipping gods, one goes to the realm of the gods[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Worshipping the ancestral realm, one goes to the realm of the ancestors[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Worshipping ghosts, one goes to the realm of ghosts[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Doing upasana on Me, one gets Me -25-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who are devoted to ancestral rituals attain the subtle ancestral realm[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 from which this elemental world of ancestors has emerged. Those who are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attached to rituals of gods, attain the overlords of this Universe. But those[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who do upasana of Atman-Consciousness, become filled with Spirit, merge[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 into that Infinite Consciousness and thereby attain Brahman. -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (11 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 patram pushpam phalam toyam yo me bhaktya prayacchati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tadaham bhaktyupahritamashnami prayatatmanah -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who gives leaf, flower, fruit, water as offerings[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because of his devotion I receive them -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who with devotion use leaf, flower, fruit, water etc. to please Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness -- those heart-immersed sadhakas' Spirit, being satisfied with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that, manifests Itself to them. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yat karoshi yadashnasi yajjuhoshi dadasi yat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yattapasyasi kaunteya tat kurushvamadarpanam -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Whatever you do, O Partha, whatever you eat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Oblation, penance, whatever charity[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Offering all those to Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Burn away the forest of sins with the fire of Knowledge -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All those things such as Vedic oblations or tantric practices or any types of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 human endeavors that can be carried out, and the good and bad karmic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 results that must be fulfilled because of them -- all of those should performed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with the intention to please Atman-Consciousness. -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shubhashubhaphalairevam mokshase karmabandhanaih[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sannyasa yogayuktatma vimuktomamupaishyasi -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Renouncing sinful things through sannyas yoga[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 You will attain Me, crossing the terrible samsara -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sadhakas who use the particular methods of renunciation, by practicing such,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 become freed from the bindings of the fulfillment of good and bad results of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karma and attain the Beingness of Consciousness. -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samohham sarbhuteshu na me dveshyohsti na priyah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (12 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ye bhajanti tu mam bhaktya mayi te teshu chapyaham -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That Which is present equally and always in all things[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who knows Me with ceaseless devotion[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He is in me, I am also in him[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The supreme mystery, is what I tell you -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness-Self is residing equally in all things. Nothing is repulsive or[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dear to It. Whoever does upasana to Consciousness-Self with devotion -- it is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by that that his Consciousness is manifested, and thus, he is able to live in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Awakened State. -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 apichet suduracharo bhajate mamanyabhak[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhureva samantavyah samyagvyasito hi sah -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who is seen by everyone as of very bad character[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If he singularly meditates upon Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 He is a great saint, regard him as such[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Who meditates upon Me is the one who is fulfills all righteousness -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Even a person of the most base character who meditates with one-pointed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 heart upon Atman-Consciousness should be regarded as a sadhu because he[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 has taken up the Supreme Path. -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kshipram bhavati dharmatma shashvacchantim nigacchati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kaunteya pratijanihi na me bhaktah pranashyati -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who are devoted to the way of sattva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With steady mind and perseverance attained[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Many kinds of things are sounded in the enemy's camp[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bursting forth with praise, take a vow to that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Destroy the Kauravas in this way[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 My devotee never has to fear -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Because sadhakas absorbed in Infinite Consciousness abide in the dharma of[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (13 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman, they are never destroyed. Completing the fulfillment of their own[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prarabdha within a short time, they attain Infinite Peace. -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mam hi partha vyapashritya yehpi syuh papayonayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 striyo vaishyastatha shudrastehpi yanti param gatim -32-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kim punah brahmanah punya bhakta rajarshaystatha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anityamasukhamlokamimam prapya bhajasva mam -33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Low caste vaishyas, sudras, women and all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Taking shelter in Me will cross over samsara -32-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmins, royal sages and all holy people[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 What to say, will easily attain nirvana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 You are also a royal sage, son of Kunti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Renounce everything else and meditate upon Me -33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 What to say of the sanctified souls of brahmins and devoted kshatriyas? The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samsara-immersed vaishyas, or ignorant sudras, or women, or no matter any[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 type of sinner -- taking refuge in Atman-Consciousness also attain Kaivalya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 easily. Therefore, having come to this strife-causing and unstabble samsara,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 realizing Atman-Consciousness is absolutely imperative. -32 and 33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manmana bhavamadbhakto madyaji mam namaskuru[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mamevaishyasi yuktaivamatmanam matparayanah -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Poetically:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Always fix your mind only on Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 With devotion, worship Me alone[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Do worship to Me in this way, Partha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 You will have Me, and all suffering of samsara will be gone -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Enjoying that Infinite Consciousness Itself, being devoted to It and humbling[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 themselves to It, sadhakas surrender as offerings their minds and lives to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Spirit by the Consciousness-revealing Kriya and live filled with Atman-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness. -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 SUMMARIZED DESCRIPTION OF CHAPTER 9[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Keeping the mind absorbed in Kutastha in this way and becoming empty of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hatred and condemnation, this supreme happiness-giving, directly obtained,[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (14 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 highest of all, extremely secret, and greatest wisdom which is Spirit is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 experienced. Jivas are liberated by It from the sufferings of samsara. And[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 lacking It, the irreverent ones are repeatedly enslaved by life and death [1 -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 3]. Like air in the sky, Infinite Consciousness unabsorbedly pervades created[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 things and thus sustains and governs them. But the strange mystery is this:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 even though it is existing in Consciousness, the phenomenal world is abiding[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 un-Consciously [4 -6]. The Consciousness-imbued Prakriti keeps this three-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 guna-entranced phenomenal world under the power of ever-repeating[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 creation and dissolution; but Infinite Consciousness, being aloof and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 detached from the works of creation, is not enmeshed in that [7 -10].[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Stupefied by the hope of useless pleasure, or useless enjoyments of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indulgences, or useless argumentative scriptural knowledge, the ignorant[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ones acquire demonic characteristics, and not being able comprehend the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Supremeness of Infinite Consciousness, perceive It in the form of created[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 things [11 - 12]. But the ones of wisdom, knowing Infinite Consciousness as[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being before creation and Imperishable, take refuge in the subtle nature and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 do upasana - some in the dvaita [dualistic] form, some in the advaita[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [monistic] form, and some in many different ways. And devotees remain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 steadfast and engrossed, humbly worship That and do upasana while singing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Its praises [13 -15]. Infinite Consciousness Itself is the fulfilling wealth for[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this realm, the fulfilling funerals for the realm of the ancestors, and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fulfilling oblations and the articles of ritual for the realm of the gods; It is the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mother, father, grandfather and Lord of this world; It is the Knowledge of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pranava, and It is the three Vedas providing the way to that Knowledge, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is That Which is to be Known. It is in Him that this world's creation,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 preservation and destruction take place, and He is the Primordial Seed of all.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is He Who is the giver of heat and the creator of cold; and it is He Who is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 residing as the Creator and as the created things [16 - 19]. The brahmins who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perform Vedic rites perform yajna with the desire to attain the realm of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 heaven; attaining which, they partake in enjoyments in the manner of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gods, and after the benefits of good works end, they again acquire a physical[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 body. In this way, they are trapped over and over in samsara [20 - 22].[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Infinite Consciousness is the Lord of all rites and It is their enjoyer. No[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 matter what god is worshipped by one, beyond the rules, he is actually[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 worshipping that Infinite Consciousness. Whatever aspect to which one does[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 upasana, whether gods, subtle aspects, physical aspects, ghosts etc. -- one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attains that state of being. One who with one-pointed heart does upasana of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness -- his finds his Spirit Selff-revealed and is bestowed that state[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of being. It is because jivas do not know this that they are repeatedly bound[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by samsara [23 - 25]. Whoever uses whatever for the sake of Consciousness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by that itself Spirit is pleased; therefore, if one can submit all works of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 world to Spirit, then by that Spirit is pleased and one can attain the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Beingness of Consciousness. Thus, one no longer has to be trapped by the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fruits of good and bad karma [26 -27]. Even persons of the most vile[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 character, by doing upasana to Consciousness, within a short time become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 righteous in Atman and attain Infinite Peace; in this type of condition, they[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 should be considered as the highest of sages, because by them abiding in[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter9.html (15 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:09 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness, even though Infinite Consciousness is Omnipresent, It[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reveals Itself to them [28 - 31]. What to say of the sanctified souls of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmins and devoted royal sages, even the greatly downtrodden uneducated[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and farm laborers attain that Supreme Substance by taking up refuge in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Consciousness. Therefore, one should know Infinite Consciousness as the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Supreme Substance, and with one-pointed mind and devotion, humbly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bowing to It and doing upasana to It, attain that Infinite Consciousness-filled[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman [32 - 34].[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the ninth chapter of the yogashastra upanishad Srimad Bhagavad[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gita with analysis via various scriptures of this country and the West, along[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with spiritual commentary.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 OM Shantih OM Shantih OM Shantih[m
