[32m+[m[32m                                 VIBHUTIYOGA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             [ Editor's Note------These last nine chapters of commentary consist of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 short, abbreviated notes which were done in Swami's own handwriting[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       and found after his passing. They were added to the later 1948 edition][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition                          bhuya eva mabaho shrinu me paramam vachah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yattehham priyamanaya vakshyami hitakamyaya -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  It is being experienced from Kutasthachaitanya: Again I speak to you who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are dear to Me for your welfare. -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na me viduh suraganah prabhavam na maharshyah[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        ahamadirhi devanam maharshinancha sarvashah -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        yo mamajamanadincha vetti lokamaheshvaram[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        asammudhah sa martyeshu sarvapapaih pramuchyate -3-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5                        Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        Many practitioners do not know; great sages do not know that I am the[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        Source of all gods and great sages - that the one who is not ignorant and[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        knows Me as Beginingless and All that is God-like, meaning the one who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abides in Consciousness -- he is the one who becomes liberated from all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sins. -2 and 3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 buddhirjnanamasammoha kshama satyam damah shamah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sukham duhkham bhavohbhavo bhayanchabhyameva cha -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter10.html (1 of 9)4/18/2006 2:42:10 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  Intelligence, knowledge, not being deluded by anything, forgiveness, truth,[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  breath, mental restraint, pleasure, the occurrence of sorrow, its non-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  occurrence, fear, fearlessness. -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  ahimsa samata tushtistapo danam yashohyashah[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  bhavanti bhava bhutanam matta eva prithagvidhah -5-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Non-violence, equanimity, contentment, austerity - meaning meditating upon[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutastha - charity, fame, disrepute - all these qualities happen to the five[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 elements; My Essence is different from these. -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 maharshyah saptapurve chatvaro manavastatha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 madbhava manasa jata yesham loka imah prajah -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The seven great sages (Marichi, Atri, Angira, Pulastya, Pulaha, Kratu,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pracheta) and the four Manus (Sanak, Sanatan, Sananda, Sanatkumar), by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 whom all this is, have been born from My Mind. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etam bibhutim yogancha mama yo vetti tattvatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sohvikampena yogena yujyate natra samshayah -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By this Knowledge, the one who knows My bibhutiyoga -- he is the one who[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 performs yoga. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aham sarvasya prabhavo mattah sarvam pravartate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ity matva bhajante mam budha bhavasamanvitah -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am the Lord of All, the Enjoyer, the Doer; all dissolves in Me; by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [knowing] this one also knows My Essence - meaning stillness. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 macchitta madagataprana bodhayantah parasparam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kathayantashcha mam nityam tushyanti cha ramanti cha -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When their minds have gone forth to Me, and when their prana vayus have[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter10.html (2 of 9)4/18/2006 2:42:10 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gone forth to Me - meaning have become still - then they understand[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 amongst each other and they speak of Me with contentment and delight. -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tesham satatayuktanam bhajatam pritipurvakam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dadami buddhiyogam tam yena mamupayanti te -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who is always united with Me (see 6:18) and who meditates upon Me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with love -- I bestow him with buddhiyoga - meaning stillness - by which, he[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is the one who attains Me. -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 teshamevanukamparthamahjnanajam tamah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nashayamyatmabhavastho jnanadipena bhasvata -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Whoever contemplates upon Atman has Grace bestowed upon him, by which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tamasic ignorance is destroyed and the Light of Knowledge illuminates. -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 param brahma param dhama pavitram paramam bhavan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purusham shashvatam divyamadidevamajam bibhum -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The energy of the body is saying, "You are the Param Brahman and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Supreme Abode," meaning beyond Which there is no abode, and, "You are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the One who is Purusha and Eternal, " meaning the Divine Brahman,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning the Great Void, the Primordial God Who is without birth. -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahustvamrishayah sarve devarshirnaradastatha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asitodevalo vyasah svayamshchaiva bravishi me -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The divine sage Narada and other great sages such as Asita, Devala, Vyas,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and You - Sri Krishna - meaning Kutastha - have said so. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvametadritam manye yanmam vadasi keshava[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na hi te bhagavan vyaktim vidurdeva na danavah -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter10.html (3 of 9)4/18/2006 2:42:10 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I believe all that You have said is the Truth -- that neither gods nor demons[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 know You. -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 swayamevatmanatmanam vettha tvam purushottama[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhutabhavana bhutesha devadeva jagatpate -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By Atman Itself You have shown the Self that You are the Lord of all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 phenomena and it is You Who is the Beloved Lord of the world of the gods[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- Purushottama. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vaktumaharsyasheshena divyahyatmabibhutayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yabhirbibhutibhirlokanimamstvam vapya tishthasi -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The miraculous visions that can be seen in the Sky/Space, that pervade all of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this plane, tell me of this. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 katham vidyamaham yogimstvam sada parichintayan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 keshu keshu cha bhaveshu chinthyohsi bhagavan maya -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In what way do yogis know You, and contemplate upon You, and in what[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 way can I contemplate? -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vistarenatmano yogam bibhutincha janardana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhuyah kathaya triptirhi shrinvato nasti mehmritam -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Please speak extensively to me again about the revelations that manifest due[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to Self-yoga, beyond the immortality of which there is nothing to be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 comprehended. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hanta te kathayishyami divya hyatmabibhutayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pradhanyatah kurushreshtha nastyanto vistarasya me -19-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is being experienced via Kutastha: I will tell you the primary ones; if I[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter10.html (4 of 9)4/18/2006 2:42:10 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 speak of these extensively, then there will be no end to it. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahamatma gudakesha sarvabhutashayasthitah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahamadishcha madhyancha bhutanamanta eva cha -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman is the very First - It's miraculous revelations - therefore Kriya is duty[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 - I am the beginning, middle and end of all phenomena. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adityanamaham vishnurjyotisham raviramshuman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 marichirmarutamasmi nakshatranamaham shashi -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vishnu among the sons of Aditi, meaning stillness, the radiance of the sun[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 among the luminous, meaning Brahman, the air within Marichi, the moon[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 among the stars. -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vedanam samavedohsmi devanamasmi vasavah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indriyanam manashchasmi bhutanamasmi chetana -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Sama Veda among Vedas, meaning abiding within the spine, the desire[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 within the gods, the mind among senses, meaning Brahman, consciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 within phenomena. -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rudranam shankarashchasmi vittesho yaksharaksharasam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vasunam pavakashchasmi meruh shikharinamaham -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Shankara [Shiva] among Rudras, meaning Kriya, Vittesha among the Yaksas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and demons, the purifying fire among Vasus, the summit among mountains.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purodhasancha mukhyam mam viddhi partha brihaspatim[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 senaninamaham skandah sarasamasmi sagarah -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brihaspati among the gods, Skanda among generals, meaning the six-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aspected Kriya, the ocean among rivers [bodies of water]. -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter10.html (5 of 9)4/18/2006 2:42:10 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 maharshinam bhriguraham giramasmyekamaksharam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajnanam japayajnohsmi sthavaranam himalayah -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bhrigu among the great sages, meaning Kutastha, ajapa japa among yajnas,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Himalaya among immovable things. -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ashvatthah sarvabrikshanam devarshinancha naradah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gadhrarvanam chitrarathah siddhanam kapilo munih -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Ashvattha among all trees, Narada among illumined sages, Chittraratha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 among Gandharvas, the sage Kapila among perfected beings [siddhas]. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ucchaih shravasamashvanam viddhi mamamritodbhavam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 airavatam gajendranam naranancha naradhipam -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ucchaihshrava among horses, Airavat among elephants, the king among[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 human beings. -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ayudhanamaham vajram dhenunamasmi kamadhuk[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prajanashchasmi kandarpah sarpanamasmi vasukih -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The thunderbolt among weapons, Kamadhenu among cows, Vasuki among[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 serpents. -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anantashchasmi naganam varuno yadavamaham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pitrinamaryama chasmi yamah samyatamaham -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Ananta among the Nagas, Yadav within Varuna, Arjuna among the heavenly[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 forefathers, samyamah among yamas, meaning dhyan, dharana, samadhi. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prahladashchasmi daityanam kalah kalayatamaham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mriganancha mrigendrohham vainateyashcha pakshinam -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter10.html (6 of 9)4/18/2006 2:42:10 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Prahlada among the Daityas, kalaya within kala, among deers - meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 among four legged mammals - the lion, Garuda among birds. -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pavanah pavatamasmi ramah shastrabhritamaham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jhashanam makarashchasmi srotasamasmi jahnavi -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The wind among purifiers, Parashuram among weapon-bearers, the Makar[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 among Jhashas, and Jahnavi among currents. -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarganamadirantashcha madhyamchaivahamarjuna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adhyatmavidya vidyanam vadah pravadatamaham -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am within the beginning and end of all - adhyatma vidya, meaning - the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mind abiding always in Atman is what is known as vidya [knowledge]. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 answer within the question. -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aksharanamakarohsmi dvandvah samasikasya cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahamevakshayah kalo dhataham vishvatomukhah -33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Among letters I am "A," the dual compound among compound words, I am[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 endless time, I am the Sustainer, I am happiness in the samsara of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Cosmos. -33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mrityuh sarvaharashchahamudbhavashcha bhavishyatam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kartih shrirvak cha narinam smritirmedha dhritih kshama -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Lord of death, the Lord of all destruction, the Lord of creation and the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Lord of the future, glory, countenance, the speech of women, memory,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intelligence, resolve, forgiveness. -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brihat sama tatha samnam gayatri cchandasamaham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 masanam margashirshohhamritunam kusumakarah -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter10.html (7 of 9)4/18/2006 2:42:10 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Brihat Sama of the Sama Veda, meaning exhalation for a long time; the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Gayatri among metric cadences, meaning Omkar Kriya; the Agrahayan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [November-December] month among months, the spring among seasons. -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dyutam cchalayatamasmi tejastejasvinamaham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jayohsmi vyavasayohsmi sattvam sattvavatamaham -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The cleverness in gambling, the fire of the fiery beings, victory, industry, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 goodness of the good. -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vrishninam vasudevohsmi pandavanam dhananjayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 muninamapyaham vyasah kavinamushanah kavih -37-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Vasudeva in the Brishni lineage, Dhananjaya among Pandavas, Vyas among[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sages, Ushana among poets. -37-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dando damayatamasmi nitirasmi jigishatam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mounam chaivasmi guhyanam jnanam jnanavatamaham -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The sentence and morality in ruling, silence among secrets, the knowledge of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the knowledgeable. -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yacchapi sarvabhutanam bijam tadahamarjuna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 natadasti vina syanmaya bhutam characharam -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The seed of all. All animate and inanimate phenomena arise from Me. -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nantohsti mama divyanam bibhutinam parantapa[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 esha tuddeshatah prokto bibhutervistaro maya -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There is no end to My divine revelations/manifestations. -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yadyad bibhutimat sattvam shrimadurjitameva va[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tattadevavagaccha tvam mama tejohmshasambhavam -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter10.html (8 of 9)4/18/2006 2:42:10 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All has happened from my Shambhavi Teja. Shambhu Trinetra, meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kutastha. -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 athava bahunaitena kim jnatena tavarjuna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vishtabhyahamidam kritsnamekamshena sthito jagat -42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 How much more should I say? This world is existing in the atom of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman. -42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the tenth chapter named "Bibhutiyoga."[m
