[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 CHAPTER TWELVE[m
[32m+[m[32m                                      BHAKTIYOGA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       evam satatayukta ye bhaktastvam paryupasate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ye chapyaksharamavyaktam tesham ke yogavittamah -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is being experienced in the energy of the body: The one who, being[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            constantly immersed in this way (see 6:38), worships with devotion, and the[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     one who meditates upon the Inexpressible and Imperishable Kutastha -- who[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   among these knows the highest yoga? Which is better among these - the[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  samadhi state after Kriya [Kriyar par samadhi avastha] - or Yoni Mudra? -1-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction                     Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        mayyaveshya mano ye mam nityayukta upasate[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        shraddhaya parayopetaste me yuktatama matah -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        It is being experienced via Kutastha: The one who whose mind enters Me[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        and reverently worships Me while remaining there eternally is the one with[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        the highest union. -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ye tvaksharamanirdeshyamavyaktam paryupasate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvatragamachintyamcha kutasthamachalam dhruvam -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who worship towards the Indestructible Kutastha. -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter12.html (1 of 5)4/18/2006 2:42:11 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  samniyamyendriyagramam sarvatra samabuddhayah[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  te prapnuvanti mameva sarvabhutahite ratah -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  Maintaining equipoise in all circumstances, and always doing good in[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  everything, they attain Me. -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  kleshohdhikatarasteshamavyaktasasaktachetasam[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  avyakta hi gatiduhkham dehavadbhiravapyate -5-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those whose minds are fixed on the Unmanifest -- their difficulty. -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ye tu sarvani karmani mayi samnyasyamatparah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ananyanaiva yogena mam dhyayanta upasate -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The way that one practices with works by which all dissolves into Atman. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 teshamaham samuddharta mrityusamsarasagarat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhavami na chirat partha mayyaveshitachetasam -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I swiftly save him from the death of samsara - the one whose heart is fixed[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 on me. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mayyeva mana adhatsva mayi buddhim niveshaya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nivasishyasi mayyeva ata urddham na samshayah -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Still your mind upon Me and enter; place your intellect upon Me. If this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happens, without a doubt you will ascend. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atha chittam samadhatum na shaknoshi mayi sthiram[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abhyasayogena tato mamicchaptum dhananjaya -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter12.html (2 of 5)4/18/2006 2:42:11 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If you cannot do this, then remain still in Me, meaning do Kriya of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samadhi. -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abhyasehpyasamarthohsi matkarmaparamo bhava[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 madarthamapi karmani kurvam siddhimavapsyasi -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If you cannot practice, then do My work, meaning do Kriya. With that also[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 will you be perfected. -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 athaitadapashaktohsi kartum madyogamashritah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarva karmaphalatyagam tatah kuru yatatmavan -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If you cannot even take refuge in yoga, then renounce the fruits of all action[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by remaining in Atman, meaning by doing Kriya. -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shreyo hi jnanamabhyasaj jnanaddhyanam vishishyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhyanat karmaphalatyagastyagacchantiranantaram -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dhyan [meditation/contemplation] is greater than jnana [knowledge]. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fruit of action is greater than dhyan. Greater than that is Tranquility. -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adveshta sarvabhutanam maitrah karuna eva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nirmamo nirahamkarah samaduhkhasukhah kshami -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Do not envy anyone; do not keep friendship with anyone; do not even be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 favorable to anyone. Nothing at all is mine; I am also nothing; knowing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pleasure and sorrow [as the same], be of a forgiving nature. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 santushtah satatam yogi yatatma dridhanishchayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mayyarpitamanobuddhiryo madbhaktah sa me priyah -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who becomes steadfast and certain by the eternally content Atman,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and who surrenders mind and intellect in Me -- that devotee is also dear to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Me. -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter12.html (3 of 5)4/18/2006 2:42:11 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yasmannedvijate loko lokannodvijate cha yah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 harshamarsha bhayodvagairmukto yah sa cha me priyah -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who does not cause anxiety in others, and who does not become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anxious because of others, one who is free of joy, despondency, fear and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anxiety, he is dear to Me. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anapekshah shuchirdaksha udasino gatavyathah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvarambhaparityagi yo madbhaktah sa me priyah -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Not contemptuous toward anyone, always being pure, competent in all[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 action, being seated while keeping air above the head, no pain remains,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 whatever is happening is renounced before and after it happens -- the one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who is a devotee such as this is the one who is dear to Me. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yo na hrishyati na dvashti na shochati na kankshati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shubhashubhaparityagi bhaktiman yah sa me priyah -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who does not rejoice, does not hate, does not grieve, does not desire,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 one who renounces both good and evil, who has faith in the words of Guru --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this type of person is the one who is dear to Me. -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samah shatrou cha mitre cha tatha manapamanayoh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shitoshnasukhaduhkheshu samah sangavivarjitah -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Enemy and friend are the same, and respect, disgrace, cold, heat, pleasure,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sorrow are the same; desire is absolutely ended. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tulyanindastutirmouni santushto yena kenachit[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aniketah sthiramatirbhaktiman me priyo narah -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Seeing them as the same, does not wish to speak in condemnation or praise;[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 content with whatever is there; does not abide at a home - meaning always[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abides in this place; steady mentality; devoted -- that human being is the one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who is dear. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter12.html (4 of 5)4/18/2006 2:42:11 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ye tu dharmamritamidam yathottam paryupasate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shraddadhana matparama bhaktastehtiva me priyah -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who worships in the way of the dharma about which I have spoken[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to you, with reverence - meaning always abiding in Brahman - this type of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 devotee, meaning abiding with faith in Guru's word -- he is the one who is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 very dear. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the twelfth chapter named "Bhaktiyoga."[m
[32m+[m
