[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter12.html (5 of 5)4/18/2006 2:42:11 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                        CHAPTER THIRTEEN[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                PRAKRITI PURUSHA VIVEKA YOGA*[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *[Translator's note: In some versions of the Gita, Chapter 13 is titled[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                      "Kshetrakshetrajnavibhagayoga."][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       prakritim purushanchaiva kshetram kshetrajnamevacha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etadveditumicchami jnanam jneyamcha keshava -1-**[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  **[Translator's note: In certain versions of the Gita, this sloka (13:1) is[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition                          omitted; in certain other versions, this sloka is presented but left[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unnumbered, and the numbering begins with the next sloka. Thus, because of[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            either the omission of the first sloka or not numbering it, some versions of[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     the Chapter 13 in different Gitas have only 34 slokas (actual or numbered)[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   instead of 35.][m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said, "O Keshava! What is the 'field' [kshetra]? Who is the knower of[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        [or knowledgeable about] the 'field' [kshetrajna]? And what are 'Prakriti,'[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        'Purusha,' 'Knowledge' [jnana] and that which is to be 'Known' [jneya]? Tell[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        me all of this. I will listen." -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5                        Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        idam shariram kaunteya kshetramitrabhidhiyate[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        etad yo vetti tam prahuh kshetrajna iti tadvidah -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is being experienced via Kutastha: This body is what is called the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter13.html (1 of 8)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  'field' [kshetra]. The one who knows this is the knower of [or knowledgeable[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  about] the 'field' [kshetrajna]. -2-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  kshetrajnamchapi mam viddhi sarvakshetreshu bharata[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  kshetrakshetrajnayorjnanam yattajjnanam matam mama -3-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  It is Me that the knower of the field knows. I am in all fields - meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 breath. Knowing the body and field is what is called "Knowledge" [jnana]. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tat kshetram yaccha yadrik cha yad vikari yatashcha yat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sa cha yo yat prabhavashcha tat samasena me shrinu -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am telling you of its mutations and their manifested effects. Listen. -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rishibhirbahudha gitam chandobhirvividhaih prithak[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmasutrapadashchaiva hetumadbhirvinishchitaih -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Rishi" - meaning Kali and Mahadeva etc. "Cchanda" - meaning Kutastha --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Light moving/culminating in the middle -- "Brahmasutra" - meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sushumna. It is He Who is the cause of them. -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mahabhutanyahamkaro buddhiravyaktamevacha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indriyani dashaikamcha pancha chendriyagocharah -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The five elements and the five super-elements (objects of the senses)***,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ego, intellect and the Inexpressible, and the ten sense-organs -- each organ of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 perception and each organ of action. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ***The parentheses and the text within them are in the original.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 iccha dveshah sukham dukham samghatashchetana dhritih[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etam kshetram samasena savikaramudahritam -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Desire, dislike/hatred, pleasure, sorrow, consciousness, resolve -- [are] the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter13.html (2 of 8)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 permutations of this field. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 amanitvamadambhitvamahimsa kshantirarjavam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 acharyopasanam shoucham sthairyamatmavinigrahah -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Absence of demonic egotism of the mind -- absence of arrogance --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [observing] non-violence, forbearance, uprightness, reverence to Guru,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purity, steadiness -- especially drawn to Atman. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 indriyartheshu vairagyamanahamkara eva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 janmamrityujaravyadhiduhkhadoshanudarshanam -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Non-attachment to the senses, mind, ego, life, death, old age, disease,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reflection upon conflict/suffering. -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asaktiranabhishvangah putradaragrihadishu[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nityamcha samachittatvamishtanishtopapattishu -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 No addiction to any desire; always even-minded, equanimity with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desirable and undesirable. -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mayi chanannyayogena bhaktiravyabhicharini[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 viviktadeshasevitvamaratirjanasamsadi -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Being exclusively fixed on Me -- faith in the word of Guru -- abiding in a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 solitary place - meaning that when one remains in oneself, one is in a place[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 without anyone -- "aratijanasamsadi" - meaning having a heart non-attached[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to others. -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adhyatmajnananitatvam tattvajnanarthadarshanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etajjnanamiti proktamajnanam yatatohnyatha -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Keeping the intellect stilled in oneself -- sky Knowledge-essence --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge-filled Form -- the cause of this -- this is what is called[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge. All other than this is ignorance/unconsciousness. -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter13.html (3 of 8)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jneya yat tat pravakshyami yajjnatvamritamashnute anadimat param[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahma na sat tannasaduchyate -13-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am telling you about the matter which is to be known, knowing which one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 imbibes immortal nectar -- all other things besides Me -- Param Brahman is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 neither truth nor untruth. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvatah panipadam tat sarvatohkshishiromukham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvatah shrutimalloke sarvamavritya tishthati -14-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 His Feet are in every place. He can hear all that is said. He is in every place.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvendriyagunabhasam sarvendriyavivarjitam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asaktam sarvabhucchaiva nirgunam gunabhoktri cha -15-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The practice of the gunas of all sense organs -- the detachment from all sense[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 organs -- infused in all elements -- beyond qualities -- Immortal -- the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyer of all gunas. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bahirantashcha bhutanamacharam charameva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sukshatvat tadavijneyam durastham chanti ke cha tat -16-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Outside and inside, and in all creation, Brahman is in His extremely subtle[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Form. Because of this such is not experienced. Being far, He is near. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avibhaktamcha bhuteshu vibhaktamiva cha sthitam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhutabhatri cha taj jneyam grasishnu prabhavishnu cha -17-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In separate and different forms am I, and I am the planets. -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jyotishamapi tajjyotistamasah paramuchyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanam jneyam jnanagamyam hridi sarvasya vishthitam -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter13.html (4 of 8)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Light of all lights -- I am beyond all darkness -- knowledge, the object of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge, the direction of knowledge - at the source of all is Kutastha,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning Is. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ity kshetram tatha jnanam jneyamchoktam samasatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 madbhaktah etadvijnaya madbhavayopapadyate -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This field, Knowledge, that which is to be known -- know, being My devotee[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- in My Essence am I attained -- "gunebhyashcha param vetti madbhavam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadhi gacchati." -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prakritim purushamchaiva viddhyanadi ubhavapi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vikaramscha gunamshchaiva viddhi prakritisambhavan -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Prakriti, Purusha, the Beginningless, Kutastha -- mutations - Prakriti's and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gunas'. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karyakaryakaranakartritve hetuh prakritiruchyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purushah sukhaduhkhanam bhoktritve heturuchyate -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Activity, cause, doership emerges from this Prakriti. Because of this, Purusha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is the partaker of pleasure, sorrow. -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 purushoh prakritistho hi bhungkte prakritijan gunan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karanam gunasangohsya sadasadyonijanmasu -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Imbued with Prakriti, Purusha partakes in the experience and enjoyment of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all of the gunas of Prakriti. Being attached to gunas, birth takes place in good[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and evil wombs. -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 upadrashtanumanta cha bharta bhokta maheshvarah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 paramatmeti chapyukto dehehsmin purushah parah -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter13.html (5 of 8)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Witness,* patron, lord, enjoyer - all of these are Brahman. He is the One[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Who is called Paramatman, meaning [the One Who is] called Kutastha. In[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this body is Kutastha -- Purusha is there after that. -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *[Translator's note: The word "witness" is the translation of the word[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "upadrashta," which is the first word of sloka 13:23. In the published Bengali[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 print, there seems to have been a printing error and the word "upadeshta" is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 written in the commentary part, even though that is not the word in the sloka.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If "upadeshta" were to be the word in the commentary section, it would be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 defined as "preceptor" instead of "witness." Both definitions are thus given[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 here for the sake of the reader.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ya evam vetti purusham prakritimcha gunaih saha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvatha vartamanohpi na sa bhuyohbhijayate -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who knows this Purusha as being permeated with the gunas of Prakriti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 has no death or fear, even while abiding in the midst of everything. -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhyanenatmani pashyanti kedidatmanamatmana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anye samkhyena yogena karmayogena chapare -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Abiding in Atman via meditation - meaning pranayam 1728 times -- some[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with the Kriya of Atman - see Atman.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [IMPORTANT NOTE: The last part of the commentary to this sloka 13:25 -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beginning at this point - becomes misaligned and is mistakenly printed under[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sloka 13:26 in the published Bengali print. Upon examination, it seems that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the displacement continues through sloka 13:27 and that there seems to be in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 actuality no commentary for 13:27. This translation presents slokas 13:25[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 through 13:27 in the manner where the alignment has been adjusted[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 according to the aforementioned discernment of the translator. If this is a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mistake, then the translator takes full responsibility for it.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Some by Samkhya - meaning see Him via jnana yoga, whose work is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Yonimudra. -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anye tvevamajanantah shrutvannyebhya upasate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tehpi chatitarantyeva mrityum shrutiparayanah -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter13.html (6 of 8)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Absent of craving for results, he can see by Kriya. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yavat samjayate kimchit sattvam sthavarajangamam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kshetrakshetrajnasamyogat tad viddhi bharatarshabha -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 THERE SEEMS TO BE NO COMMENTARY FOR SLOKA 13:27.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samam sarveshu bhuteshu tishthantam parameshvam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vinashyatsvavinashyantam yah pashyati sa pashyati -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahman exists equally in all things. That which is destructible is being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 destroyed. Whoever is seeing this is the one who is seeing. -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samam pashyan hi sarvatra samavasthitameshvaram[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na hinastyatmanatmanam tato yati param gatim -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Whoever sees the Lord present equally in all -- he, by seeing Atman by[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Atman attains Param Gati - meaning the Stillness after movement. -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prakrityaiva to karmani kriyamanani sarvashah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yah pashyati tathatmanamakartaram sa pashyati -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Everyone is acting because of Prakriti -- whoever has seen Atman becomes[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 his own lord. -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yada bhutaprithagbhavamekasthamanupashyati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tata eva cha vistaram brahma sampadyate tada -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When all things are seen as the same - meaning the Knowledge of Brahman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is known everywhere, that is when Brahman is attained. -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   anaditvannirgunatvat paramatmayamavyayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   sharirasthohpi kaunteya na karoti na lipyate -32-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter13.html (7 of 8)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Beginningless, beyond qualities, the Supreme Soul, Immutable,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Indestructible -- being in the body - does not do anything and is not enjoined[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with anything. -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatha sarvagatam soukshyadakasham nopalipyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvatravasthito dehe tathatma nopalipyate -33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Just as space, though everywhere, is not enjoined with anything, in the same[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 way, Brahman, even though in every body, in its subtlety is not enjoined. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatha prakashayatyekah kritsnam lokamimam ravih[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kshetram kshetri tatha kritsnat prakashayati bharata -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Just as the sun illuminates everything, in the same way the dweller of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 field reveals the field. -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kshetrakshetrajnayorevamantaram jnanachakshusha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhutaprakritimokshamcha ye viduryanti te param -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One can know of the field and the knower of the field by the Eye of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Insightful Knowledge -- whoever sees the elements, Prakriti and Atman - he[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is supreme. -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the thirteenth chapter named "Prakriti Purusha Viveka Yoga."[m
[32m+[m
