[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter13.html (8 of 8)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                    CHAPTER FOURTEEN[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 GUNATRAYAVIBHAGAYOGA[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       param bhuyah pravakshyami jnananam jnanamuttamam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajjnatva munayah sarve param siddhimito gathah -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is being experienced via Kutastha: Again I am telling you of the Supreme[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            Knowledge among all knowledge, knowing which, all sages attain the[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     Supreme Destiny. -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  idam jnanamypashritya mama sadharmyamagatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sargehpi nopajayante pralaye na vyathanti cha -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        Taking recourse in this Knowledge, if people come to My Dharma, in that[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        heaven there is no Grand Dissolution. -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5                        mama yonirmahad brahman tasmin garbham dadhamyaham[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6                        sambhavah sarvabhutanam tato bhavati bharata -3-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 My Yoni is the Supreme Brahman. I give in that Womb, from Which[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 everything has become. -3-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvayonishu kaunteya murtayah sambhavanti yah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasam brahman mahadyoniraham bijapradah pita -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter14.html (1 of 6)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  All forms have come from that Brahman-Yoni. Thus, I am Progenitor of the[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  Seed in Brahman-Yoni; I am the Father. -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  sattvam rajastama ity gunah prakritisambhavah[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  nibadhnanti mahabaho dehe dehinamavyayam -5-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  Sattva, rajas, tama - these three are the gunas of Prakriti. [These have] bound[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  the embodied - [which is] the Indestructible - in the body. -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatra sattvam nirmalatvat prakashakamanamayam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sukhasangena badhnati jnanasangena chanagha -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sattva is endowed with purity, it illuminates and binds the Indestructible[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [within the body] and binds It to happiness, and no binding happens with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajo ragatmakam viddhi trishnasangasamudbhavam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tannibadhnati kaunteya karmasangena dehinam -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Rajo guna is born out of desire -- desire is born out of thirst -- those karmas[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 cause the craving for the fruits [of desire] -- because of this, the embodied[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 becomes bound. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tamastvajnanajam viddhi mohanam sarvadehinam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pramadalasyanidrabhistannibadhnati bharata -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Tama emerges from ignorance/unconsciousness. Deluding all embodied[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beings, it binds them through carelessness, laziness, sleep. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sattvam sukhe sanjayati rajah karmani bharata[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanamavritya tu tamah pramade sanjayatyuta -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter14.html (2 of 6)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 From sattva comes happiness, from raja comes the desire for the fruits of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 action, keeping wisdom covered causes tama guna - meaning careless[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intoxication - whose extreme representation is liquor. -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajastamashchabhibhuya sattvam bhavati bharata[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajah sattvam tamashchaiva tamah sattvam rajastatha -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When raja and tama gunas are absent, sattva guna is illuminated -- sattva[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 after raja, tama after sattva, sattva after tama -- raja after sattva -- that form --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ida, sushumna, pingala before -- ida again after sushumna -- meaning after[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scuffling and fighting -- after mercy and forgiveness - tama -- meaning after[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the noisy aggressiveness - peacefulness -- after peacefulness, again fighting.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvadvareshu dehehsmin prakasha upajayate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanam yada tada vidyad vivriddham sattvamityuta -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When Knowledge is illuminated through all doors, then one knows, and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sattva guna emerges. -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 lobhah pravrittirarambhah karmanamashamah spriha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajasyetani jayante vivriddhe bharatarshabha -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Greed, addiction to extroverted action -- the work of rajaguna. -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aprakashohpravrittishcha pramado moha eva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tamasyetani jayante vivriddhe kurunandana -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Unawareness, inaction, carelessness, delusion -- the work of tamaguna. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yada sattve pravriddhe tu pralayam yati dehabhrit[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tadottamavidam lokanamalan pratipadyate -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 When engaged in sattva guna, then one becomes an excellent person --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attains purity of heart. -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter14.html (3 of 6)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   rajasi pralayam gatva karmasangishu jayate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   tatha pralinastamai mudhayonishu jayate -15-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In rajoguna, there is craving for the fruits of action. If one is immersed in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   tamoguna, then birth takes place in the womb of an ignorant being. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   karmanah sukritasyahuh sattvikam nirmalam phalam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   rajasastu phalam duhkhamajnanam tamasah phalam -16-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   If one performs good actions, then sattvic and pure results are produced. The[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   result of rajaguna is sorrow. Tama is the fruit of ignorance. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   sattvat samjayate jnanam rajaso lobha eva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   pramadamohou tamaso bhavatohjnanameva cha -17-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   In sattva guna there is knowledge/wisdom. In raja, there is greed.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Negligence, delusion are in the ignorance of tama. -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   urdhve gacchanti sattvastha madhye tishthanti rajasah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   jaghanyagunavrittistha adho gacchanti tamasah -18-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   One ascends in sattva guna, is in the middle with rajoguna and descends with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   tama - meaning: air goes to the head -- a battle occurs in the heart with the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   energy of air -- below intercourse happens with the sexual organ. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   nanyam gunabhyah kartaram yada drasthanupashyati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   gunebhyashcha param vetti madbhavam sohdhigacchati -19-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   When one goes beyond the three gunas, one then attains My Essence. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   gunanetanatitya trin dehi dehasamudbhavan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   janmamrityujaraduhkhairvimuktohmritamashnute -20-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter14.html (4 of 6)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is the three gunas by which the embodied is bound -- the one who is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 absolutely free from old age, death, birth, sorrow -- he is the one who drinks[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the immortal nectar. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karlingaistrin gunanatito bhavati prabho[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kimacharah katham chaitam strin guna nativartate -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is being experienced in the energy of the body: What are the signs of a[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 person who has gone beyond the three gunas? How is his behavior? -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prakashamcha pravrittimcha mohameva cha pandava[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na dveshti sampravrittani na nivrittani kamkhati -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is being experienced via Kutastha: When illumination, activity, delusion[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 present themselves, he neither hates them nor desires for them. -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 udasinovadasino gunairyo na vichalyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 guna vartanta ityevam yohvatishthati nengate -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Abides above -- is unmoved by the three gunas -- remains still in this way. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samaduhkhasukhah svasthah samaloshtashmakanchanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tulyapriyapriyo dhirastulyanindatmasamstutih -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowing sorrow and happiness as the same -- in the same way with a lump[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of earth and gold -- steady in both dear and non-dear -- silent in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 condemnation or praise. -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manapamanayostulyastulyo mitraripakshayoh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvarambhaparityagi gunatitah sa ucchyate -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter14.html (5 of 6)4/18/2006 2:42:12 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The same in respect and disgrace -- the same in friendship and enmity --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renouncing everything right at their starting. This is called "[being] beyond[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the gunas." -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mamcha yohvyabhicharena bhaktiyogena sevate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sa gunan samatityaitana brahmabhuyaya kalpate -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who is proper and lawful in conduct and practices bhaktiyoga -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meaning has faith in the word of Guru -- he is the one who goes beyond the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 gunas and becomes Brahman. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmano hi pratishthahamamritasyavyayasya cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shashvatasya cha dharmasya sukhasyaikantikasyacha -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Being completely established in Brahman, knowing the Eternal, Nectarous[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge, devoted to Brahman-Dharma, one becomes Brahman by such[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 absorbed single-mindedness. -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends Gunatraya Vijnana Yoga* - the fourteenth chapter.**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *[Translator's note: In the statement of conclusion to this Chapter 14, the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 author has used a variation of the title of the Chapter. The title of Chapter 14[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 at the beginning is "Gunatrayavibhagayoga" which means: "the yoga of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 distinguishing the distinction between the three gunas." The concluding[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 statement uses the title "Gunatraya Vijnana Yoga," which means: "the yoga[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of the science of the three gunas."][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 **[Translator's note: The author has used a different format for the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 concluding statement of Chapter 14 than the one followed from Chapter 10[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 through 13.][m
