[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 CHAPTER SIXTEEN[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                                                  DAIVASURASAMPADA YOGA*[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                        *[Translator's note: In some versions of the Gita, the title for Chapter[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   16 is "Daivasurasampadavibhagayoga." Even though the title at the[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   beginning of Chapter 16 of the published Bengali print - to which this[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition                               translation tries to remain true - is as the transliteration above -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                  "Daivasurasampada Yoga," the concluding reference to the title at the[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                             end of Chapter 16 is "Daivasura Sampada Vibhagayoga," which is a[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     more or less uncompounded variant of the aforementioned usage of the[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                    title as in some other versions of the Gita (see first sentence of this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                                        note).][m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        abhayam sattvasamshuddhvirajnanayogavyavasthiti[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        danam damashcha yajnashcha svadhyayastapa arjavam -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5                        Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7                        It is being experienced via Kutastha: Fearlessness and in the purity of sattva[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8                        guna -- persevering wholly in knowledge and yoga -- charity, control,[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9                        performing yajna and studying, and being upright. -1-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahimsa satyamakrodhastyagah shantirapaishunam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 daya bhuteshvaloluptam mardavam hrirachapalam -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Non-violence, truthfulness, non-anger, renunciation, peace, not being mean,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 compassion for all beings, not being greedy, soft-heartedness, not being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fickle. -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter16.html (1 of 6)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  tejah kshama dhritih shouchamadroho natimanita[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11                  bhavanti sampadam daivimabhijatasya bharata -3-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  Power, forgiveness, strength in self, cleanliness, absence of malice, absence[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14                  of egotism -- know that all these are possessions/qualities of the divine. -3-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16                  dambho darpohbhimana cha krodhah parushyamevacha[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  ajnanam chabhijatasya partha sampadasurim -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Conceit, arrogance, vanity, anger, harshness, and ignorance/unconsciousness[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- all these are possessions/qualities of the demonic. -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 daivi sampadvimokshaya nibandhayasuri mata[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ma shuchah sampadam daivimabhijatohsi pandava -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The possessions of divine character lead to liberation and the possessions of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the demonic lead to suffocating bondage. You have been born with divine[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 possessions. -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dvou bhutasargou lokehsmin daiva asura eva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 daivo vistarashah prokta asuram partha me shrinu -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I have said much about possessions of the divine; now listen about the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 possessions of the demonic. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pravrittimcha nivrittimcha jana na vidurasurah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na shoucham napi chacharo na satyam teshu vidyate -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 In the character of the demonic, neither pravritti [engagement] nor nivritti[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [withdrawal] -- do not care about purity or conduct. Their words are lies --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 besides that, they have no truth at all. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asatyamapratishtham te jagadahuranishvaram[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter16.html (2 of 6)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aparasparasambhutam kimanyat kamahaitukam -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 All is false -- there is no God -- everything has happened by happenstance --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 there is nothing but sexual lust. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etam drishtimavashtabhya nashtatmanohlpabuddhayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prabhavantyagrakarmanah kshayaya jagatohhitah -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Degrading Atman, and with limited intellect, they do base and disgusting[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 things -- the reason for destructiveness and evil in the world. -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kamamashritya dushpuram dambhamanamadanvitah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mohad grihitvahsadgrahan pravartantehshuchivratah -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Taking recourse in lustfulness, drunken with a conceited mind, they are[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 swallowed by the crocodile-like delusion, and thus they act with impure[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intention. -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chintamaparimeyamcha pralayantamupashritah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kamopabhogaparama etavaditinishchitah -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Until the time of their total dissolution, they constantly think of the pleasures[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of lust -- being certain that that is the ultimate. -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ashapashashatairbaddhah kamakrodhaparayanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ihante kamabhogarthamanyayenarthasanchayan -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Bound all around by hundreds of ties, devoted to lust and anger, they obtain[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 wealth unlawfully for the enjoyment of lustful pleasures. -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 idamadya maya labdhamimam prapsye manoratham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 idamastidamapi me bhavishyati punardhanam -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter16.html (3 of 6)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Today, this was able to be acquired -- and thinking that I will get even more[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- I have acquired this, I am acquiring this, and I will get this. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asou maya hatah shatrurhanishye chaparanapi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ishvarohhamaham bhogi siddhohham balavan sukhi -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This time I have killed the enemy; I will kill another enemy -- I am Lord,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 enjoyer, perfected/realized, mighty and happy. -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adhyohbhijanavanasmi kohnyohsti sadrisho maya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yakshye dasyami modishya ityajnanavimohitah -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am the greatest and wealthy -- no one is equal to me -- they remain deluded[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 in this type of ignorance. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anekachittavibhranta mohajalasamavritah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prasaktah kamabhogeshu patanti narakehshuchou -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Mind confused by many things, enmeshed in the net of delusion, addicted to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the enjoyment of lustful pleasures, they fall to hell due to the enjoyment of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 lustful pleasures. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atmasambhavitah stabdha dhanamanamadanvitah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajante namayajnaiste dambhenavidhipurvakam -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Intoxicated by ego, they boast of wealth, and for egotistical reasons of self-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renown, they perform yajnas which disregard scriptural edicts. -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahamkaram balam darpam kamam krodhamcha samshritah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mamatmaparadeheshu pradvishyantohbhyasuyakah -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Taking recourse in ego, might, arrogance, lust and anger, they hate others. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter16.html (4 of 6)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tanaham dvishatah kriuran samsareshu naradhaman[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kshipamyajasramashubhanasurishvevayonishu -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 They are sub-human, cruel -- I quickly set them into demonic births. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asurim yonimapanna mudha janmani janmani[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mamaprapaiva kaunteya tato yantyadhamam gatim -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Giving them demonic births again and again, I make them go on the path of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 descent. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 trividham narakasyedam dvaram nashanamatmanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kamah krodhastatha lobhastasmadetatrayam tyajet -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Lust, anger and greed - these three destroy the door to Atman -- thus,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renounce them. -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etairvimuktah kaunteya tamodvaraistribhirnarah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 acharatyatmanah shreyastato yati param gatim -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Renouncing these and performing the Kriya of Atman, one attains Paragati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [beyond the path] - meaning Tranquility/Stillness. -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yah shastravidhimutsrijya vartate kamakaratah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na sa siddhimavapnoti na sukham na param gatim -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who acts under lust and not according to scriptural wisdom -- he does[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not attain perfection and the Supreme Destiny. -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tasmacchastram pramanam te karyakaryavyavasthitou[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnatva shastravvidhanoktam karma kartumiharhasi -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Therefore, one should perform the dutiful act as concluded upon by the[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter16.html (5 of 6)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 scriptures. -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the sixteenth chapter named "Daivasura Sampada Vibhagayoga."*[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *[Please see note at the beginning of Chapter 16.][m
