[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                       CHAPTER SEVENTEEN[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                       SHRADDHATRAYA YOGA*[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *[Translator's note: In some versions of the Gita, Chapter 17 is titled[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                        "Shraddhatrayavibhagayoga."][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ye shastravidhimutsrijya yajante shraddhayanvitah[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       tesham nishttha tu ka krishna sattvamaho rajastamah -1-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   It is being experienced in the energy of the body: That which is done - not[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  according to scriptural injunctions yet with reverence -- those who do that --[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition                          their karma -- sattva, raja, tama. -1-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     trividha bhavati shraddha dehinam sa svabhavaja[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   sattviki rajasi chaiva tamasi cheti tam shrinu -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 It is experienced via Kutastha that there are three types of embodied[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction                     behavior: sattvic, rajasic and tamasic. -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        sattvanurupa sarvasya shraddha bhavati bharata[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        shraddhamayohyam purusho yo yacchraddhah sa eva sah -3-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        The [type of] reverence which corresponds with sattva -- that person is the[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter17.html (1 of 7)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  one who is reverent, and reverence itself is the form of God. -3-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  yajante sattvika devan yaksharakshamsi rajasah[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  pretan bhutaganamshchanye yajante tamasa janah -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  Sattvic persons are gods, rajasic persons are yakshas - meaning ego --[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  demons - meaning delusion, spirits and ghosts - meaning tama-dominated[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 people. -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ashastravihitam ghoram tapyante ye tapojanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dambhahamkarasamyuktah kamaragabalanvitah -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Austerities which are severe and not according to scriptural edicts, filled with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 haughtiness and pride, desires of the present -- lust and vile things -- and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 with the desires of the future, and with force. -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karshayantah sharirastham bhutagramamachetasah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mamchaivantah sharirastham tan viddhyasuranishchayan -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The frictions of the body - meaning bringing about afflictions -- beings[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unconscious of Me -- do such things in the body -- know them to be of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 demonic nature. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aharastvapi sarvasya trividho bhavati priyah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajnantapastatha danam tesham bhedamimam shrinu -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Food is of three types. Yajna, austerity, charity -- there are also differences[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 among these -- [now] hear about that. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ayuhsattvabalarogasukhapritivivardhanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rasyah snigdhah sthira hridya aharah sattvikapriyah -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That which promotes longevity, sattva, strength, prevention of disease,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 happiness and delight, is juicy and smooth, enhances peacefulness in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 heart -- the things that are of these types -- those are sattvic and dear foods --[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter17.html (2 of 7)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ghee [clarified butter] increases lifespan, boileed sunned rice and ghee[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 increases sattva guna, strength by milk, prevention of disease by bitter[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [foods], emblica increases sperm/virility, salt/alkaline increases[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 delightfulness, whey with sea-salt and mung bean soup -- gentleness -- rice[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pudding, rock candy increases [the breadth of] the heart. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 katvamlavanatyushna tikshnarukshavidahinah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahara rajasasyeshta duhkhashokamayapradah -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pungent - meaning sour, salt, hot, sharp, overly dry, that which is burning to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the body -- these types of foods are rajasic. Grief and sorrow are increased[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 by these. -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatatamam gatarasam putiparyushitamcha yat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ucchishtamapi chamedhyam bhojanam tamasapriyam -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Lifeless, cold, and stale and impure -- all these foods are tamasic. -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aphalakankhibhiryajno vidhidrishto ya ijyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yashtavyameveti manah samadhaya sa sattvikah -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The yajna which is performed without wanting results, is according to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 injunctions, which bring the mind to samadhi -- that is sattvic. -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abhisandhaya to phalam dambharthamapi chaiva yat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ijyate bharatashreshttha tam yajnam viddhi rajasam -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who performs yajna with pride and arrogance is rajasic. -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vidhihinamasrishtannam mantrahinamadakshinam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shraddhavirahitam yajnam tamasam parichakshate -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The yajna which is [performed] without adhering to injunctions, without[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mantra, without offering, without reverence - that is tamas. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter17.html (3 of 7)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 devadvijaguruprajnapujanam shouchamarjavam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmacharyamahimsa cha shariram tapa uchyate -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The worship of gods, brahmins, guru, wise persons, and being of a character[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 which is pure and upright in Brahman -- non-violence -- these are bodily[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 austerities. -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anudvegakaram vakyam satyam priyahitamcha yat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 svadhyayabhyasanam chaiva vangmayam tapa uchyate -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The type of speech which does not cause agitation, true, loving, beneficent[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 words, and the practice of study -- these are austerities of speech. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manahprasadah soumatvam mounamatmavinigrahah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhavasamshuddhirityetat tapo manasamuchyate -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Joy in mind, stillness, and silence, self-control, purity in thought and feeling[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- these austerities of mind - meaning sanctified happiness of mind - meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the state of being that follows Kriya [Kriyar paarer je avastha] - that is Bliss,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Stillness, Silence etc. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shraddhara paraya taptam tapastat trividham naraih[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aphalakankshibhiryuktaih sattvikam parichakshate -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Reverence is of three types -- being without desire for results and united (see[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 6:18) -- that is sattvic reverence. -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 satkaramanapujartham tapo dambhena chaiva yat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kriyate tadiha proktam rajasam chalamadhruvam -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who performs austerities proudly, [wanting] to gain respect and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adulation for having done charitable works -- that is rajasic reverence. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mudhagrahenatmano yat pidaya kriyate tapah[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter17.html (4 of 7)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 parasyotsadanartham va tat tamasamudahritam -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who performs rituals to bring about good or evil for others -- that is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tamasic reverence. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 datavyamiti yaddanam diyatehnupakarine[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 deshe kale cha patre cha taddanam sattvikam smritam -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who gives charity in which there is no expectation of anything in return,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and performs charity with due respect to - and proper analysis of - place,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 time and personage -- that is sattvic charity. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yattu pratyupakarartham phalamuddishya va punah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 diyate cha pariklishtam taddanam rajasam smritam -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Charity that is given with the intention of receiving something in return, yet[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 given unwillingly/contemptuously as well, is rajasic charity. -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adeshakale yaddanamapatrebhyashcha diyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asatkritamavajnatam tat tamasamudahritam -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Charity given to evil places, for the wrong kinds of people, at the wrong time[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is tamasic. -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 OM tatsaditi nirdesho brahmanastrividhah smritah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmanastena vedashcha yajnashcha vihitah pura -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 OM Tat Sat is used in three types of work [ritual or spiritual work]. -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tsmadomityudahritya yajnadanatapahkriyah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pravartante vidhanoktah satatam brahmavadinam -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 OM is used in yajna, charity, austerity, Kriya. -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter17.html (5 of 7)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tadityanabhisandhyaya phalam yajnatapahkriyah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 danakriyashcha vividhah kriyante mokshakankhibhih -25-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who perform works desiring results use the "tat" substance. -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sadbhave sadhubhave cha sadityet prayujyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prashaste karmani tatha sacchabdah partha yujyate -26-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sadhus use "sat" in doing works of beneficence. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajne tapasi dane cha sthitih saditi chochyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmachaiva tadathiyam sadityevabhidhiyate -27-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Usage [of such] in yajna, charity and austerity is for the attainment of the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Omkar Substance. -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ashraddhaya hutam dattam tapastaptam kritamcha yat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asadityuchyate partha na cha tat pretya no iha -28-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Those who offer oblations, give charity and perform austerities without[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 reverence -- they [and their works] are called "asat" [with no basis on Truth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or goodness]. -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Thus ends the seventeenth chapter named "Shraddhatrayayoga."*[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *[Translator's note: The author has used a less compounded form of the title[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 at the beginning of the chapter.][m
