[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter17.html (7 of 7)4/18/2006 2:42:13 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                        CHAPTER EIGHTEEN[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                               MOKSHAYOGA*[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *[Translator's note: In some versions of the Gita, Chapter 18 is titled[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                                           "Mokshasannyasayoga."][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mHome                             Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sannyasasya mahabaho tattvamicchami veditum[m
[32m+[m[32mCover Page                       tyagasya cha hrishikesha prithak keshinisudana -1-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   It being experienced in the energy of the body: What is the difference[m
[32m+[m[32mpresent English                  between "sannyas" and "tyaga"? -1-[m
[32m+[m[32mEdition[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sri Bhagavan said:[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami                            kamyanam karmanam nyasam sannyasam kavayo viduh[m
[32m+[m[32mSatyananda's                     sarvakarmaphalatyagam prahustyagam vichakshanah -2-[m
[32m+[m[32mPreface to the                   Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mBengali Edition                  It is being experienced via Kutastha: The extinguishing of desire for any[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 object immediately in the present is called "sannyas." The abandonment of[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduction                     all fruits from all actions is called "tyaga." -2-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 1                        tyajyam doshavadityeke karma prahurmanishinah[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 2                        yajnadanatapahkarma na tyajyamiti chapare -3-[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 3                        Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 4                        All work should be done; abandoning them causes wrong. Yajna, charity,[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 5[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 6[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 7[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 8[m
[32m+[m[32mChapter 9[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (1 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 10                  austerities should not be abandoned. -3-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 11[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 12                  nishchayam shrinu me tatra tyage bharatasattama[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 13                  tyago hi purushavyaghra trividhah samprakirtitah -4-[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 14[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 15                  Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 16[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 17                  The "tyagi" person is powerful like a tiger. Just as a tiger devours an animal[m
[32m+[m[32m     Chapter 18                  when it gets near him, in the same way [the tyagi] destroys all unworthy[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desires. As [the tyagi] continues to destroy [desires] in this way, no desires[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 come within his proximity in the future. That is of three types. -4-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajnadanatapahkarma na tyajyam karyameva tat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yajno danam tapashchaiva pavanani manishinam -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Yajna, charity, austerities purify. -5-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 etanyapi ti karmani sangam tyaktva phalani cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kartavyaniti me partha nishchitam matamuttamam -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Accompanied with the renunciation of all desire for results, these must be[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 performed. This is of the highest perception. -6-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 niyatasya tu sannyasah karmano nopapadyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mohat tasya parityagastamasah parikirtitah -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The sannyasi [is one] who extinguishes all and with steadfast discipline[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 renounces all desire in the present condition itself. A sannyasi renouncing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 out of delusion is performing tamasic action. -7-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 duhkhametyeva yat karma kayakleshabhayat tyajet[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sa kritva rajasam tyagam naiva tyagaphalam labhet -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sorrow - meaning one who abandons action out the fear of physical[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 afflictions -- that is rajasic tyaga. -8-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (2 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karyamityeva yat karma niyatam kriyatehrjunah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sangam tyaktva phalamchaiva sa tyagah sattviko matah -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who performs actions without judgment and free of craving for results --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that is what is known as sattvic tyaga. -9-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nadveshtyakushalam karma kushale nanushajjate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tyagi sattvasamavishto medhavi cchinnasamshayah -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There is no hatred for bad work; there is also no desire for good work -- the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tyagi is established in sattva guna -- intelligent -- free of doubts. -10-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na hi dehabhrita shakyam taktyum karmanyasheshatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yastu karmaphalatyagi sa tyagityabhidhiyate -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Embodying a physical form, one is not able to renounce endless action. -11-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anishtamishtam mishramcha trividham karmanah phalam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhavatyatyaginam pretya na tu sannyasinam kvachit -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Undesirable, desirable, mixed -- three types of results of action -- only tyagis[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 can do this -- this never happens to sannyasis. -12-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 panchemani mahabaho karanani nibodha me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samkhye kritante proktani siddhaye sarvakarmanam -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 These have five causes -- in Samkhya and Yoga -- all actions are for the sake[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of attaining perfection. -13-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adhishtthanam tatha karta karanamcha prithagvidham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vividhashcha prithak cheshta daivamchaivatra panchamam -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The dwelling or place [of action], the doer, action, the numerous types of[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (3 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 efforts/impulses, deities. -14-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shariravangmanobhiryat karma prarabhate narah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nyayam va viparitam va panchaite tasya hetavah -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Body, speech -- the actions from the mind that human beings begin --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 appropriate or harmful -- they are so because of the five. -15-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatraiva sati kartaramatmanam kevalantu yah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pashyatyakritabuddhitvanna sa pashyati durmatih -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [Seeing] only karma in the Self -- that is what is misfortune in action --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 employing an incapable intellect - meaning not being able to go beyond[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intellect -- cannot see. -16-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yasya nahamkrito bhavo buddhiryasya na lipyate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 hatvapi sa imamllokan na sasti na nibadhyate -17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who does not have ego and one whose intellect is not enmeshed in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karma -- one who even while killing people does not kill and is not bound. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 17-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanam jneyam parijnata trividha karmachodana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karanam karma karteti trividham karmasamgrahah -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Beyond knowledge and the known is the Knower -- three types of causes --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the doer of action. -18-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanam karma cha karta cha tridhaiva gunabhedatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prochyate gunasamkhyane yathavacchrinu tanyapi -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Knowledge, action and doer -- their gunas have three types of distinctions --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 listen to what has been said in Samkhya. -19-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (4 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvabhuteshu yenaikam bhavamavyaikshate[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 avibhaktam vibhakteshu tajjnanam viddhi sattvikam -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who sees the Eternal-Indestructible equally in all things, in undivided[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and divided forms -- that knowledge is sattvic knowledge. -20-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prithaktvena tu yajjnanam nanabhavan prithagvidhan[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vetti sarveshu bhuteshu tajjnanam viddhi rajasam -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who sees the separate types in all things as separate -- that is rajasic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge. -21-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yat tu kritsnavadekasmin karye saktamahaitukam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atattvarthavadalpamcha tat tamasamudahritam -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who is attached to work and is unaccountable, one who acquires[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 knowledge knowing it to be worthless -- that is tamasic knowledge. -22-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 niyatam sangarahitamaragadveshatah kritam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aphalaprepsuna karma yat tat sattvikamucchyate -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who performs action without desire, having renounced like and dislike,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 having renounced the desire for results -- that is sattvic karma [action]. -23-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yat tu kamepsu na karma sahamkarena va punah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kriyate bahulayasam tadrajasamudahritam -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who performs action with desire -- with ego -- by great effort -- that is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajas karma. -24-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 anubandham kshayam himsamanapeksha cha paurusham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mohadarabhyate karma yat tat tamasamuchyate -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (5 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who performs actions which are bound up, destructive, aggressive/[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 violent, inconsiderate, selfish and out of delusion -- that is tamas. -25-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yuktasangohnahamvadi dhrityusaha samanvitah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 siddhyasiddhyonirvikarah karta sattvic uchyate -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who performs action without desire, without ego, with enthusiasm --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 unmoved by success or failure -- that is one who is a sattvic doer. -26-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ragi karmaphalaprepsurlubdho himsatmakohshuchih[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 harshashokanvitah karta rajasah parikirtitah -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Caught up in desire and the desire for the fruits of actions, one who with[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 impurity performs actions imbued with pleasure and sorrow -- that is one[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 who is a rajas doer. -27-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ayuktah prakritah stabdhah shatho naishkritikohlasah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vishadi dirghasutri cha karta tamasa uchyate -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who is not mentally engaged and is stupidly silent in the situation,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 deceitful, lazy, a procrastinating depressive, slothful -- that is tamas. -28-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 buddherbhedam dhriteshchaiva ginatastrividham shrinu[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prochyamanamasheshena prithaktvena dhananjaya -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The distinctions of intellect and resolve are of three types. -29-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pravrittimcha nivrittimcha karyakarye bhayabhaye[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bandham mokshamcha ya vetti buddhih sa partha sattviki -30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who knows engagement and withdrawal, work and work not to be done,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 fear and non-fear, bondage and liberation -- this type of intellect is sattvic. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 30-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (6 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
