[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yaya dharmadharmamcha karyamchakaryameva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ayathavat prajanati buddhih sa partha rajasi -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dharma and non-dharma, work and work not to be done, like this and like[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 that -- intellect which is of this type -- he has rajasic intellect. -31-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adharmam dharmamiti ya manyate tamasavrita[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvarthan viparitamshcha buddhih sa partha tamasi -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who perceives un-dharma as dharma, who, being obscured by darkness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 always ascertains contrarily to what [should be] understood -- tamasic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 intellect. -32-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhritya yaya dharayate manah pranendriyakriyah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogenavyabhicharinya dhriti sa partha sattviki -33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Concentrating mind and senses by Kriya and becoming steadfast in yoga --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 this type of resolve is called sattvic. -33-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yaya tu dharmakamarthan dhritya dharayatehrjuna[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 prasangena phalakankhi dhritih sa partha rajasi -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Resolve which is for dharma and desire -- related in any way to the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 attachment for the craving of results -- that is rajasic resolve. -34-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yaya svapnam bhayam shokam vishadam madameva cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na vimunchati durmedha dhritih sa partha tamasi -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dream, fear, grief, depression, intoxicants -- sorrow by these -- resolve while[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 not being very composed -- that is tamasic resolve. -35-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sukham tvidanim trividham shrinu me bharatarshabha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 abhyasad ramate yatra duhkhantamcha nigacchati -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (7 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Pleasure is of three types -- where sorrow ends by practice -- that is pleasure[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- that is of three types. -36-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yattadagre vishamiva parinamehmritopamam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tat sukham sattvikam proktamatmabuddhiprasadajam -37-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 First like poison, in the end like the nectar of immortality -- that is sattvic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pleasure -- stilling the mind in Atman -- it is attained by His Grace Itself. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 37-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vishayendriya samyogad yattadagrehmritopamam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pariname vishamiva tat sukham rajasam smritam -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That which is attached to the senses and sense-objects, which seems at the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beginning to be ambrosia but at the end feels like poison -- that is rajasic[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 pleasure. -38-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yadagre chanubandhe cha sukham mohanamatmanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nidralasyapramadottham tat tamasamudahritam -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 That which binds and deludes me right at the beginning -- sleep, laziness,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 negligence -- this is tamas pleasure. -39-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na tadasti prithivyam va divi deveshu va punah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sattvam prakritijairmuktam yadebhih syat tribhirguaih -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 There is no freedom from sattva and the three gunas of Prakriti on this earth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 or in heaven. -40-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmanakshatriyavisham shudranamcha parantapah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 karmani pravibhaktani svabhavaprabhavairgunaih -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Brahmin, kshatriya, vaishya, shudra are differentiated by the qualities of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 action/work. -41-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (8 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj  www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shamodamantapah shoucham kshantirarjavamevacha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanam vijnanamastikyam brahmakarma svavajam -42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Calmness, discipline, austerity, purity, tolerance, uprightness, knowledge,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 beyond knowledge, and faith in God -- these are characteristics of Brahman*-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 action/work. -42-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *[Translator's note: The author has used the term "Brahman" [Divine] here[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and not the term "brahmin" [name of caste], even though it refers to the work[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 of "brahmins." It is understood that a true "brahmin" is one who lives in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "Brahman" - a philosophy that supersedes the system of familial lineage[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 which is commonly followed in India.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shouryam tejo dhritirdakshyam yuddhe chapyalayanam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 danamishvarabhavashcha kshatram karma svabhavajam -43-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Valor, vigor, resolve, skillfulness, not fleeing in battle, charity, thinking of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 God -- these are kshatriya-actions/work. -43-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 krishigourakshyavanijyam vaishyakarma svabhavajam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 paricharyatmakam karma shudrasyapi svbhavajam -44-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Farming, cattle raising, trade -- vaishya-action/work. To serve Atman is[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shudra-action/work. -44-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sve sve karmanyabhiratah samsiddhi labhate narah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 svakarmaniratah siddhim yatha vindati tacchrinu -45-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One attains full perfection by tending to one's natural work. -45-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatah pravrittirbhutanam yena sarvamidam tatam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 svakarmana tamabhyarchya siddhim vindati manavah -46-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By performing action appropriate to each being in the place from where all[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (9 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 phenomena emerge, human beings attain perfection. -46-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shreyan svadharmo vigunah paradharmat svanushthitat[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 svabhavaniyatam karma kurvannapnoti kilbisham -47-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Remaining in one's inferior path is better than performing acts on a path[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 belonging to another. There is no sin incurred if one performs work natural[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 to oneself. -47-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sahajam karma kaunteya sadoshamapi na tyajet[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvarambha hi doshena dhumenagnirivavrita -48-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Easy work - meaning Kriya, do not abandon even if with faults -- in the[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sphere of smoke, there is fire. -48-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 asaktabuddhih sarvatra jitatma vigatasprihah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 naishkarmyasaddhim paramam sannyasenadhigacchati -49-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Mind free from attachment in all things, victorious over oneself - meaning[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 being still, without desire and without craving results -- Supreme Perfection[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 is attained by sannyas. -49-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 siddhim prapto yatha brahma tathapnoti nibodha me[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samasenaiva kaunteya nishtha jnanasya ya para -50-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I am telling you how Brahman is attained by devotion with Knowledge. -50-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 buddhya vishuddhaya mukto dhrityatmanam niyamya cha[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shabdadin vishayamstyaktva ragadvesha vyudasya cha -51-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Having purified the intellect, being concentrated and united in Atman, being[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 completely focused -- given up sound and such objects of the senses -- like[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 and dislike. -51-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (10 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 viviktasevi laghvashi yatavakkayamanasah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 dhyanayogaparo nityam vairagyam samupashritah -52-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Solitude, eating lightly, disciplined in speech, body, mind -- always in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meditation and yoga -- and devoid of desire -- one who takes refuge in this[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 way. -52-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ahamkaram balam darpam kamam krodham parigraham[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vimuchya nirmamah shanto brahmabhuyaya kalpate -53-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 [Abandoning] ego, might, arrogance, anger, lust, relinquishing wealth[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 somewhere else -- being completely composed -- nothing at all is mine --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 later, after having attained Tranquility, the idea of being Brahman happens. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 53-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 brahmabhutah prasannatma na shochati na kankshati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samah sarveshu bhuteshu madbhaktim labhate param -54-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Being Brahman, the delighted Atman neither grieves over anything nor[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 desires -- the same in all things -- attains My Para-Bhakti. -54-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhaktya mamabhijanati yavan yashchasmi tattvatah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tato mam tattvato jnatva vishate tadanantaram -55-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 By devotion knows Me -- by the Knowledge/Essence - meaning by Kriya. -[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 55-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvakarmanyapi sada kurvano madvyapashrayah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 matprasadadavapnoti shashvatam padamavyam -56-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Do all work while being in My refuge -- by My Blessing You will receive[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Everlasting, Eternal Substance. -56-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 chetasa sarvakarmani mayi samnyasya matparah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 buddhiyogamupashritya macchittah satatam bhava -57-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (11 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Dedicate all action to Me from the heart, extinguish wholly, be devoted to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Me, take recourse in buddhi-yoga and keep your consciousness always on[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Me. -57-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 macchittah sarvadurgani matprasadat tarishyasi[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 atha chet tvamahamkaranna shroshyasi vinankshyasi -58-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If that happens, you will cross over all afflictions by My Blessing. But if you[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are egotistical and do not listen to My words, then there will be destruction.[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -58-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yadahamkaramashritya na yotsya ity manyase[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mithyaiva vyavasayaste prakritistvam niyokshyati -59-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 If, taking recourse in ego, you do not do Kriya -- your result-craving actions[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 are false -- by nature, you will remain devoted. -59-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 svabhavajena kaunteya nibaddhah svena karmana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kartum necchasi yanmohat karishyasyavashohpi tat -60-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 People, are imprisoned by delusion because of each one's own nature and[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 thereby each one's actions. If you desire to not act, then, having become[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 compelled, you will have to act. -60-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ishvarah sarvabhutanam hriddesheharjuna tishthati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhramayan sarvabhutani yantrarudhani mayaya -61-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The Lord is in the heart of all things and is traveling about, having mounted[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 all things to the machinery of His own maya. -61-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tameva sharanam gaccha sarvabhavena bharata[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatprasadat param shantim sthanam prapsyasi shashvatam -62-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (12 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Take refuge in Him in all ways. By His Blessing you will attain Brahman,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 the Abode of Supreme Peace. -62-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ity te jnanamakhyatam guhyad guhyataram maya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vimrishyaitedasheshena yathecchasi tatha kuru -63-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I have told you this deep secret -- now do whatever you wish. -63-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvaguhyatamam bhuyah shrinu me paramam vachah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ishtohsi me dridhamiti tato vakshyami te hitam -64-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I will tell you even more of such secret, because you are My friend and I am[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 your Benefactor. -64-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 manmana bhava madbhakto madyaji mam namabhuru[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 mamevaidyasi satyam te pratijane priyohsi me -65-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Keep mind on Me - meaning, perform Kriya. Believing in the words of Guru,[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 meditate on Me and bow. You will certainly be Mine. I tell you truly. I give[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 you My vow -- because you are My beloved. -65-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sarvadharman parityajya mamekam sharanam vraja[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 aham tvam sarvapapebhyo mokshayishyami ma shuchah -66-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Renounce all dharma and surrender directly to Me - meaning perform Kriya[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 -- I will liberate you from all sins. -66-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 idam te natapaskaya nabhaktaya kadachana[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na chashushrushave vachyam na cha mam yohbhyasuyati -67-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ya idam* paramam guhyam madbhakeshvabhidhasyati[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhaktim mayi param kritva mamevaishyatyasamshayah -68-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *[Translator's note: In some versions of the Gita, "imam" is used instead of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 "idam" at this place in sloka 11:68][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (13 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 This supreme secret should be told to My devotee -- if he devotes himself to[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Me, he will get Me. -67 and 68-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 na cha tasmanmanushyeshu kashchinme priyakrittamah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 bhavita na cha me tasmadanyah priyataro bhuvi -69-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 No one is more dear to Me than the devotee - there has not been, neither will[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 there be. -69-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 adhyashyate cha ya imam dharmyam samvadamavyoh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 jnanayajnena tenahamishtah syamiti me matih -70-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 One who listens to our conversation -- [Divine] Knowledge will manifest in[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 him. -70-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 shraddhavananasuyashcha shrinuyadapi yo narah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sohpi muktah shurbhallokan prapnuyat punyakarmanam -71-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who listens with reverence -- he is the one who is a good person --[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 will attain and do beneficent works. -71-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kacchidetam shrutam partha tvayaikagrena chetasa[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 kacchidajnanasammohah pranashtaste dhananjaya -72-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The one who will not listen with reverence -- he will be ruined. -72-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Arjuna said:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 nasto mohah smritirlabdha tatprasadatanmayachyta[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 sthitohsmi gatasandehah karishye vachanam tava -73-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The energy of the body says: My delusion and shame are gone because of[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Your Grace -- now I am still -- my doubts are gone -- whatever You say, that[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 I will do. -73-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mfile:///C|/Yoga%20Niketan/sriyukteshvargita/chapter18.html (14 of 16)4/18/2006 2:42:14 PM[m
[32m+[m[32mSwami Sriyukteswar Giri Maharaj        www.yoganiketan.net[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Sanjay said:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 ityaham vasudevasya parthasya cha mahatmanah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 samvadamimamashroushamadbhutam lomaharshanam -74-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 The total perception of mind is saying: Listening to this conversation[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 between these great beings is causing my hairs to stand on end. -74-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vyasaprasadat shrutavanimam guhyamaham param[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yogam yogeshvarat krishnat sakshat kathayatah svayam -75-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Via Kutastha Itself was all this experienced. -75-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 rajan samsmritya samsmritya samvadamimamadbhutam[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 keshavarjunayoh punyam hrishyami cha muhurmuhuh -76-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Remembering - became contented - (mind)*. -76-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 *[Translator's note: The parentheses and the text within are in the original.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 taccha samsmritya samsmritya rupamatyadbhutam hareh[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 vismayo me mahan rajan hrishyami cha punah punah -77-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Remembering the Incredible Form - became contented - (mind)**. -77-[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 **[See note accompanying sloka 18:76.][m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 yatra yogeshvarah krishno yatra partho dhanurdharah[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 tatra shrirvijayo bhutirdhruva nitirmatirmama -78-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Commentary:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Where there is Kutastha and where the energy of the body is performing[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Kriya, there, in that place, is and will be the highest form of Sacred[m
[32m+[m[32m                                 Prosperity -- this is my deepest conviction. -78-[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m                                   Thus ends the eighteenth chapter named "Mokshayoga."[m
[32m+[m
